101RawComment *ASTContext::getRawCommentForDeclNoCache(const Decl *D) const {
102 assert(D);
103
104 // If we already tried to load comments but there are none,
105 // we won't find anything.
106 if (CommentsLoaded && Comments.getComments().empty())
107 return nullptr;
108
109 // User can not attach documentation to implicit declarations.
110 if (D->isImplicit())
111 return nullptr;
112
113 // User can not attach documentation to implicit instantiations.
114 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
115 if (FD->getTemplateSpecializationKind() == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation)
116 return nullptr;
117 }
118
119 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
120 if (VD->isStaticDataMember() &&
121 VD->getTemplateSpecializationKind() == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation)
122 return nullptr;
123 }
124
125 if (const auto *CRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
126 if (CRD->getTemplateSpecializationKind() == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation)
127 return nullptr;
128 }
129
130 if (const auto *CTSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(D)) {
131 TemplateSpecializationKind TSK = CTSD->getSpecializationKind();
132 if (TSK == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation ||
133 TSK == TSK_Undeclared)
134 return nullptr;
135 }
136
137 if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D)) {
138 if (ED->getTemplateSpecializationKind() == TSK_ImplicitInstantiation)
139 return nullptr;
140 }
141 if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(D)) {
142 // When tag declaration (but not definition!) is part of the
143 // decl-specifier-seq of some other declaration, it doesn't get comment
144 if (TD->isEmbeddedInDeclarator() && !TD->isCompleteDefinition())
145 return nullptr;
146 }
147 // TODO: handle comments for function parameters properly.
148 if (isa<ParmVarDecl>(D))
149 return nullptr;
150
151 // TODO: we could look up template parameter documentation in the template
152 // documentation.
153 if (isa<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(D) ||
154 isa<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(D) ||
155 isa<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(D))
156 return nullptr;
157
158 // Find declaration location.
159 // For Objective-C declarations we generally don't expect to have multiple
160 // declarators, thus use declaration starting location as the "declaration
161 // location".
162 // For all other declarations multiple declarators are used quite frequently,
163 // so we use the location of the identifier as the "declaration location".
164 SourceLocation DeclLoc;
165 if (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D) || isa<ObjCContainerDecl>(D) ||
166 isa<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D) ||
167 isa<RedeclarableTemplateDecl>(D) ||
168 isa<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(D))
169 DeclLoc = D->getBeginLoc();
170 else {
171 DeclLoc = D->getLocation();
172 if (DeclLoc.isMacroID()) {
173 if (isa<TypedefDecl>(D)) {
174 // If location of the typedef name is in a macro, it is because being
175 // declared via a macro. Try using declaration's starting location as
176 // the "declaration location".
177 DeclLoc = D->getBeginLoc();
178 } else if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(D)) {
179 // If location of the tag decl is inside a macro, but the spelling of
180 // the tag name comes from a macro argument, it looks like a special
181 // macro like NS_ENUM is being used to define the tag decl. In that
182 // case, adjust the source location to the expansion loc so that we can
183 // attach the comment to the tag decl.
184 if (SourceMgr.isMacroArgExpansion(DeclLoc) &&
185 TD->isCompleteDefinition())
186 DeclLoc = SourceMgr.getExpansionLoc(DeclLoc);
187 }
188 }
189 }
190
191 // If the declaration doesn't map directly to a location in a file, we
192 // can't find the comment.
193 if (DeclLoc.isInvalid() || !DeclLoc.isFileID())
194 return nullptr;
195
196 if (!CommentsLoaded && ExternalSource) {
197 ExternalSource->ReadComments();
198
199#ifndef NDEBUG
200 ArrayRef<RawComment *> RawComments = Comments.getComments();
201 assert(std::is_sorted(RawComments.begin(), RawComments.end(),
202 BeforeThanCompare<RawComment>(SourceMgr)));
203#endif
204
205 CommentsLoaded = true;
206 }
207
208 ArrayRef<RawComment *> RawComments = Comments.getComments();
209 // If there are no comments anywhere, we won't find anything.
210 if (RawComments.empty())
211 return nullptr;
212
213 // Find the comment that occurs just after this declaration.
214 ArrayRef<RawComment *>::iterator Comment;
215 {
216 // When searching for comments during parsing, the comment we are looking
217 // for is usually among the last two comments we parsed -- check them
218 // first.
219 RawComment CommentAtDeclLoc(
220 SourceMgr, SourceRange(DeclLoc), LangOpts.CommentOpts, false);
221 BeforeThanCompare<RawComment> Compare(SourceMgr);
222 ArrayRef<RawComment *>::iterator MaybeBeforeDecl = RawComments.end() - 1;
223 bool Found = Compare(*MaybeBeforeDecl, &CommentAtDeclLoc);
224 if (!Found && RawComments.size() >= 2) {
225 MaybeBeforeDecl--;
226 Found = Compare(*MaybeBeforeDecl, &CommentAtDeclLoc);
227 }
228
229 if (Found) {
230 Comment = MaybeBeforeDecl + 1;
231 assert(Comment == std::lower_bound(RawComments.begin(), RawComments.end(),
232 &CommentAtDeclLoc, Compare));
233 } else {
234 // Slow path.
235 Comment = std::lower_bound(RawComments.begin(), RawComments.end(),
236 &CommentAtDeclLoc, Compare);
237 }
238 }
239
240 // Decompose the location for the declaration and find the beginning of the
241 // file buffer.
242 std::pair<FileID, unsigned> DeclLocDecomp = SourceMgr.getDecomposedLoc(DeclLoc);
243
244 // First check whether we have a trailing comment.
245 if (Comment != RawComments.end() &&
246 ((*Comment)->isDocumentation() || LangOpts.CommentOpts.ParseAllComments)
247 && (*Comment)->isTrailingComment() &&
248 (isa<FieldDecl>(D) || isa<EnumConstantDecl>(D) || isa<VarDecl>(D) ||
249 isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D) || isa<ObjCPropertyDecl>(D))) {
250 std::pair<FileID, unsigned> CommentBeginDecomp
251 = SourceMgr.getDecomposedLoc((*Comment)->getSourceRange().getBegin());
252 // Check that Doxygen trailing comment comes after the declaration, starts
253 // on the same line and in the same file as the declaration.
254 if (DeclLocDecomp.first == CommentBeginDecomp.first &&
255 SourceMgr.getLineNumber(DeclLocDecomp.first, DeclLocDecomp.second)
256 == SourceMgr.getLineNumber(CommentBeginDecomp.first,
257 CommentBeginDecomp.second)) {
258 (**Comment).setAttached();
259 return *Comment;
260 }
261 }
262
263 // The comment just after the declaration was not a trailing comment.
264 // Let's look at the previous comment.
265 if (Comment == RawComments.begin())
266 return nullptr;
267 --Comment;
268
269 // Check that we actually have a non-member Doxygen comment.
270 if (!((*Comment)->isDocumentation() ||
271 LangOpts.CommentOpts.ParseAllComments) ||
272 (*Comment)->isTrailingComment())
273 return nullptr;
274
275 // Decompose the end of the comment.
276 std::pair<FileID, unsigned> CommentEndDecomp
277 = SourceMgr.getDecomposedLoc((*Comment)->getSourceRange().getEnd());
278
279 // If the comment and the declaration aren't in the same file, then they
280 // aren't related.
281 if (DeclLocDecomp.first != CommentEndDecomp.first)
282 return nullptr;
283
284 // Get the corresponding buffer.
285 bool Invalid = false;
286 const char *Buffer = SourceMgr.getBufferData(DeclLocDecomp.first,
287 &Invalid).data();
288 if (Invalid)
289 return nullptr;
290
291 // Extract text between the comment and declaration.
292 StringRef Text(Buffer + CommentEndDecomp.second,
293 DeclLocDecomp.second - CommentEndDecomp.second);
294
295 // There should be no other declarations or preprocessor directives between
296 // comment and declaration.
297 if (Text.find_first_of(";{}#@") != StringRef::npos)
298 return nullptr;
299
300 (**Comment).setAttached();
301 return *Comment;
302}
303
304/// If we have a 'templated' declaration for a template, adjust 'D' to
305/// refer to the actual template.
306/// If we have an implicit instantiation, adjust 'D' to refer to template.
307static const Decl *adjustDeclToTemplate(const Decl *D) {
308 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
309 // Is this function declaration part of a function template?
310 if (const FunctionTemplateDecl *FTD = FD->getDescribedFunctionTemplate())
311 return FTD;
312
313 // Nothing to do if function is not an implicit instantiation.
314 if (FD->getTemplateSpecializationKind() != TSK_ImplicitInstantiation)
315 return D;
316
317 // Function is an implicit instantiation of a function template?
318 if (const FunctionTemplateDecl *FTD = FD->getPrimaryTemplate())
319 return FTD;
320
321 // Function is instantiated from a member definition of a class template?
322 if (const FunctionDecl *MemberDecl =
323 FD->getInstantiatedFromMemberFunction())
324 return MemberDecl;
325
326 return D;
327 }
328 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
329 // Static data member is instantiated from a member definition of a class
330 // template?
331 if (VD->isStaticDataMember())
332 if (const VarDecl *MemberDecl = VD->getInstantiatedFromStaticDataMember())
333 return MemberDecl;
334
335 return D;
336 }
337 if (const auto *CRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
338 // Is this class declaration part of a class template?
339 if (const ClassTemplateDecl *CTD = CRD->getDescribedClassTemplate())
340 return CTD;
341
342 // Class is an implicit instantiation of a class template or partial
343 // specialization?
344 if (const auto *CTSD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(CRD)) {
345 if (CTSD->getSpecializationKind() != TSK_ImplicitInstantiation)
346 return D;
347 llvm::PointerUnion<ClassTemplateDecl *,
348 ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *>
349 PU = CTSD->getSpecializedTemplateOrPartial();
350 return PU.is<ClassTemplateDecl*>() ?
351 static_cast<const Decl*>(PU.get<ClassTemplateDecl *>()) :
352 static_cast<const Decl*>(
353 PU.get<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl *>());
354 }
355
356 // Class is instantiated from a member definition of a class template?
357 if (const MemberSpecializationInfo *Info =
358 CRD->getMemberSpecializationInfo())
359 return Info->getInstantiatedFrom();
360
361 return D;
362 }
363 if (const auto *ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D)) {
364 // Enum is instantiated from a member definition of a class template?
365 if (const EnumDecl *MemberDecl = ED->getInstantiatedFromMemberEnum())
366 return MemberDecl;
367
368 return D;
369 }
370 // FIXME: Adjust alias templates?
371 return D;
372}
373
374const RawComment *ASTContext::getRawCommentForAnyRedecl(
375 const Decl *D,
376 const Decl **OriginalDecl) const {
377 D = adjustDeclToTemplate(D);
378
379 // Check whether we have cached a comment for this declaration already.
380 {
381 llvm::DenseMap<const Decl *, RawCommentAndCacheFlags>::iterator Pos =
382 RedeclComments.find(D);
383 if (Pos != RedeclComments.end()) {
384 const RawCommentAndCacheFlags &Raw = Pos->second;
385 if (Raw.getKind() != RawCommentAndCacheFlags::NoCommentInDecl) {
386 if (OriginalDecl)
387 *OriginalDecl = Raw.getOriginalDecl();
388 return Raw.getRaw();
389 }
390 }
391 }
392
393 // Search for comments attached to declarations in the redeclaration chain.
394 const RawComment *RC = nullptr;
395 const Decl *OriginalDeclForRC = nullptr;
396 for (auto I : D->redecls()) {
397 llvm::DenseMap<const Decl *, RawCommentAndCacheFlags>::iterator Pos =
398 RedeclComments.find(I);
399 if (Pos != RedeclComments.end()) {
400 const RawCommentAndCacheFlags &Raw = Pos->second;
401 if (Raw.getKind() != RawCommentAndCacheFlags::NoCommentInDecl) {
402 RC = Raw.getRaw();
403 OriginalDeclForRC = Raw.getOriginalDecl();
404 break;
405 }
406 } else {
407 RC = getRawCommentForDeclNoCache(I);
408 OriginalDeclForRC = I;
409 RawCommentAndCacheFlags Raw;
410 if (RC) {
411 // Call order swapped to work around ICE in VS2015 RTM (Release Win32)
412 // https://connect.microsoft.com/VisualStudio/feedback/details/1741530
413 Raw.setKind(RawCommentAndCacheFlags::FromDecl);
414 Raw.setRaw(RC);
415 } else
416 Raw.setKind(RawCommentAndCacheFlags::NoCommentInDecl);
417 Raw.setOriginalDecl(I);
418 RedeclComments[I] = Raw;
419 if (RC)
420 break;
421 }
422 }
423
424 // If we found a comment, it should be a documentation comment.
425 assert(!RC || RC->isDocumentation() || LangOpts.CommentOpts.ParseAllComments);
426
427 if (OriginalDecl)
428 *OriginalDecl = OriginalDeclForRC;
429
430 // Update cache for every declaration in the redeclaration chain.
431 RawCommentAndCacheFlags Raw;
432 Raw.setRaw(RC);
433 Raw.setKind(RawCommentAndCacheFlags::FromRedecl);
434 Raw.setOriginalDecl(OriginalDeclForRC);
435
436 for (auto I : D->redecls()) {
437 RawCommentAndCacheFlags &R = RedeclComments[I];
438 if (R.getKind() == RawCommentAndCacheFlags::NoCommentInDecl)
439 R = Raw;
440 }
441
442 return RC;
443}
444
445static void addRedeclaredMethods(const ObjCMethodDecl *ObjCMethod,
446 SmallVectorImpl<const NamedDecl *> &Redeclared) {
447 const DeclContext *DC = ObjCMethod->getDeclContext();
448 if (const auto *IMD = dyn_cast<ObjCImplDecl>(DC)) {
449 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *ID = IMD->getClassInterface();
450 if (!ID)
451 return;
452 // Add redeclared method here.
453 for (const auto *Ext : ID->known_extensions()) {
454 if (ObjCMethodDecl *RedeclaredMethod =
455 Ext->getMethod(ObjCMethod->getSelector(),
456 ObjCMethod->isInstanceMethod()))
457 Redeclared.push_back(RedeclaredMethod);
458 }
459 }
460}
461
462comments::FullComment *ASTContext::cloneFullComment(comments::FullComment *FC,
463 const Decl *D) const {
464 auto *ThisDeclInfo = new (*this) comments::DeclInfo;
465 ThisDeclInfo->CommentDecl = D;
466 ThisDeclInfo->IsFilled = false;
467 ThisDeclInfo->fill();
468 ThisDeclInfo->CommentDecl = FC->getDecl();
469 if (!ThisDeclInfo->TemplateParameters)
470 ThisDeclInfo->TemplateParameters = FC->getDeclInfo()->TemplateParameters;
471 comments::FullComment *CFC =
472 new (*this) comments::FullComment(FC->getBlocks(),
473 ThisDeclInfo);
474 return CFC;
475}
476
477comments::FullComment *ASTContext::getLocalCommentForDeclUncached(const Decl *D) const {
478 const RawComment *RC = getRawCommentForDeclNoCache(D);
479 return RC ? RC->parse(*this, nullptr, D) : nullptr;
480}
481
482comments::FullComment *ASTContext::getCommentForDecl(
483 const Decl *D,
484 const Preprocessor *PP) const {
485 if (D->isInvalidDecl())
486 return nullptr;
487 D = adjustDeclToTemplate(D);
488
489 const Decl *Canonical = D->getCanonicalDecl();
490 llvm::DenseMap<const Decl *, comments::FullComment *>::iterator Pos =
491 ParsedComments.find(Canonical);
492
493 if (Pos != ParsedComments.end()) {
494 if (Canonical != D) {
495 comments::FullComment *FC = Pos->second;
496 comments::FullComment *CFC = cloneFullComment(FC, D);
497 return CFC;
498 }
499 return Pos->second;
500 }
501
502 const Decl *OriginalDecl;
503
504 const RawComment *RC = getRawCommentForAnyRedecl(D, &OriginalDecl);
505 if (!RC) {
506 if (isa<ObjCMethodDecl>(D) || isa<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
507 SmallVector<const NamedDecl*, 8> Overridden;
508 const auto *OMD = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
509 if (OMD && OMD->isPropertyAccessor())
510 if (const ObjCPropertyDecl *PDecl = OMD->findPropertyDecl())
511 if (comments::FullComment *FC = getCommentForDecl(PDecl, PP))
512 return cloneFullComment(FC, D);
513 if (OMD)
514 addRedeclaredMethods(OMD, Overridden);
515 getOverriddenMethods(dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(D), Overridden);
516 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Overridden.size(); i < e; i++)
517 if (comments::FullComment *FC = getCommentForDecl(Overridden[i], PP))
518 return cloneFullComment(FC, D);
519 }
520 else if (const auto *TD = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(D)) {
521 // Attach any tag type's documentation to its typedef if latter
522 // does not have one of its own.
523 QualType QT = TD->getUnderlyingType();
524 if (const auto *TT = QT->getAs<TagType>())
525 if (const Decl *TD = TT->getDecl())
526 if (comments::FullComment *FC = getCommentForDecl(TD, PP))
527 return cloneFullComment(FC, D);
528 }
529 else if (const auto *IC = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(D)) {
530 while (IC->getSuperClass()) {
531 IC = IC->getSuperClass();
532 if (comments::FullComment *FC = getCommentForDecl(IC, PP))
533 return cloneFullComment(FC, D);
534 }
535 }
536 else if (const auto *CD = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(D)) {
537 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *IC = CD->getClassInterface())
538 if (comments::FullComment *FC = getCommentForDecl(IC, PP))
539 return cloneFullComment(FC, D);
540 }
541 else if (const auto *RD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
542 if (!(RD = RD->getDefinition()))
543 return nullptr;
544 // Check non-virtual bases.
545 for (const auto &I : RD->bases()) {
546 if (I.isVirtual() || (I.getAccessSpecifier() != AS_public))
547 continue;
548 QualType Ty = I.getType();
549 if (Ty.isNull())
550 continue;
551 if (const CXXRecordDecl *NonVirtualBase = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
552 if (!(NonVirtualBase= NonVirtualBase->getDefinition()))
553 continue;
554
555 if (comments::FullComment *FC = getCommentForDecl((NonVirtualBase), PP))
556 return cloneFullComment(FC, D);
557 }
558 }
559 // Check virtual bases.
560 for (const auto &I : RD->vbases()) {
561 if (I.getAccessSpecifier() != AS_public)
562 continue;
563 QualType Ty = I.getType();
564 if (Ty.isNull())
565 continue;
566 if (const CXXRecordDecl *VirtualBase = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
567 if (!(VirtualBase= VirtualBase->getDefinition()))
568 continue;
569 if (comments::FullComment *FC = getCommentForDecl((VirtualBase), PP))
570 return cloneFullComment(FC, D);
571 }
572 }
573 }
574 return nullptr;
575 }
576
577 // If the RawComment was attached to other redeclaration of this Decl, we
578 // should parse the comment in context of that other Decl. This is important
579 // because comments can contain references to parameter names which can be
580 // different across redeclarations.
581 if (D != OriginalDecl)
582 return getCommentForDecl(OriginalDecl, PP);
583
584 comments::FullComment *FC = RC->parse(*this, PP, D);
585 ParsedComments[Canonical] = FC;
586 return FC;
587}
588
589void
590ASTContext::CanonicalTemplateTemplateParm::Profile(llvm::FoldingSetNodeID &ID,
591 TemplateTemplateParmDecl *Parm) {
592 ID.AddInteger(Parm->getDepth());
593 ID.AddInteger(Parm->getPosition());
594 ID.AddBoolean(Parm->isParameterPack());
595
596 TemplateParameterList *Params = Parm->getTemplateParameters();
597 ID.AddInteger(Params->size());
598 for (TemplateParameterList::const_iterator P = Params->begin(),
599 PEnd = Params->end();
600 P != PEnd; ++P) {
601 if (const auto *TTP = dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(*P)) {
602 ID.AddInteger(0);
603 ID.AddBoolean(TTP->isParameterPack());
604 continue;
605 }
606
607 if (const auto *NTTP = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(*P)) {
608 ID.AddInteger(1);
609 ID.AddBoolean(NTTP->isParameterPack());
610 ID.AddPointer(NTTP->getType().getCanonicalType().getAsOpaquePtr());
611 if (NTTP->isExpandedParameterPack()) {
612 ID.AddBoolean(true);
613 ID.AddInteger(NTTP->getNumExpansionTypes());
614 for (unsigned I = 0, N = NTTP->getNumExpansionTypes(); I != N; ++I) {
615 QualType T = NTTP->getExpansionType(I);
616 ID.AddPointer(T.getCanonicalType().getAsOpaquePtr());
617 }
618 } else
619 ID.AddBoolean(false);
620 continue;
621 }
622
623 auto *TTP = cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(*P);
624 ID.AddInteger(2);
625 Profile(ID, TTP);
626 }
627}
628
629TemplateTemplateParmDecl *
630ASTContext::getCanonicalTemplateTemplateParmDecl(
631 TemplateTemplateParmDecl *TTP) const {
632 // Check if we already have a canonical template template parameter.
633 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
634 CanonicalTemplateTemplateParm::Profile(ID, TTP);
635 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
636 CanonicalTemplateTemplateParm *Canonical
637 = CanonTemplateTemplateParms.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
638 if (Canonical)
639 return Canonical->getParam();
640
641 // Build a canonical template parameter list.
642 TemplateParameterList *Params = TTP->getTemplateParameters();
643 SmallVector<NamedDecl *, 4> CanonParams;
644 CanonParams.reserve(Params->size());
645 for (TemplateParameterList::const_iterator P = Params->begin(),
646 PEnd = Params->end();
647 P != PEnd; ++P) {
648 if (const auto *TTP = dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(*P))
649 CanonParams.push_back(
650 TemplateTypeParmDecl::Create(*this, getTranslationUnitDecl(),
651 SourceLocation(),
652 SourceLocation(),
653 TTP->getDepth(),
654 TTP->getIndex(), nullptr, false,
655 TTP->isParameterPack()));
656 else if (const auto *NTTP = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(*P)) {
657 QualType T = getCanonicalType(NTTP->getType());
658 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T);
659 NonTypeTemplateParmDecl *Param;
660 if (NTTP->isExpandedParameterPack()) {
661 SmallVector<QualType, 2> ExpandedTypes;
662 SmallVector<TypeSourceInfo *, 2> ExpandedTInfos;
663 for (unsigned I = 0, N = NTTP->getNumExpansionTypes(); I != N; ++I) {
664 ExpandedTypes.push_back(getCanonicalType(NTTP->getExpansionType(I)));
665 ExpandedTInfos.push_back(
666 getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(ExpandedTypes.back()));
667 }
668
669 Param = NonTypeTemplateParmDecl::Create(*this, getTranslationUnitDecl(),
670 SourceLocation(),
671 SourceLocation(),
672 NTTP->getDepth(),
673 NTTP->getPosition(), nullptr,
674 T,
675 TInfo,
676 ExpandedTypes,
677 ExpandedTInfos);
678 } else {
679 Param = NonTypeTemplateParmDecl::Create(*this, getTranslationUnitDecl(),
680 SourceLocation(),
681 SourceLocation(),
682 NTTP->getDepth(),
683 NTTP->getPosition(), nullptr,
684 T,
685 NTTP->isParameterPack(),
686 TInfo);
687 }
688 CanonParams.push_back(Param);
689
690 } else
691 CanonParams.push_back(getCanonicalTemplateTemplateParmDecl(
692 cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(*P)));
693 }
694
695 assert(!TTP->getRequiresClause() &&
696 "Unexpected requires-clause on template template-parameter");
697 Expr *const CanonRequiresClause = nullptr;
698
699 TemplateTemplateParmDecl *CanonTTP
700 = TemplateTemplateParmDecl::Create(*this, getTranslationUnitDecl(),
701 SourceLocation(), TTP->getDepth(),
702 TTP->getPosition(),
703 TTP->isParameterPack(),
704 nullptr,
705 TemplateParameterList::Create(*this, SourceLocation(),
706 SourceLocation(),
707 CanonParams,
708 SourceLocation(),
709 CanonRequiresClause));
710
711 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
712 Canonical = CanonTemplateTemplateParms.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
713 assert(!Canonical && "Shouldn't be in the map!");
714 (void)Canonical;
715
716 // Create the canonical template template parameter entry.
717 Canonical = new (*this) CanonicalTemplateTemplateParm(CanonTTP);
718 CanonTemplateTemplateParms.InsertNode(Canonical, InsertPos);
719 return CanonTTP;
720}
721
722CXXABI *ASTContext::createCXXABI(const TargetInfo &T) {
723 if (!LangOpts.CPlusPlus) return nullptr;
724
725 switch (T.getCXXABI().getKind()) {
726 case TargetCXXABI::GenericARM: // Same as Itanium at this level
727 case TargetCXXABI::iOS:
728 case TargetCXXABI::iOS64:
729 case TargetCXXABI::WatchOS:
730 case TargetCXXABI::GenericAArch64:
731 case TargetCXXABI::GenericMIPS:
732 case TargetCXXABI::GenericItanium:
733 case TargetCXXABI::WebAssembly:
734 return CreateItaniumCXXABI(*this);
735 case TargetCXXABI::Microsoft:
736 return CreateMicrosoftCXXABI(*this);
737 }
738 llvm_unreachable("Invalid CXXABI type!");
739}
740
741static const LangASMap *getAddressSpaceMap(const TargetInfo &T,
742 const LangOptions &LOpts) {
743 if (LOpts.FakeAddressSpaceMap) {
744 // The fake address space map must have a distinct entry for each
745 // language-specific address space.
746 static const unsigned FakeAddrSpaceMap[] = {
747 0, // Default
748 1, // opencl_global
749 3, // opencl_local
750 2, // opencl_constant
751 0, // opencl_private
752 4, // opencl_generic
753 5, // cuda_device
754 6, // cuda_constant
755 7 // cuda_shared
756 };
757 return &FakeAddrSpaceMap;
758 } else {
759 return &T.getAddressSpaceMap();
760 }
761}
762
763static bool isAddrSpaceMapManglingEnabled(const TargetInfo &TI,
764 const LangOptions &LangOpts) {
765 switch (LangOpts.getAddressSpaceMapMangling()) {
766 case LangOptions::ASMM_Target:
767 return TI.useAddressSpaceMapMangling();
768 case LangOptions::ASMM_On:
769 return true;
770 case LangOptions::ASMM_Off:
771 return false;
772 }
773 llvm_unreachable("getAddressSpaceMapMangling() doesn't cover anything.");
774}

776ASTContext::ASTContext(LangOptions &LOpts, SourceManager &SM,
777 IdentifierTable &idents, SelectorTable &sels,
778 Builtin::Context &builtins)
779 : FunctionProtoTypes(this_()), TemplateSpecializationTypes(this_()),
780 DependentTemplateSpecializationTypes(this_()),
781 SubstTemplateTemplateParmPacks(this_()), SourceMgr(SM), LangOpts(LOpts),
782 SanitizerBL(new SanitizerBlacklist(LangOpts.SanitizerBlacklistFiles, SM)),
783 XRayFilter(new XRayFunctionFilter(LangOpts.XRayAlwaysInstrumentFiles,
784 LangOpts.XRayNeverInstrumentFiles,
785 LangOpts.XRayAttrListFiles, SM)),
786 PrintingPolicy(LOpts), Idents(idents), Selectors(sels),
787 BuiltinInfo(builtins), DeclarationNames(*this), Comments(SM),
788 CommentCommandTraits(BumpAlloc, LOpts.CommentOpts),
789 CompCategories(this_()), LastSDM(nullptr, 0) {
790 TUDecl = TranslationUnitDecl::Create(*this);
791 TraversalScope = {TUDecl};
792}
793
794ASTContext::~ASTContext() {
795 // Release the DenseMaps associated with DeclContext objects.
796 // FIXME: Is this the ideal solution?
797 ReleaseDeclContextMaps();
798
799 // Call all of the deallocation functions on all of their targets.
800 for (auto &Pair : Deallocations)
801 (Pair.first)(Pair.second);
802
803 // ASTRecordLayout objects in ASTRecordLayouts must always be destroyed
804 // because they can contain DenseMaps.
805 for (llvm::DenseMap<const ObjCContainerDecl*,
806 const ASTRecordLayout*>::iterator
807 I = ObjCLayouts.begin(), E = ObjCLayouts.end(); I != E; )
808 // Increment in loop to prevent using deallocated memory.
809 if (auto *R = const_cast<ASTRecordLayout *>((I++)->second))
810 R->Destroy(*this);
811
812 for (llvm::DenseMap<const RecordDecl*, const ASTRecordLayout*>::iterator
813 I = ASTRecordLayouts.begin(), E = ASTRecordLayouts.end(); I != E; ) {
814 // Increment in loop to prevent using deallocated memory.
815 if (auto *R = const_cast<ASTRecordLayout *>((I++)->second))
816 R->Destroy(*this);
817 }
818
819 for (llvm::DenseMap<const Decl*, AttrVec*>::iterator A = DeclAttrs.begin(),
820 AEnd = DeclAttrs.end();
821 A != AEnd; ++A)
822 A->second->~AttrVec();
823
824 for (std::pair<const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *, APValue *> &MTVPair :
825 MaterializedTemporaryValues)
826 MTVPair.second->~APValue();
827
828 for (const auto &Value : ModuleInitializers)
829 Value.second->~PerModuleInitializers();
830}
831
832class ASTContext::ParentMap {
833 /// Contains parents of a node.
834 using ParentVector = llvm::SmallVector<ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode, 2>;
835
836 /// Maps from a node to its parents. This is used for nodes that have
837 /// pointer identity only, which are more common and we can save space by
838 /// only storing a unique pointer to them.
839 using ParentMapPointers = llvm::DenseMap<
840 const void *,
841 llvm::PointerUnion4<const Decl *, const Stmt *,
842 ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode *, ParentVector *>>;
843
844 /// Parent map for nodes without pointer identity. We store a full
845 /// DynTypedNode for all keys.
846 using ParentMapOtherNodes = llvm::DenseMap<
847 ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode,
848 llvm::PointerUnion4<const Decl *, const Stmt *,
849 ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode *, ParentVector *>>;
850
851 ParentMapPointers PointerParents;
852 ParentMapOtherNodes OtherParents;
853 class ASTVisitor;
854
855 static ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode
856 getSingleDynTypedNodeFromParentMap(ParentMapPointers::mapped_type U) {
857 if (const auto *D = U.dyn_cast<const Decl *>())
858 return ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode::create(*D);
859 if (const auto *S = U.dyn_cast<const Stmt *>())
860 return ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode::create(*S);
861 return *U.get<ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode *>();
862 }
863
864 template <typename NodeTy, typename MapTy>
865 static ASTContext::DynTypedNodeList getDynNodeFromMap(const NodeTy &Node,
866 const MapTy &Map) {
867 auto I = Map.find(Node);
868 if (I == Map.end()) {
869 return llvm::ArrayRef<ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode>();
870 }
871 if (const auto *V = I->second.template dyn_cast<ParentVector *>()) {
872 return llvm::makeArrayRef(*V);
873 }
874 return getSingleDynTypedNodeFromParentMap(I->second);
875 }
876
877public:
878 ParentMap(ASTContext &Ctx);
879 ~ParentMap() {
880 for (const auto &Entry : PointerParents) {
881 if (Entry.second.is<ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode *>()) {
882 delete Entry.second.get<ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode *>();
883 } else if (Entry.second.is<ParentVector *>()) {
884 delete Entry.second.get<ParentVector *>();
885 }
886 }
887 for (const auto &Entry : OtherParents) {
888 if (Entry.second.is<ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode *>()) {
889 delete Entry.second.get<ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode *>();
890 } else if (Entry.second.is<ParentVector *>()) {
891 delete Entry.second.get<ParentVector *>();
892 }
893 }
894 }
895
896 DynTypedNodeList getParents(const ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode &Node) {
897 if (Node.getNodeKind().hasPointerIdentity())
898 return getDynNodeFromMap(Node.getMemoizationData(), PointerParents);
899 return getDynNodeFromMap(Node, OtherParents);
900 }
901};
902
903void ASTContext::setTraversalScope(const std::vector<Decl *> &TopLevelDecls) {
904 TraversalScope = TopLevelDecls;
905 Parents.reset();
906}

909 Deallocations.push_back({Callback, Data});
910}

916
917void ASTContext::PrintStats() const {
918 llvm::errs() << "\n*** AST Context Stats:\n";
919 llvm::errs() << " " << Types.size() << " types total.\n";
920
921 unsigned counts[] = {
922#define TYPE(Name, Parent) 0,
923#define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Name, Parent)
924#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
925 0 // Extra
926 };
927
928 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Types.size(); i != e; ++i) {
929 Type *T = Types[i];
930 counts[(unsigned)T->getTypeClass()]++;
931 }
932
933 unsigned Idx = 0;
934 unsigned TotalBytes = 0;
935#define TYPE(Name, Parent) \
936 if (counts[Idx]) \
937 llvm::errs() << " " << counts[Idx] << " " << #Name \
938 << " types, " << sizeof(Name##Type) << " each " \
939 << "(" << counts[Idx] * sizeof(Name##Type) \
940 << " bytes)\n"; \
941 TotalBytes += counts[Idx] * sizeof(Name##Type); \
942 ++Idx;
943#define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Name, Parent)
944#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
945
946 llvm::errs() << "Total bytes = " << TotalBytes << "\n";
947
948 // Implicit special member functions.
949 llvm::errs() << NumImplicitDefaultConstructorsDeclared << "/"
950 << NumImplicitDefaultConstructors
951 << " implicit default constructors created\n";
952 llvm::errs() << NumImplicitCopyConstructorsDeclared << "/"
953 << NumImplicitCopyConstructors
954 << " implicit copy constructors created\n";
955 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
956 llvm::errs() << NumImplicitMoveConstructorsDeclared << "/"
957 << NumImplicitMoveConstructors
958 << " implicit move constructors created\n";
959 llvm::errs() << NumImplicitCopyAssignmentOperatorsDeclared << "/"
960 << NumImplicitCopyAssignmentOperators
961 << " implicit copy assignment operators created\n";
962 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
963 llvm::errs() << NumImplicitMoveAssignmentOperatorsDeclared << "/"
964 << NumImplicitMoveAssignmentOperators
965 << " implicit move assignment operators created\n";
966 llvm::errs() << NumImplicitDestructorsDeclared << "/"
967 << NumImplicitDestructors
968 << " implicit destructors created\n";
969
970 if (ExternalSource) {
971 llvm::errs() << "\n";
972 ExternalSource->PrintStats();
973 }
974
975 BumpAlloc.PrintStats();
976}
977
978void ASTContext::mergeDefinitionIntoModule(NamedDecl *ND, Module *M,
979 bool NotifyListeners) {
980 if (NotifyListeners)
981 if (auto *Listener = getASTMutationListener())
982 Listener->RedefinedHiddenDefinition(ND, M);
983
984 MergedDefModules[cast<NamedDecl>(ND->getCanonicalDecl())].push_back(M);
985}
986
987void ASTContext::deduplicateMergedDefinitonsFor(NamedDecl *ND) {
988 auto It = MergedDefModules.find(cast<NamedDecl>(ND->getCanonicalDecl()));
989 if (It == MergedDefModules.end())
990 return;
991
992 auto &Merged = It->second;
993 llvm::DenseSet<Module*> Found;
994 for (Module *&M : Merged)
995 if (!Found.insert(M).second)
996 M = nullptr;
997 Merged.erase(std::remove(Merged.begin(), Merged.end(), nullptr), Merged.end());
998}
999
1000void ASTContext::PerModuleInitializers::resolve(ASTContext &Ctx) {
1001 if (LazyInitializers.empty())
1002 return;
1003
1004 auto *Source = Ctx.getExternalSource();
1005 assert(Source && "lazy initializers but no external source");
1006
1007 auto LazyInits = std::move(LazyInitializers);
1008 LazyInitializers.clear();
1009
1010 for (auto ID : LazyInits)
1011 Initializers.push_back(Source->GetExternalDecl(ID));
1012
1013 assert(LazyInitializers.empty() &&
1014 "GetExternalDecl for lazy module initializer added more inits");
1015}
1016
1017void ASTContext::addModuleInitializer(Module *M, Decl *D) {
1018 // One special case: if we add a module initializer that imports another
1019 // module, and that module's only initializer is an ImportDecl, simplify.
1020 if (const auto *ID = dyn_cast<ImportDecl>(D)) {
1021 auto It = ModuleInitializers.find(ID->getImportedModule());
1022
1023 // Maybe the ImportDecl does nothing at all. (Common case.)
1024 if (It == ModuleInitializers.end())
1025 return;
1026
1027 // Maybe the ImportDecl only imports another ImportDecl.
1028 auto &Imported = *It->second;
1029 if (Imported.Initializers.size() + Imported.LazyInitializers.size() == 1) {
1030 Imported.resolve(*this);
1031 auto *OnlyDecl = Imported.Initializers.front();
1032 if (isa<ImportDecl>(OnlyDecl))
1033 D = OnlyDecl;
1034 }
1035 }
1036
1037 auto *&Inits = ModuleInitializers[M];
1038 if (!Inits)
1039 Inits = new (*this) PerModuleInitializers;
1040 Inits->Initializers.push_back(D);
1041}
1042
1043void ASTContext::addLazyModuleInitializers(Module *M, ArrayRef<uint32_t> IDs) {
1044 auto *&Inits = ModuleInitializers[M];
1045 if (!Inits)
1046 Inits = new (*this) PerModuleInitializers;
1047 Inits->LazyInitializers.insert(Inits->LazyInitializers.end(),
1048 IDs.begin(), IDs.end());
1049}
1050
1051ArrayRef<Decl *> ASTContext::getModuleInitializers(Module *M) {
1052 auto It = ModuleInitializers.find(M);
1053 if (It == ModuleInitializers.end())
1054 return None;
1055
1056 auto *Inits = It->second;
1057 Inits->resolve(*this);
1058 return Inits->Initializers;
1059}

1061ExternCContextDecl *ASTContext::getExternCContextDecl() const {
1062 if (!ExternCContext)
1063 ExternCContext = ExternCContextDecl::Create(*this, getTranslationUnitDecl());
1064
1065 return ExternCContext;
1066}

1093
1094RecordDecl *ASTContext::buildImplicitRecord(StringRef Name,
1095 RecordDecl::TagKind TK) const {
1096 SourceLocation Loc;
1097 RecordDecl *NewDecl;
1098 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
1099 NewDecl = CXXRecordDecl::Create(*this, TK, getTranslationUnitDecl(), Loc,
1100 Loc, &Idents.get(Name));
1101 else
1102 NewDecl = RecordDecl::Create(*this, TK, getTranslationUnitDecl(), Loc, Loc,
1103 &Idents.get(Name));
1104 NewDecl->setImplicit();
1105 NewDecl->addAttr(TypeVisibilityAttr::CreateImplicit(
1106 const_cast<ASTContext &>(*this), TypeVisibilityAttr::Default));
1107 return NewDecl;
1108}
1109
1110TypedefDecl *ASTContext::buildImplicitTypedef(QualType T,
1111 StringRef Name) const {
1112 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(T);
1113 TypedefDecl *NewDecl = TypedefDecl::Create(
1114 const_cast<ASTContext &>(*this), getTranslationUnitDecl(),
1115 SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(), &Idents.get(Name), TInfo);
1116 NewDecl->setImplicit();
1117 return NewDecl;
1118}

1120TypedefDecl *ASTContext::getIntCapDecl() const {
1121 if (!IntCapDecl) {
1122 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(IntCapTy);
1123 IntCapDecl = TypedefDecl::Create(const_cast<ASTContext &>(*this),
1124 getTranslationUnitDecl(),
1125 SourceLocation(),
1126 SourceLocation(),
1127 &Idents.get("__intcap_t"),
1128 TInfo);
1129 }
1130
1131 return IntCapDecl;
1132}

1136 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(UnsignedIntCapTy);
1137 UIntCapDecl = TypedefDecl::Create(const_cast<ASTContext &>(*this),
1138 getTranslationUnitDecl(),
1139 SourceLocation(),
1140 SourceLocation(),
1141 &Idents.get("__uintcap_t"),
1142 TInfo);
1143 }
1144
1145 return UIntCapDecl;
1146}

1160void ASTContext::InitBuiltinType(CanQualType &R, BuiltinType::Kind K) {
1161 auto *Ty = new (*this, TypeAlignment) BuiltinType(K);
1162 R = CanQualType::CreateUnsafe(QualType(Ty, 0));
1163 Types.push_back(Ty);
1164}
1165
1166void ASTContext::InitBuiltinTypes(const TargetInfo &Target,
1167 const TargetInfo *AuxTarget) {
1168 assert((!this->Target || this->Target == &Target) &&
1169 "Incorrect target reinitialization");
1170 assert(VoidTy.isNull() && "Context reinitialized?");
1171
1172 this->Target = &Target;
1173 this->AuxTarget = AuxTarget;
1174
1175 ABI.reset(createCXXABI(Target));
1176 AddrSpaceMap = getAddressSpaceMap(Target, LangOpts);
1177 AddrSpaceMapMangling = isAddrSpaceMapManglingEnabled(Target, LangOpts);
1178
1179 // C99 6.2.5p19.
1180 InitBuiltinType(VoidTy, BuiltinType::Void);
1181
1182 // C99 6.2.5p2.
1183 InitBuiltinType(BoolTy, BuiltinType::Bool);
1184 // C99 6.2.5p3.
1185 if (LangOpts.CharIsSigned)
1186 InitBuiltinType(CharTy, BuiltinType::Char_S);
1187 else
1188 InitBuiltinType(CharTy, BuiltinType::Char_U);
1189 // C99 6.2.5p4.
1190 InitBuiltinType(SignedCharTy, BuiltinType::SChar);
1191 InitBuiltinType(ShortTy, BuiltinType::Short);
1192 InitBuiltinType(IntTy, BuiltinType::Int);
1193 InitBuiltinType(LongTy, BuiltinType::Long);
1194 InitBuiltinType(LongLongTy, BuiltinType::LongLong);
1195
1196 // C99 6.2.5p6.
1197 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedCharTy, BuiltinType::UChar);
1198 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedShortTy, BuiltinType::UShort);
1199 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedIntTy, BuiltinType::UInt);
1200 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedLongTy, BuiltinType::ULong);
1201 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedLongLongTy, BuiltinType::ULongLong);
1202
1203 // C99 6.2.5p10.
1204 InitBuiltinType(FloatTy, BuiltinType::Float);
1205 InitBuiltinType(DoubleTy, BuiltinType::Double);
1206 InitBuiltinType(LongDoubleTy, BuiltinType::LongDouble);
1207
1208 InitBuiltinType(IntCapTy, BuiltinType::IntCap);
1209 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedIntCapTy, BuiltinType::UIntCap);
1210
1211 // GNU extension, __float128 for IEEE quadruple precision
1212 InitBuiltinType(Float128Ty, BuiltinType::Float128);
1213
1214 // C11 extension ISO/IEC TS 18661-3
1215 InitBuiltinType(Float16Ty, BuiltinType::Float16);
1216
1217 // ISO/IEC JTC1 SC22 WG14 N1169 Extension
1218 InitBuiltinType(ShortAccumTy, BuiltinType::ShortAccum);
1219 InitBuiltinType(AccumTy, BuiltinType::Accum);
1220 InitBuiltinType(LongAccumTy, BuiltinType::LongAccum);
1221 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedShortAccumTy, BuiltinType::UShortAccum);
1222 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedAccumTy, BuiltinType::UAccum);
1223 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedLongAccumTy, BuiltinType::ULongAccum);
1224 InitBuiltinType(ShortFractTy, BuiltinType::ShortFract);
1225 InitBuiltinType(FractTy, BuiltinType::Fract);
1226 InitBuiltinType(LongFractTy, BuiltinType::LongFract);
1227 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedShortFractTy, BuiltinType::UShortFract);
1228 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedFractTy, BuiltinType::UFract);
1229 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedLongFractTy, BuiltinType::ULongFract);
1230 InitBuiltinType(SatShortAccumTy, BuiltinType::SatShortAccum);
1231 InitBuiltinType(SatAccumTy, BuiltinType::SatAccum);
1232 InitBuiltinType(SatLongAccumTy, BuiltinType::SatLongAccum);
1233 InitBuiltinType(SatUnsignedShortAccumTy, BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum);
1234 InitBuiltinType(SatUnsignedAccumTy, BuiltinType::SatUAccum);
1235 InitBuiltinType(SatUnsignedLongAccumTy, BuiltinType::SatULongAccum);
1236 InitBuiltinType(SatShortFractTy, BuiltinType::SatShortFract);
1237 InitBuiltinType(SatFractTy, BuiltinType::SatFract);
1238 InitBuiltinType(SatLongFractTy, BuiltinType::SatLongFract);
1239 InitBuiltinType(SatUnsignedShortFractTy, BuiltinType::SatUShortFract);
1240 InitBuiltinType(SatUnsignedFractTy, BuiltinType::SatUFract);
1241 InitBuiltinType(SatUnsignedLongFractTy, BuiltinType::SatULongFract);
1242
1243 // GNU extension, 128-bit integers.
1244 InitBuiltinType(Int128Ty, BuiltinType::Int128);
1245 InitBuiltinType(UnsignedInt128Ty, BuiltinType::UInt128);
1246
1247 // C++ 3.9.1p5
1248 if (TargetInfo::isTypeSigned(Target.getWCharType()))
1249 InitBuiltinType(WCharTy, BuiltinType::WChar_S);
1250 else // -fshort-wchar makes wchar_t be unsigned.
1251 InitBuiltinType(WCharTy, BuiltinType::WChar_U);
1252 if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus && LangOpts.WChar)
1253 WideCharTy = WCharTy;
1254 else {
1255 // C99 (or C++ using -fno-wchar).
1256 WideCharTy = getFromTargetType(Target.getWCharType());
1257 }
1258
1259 WIntTy = getFromTargetType(Target.getWIntType());
1260
1261 // C++20 (proposed)
1262 InitBuiltinType(Char8Ty, BuiltinType::Char8);
1263
1264 if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus) // C++0x 3.9.1p5, extension for C++
1265 InitBuiltinType(Char16Ty, BuiltinType::Char16);
1266 else // C99
1267 Char16Ty = getFromTargetType(Target.getChar16Type());
1268
1269 if (LangOpts.CPlusPlus) // C++0x 3.9.1p5, extension for C++
1270 InitBuiltinType(Char32Ty, BuiltinType::Char32);
1271 else // C99
1272 Char32Ty = getFromTargetType(Target.getChar32Type());
1273
1274 // Placeholder type for type-dependent expressions whose type is
1275 // completely unknown. No code should ever check a type against
1276 // DependentTy and users should never see it; however, it is here to
1277 // help diagnose failures to properly check for type-dependent
1278 // expressions.
1279 InitBuiltinType(DependentTy, BuiltinType::Dependent);
1280
1281 // Placeholder type for functions.
1282 InitBuiltinType(OverloadTy, BuiltinType::Overload);
1283
1284 // Placeholder type for bound members.
1285 InitBuiltinType(BoundMemberTy, BuiltinType::BoundMember);
1286
1287 // Placeholder type for pseudo-objects.
1288 InitBuiltinType(PseudoObjectTy, BuiltinType::PseudoObject);
1289
1290 // "any" type; useful for debugger-like clients.
1291 InitBuiltinType(UnknownAnyTy, BuiltinType::UnknownAny);
1292
1293 // Placeholder type for unbridged ARC casts.
1294 InitBuiltinType(ARCUnbridgedCastTy, BuiltinType::ARCUnbridgedCast);
1295
1296 // Placeholder type for builtin functions.
1297 InitBuiltinType(BuiltinFnTy, BuiltinType::BuiltinFn);
1298
1299 // Placeholder type for OMP array sections.
1300 if (LangOpts.OpenMP)
1301 InitBuiltinType(OMPArraySectionTy, BuiltinType::OMPArraySection);
1302
1303 // C99 6.2.5p11.
1304 FloatComplexTy = getComplexType(FloatTy);
1305 DoubleComplexTy = getComplexType(DoubleTy);
1306 LongDoubleComplexTy = getComplexType(LongDoubleTy);
1307 Float128ComplexTy = getComplexType(Float128Ty);
1308
1309 // Builtin types for 'id', 'Class', and 'SEL'.
1310 InitBuiltinType(ObjCBuiltinIdTy, BuiltinType::ObjCId);
1311 InitBuiltinType(ObjCBuiltinClassTy, BuiltinType::ObjCClass);
1312 InitBuiltinType(ObjCBuiltinSelTy, BuiltinType::ObjCSel);
1313
1314 if (LangOpts.OpenCL) {
1315#define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
1316 InitBuiltinType(SingletonId, BuiltinType::Id);
1317#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
1318
1319 InitBuiltinType(OCLSamplerTy, BuiltinType::OCLSampler);
1320 InitBuiltinType(OCLEventTy, BuiltinType::OCLEvent);
1321 InitBuiltinType(OCLClkEventTy, BuiltinType::OCLClkEvent);
1322 InitBuiltinType(OCLQueueTy, BuiltinType::OCLQueue);
1323 InitBuiltinType(OCLReserveIDTy, BuiltinType::OCLReserveID);
1324
1325#define EXT_OPAQUE_TYPE(ExtType, Id, Ext) \
1326 InitBuiltinType(Id##Ty, BuiltinType::Id);
1327#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLExtensionTypes.def"
1328 }
1329
1330 // Builtin type for __objc_yes and __objc_no
1331 ObjCBuiltinBoolTy = (Target.useSignedCharForObjCBool() ?
1332 SignedCharTy : BoolTy);
1333
1334 ObjCConstantStringType = QualType();
1335
1336 ObjCSuperType = QualType();
1337
1338 // void * type
1339 if (LangOpts.OpenCLVersion >= 200) {
1340 auto Q = VoidTy.getQualifiers();
1341 Q.setAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_generic);
1342 VoidPtrTy = getPointerType(getCanonicalType(
1343 getQualifiedType(VoidTy.getUnqualifiedType(), Q)));
1344 } else {
1345 VoidPtrTy = getPointerType(VoidTy);
1346 }
1347
1348 // nullptr type (C++0x 2.14.7)
1349 InitBuiltinType(NullPtrTy, BuiltinType::NullPtr);
1350
1351 // half type (OpenCL 6.1.1.1) / ARM NEON __fp16
1352 InitBuiltinType(HalfTy, BuiltinType::Half);
1353
1354 // Builtin type used to help define __builtin_va_list.
1355 VaListTagDecl = nullptr;
1356}

1358DiagnosticsEngine &ASTContext::getDiagnostics() const {
1359 return SourceMgr.getDiagnostics();
1360}
1361
1362AttrVec& ASTContext::getDeclAttrs(const Decl *D) {
1363 AttrVec *&Result = DeclAttrs[D];
1364 if (!Result) {
1365 void *Mem = Allocate(sizeof(AttrVec));
1366 Result = new (Mem) AttrVec;
1367 }
1368
1369 return *Result;
1370}
1371
1372/// Erase the attributes corresponding to the given declaration.
1373void ASTContext::eraseDeclAttrs(const Decl *D) {
1374 llvm::DenseMap<const Decl*, AttrVec*>::iterator Pos = DeclAttrs.find(D);
1375 if (Pos != DeclAttrs.end()) {
1376 Pos->second->~AttrVec();
1377 DeclAttrs.erase(Pos);
1378 }
1379}

1476ASTContext::overridden_cxx_method_iterator
1477ASTContext::overridden_methods_begin(const CXXMethodDecl *Method) const {
1478 return overridden_methods(Method).begin();
1479}
1480
1481ASTContext::overridden_cxx_method_iterator
1482ASTContext::overridden_methods_end(const CXXMethodDecl *Method) const {
1483 return overridden_methods(Method).end();
1484}
1485
1486unsigned
1487ASTContext::overridden_methods_size(const CXXMethodDecl *Method) const {
1488 auto Range = overridden_methods(Method);
1489 return Range.end() - Range.begin();
1490}
1491
1492ASTContext::overridden_method_range
1493ASTContext::overridden_methods(const CXXMethodDecl *Method) const {
1494 llvm::DenseMap<const CXXMethodDecl *, CXXMethodVector>::const_iterator Pos =
1495 OverriddenMethods.find(Method->getCanonicalDecl());
1496 if (Pos == OverriddenMethods.end())
1497 return overridden_method_range(nullptr, nullptr);
1498 return overridden_method_range(Pos->second.begin(), Pos->second.end());
1499}
1500
1501void ASTContext::addOverriddenMethod(const CXXMethodDecl *Method,
1502 const CXXMethodDecl *Overridden) {
1503 assert(Method->isCanonicalDecl() && Overridden->isCanonicalDecl());
1504 OverriddenMethods[Method].push_back(Overridden);
1505}
1506
1507void ASTContext::getOverriddenMethods(
1508 const NamedDecl *D,
1509 SmallVectorImpl<const NamedDecl *> &Overridden) const {
1510 assert(D);
1511
1512 if (const auto *CXXMethod = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D)) {
1513 Overridden.append(overridden_methods_begin(CXXMethod),
1514 overridden_methods_end(CXXMethod));
1515 return;
1516 }
1517
1518 const auto *Method = dyn_cast<ObjCMethodDecl>(D);
1519 if (!Method)
1520 return;
1521
1522 SmallVector<const ObjCMethodDecl *, 8> OverDecls;
1523 Method->getOverriddenMethods(OverDecls);
1524 Overridden.append(OverDecls.begin(), OverDecls.end());
1525}
1526
1527void ASTContext::addedLocalImportDecl(ImportDecl *Import) {
1528 assert(!Import->NextLocalImport && "Import declaration already in the chain");
1529 assert(!Import->isFromASTFile() && "Non-local import declaration");
1530 if (!FirstLocalImport) {
1531 FirstLocalImport = Import;
1532 LastLocalImport = Import;
1533 return;
1534 }
1535
1536 LastLocalImport->NextLocalImport = Import;
1537 LastLocalImport = Import;
1538}

1540//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1541// Type Sizing and Analysis
1542//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
1543
1544/// getFloatTypeSemantics - Return the APFloat 'semantics' for the specified
1545/// scalar floating point type.
1546const llvm::fltSemantics &ASTContext::getFloatTypeSemantics(QualType T) const {
1547 const auto *BT = T->getAs<BuiltinType>();
1548 assert(BT && "Not a floating point type!");
1549 switch (BT->getKind()) {
1550 default: llvm_unreachable("Not a floating point type!");
1551 case BuiltinType::Float16:
1552 case BuiltinType::Half:
1553 return Target->getHalfFormat();
1554 case BuiltinType::Float: return Target->getFloatFormat();
1555 case BuiltinType::Double: return Target->getDoubleFormat();
1556 case BuiltinType::LongDouble: return Target->getLongDoubleFormat();
1557 case BuiltinType::Float128: return Target->getFloat128Format();
1558 }
1559}
1560
1561CharUnits ASTContext::getDeclAlign(const Decl *D, bool ForAlignof) const {
1562 unsigned Align = Target->getCharWidth();
1563
1564 bool UseAlignAttrOnly = false;
1565 if (unsigned AlignFromAttr = D->getMaxAlignment()) {
1566 Align = AlignFromAttr;
1567
1568 // __attribute__((aligned)) can increase or decrease alignment
1569 // *except* on a struct or struct member, where it only increases
1570 // alignment unless 'packed' is also specified.
1571 //
1572 // It is an error for alignas to decrease alignment, so we can
1573 // ignore that possibility; Sema should diagnose it.
1574 if (isa<FieldDecl>(D)) {
1575 UseAlignAttrOnly = D->hasAttr<PackedAttr>() ||
1576 cast<FieldDecl>(D)->getParent()->hasAttr<PackedAttr>();
1577 } else {
1578 UseAlignAttrOnly = true;
1579 }
1580 }
1581 else if (isa<FieldDecl>(D))
1582 UseAlignAttrOnly =
1583 D->hasAttr<PackedAttr>() ||
1584 cast<FieldDecl>(D)->getParent()->hasAttr<PackedAttr>();
1585
1586 // If we're using the align attribute only, just ignore everything
1587 // else about the declaration and its type.
1588 if (UseAlignAttrOnly) {
1589 // do nothing
1590 } else if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(D)) {
1591 QualType T = VD->getType();
1592 if (const auto *RT = T->getAs<ReferenceType>()) {
1593 if (ForAlignof)
1594 T = RT->getPointeeType();
1595 else
1596 T = getPointerType(RT->getPointeeType());
1597 }
1598 QualType BaseT = getBaseElementType(T);
1599 if (T->isFunctionType())
1600 Align = getTypeInfoImpl(T.getTypePtr()).Align;
1601 else if (!BaseT->isIncompleteType()) {
1602 // Adjust alignments of declarations with array type by the
1603 // large-array alignment on the target.
1604 if (const ArrayType *arrayType = getAsArrayType(T)) {
1605 unsigned MinWidth = Target->getLargeArrayMinWidth();
1606 if (!ForAlignof && MinWidth) {
1607 if (isa<VariableArrayType>(arrayType))
1608 Align = std::max(Align, Target->getLargeArrayAlign());
1609 else if (isa<ConstantArrayType>(arrayType) &&
1610 MinWidth <= getTypeSize(cast<ConstantArrayType>(arrayType)))
1611 Align = std::max(Align, Target->getLargeArrayAlign());
1612 }
1613 }
1614 Align = std::max(Align, getPreferredTypeAlign(T.getTypePtr()));
1615 if (BaseT.getQualifiers().hasUnaligned())
1616 Align = Target->getCharWidth();
1617 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
1618 if (VD->hasGlobalStorage() && !ForAlignof) {
1619 uint64_t TypeSize = getTypeSize(T.getTypePtr());
1620 Align = std::max(Align, getTargetInfo().getMinGlobalAlign(TypeSize));
1621 }
1622 }
1623 }
1624
1625 // Fields can be subject to extra alignment constraints, like if
1626 // the field is packed, the struct is packed, or the struct has a
1627 // a max-field-alignment constraint (#pragma pack). So calculate
1628 // the actual alignment of the field within the struct, and then
1629 // (as we're expected to) constrain that by the alignment of the type.
1630 if (const auto *Field = dyn_cast<FieldDecl>(VD)) {
1631 const RecordDecl *Parent = Field->getParent();
1632 // We can only produce a sensible answer if the record is valid.
1633 if (!Parent->isInvalidDecl()) {
1634 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getASTRecordLayout(Parent);
1635
1636 // Start with the record's overall alignment.
1637 unsigned FieldAlign = toBits(Layout.getAlignment());
1638
1639 // Use the GCD of that and the offset within the record.
1640 uint64_t Offset = Layout.getFieldOffset(Field->getFieldIndex());
1641 if (Offset > 0) {
1642 // Alignment is always a power of 2, so the GCD will be a power of 2,
1643 // which means we get to do this crazy thing instead of Euclid's.
1644 uint64_t LowBitOfOffset = Offset & (~Offset + 1);
1645 if (LowBitOfOffset < FieldAlign)
1646 FieldAlign = static_cast<unsigned>(LowBitOfOffset);
1647 }
1648
1649 Align = std::min(Align, FieldAlign);
1650 }
1651 }
1652 }
1653
1654 return toCharUnitsFromBits(Align);
1655}
1656
1657// getTypeInfoDataSizeInChars - Return the size of a type, in
1658// chars. If the type is a record, its data size is returned. This is
1659// the size of the memcpy that's performed when assigning this type
1660// using a trivial copy/move assignment operator.
1661std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits>
1662ASTContext::getTypeInfoDataSizeInChars(QualType T) const {
1663 std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits> sizeAndAlign = getTypeInfoInChars(T);
1664
1665 // In C++, objects can sometimes be allocated into the tail padding
1666 // of a base-class subobject. We decide whether that's possible
1667 // during class layout, so here we can just trust the layout results.
1668 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
1669 if (const auto *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
1670 const ASTRecordLayout &layout = getASTRecordLayout(RT->getDecl());
1671 sizeAndAlign.first = layout.getDataSize();
1672 }
1673 }
1674
1675 return sizeAndAlign;
1676}
1677
1678/// getConstantArrayInfoInChars - Performing the computation in CharUnits
1679/// instead of in bits prevents overflowing the uint64_t for some large arrays.
1680std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits>
1681static getConstantArrayInfoInChars(const ASTContext &Context,
1682 const ConstantArrayType *CAT) {
1683 std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits> EltInfo =
1684 Context.getTypeInfoInChars(CAT->getElementType());
1685 uint64_t Size = CAT->getSize().getZExtValue();
1686 assert((Size == 0 || static_cast<uint64_t>(EltInfo.first.getQuantity()) <=
1687 (uint64_t)(-1)/Size) &&
1688 "Overflow in array type char size evaluation");
1689 uint64_t Width = EltInfo.first.getQuantity() * Size;
1690 unsigned Align = EltInfo.second.getQuantity();
1691 if (!Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() ||
1692 Context.getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0) == 64)
1693 Width = llvm::alignTo(Width, Align);
1694 return std::make_pair(CharUnits::fromQuantity(Width),
1695 CharUnits::fromQuantity(Align));
1696}
1697
1698std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits>
1699ASTContext::getTypeInfoInChars(const Type *T) const {
1700 if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(T))
1701 return getConstantArrayInfoInChars(*this, CAT);
1702 TypeInfo Info = getTypeInfo(T);
1703 return std::make_pair(toCharUnitsFromBits(Info.Width),
1704 toCharUnitsFromBits(Info.Align));
1705}
1706
1707std::pair<CharUnits, CharUnits>
1708ASTContext::getTypeInfoInChars(QualType T) const {
1709 return getTypeInfoInChars(T.getTypePtr());
1710}
1711
1712bool ASTContext::isAlignmentRequired(const Type *T) const {
1713 return getTypeInfo(T).AlignIsRequired;
1714}
1715
1716bool ASTContext::isAlignmentRequired(QualType T) const {
1717 return isAlignmentRequired(T.getTypePtr());
1718}
1719
1720unsigned ASTContext::getTypeAlignIfKnown(QualType T) const {
1721 // An alignment on a typedef overrides anything else.
1722 if (const auto *TT = T->getAs<TypedefType>())
1723 if (unsigned Align = TT->getDecl()->getMaxAlignment())
1724 return Align;
1725
1726 // If we have an (array of) complete type, we're done.
1727 T = getBaseElementType(T);
1728 if (!T->isIncompleteType())
1729 return getTypeAlign(T);
1730
1731 // If we had an array type, its element type might be a typedef
1732 // type with an alignment attribute.
1733 if (const auto *TT = T->getAs<TypedefType>())
1734 if (unsigned Align = TT->getDecl()->getMaxAlignment())
1735 return Align;
1736
1737 // Otherwise, see if the declaration of the type had an attribute.
1738 if (const auto *TT = T->getAs<TagType>())
1739 return TT->getDecl()->getMaxAlignment();
1740
1741 return 0;
1742}
1743
1744TypeInfo ASTContext::getTypeInfo(const Type *T) const {
1745 TypeInfoMap::iterator I = MemoizedTypeInfo.find(T);
1746 if (I != MemoizedTypeInfo.end())
1747 return I->second;
1748
1749 // This call can invalidate MemoizedTypeInfo[T], so we need a second lookup.
1750 TypeInfo TI = getTypeInfoImpl(T);
1751 MemoizedTypeInfo[T] = TI;
1752 return TI;
1753}
1754
1755/// getTypeInfoImpl - Return the size of the specified type, in bits. This
1756/// method does not work on incomplete types.
1757///
1758/// FIXME: Pointers into different addr spaces could have different sizes and
1759/// alignment requirements: getPointerInfo should take an AddrSpace, this
1760/// should take a QualType, &c.
1761TypeInfo ASTContext::getTypeInfoImpl(const Type *T) const {
1762 uint64_t Width = 0;
1763 unsigned Align = 8;
1764 bool AlignIsRequired = false;
1765 unsigned AS = 0;
1766 switch (T->getTypeClass()) {
1767#define TYPE(Class, Base)
1768#define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Class, Base)
1769#define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Base)
1770#define DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
1771#define NON_CANONICAL_UNLESS_DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) \
1772 case Type::Class: \
1773 assert(!T->isDependentType() && "should not see dependent types here"); \
1774 return getTypeInfo(cast<Class##Type>(T)->desugar().getTypePtr());
1775#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
1776 llvm_unreachable("Should not see dependent types");
1777
1778 case Type::FunctionNoProto:
1779 case Type::FunctionProto:
1780 // GCC extension: alignof(function) = 32 bits
1781 Width = 0;
1782 Align = 32;
1783 break;
1784
1785 case Type::IncompleteArray:
1786 case Type::VariableArray:
1787 Width = 0;
1788 Align = getTypeAlign(cast<ArrayType>(T)->getElementType());
1789 break;
1790
1791 case Type::ConstantArray: {
1792 const auto *CAT = cast<ConstantArrayType>(T);
1793
1794 TypeInfo EltInfo = getTypeInfo(CAT->getElementType());
1795 uint64_t Size = CAT->getSize().getZExtValue();
1796 assert((Size == 0 || EltInfo.Width <= (uint64_t)(-1) / Size) &&
1797 "Overflow in array type bit size evaluation");
1798 Width = EltInfo.Width * Size;
1799 Align = EltInfo.Align;
1800 if (!getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() ||
1801 getTargetInfo().getPointerWidth(0) == 64)
1802 Width = llvm::alignTo(Width, Align);
1803 break;
1804 }
1805 case Type::ExtVector:
1806 case Type::Vector: {
1807 const auto *VT = cast<VectorType>(T);
1808 TypeInfo EltInfo = getTypeInfo(VT->getElementType());
1809 Width = EltInfo.Width * VT->getNumElements();
1810 Align = Width;
1811 // If the alignment is not a power of 2, round up to the next power of 2.
1812 // This happens for non-power-of-2 length vectors.
1813 if (Align & (Align-1)) {
1814 Align = llvm::NextPowerOf2(Align);
1815 Width = llvm::alignTo(Width, Align);
1816 }
1817 // Adjust the alignment based on the target max.
1818 uint64_t TargetVectorAlign = Target->getMaxVectorAlign();
1819 if (TargetVectorAlign && TargetVectorAlign < Align)
1820 Align = TargetVectorAlign;
1821 break;
1822 }
1823
1824 case Type::Builtin:
1825 switch (cast<BuiltinType>(T)->getKind()) {
1826 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown builtin type!");
1827 case BuiltinType::Void:
1828 // GCC extension: alignof(void) = 8 bits.
1829 Width = 0;
1830 Align = 8;
1831 break;
1832 case BuiltinType::Bool:
1833 Width = Target->getBoolWidth();
1834 Align = Target->getBoolAlign();
1835 break;
1836 case BuiltinType::Char_S:
1837 case BuiltinType::Char_U:
1838 case BuiltinType::UChar:
1839 case BuiltinType::SChar:
1840 case BuiltinType::Char8:
1841 Width = Target->getCharWidth();
1842 Align = Target->getCharAlign();
1843 break;
1844 case BuiltinType::WChar_S:
1845 case BuiltinType::WChar_U:
1846 Width = Target->getWCharWidth();
1847 Align = Target->getWCharAlign();
1848 break;
1849 case BuiltinType::Char16:
1850 Width = Target->getChar16Width();
1851 Align = Target->getChar16Align();
1852 break;
1853 case BuiltinType::Char32:
1854 Width = Target->getChar32Width();
1855 Align = Target->getChar32Align();
1856 break;
1857 case BuiltinType::UShort:
1858 case BuiltinType::Short:
1859 Width = Target->getShortWidth();
1860 Align = Target->getShortAlign();
1861 break;
1862 case BuiltinType::UInt:
1863 case BuiltinType::Int:
1864 Width = Target->getIntWidth();
1865 Align = Target->getIntAlign();
1866 break;
1867 case BuiltinType::ULong:
1868 case BuiltinType::Long:
1869 Width = Target->getLongWidth();
1870 Align = Target->getLongAlign();
1871 break;
1872 case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
1873 case BuiltinType::LongLong:
1874 Width = Target->getLongLongWidth();
1875 Align = Target->getLongLongAlign();
1876 break;
1877 case BuiltinType::IntCap:
1878 case BuiltinType::UIntCap:
1879 Width = Target->getIntCapWidth();
1880 Align = Target->getIntCapAlign();
1881 break;
1882 case BuiltinType::Int128:
1883 case BuiltinType::UInt128:
1884 Width = 128;
1885 Align = 128; // int128_t is 128-bit aligned on all targets.
1886 break;
1887 case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
1888 case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
1889 case BuiltinType::SatShortAccum:
1890 case BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum:
1891 Width = Target->getShortAccumWidth();
1892 Align = Target->getShortAccumAlign();
1893 break;
1894 case BuiltinType::Accum:
1895 case BuiltinType::UAccum:
1896 case BuiltinType::SatAccum:
1897 case BuiltinType::SatUAccum:
1898 Width = Target->getAccumWidth();
1899 Align = Target->getAccumAlign();
1900 break;
1901 case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
1902 case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
1903 case BuiltinType::SatLongAccum:
1904 case BuiltinType::SatULongAccum:
1905 Width = Target->getLongAccumWidth();
1906 Align = Target->getLongAccumAlign();
1907 break;
1908 case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
1909 case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
1910 case BuiltinType::SatShortFract:
1911 case BuiltinType::SatUShortFract:
1912 Width = Target->getShortFractWidth();
1913 Align = Target->getShortFractAlign();
1914 break;
1915 case BuiltinType::Fract:
1916 case BuiltinType::UFract:
1917 case BuiltinType::SatFract:
1918 case BuiltinType::SatUFract:
1919 Width = Target->getFractWidth();
1920 Align = Target->getFractAlign();
1921 break;
1922 case BuiltinType::LongFract:
1923 case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
1924 case BuiltinType::SatLongFract:
1925 case BuiltinType::SatULongFract:
1926 Width = Target->getLongFractWidth();
1927 Align = Target->getLongFractAlign();
1928 break;
1929 case BuiltinType::Float16:
1930 case BuiltinType::Half:
1931 if (Target->hasFloat16Type() || !getLangOpts().OpenMP ||
1932 !getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice) {
1933 Width = Target->getHalfWidth();
1934 Align = Target->getHalfAlign();
1935 } else {
1936 assert(getLangOpts().OpenMP && getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice &&
1937 "Expected OpenMP device compilation.");
1938 Width = AuxTarget->getHalfWidth();
1939 Align = AuxTarget->getHalfAlign();
1940 }
1941 break;
1942 case BuiltinType::Float:
1943 Width = Target->getFloatWidth();
1944 Align = Target->getFloatAlign();
1945 break;
1946 case BuiltinType::Double:
1947 Width = Target->getDoubleWidth();
1948 Align = Target->getDoubleAlign();
1949 break;
1950 case BuiltinType::LongDouble:
1951 Width = Target->getLongDoubleWidth();
1952 Align = Target->getLongDoubleAlign();
1953 break;
1954 case BuiltinType::Float128:
1955 if (Target->hasFloat128Type() || !getLangOpts().OpenMP ||
1956 !getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice) {
1957 Width = Target->getFloat128Width();
1958 Align = Target->getFloat128Align();
1959 } else {
1960 assert(getLangOpts().OpenMP && getLangOpts().OpenMPIsDevice &&
1961 "Expected OpenMP device compilation.");
1962 Width = AuxTarget->getFloat128Width();
1963 Align = AuxTarget->getFloat128Align();
1964 }
1965 break;
1966 case BuiltinType::NullPtr:
1967 Width = Target->getPointerWidth(0); // C++ 3.9.1p11: sizeof(nullptr_t)
1968 Align = Target->getPointerAlign(0); // == sizeof(void*)
1969 break;
1970 case BuiltinType::ObjCId:
1971 case BuiltinType::ObjCClass:
1972 case BuiltinType::ObjCSel:
1973 Width = Target->getPointerWidth(0);
1974 Align = Target->getPointerAlign(0);
1975 break;
1976 case BuiltinType::OCLSampler:
1977 case BuiltinType::OCLEvent:
1978 case BuiltinType::OCLClkEvent:
1979 case BuiltinType::OCLQueue:
1980 case BuiltinType::OCLReserveID:
1981#define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
1982 case BuiltinType::Id:
1983#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
1984#define EXT_OPAQUE_TYPE(ExtType, Id, Ext) \
1985 case BuiltinType::Id:
1986#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLExtensionTypes.def"
1987 AS = getTargetAddressSpace(
1988 Target->getOpenCLTypeAddrSpace(getOpenCLTypeKind(T)));
1989 Width = Target->getPointerWidth(AS);
1990 Align = Target->getPointerAlign(AS);
1991 break;
1992 }
1993 break;
1994 case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
1995 Width = Target->getPointerWidth(0);
1996 Align = Target->getPointerAlign(0);
1997 break;
1998 case Type::BlockPointer:
1999 if (Target->areAllPointersCapabilities() ||
2000 T->isCHERICapabilityType(*this, false)) {
2001 Width = Target->getCHERICapabilityWidth();
2002 Align = Target->getCHERICapabilityAlign();
2003 } else {
2004 AS = getTargetAddressSpace(cast<BlockPointerType>(T)->getPointeeType());
2005 Width = Target->getPointerWidth(AS);
2006 Align = Target->getPointerAlign(AS);
2007 }
2008 break;
2009 case Type::LValueReference:
2010 case Type::RValueReference:
2011 // alignof and sizeof should never enter this code path here, so we go
2012 // the pointer route.
2013 if (cast<ReferenceType>(T)->isCHERICapability() ||
2014 Target->areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
2015 Width = Target->getCHERICapabilityWidth();
2016 Align = Target->getCHERICapabilityAlign();
2017 } else {
2018 AS = getTargetAddressSpace(cast<ReferenceType>(T)->getPointeeType());
2019 Width = Target->getPointerWidth(AS);
2020 Align = Target->getPointerAlign(AS);
2021 }
2022 break;
2023 case Type::Pointer: {
2024 auto PointeeTy = cast<PointerType>(T)->getPointeeType();
2025 if (PointeeTy->isFunctionProtoType()) {
2026 auto FPT = PointeeTy->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2027 if (FPT->getCallConv() == CC_CHERICCallback) {
2028 Width = Target->getCHERICapabilityWidth() * 3;
2029 Align = Target->getCHERICapabilityAlign();
2030 break;
2031 }
2032 }
2033
2034 if (cast<PointerType>(T)->isCHERICapability() ||
2035 Target->areAllPointersCapabilities()) {
2036 Width = Target->getCHERICapabilityWidth();
2037 Align = Target->getCHERICapabilityAlign();
2038 } else {
2039 AS = getTargetAddressSpace(PointeeTy);
2040 Width = Target->getPointerWidth(AS);
2041 Align = Target->getPointerAlign(AS);
2042 }
2043 break;
2044 }
2045 case Type::MemberPointer: {
2046 const auto *MPT = cast<MemberPointerType>(T);
2047 CXXABI::MemberPointerInfo MPI = ABI->getMemberPointerInfo(MPT);
2048 Width = MPI.Width;
2049 Align = MPI.Align;
2050 break;
2051 }
2052 case Type::Complex: {
2053 // Complex types have the same alignment as their elements, but twice the
2054 // size.
2055 TypeInfo EltInfo = getTypeInfo(cast<ComplexType>(T)->getElementType());
2056 Width = EltInfo.Width * 2;
2057 Align = EltInfo.Align;
2058 break;
2059 }
2060 case Type::ObjCObject:
2061 return getTypeInfo(cast<ObjCObjectType>(T)->getBaseType().getTypePtr());
2062 case Type::Adjusted:
2063 case Type::Decayed:
2064 return getTypeInfo(cast<AdjustedType>(T)->getAdjustedType().getTypePtr());
2065 case Type::ObjCInterface: {
2066 const auto *ObjCI = cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(T);
2067 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getASTObjCInterfaceLayout(ObjCI->getDecl());
2068 Width = toBits(Layout.getSize());
2069 Align = toBits(Layout.getAlignment());
2070 break;
2071 }
2072 case Type::Record:
2073 case Type::Enum: {
2074 const auto *TT = cast<TagType>(T);
2075
2076 if (TT->getDecl()->isInvalidDecl()) {
2077 Width = 8;
2078 Align = 8;
2079 break;
2080 }
2081
2082 if (const auto *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(TT)) {
2083 const EnumDecl *ED = ET->getDecl();
2084 TypeInfo Info =
2085 getTypeInfo(ED->getIntegerType()->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
2086 if (unsigned AttrAlign = ED->getMaxAlignment()) {
2087 Info.Align = AttrAlign;
2088 Info.AlignIsRequired = true;
2089 }
2090 return Info;
2091 }
2092
2093 const auto *RT = cast<RecordType>(TT);
2094 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
2095 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2096 Width = toBits(Layout.getSize());
2097 Align = toBits(Layout.getAlignment());
2098 AlignIsRequired = RD->hasAttr<AlignedAttr>();
2099 break;
2100 }
2101
2102 case Type::SubstTemplateTypeParm:
2103 return getTypeInfo(cast<SubstTemplateTypeParmType>(T)->
2104 getReplacementType().getTypePtr());
2105
2106 case Type::Auto:
2107 case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization: {
2108 const auto *A = cast<DeducedType>(T);
2109 assert(!A->getDeducedType().isNull() &&
2110 "cannot request the size of an undeduced or dependent auto type");
2111 return getTypeInfo(A->getDeducedType().getTypePtr());
2112 }
2113
2114 case Type::Paren:
2115 return getTypeInfo(cast<ParenType>(T)->getInnerType().getTypePtr());
2116
2117 case Type::MacroQualified:
2118 return getTypeInfo(
2119 cast<MacroQualifiedType>(T)->getUnderlyingType().getTypePtr());
2120
2121 case Type::ObjCTypeParam:
2122 return getTypeInfo(cast<ObjCTypeParamType>(T)->desugar().getTypePtr());
2123
2124 case Type::Typedef: {
2125 const TypedefNameDecl *Typedef = cast<TypedefType>(T)->getDecl();
2126 TypeInfo Info = getTypeInfo(Typedef->getUnderlyingType().getTypePtr());
2127 // If the typedef has an aligned attribute on it, it overrides any computed
2128 // alignment we have. This violates the GCC documentation (which says that
2129 // attribute(aligned) can only round up) but matches its implementation.
2130 if (unsigned AttrAlign = Typedef->getMaxAlignment()) {
2131 Align = AttrAlign;
2132 AlignIsRequired = true;
2133 } else {
2134 Align = Info.Align;
2135 AlignIsRequired = Info.AlignIsRequired;
2136 }
2137 Width = Info.Width;
2138 break;
2139 }
2140
2141 case Type::Elaborated:
2142 return getTypeInfo(cast<ElaboratedType>(T)->getNamedType().getTypePtr());
2143
2144 case Type::Attributed:
2145 return getTypeInfo(
2146 cast<AttributedType>(T)->getEquivalentType().getTypePtr());
2147
2148 case Type::Atomic: {
2149 // Start with the base type information.
2150 TypeInfo Info = getTypeInfo(cast<AtomicType>(T)->getValueType());
2151 Width = Info.Width;
2152 Align = Info.Align;
2153
2154 if (!Width) {
2155 // An otherwise zero-sized type should still generate an
2156 // atomic operation.
2157 Width = Target->getCharWidth();
2158 assert(Align);
2159 } else if (Width <= Target->getMaxAtomicPromoteWidth()) {
2160 // If the size of the type doesn't exceed the platform's max
2161 // atomic promotion width, make the size and alignment more
2162 // favorable to atomic operations:
2163
2164 // Round the size up to a power of 2.
2165 if (!llvm::isPowerOf2_64(Width))
2166 Width = llvm::NextPowerOf2(Width);
2167
2168 // Set the alignment equal to the size.
2169 Align = static_cast<unsigned>(Width);
2170 }
2171 }
2172 break;
2173
2174 case Type::Pipe:
2175 Width =
2176 Target->getPointerWidth(getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_global));
2177 Align =
2178 Target->getPointerAlign(getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_global));
2179 break;
2180 }
2181
2182 assert(llvm::isPowerOf2_32(Align) && "Alignment must be power of 2");
2183 return TypeInfo(Width, Align, AlignIsRequired);
2184}
2185
2186unsigned ASTContext::getTypeUnadjustedAlign(const Type *T) const {
2187 UnadjustedAlignMap::iterator I = MemoizedUnadjustedAlign.find(T);
2188 if (I != MemoizedUnadjustedAlign.end())
2189 return I->second;
2190
2191 unsigned UnadjustedAlign;
2192 if (const auto *RT = T->getAs<RecordType>()) {
2193 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
2194 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2195 UnadjustedAlign = toBits(Layout.getUnadjustedAlignment());
2196 } else if (const auto *ObjCI = T->getAs<ObjCInterfaceType>()) {
2197 const ASTRecordLayout &Layout = getASTObjCInterfaceLayout(ObjCI->getDecl());
2198 UnadjustedAlign = toBits(Layout.getUnadjustedAlignment());
2199 } else {
2200 UnadjustedAlign = getTypeAlign(T->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
2201 }
2202
2203 MemoizedUnadjustedAlign[T] = UnadjustedAlign;
2204 return UnadjustedAlign;
2205}
2206
2207unsigned ASTContext::getOpenMPDefaultSimdAlign(QualType T) const {
2208 unsigned SimdAlign = getTargetInfo().getSimdDefaultAlign();
2209 // Target ppc64 with QPX: simd default alignment for pointer to double is 32.
2210 if ((getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::ppc64 ||
2211 getTargetInfo().getTriple().getArch() == llvm::Triple::ppc64le) &&
2212 getTargetInfo().getABI() == "elfv1-qpx" &&
2213 T->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Double))
2214 SimdAlign = 256;
2215 return SimdAlign;
2216}

2218/// toCharUnitsFromBits - Convert a size in bits to a size in characters.
2219CharUnits ASTContext::toCharUnitsFromBits(int64_t BitSize) const {
2220 return CharUnits::fromQuantity(BitSize / getCharWidth());
2221}
2222
2223/// toBits - Convert a size in characters to a size in characters.
2224int64_t ASTContext::toBits(CharUnits CharSize) const {
2225 return CharSize.getQuantity() * getCharWidth();
2226}

2228/// getTypeSizeInChars - Return the size of the specified type, in characters.
2229/// This method does not work on incomplete types.
2230CharUnits ASTContext::getTypeSizeInChars(QualType T) const {
2231 return getTypeInfoInChars(T).first;
2232}
2233CharUnits ASTContext::getTypeSizeInChars(const Type *T) const {
2234 return getTypeInfoInChars(T).first;
2235}
2236
2237/// getTypeAlignInChars - Return the ABI-specified alignment of a type, in
2238/// characters. This method does not work on incomplete types.
2239CharUnits ASTContext::getTypeAlignInChars(QualType T) const {
2240 return toCharUnitsFromBits(getTypeAlign(T));
2241}
2242CharUnits ASTContext::getTypeAlignInChars(const Type *T) const {
2243 return toCharUnitsFromBits(getTypeAlign(T));
2244}
2245
2246/// getTypeUnadjustedAlignInChars - Return the ABI-specified alignment of a
2247/// type, in characters, before alignment adustments. This method does
2248/// not work on incomplete types.
2249CharUnits ASTContext::getTypeUnadjustedAlignInChars(QualType T) const {
2250 return toCharUnitsFromBits(getTypeUnadjustedAlign(T));
2251}
2252CharUnits ASTContext::getTypeUnadjustedAlignInChars(const Type *T) const {
2253 return toCharUnitsFromBits(getTypeUnadjustedAlign(T));
2254}
2255
2256/// getPreferredTypeAlign - Return the "preferred" alignment of the specified
2257/// type for the current target in bits. This can be different than the ABI
2258/// alignment in cases where it is beneficial for performance to overalign
2259/// a data type.
2260unsigned ASTContext::getPreferredTypeAlign(const Type *T) const {
2261 TypeInfo TI = getTypeInfo(T);
2262 unsigned ABIAlign = TI.Align;
2263
2264 T = T->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe();
2265
2266 // The preferred alignment of member pointers is that of a pointer (unless we
2267 // are targeting CHERI capability ABI, where data pointers are less aligned)
2268 //
2269 // XXXAR: do we want member data pointers to also be capability aligned
2270 // although they are only a ptrdiff_t?
2271 if (T->isMemberPointerType() && !getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities())
2272 return getPreferredTypeAlign(VoidPtrTy.getTypePtr());
2273
2274 if (!Target->allowsLargerPreferedTypeAlignment())
2275 return ABIAlign;
2276
2277 // Double and long long should be naturally aligned if possible.
2278 if (const auto *CT = T->getAs<ComplexType>())
2279 T = CT->getElementType().getTypePtr();
2280 if (const auto *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>())
2281 T = ET->getDecl()->getIntegerType().getTypePtr();
2282 if (T->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::Double) ||
2283 T->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::LongLong) ||
2284 T->isSpecificBuiltinType(BuiltinType::ULongLong))
2285 // Don't increase the alignment if an alignment attribute was specified on a
2286 // typedef declaration.
2287 if (!TI.AlignIsRequired)
2288 return std::max(ABIAlign, (unsigned)getTypeSize(T));
2289
2290 return ABIAlign;
2291}
2292
2293/// getTargetDefaultAlignForAttributeAligned - Return the default alignment
2294/// for __attribute__((aligned)) on this target, to be used if no alignment
2295/// value is specified.
2296unsigned ASTContext::getTargetDefaultAlignForAttributeAligned() const {
2297 return getTargetInfo().getDefaultAlignForAttributeAligned();
2298}
