2300/// getAlignOfGlobalVar - Return the alignment in bits that should be given
2301/// to a global variable of the specified type.
2302unsigned ASTContext::getAlignOfGlobalVar(QualType T) const {
2303 uint64_t TypeSize = getTypeSize(T.getTypePtr());
2304 return std::max(getTypeAlign(T), getTargetInfo().getMinGlobalAlign(TypeSize));
2305}
2306
2307/// getAlignOfGlobalVarInChars - Return the alignment in characters that
2308/// should be given to a global variable of the specified type.
2309CharUnits ASTContext::getAlignOfGlobalVarInChars(QualType T) const {
2310 return toCharUnitsFromBits(getAlignOfGlobalVar(T));
2311}
2312
2313CharUnits ASTContext::getOffsetOfBaseWithVBPtr(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
2314 CharUnits Offset = CharUnits::Zero();
2315 const ASTRecordLayout *Layout = &getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2316 while (const CXXRecordDecl *Base = Layout->getBaseSharingVBPtr()) {
2317 Offset += Layout->getBaseClassOffset(Base);
2318 Layout = &getASTRecordLayout(Base);
2319 }
2320 return Offset;
2321}
2322
2323/// DeepCollectObjCIvars -
2324/// This routine first collects all declared, but not synthesized, ivars in
2325/// super class and then collects all ivars, including those synthesized for
2326/// current class. This routine is used for implementation of current class
2327/// when all ivars, declared and synthesized are known.
2328void ASTContext::DeepCollectObjCIvars(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OI,
2329 bool leafClass,
2330 SmallVectorImpl<const ObjCIvarDecl*> &Ivars) const {
2331 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *SuperClass = OI->getSuperClass())
2332 DeepCollectObjCIvars(SuperClass, false, Ivars);
2333 if (!leafClass) {
2334 for (const auto *I : OI->ivars())
2335 Ivars.push_back(I);
2336 } else {
2337 auto *IDecl = const_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl *>(OI);
2338 for (const ObjCIvarDecl *Iv = IDecl->all_declared_ivar_begin(); Iv;
2339 Iv= Iv->getNextIvar())
2340 Ivars.push_back(Iv);
2341 }
2342}
2343
2344/// CollectInheritedProtocols - Collect all protocols in current class and
2345/// those inherited by it.
2346void ASTContext::CollectInheritedProtocols(const Decl *CDecl,
2347 llvm::SmallPtrSet<ObjCProtocolDecl*, 8> &Protocols) {
2348 if (const auto *OI = dyn_cast<ObjCInterfaceDecl>(CDecl)) {
2349 // We can use protocol_iterator here instead of
2350 // all_referenced_protocol_iterator since we are walking all categories.
2351 for (auto *Proto : OI->all_referenced_protocols()) {
2352 CollectInheritedProtocols(Proto, Protocols);
2353 }
2354
2355 // Categories of this Interface.
2356 for (const auto *Cat : OI->visible_categories())
2357 CollectInheritedProtocols(Cat, Protocols);
2358
2359 if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *SD = OI->getSuperClass())
2360 while (SD) {
2361 CollectInheritedProtocols(SD, Protocols);
2362 SD = SD->getSuperClass();
2363 }
2364 } else if (const auto *OC = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryDecl>(CDecl)) {
2365 for (auto *Proto : OC->protocols()) {
2366 CollectInheritedProtocols(Proto, Protocols);
2367 }
2368 } else if (const auto *OP = dyn_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl>(CDecl)) {
2369 // Insert the protocol.
2370 if (!Protocols.insert(
2371 const_cast<ObjCProtocolDecl *>(OP->getCanonicalDecl())).second)
2372 return;
2373
2374 for (auto *Proto : OP->protocols())
2375 CollectInheritedProtocols(Proto, Protocols);
2376 }
2377}
2378
2379static bool unionHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(const ASTContext &Context,
2380 const RecordDecl *RD) {
2381 assert(RD->isUnion() && "Must be union type");
2382 CharUnits UnionSize = Context.getTypeSizeInChars(RD->getTypeForDecl());
2383
2384 for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
2385 if (!Context.hasUniqueObjectRepresentations(Field->getType()))
2386 return false;
2387 CharUnits FieldSize = Context.getTypeSizeInChars(Field->getType());
2388 if (FieldSize != UnionSize)
2389 return false;
2390 }
2391 return !RD->field_empty();
2392}
2393
2394static bool isStructEmpty(QualType Ty) {
2395 const RecordDecl *RD = Ty->castAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
2396
2397 if (!RD->field_empty())
2398 return false;
2399
2400 if (const auto *ClassDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD))
2401 return ClassDecl->isEmpty();
2402
2403 return true;
2404}
2405
2406static llvm::Optional<int64_t>
2407structHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(const ASTContext &Context,
2408 const RecordDecl *RD) {
2409 assert(!RD->isUnion() && "Must be struct/class type");
2410 const auto &Layout = Context.getASTRecordLayout(RD);
2411
2412 int64_t CurOffsetInBits = 0;
2413 if (const auto *ClassDecl = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
2414 if (ClassDecl->isDynamicClass())
2415 return llvm::None;
2416
2417 SmallVector<std::pair<QualType, int64_t>, 4> Bases;
2418 for (const auto Base : ClassDecl->bases()) {
2419 // Empty types can be inherited from, and non-empty types can potentially
2420 // have tail padding, so just make sure there isn't an error.
2421 if (!isStructEmpty(Base.getType())) {
2422 llvm::Optional<int64_t> Size = structHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(
2423 Context, Base.getType()->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl());
2424 if (!Size)
2425 return llvm::None;
2426 Bases.emplace_back(Base.getType(), Size.getValue());
2427 }
2428 }
2429
2430 llvm::sort(Bases, [&](const std::pair<QualType, int64_t> &L,
2431 const std::pair<QualType, int64_t> &R) {
2432 return Layout.getBaseClassOffset(L.first->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) <
2433 Layout.getBaseClassOffset(R.first->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
2434 });
2435
2436 for (const auto Base : Bases) {
2437 int64_t BaseOffset = Context.toBits(
2438 Layout.getBaseClassOffset(Base.first->getAsCXXRecordDecl()));
2439 int64_t BaseSize = Base.second;
2440 if (BaseOffset != CurOffsetInBits)
2441 return llvm::None;
2442 CurOffsetInBits = BaseOffset + BaseSize;
2443 }
2444 }
2445
2446 for (const auto *Field : RD->fields()) {
2447 if (!Field->getType()->isReferenceType() &&
2448 !Context.hasUniqueObjectRepresentations(Field->getType()))
2449 return llvm::None;
2450
2451 int64_t FieldSizeInBits =
2452 Context.toBits(Context.getTypeSizeInChars(Field->getType()));
2453 if (Field->isBitField()) {
2454 int64_t BitfieldSize = Field->getBitWidthValue(Context);
2455
2456 if (BitfieldSize > FieldSizeInBits)
2457 return llvm::None;
2458 FieldSizeInBits = BitfieldSize;
2459 }
2460
2461 int64_t FieldOffsetInBits = Context.getFieldOffset(Field);
2462
2463 if (FieldOffsetInBits != CurOffsetInBits)
2464 return llvm::None;
2465
2466 CurOffsetInBits = FieldSizeInBits + FieldOffsetInBits;
2467 }
2468
2469 return CurOffsetInBits;
2470}
2471
2472bool ASTContext::hasUniqueObjectRepresentations(QualType Ty) const {
2473 // C++17 [meta.unary.prop]:
2474 // The predicate condition for a template specialization
2475 // has_unique_object_representations<T> shall be
2476 // satisfied if and only if:
2477 // (9.1) - T is trivially copyable, and
2478 // (9.2) - any two objects of type T with the same value have the same
2479 // object representation, where two objects
2480 // of array or non-union class type are considered to have the same value
2481 // if their respective sequences of
2482 // direct subobjects have the same values, and two objects of union type
2483 // are considered to have the same
2484 // value if they have the same active member and the corresponding members
2485 // have the same value.
2486 // The set of scalar types for which this condition holds is
2487 // implementation-defined. [ Note: If a type has padding
2488 // bits, the condition does not hold; otherwise, the condition holds true
2489 // for unsigned integral types. -- end note ]
2490 assert(!Ty.isNull() && "Null QualType sent to unique object rep check");
2491
2492 // Arrays are unique only if their element type is unique.
2493 if (Ty->isArrayType())
2494 return hasUniqueObjectRepresentations(getBaseElementType(Ty));
2495
2496 // (9.1) - T is trivially copyable...
2497 if (!Ty.isTriviallyCopyableType(*this))
2498 return false;
2499
2500 // All integrals and enums are unique.
2501 if (Ty->isIntegralOrEnumerationType())
2502 return true;
2503
2504 // All other pointers are unique.
2505 if (Ty->isPointerType())
2506 return true;
2507
2508 if (Ty->isMemberPointerType()) {
2509 const auto *MPT = Ty->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
2510 return !ABI->getMemberPointerInfo(MPT).HasPadding;
2511 }
2512
2513 if (Ty->isRecordType()) {
2514 const RecordDecl *Record = Ty->getAs<RecordType>()->getDecl();
2515
2516 if (Record->isInvalidDecl())
2517 return false;
2518
2519 if (Record->isUnion())
2520 return unionHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(*this, Record);
2521
2522 Optional<int64_t> StructSize =
2523 structHasUniqueObjectRepresentations(*this, Record);
2524
2525 return StructSize &&
2526 StructSize.getValue() == static_cast<int64_t>(getTypeSize(Ty));
2527 }
2528
2529 // FIXME: More cases to handle here (list by rsmith):
2530 // vectors (careful about, eg, vector of 3 foo)
2531 // _Complex int and friends
2532 // _Atomic T
2533 // Obj-C block pointers
2534 // Obj-C object pointers
2535 // and perhaps OpenCL's various builtin types (pipe, sampler_t, event_t,
2536 // clk_event_t, queue_t, reserve_id_t)
2537 // There're also Obj-C class types and the Obj-C selector type, but I think it
2538 // makes sense for those to return false here.
2539
2540 return false;
2541}
2542
2543unsigned ASTContext::CountNonClassIvars(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *OI) const {
2544 unsigned count = 0;
2545 // Count ivars declared in class extension.
2546 for (const auto *Ext : OI->known_extensions())
2547 count += Ext->ivar_size();
2548
2549 // Count ivar defined in this class's implementation. This
2550 // includes synthesized ivars.
2551 if (ObjCImplementationDecl *ImplDecl = OI->getImplementation())
2552 count += ImplDecl->ivar_size();
2553
2554 return count;
2555}
2556
2557bool ASTContext::isSentinelNullExpr(const Expr *E) {
2558 if (!E)
2559 return false;
2560
2561 // nullptr_t is always treated as null.
2562 if (E->getType()->isNullPtrType()) return true;
2563
2564 if (E->getType()->isAnyPointerType() &&
2565 E->IgnoreParenCasts()->isNullPointerConstant(*this,
2566 Expr::NPC_ValueDependentIsNull))
2567 return true;
2568
2569 // Unfortunately, __null has type 'int'.
2570 if (isa<GNUNullExpr>(E)) return true;
2571
2572 return false;
2573}

2579 I = ObjCImpls.find(D);

2654TypeSourceInfo *ASTContext::CreateTypeSourceInfo(QualType T,
2655 unsigned DataSize) const {
2656 if (!DataSize)
2657 DataSize = TypeLoc::getFullDataSizeForType(T);
2658 else
2659 assert(DataSize == TypeLoc::getFullDataSizeForType(T) &&
2660 "incorrect data size provided to CreateTypeSourceInfo!");
2661
2662 auto *TInfo =
2663 (TypeSourceInfo*)BumpAlloc.Allocate(sizeof(TypeSourceInfo) + DataSize, 8);
2664 new (TInfo) TypeSourceInfo(T);
2665 return TInfo;
2666}
2667
2668TypeSourceInfo *ASTContext::getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(QualType T,
2669 SourceLocation L) const {
2670 TypeSourceInfo *DI = CreateTypeSourceInfo(T);
2671 DI->getTypeLoc().initialize(const_cast<ASTContext &>(*this), L);
2672 return DI;
2673}

2686//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2687// Type creation/memoization methods
2688//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
2689
2690QualType
2691ASTContext::getExtQualType(const Type *baseType, Qualifiers quals) const {
2692 unsigned fastQuals = quals.getFastQualifiers();
2693 quals.removeFastQualifiers();
2694
2695 // Check if we've already instantiated this type.
2696 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
2697 ExtQuals::Profile(ID, baseType, quals);
2698 void *insertPos = nullptr;
2699 if (ExtQuals *eq = ExtQualNodes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos)) {
2700 assert(eq->getQualifiers() == quals);
2701 return QualType(eq, fastQuals);
2702 }
2703
2704 // If the base type is not canonical, make the appropriate canonical type.
2705 QualType canon;
2706 if (!baseType->isCanonicalUnqualified()) {
2707 SplitQualType canonSplit = baseType->getCanonicalTypeInternal().split();
2708 canonSplit.Quals.addConsistentQualifiers(quals);
2709 canon = getExtQualType(canonSplit.Ty, canonSplit.Quals);
2710
2711 // Re-find the insert position.
2712 (void) ExtQualNodes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos);
2713 }
2714
2715 auto *eq = new (*this, TypeAlignment) ExtQuals(baseType, canon, quals);
2716 ExtQualNodes.InsertNode(eq, insertPos);
2717 return QualType(eq, fastQuals);
2718}
2719
2720QualType ASTContext::getAddrSpaceQualType(QualType T,
2721 LangAS AddressSpace) const {
2722 QualType CanT = getCanonicalType(T);
2723 if (CanT.getAddressSpace() == AddressSpace)
2724 return T;
2725
2726 // If we are composing extended qualifiers together, merge together
2727 // into one ExtQuals node.
2728 QualifierCollector Quals;
2729 const Type *TypeNode = Quals.strip(T);
2730
2731 // If this type already has an address space specified, it cannot get
2732 // another one.
2733 assert(!Quals.hasAddressSpace() &&
2734 "Type cannot be in multiple addr spaces!");
2735 Quals.addAddressSpace(AddressSpace);
2736
2737 return getExtQualType(TypeNode, Quals);
2738}
2739
2740QualType ASTContext::removeAddrSpaceQualType(QualType T) const {
2741 // If we are composing extended qualifiers together, merge together
2742 // into one ExtQuals node.
2743 QualifierCollector Quals;
2744 const Type *TypeNode = Quals.strip(T);
2745
2746 // If the qualifier doesn't have an address space just return it.
2747 if (!Quals.hasAddressSpace())
2748 return T;
2749
2750 Quals.removeAddressSpace();
2751
2752 // Removal of the address space can mean there are no longer any
2753 // non-fast qualifiers, so creating an ExtQualType isn't possible (asserts)
2754 // or required.
2755 if (Quals.hasNonFastQualifiers())
2756 return getExtQualType(TypeNode, Quals);
2757 else
2758 return QualType(TypeNode, Quals.getFastQualifiers());
2759}
2760
2761QualType ASTContext::getObjCGCQualType(QualType T,
2762 Qualifiers::GC GCAttr) const {
2763 QualType CanT = getCanonicalType(T);
2764 if (CanT.getObjCGCAttr() == GCAttr)
2765 return T;
2766
2767 if (const auto *ptr = T->getAs<PointerType>()) {
2768 QualType Pointee = ptr->getPointeeType();
2769 if (Pointee->isAnyPointerType()) {
2770 QualType ResultType = getObjCGCQualType(Pointee, GCAttr);
2771 return getPointerType(ResultType);
2772 }
2773 }
2774
2775 // If we are composing extended qualifiers together, merge together
2776 // into one ExtQuals node.
2777 QualifierCollector Quals;
2778 const Type *TypeNode = Quals.strip(T);
2779
2780 // If this type already has an ObjCGC specified, it cannot get
2781 // another one.
2782 assert(!Quals.hasObjCGCAttr() &&
2783 "Type cannot have multiple ObjCGCs!");
2784 Quals.addObjCGCAttr(GCAttr);
2785
2786 return getExtQualType(TypeNode, Quals);
2787}
2788
2789const FunctionType *ASTContext::adjustFunctionType(const FunctionType *T,
2790 FunctionType::ExtInfo Info) {
2791 if (T->getExtInfo() == Info)
2792 return T;
2793
2794 QualType Result;
2795 if (const auto *FNPT = dyn_cast<FunctionNoProtoType>(T)) {
2796 Result = getFunctionNoProtoType(FNPT->getReturnType(), Info);
2797 } else {
2798 const auto *FPT = cast<FunctionProtoType>(T);
2799 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = FPT->getExtProtoInfo();
2800 EPI.ExtInfo = Info;
2801 Result = getFunctionType(FPT->getReturnType(), FPT->getParamTypes(), EPI);
2802 }
2803
2804 return cast<FunctionType>(Result.getTypePtr());
2805}
2806
2807void ASTContext::adjustDeducedFunctionResultType(FunctionDecl *FD,
2808 QualType ResultType) {
2809 FD = FD->getMostRecentDecl();
2810 while (true) {
2811 const auto *FPT = FD->getType()->castAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2812 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = FPT->getExtProtoInfo();
2813 FD->setType(getFunctionType(ResultType, FPT->getParamTypes(), EPI));
2814 if (FunctionDecl *Next = FD->getPreviousDecl())
2815 FD = Next;
2816 else
2817 break;
2818 }
2819 if (ASTMutationListener *L = getASTMutationListener())
2820 L->DeducedReturnType(FD, ResultType);
2821}
2822
2823/// Get a function type and produce the equivalent function type with the
2824/// specified exception specification. Type sugar that can be present on a
2825/// declaration of a function with an exception specification is permitted
2826/// and preserved. Other type sugar (for instance, typedefs) is not.
2827QualType ASTContext::getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(
2828 QualType Orig, const FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI) {
2829 // Might have some parens.
2830 if (const auto *PT = dyn_cast<ParenType>(Orig))
2831 return getParenType(
2832 getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(PT->getInnerType(), ESI));
2833
2834 // Might be wrapped in a macro qualified type.
2835 if (const auto *MQT = dyn_cast<MacroQualifiedType>(Orig))
2836 return getMacroQualifiedType(
2837 getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(MQT->getUnderlyingType(), ESI),
2838 MQT->getMacroIdentifier());
2839
2840 // Might have a calling-convention attribute.
2841 if (const auto *AT = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(Orig))
2842 return getAttributedType(
2843 AT->getAttrKind(),
2844 getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(AT->getModifiedType(), ESI),
2845 getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(AT->getEquivalentType(), ESI));
2846
2847 // Anything else must be a function type. Rebuild it with the new exception
2848 // specification.
2849 const auto *Proto = Orig->getAs<FunctionProtoType>();
2850 return getFunctionType(
2851 Proto->getReturnType(), Proto->getParamTypes(),
2852 Proto->getExtProtoInfo().withExceptionSpec(ESI));
2853}
2854
2855bool ASTContext::hasSameFunctionTypeIgnoringExceptionSpec(QualType T,
2856 QualType U) {
2857 return hasSameType(T, U) ||
2858 (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17 &&
2859 hasSameType(getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(T, EST_None),
2860 getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(U, EST_None)));
2861}
2862
2863void ASTContext::adjustExceptionSpec(
2864 FunctionDecl *FD, const FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI,
2865 bool AsWritten) {
2866 // Update the type.
2867 QualType Updated =
2868 getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(FD->getType(), ESI);
2869 FD->setType(Updated);
2870
2871 if (!AsWritten)
2872 return;
2873
2874 // Update the type in the type source information too.
2875 if (TypeSourceInfo *TSInfo = FD->getTypeSourceInfo()) {
2876 // If the type and the type-as-written differ, we may need to update
2877 // the type-as-written too.
2878 if (TSInfo->getType() != FD->getType())
2879 Updated = getFunctionTypeWithExceptionSpec(TSInfo->getType(), ESI);
2880
2881 // FIXME: When we get proper type location information for exceptions,
2882 // we'll also have to rebuild the TypeSourceInfo. For now, we just patch
2883 // up the TypeSourceInfo;
2884 assert(TypeLoc::getFullDataSizeForType(Updated) ==
2885 TypeLoc::getFullDataSizeForType(TSInfo->getType()) &&
2886 "TypeLoc size mismatch from updating exception specification");
2887 TSInfo->overrideType(Updated);
2888 }
2889}
2890
2891/// getComplexType - Return the uniqued reference to the type for a complex
2892/// number with the specified element type.
2893QualType ASTContext::getComplexType(QualType T) const {
2894 // Unique pointers, to guarantee there is only one pointer of a particular
2895 // structure.
2896 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
2897 ComplexType::Profile(ID, T);
2898
2899 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
2900 if (ComplexType *CT = ComplexTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
2901 return QualType(CT, 0);
2902
2903 // If the pointee type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type either,
2904 // so fill in the canonical type field.
2905 QualType Canonical;
2906 if (!T.isCanonical()) {
2907 Canonical = getComplexType(getCanonicalType(T));
2908
2909 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
2910 ComplexType *NewIP = ComplexTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
2911 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
2912 }
2913 auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) ComplexType(T, Canonical);
2914 Types.push_back(New);
2915 ComplexTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
2916 return QualType(New, 0);
2917}
2918
2919bool ASTContext::shouldUseCHERICap(PointerInterpretationKind PIK) const {
2920 switch (PIK) {
2921 case PIK_Capability:
2922 return true;
2923 case PIK_Integer:
2924 assert(!getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities() &&
2925 "Can't use PointerType with integer representation in pure ABI");
2926 return false;
2927 case PIK_Default:
2928 return getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities();
2929 default:
2930 llvm_unreachable("Invalid pointer interpretation!");
2931 }
2932}
2933
2934/// getPointerType - Return the uniqued reference to the type for a pointer to
2935/// the specified type.
2936QualType ASTContext::getPointerType(QualType T, PointerInterpretationKind PIK) const {
2937 bool isCHERICap = shouldUseCHERICap(PIK);
2938 // Unique pointers, to guarantee there is only one pointer of a particular
2939 // structure.
2940 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
2941 PointerType::Profile(ID, T, isCHERICap);
2942
2943 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
2944 if (PointerType *PT = PointerTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
2945 return QualType(PT, 0);
2946
2947 // If the pointee type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type either,
2948 // so fill in the canonical type field.
2949 QualType Canonical;
2950 if (!T.isCanonical()) {
2951 Canonical = getPointerType(getCanonicalType(T), PIK);
2952
2953 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
2954 PointerType *NewIP = PointerTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
2955 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
2956 }
2957 auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) PointerType(T, Canonical, isCHERICap);
2958 Types.push_back(New);
2959 PointerTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
2960 return QualType(New, 0);
2961}
2962
2963QualType ASTContext::getAdjustedType(QualType Orig, QualType New) const {
2964 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
2965 AdjustedType::Profile(ID, Orig, New);
2966 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
2967 AdjustedType *AT = AdjustedTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
2968 if (AT)
2969 return QualType(AT, 0);
2970
2971 QualType Canonical = getCanonicalType(New);
2972
2973 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
2974 AT = AdjustedTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
2975 assert(!AT && "Shouldn't be in the map!");
2976
2977 AT = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
2978 AdjustedType(Type::Adjusted, Orig, New, Canonical);
2979 Types.push_back(AT);
2980 AdjustedTypes.InsertNode(AT, InsertPos);
2981 return QualType(AT, 0);
2982}
2983
2984QualType ASTContext::getDecayedType(QualType T) const {
2985 assert((T->isArrayType() || T->isFunctionType()) && "T does not decay");
2986
2987 QualType Decayed;
2988
2989 // C99 6.7.5.3p7:
2990 // A declaration of a parameter as "array of type" shall be
2991 // adjusted to "qualified pointer to type", where the type
2992 // qualifiers (if any) are those specified within the [ and ] of
2993 // the array type derivation.
2994 if (T->isArrayType())
2995 Decayed = getArrayDecayedType(T);
2996
2997 // C99 6.7.5.3p8:
2998 // A declaration of a parameter as "function returning type"
2999 // shall be adjusted to "pointer to function returning type", as
3000 // in 6.3.2.1.
3001 if (T->isFunctionType())
3002 Decayed = getPointerType(T);
3003
3004 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3005 AdjustedType::Profile(ID, T, Decayed);
3006 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3007 AdjustedType *AT = AdjustedTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3008 if (AT)
3009 return QualType(AT, 0);
3010
3011 QualType Canonical = getCanonicalType(Decayed);
3012
3013 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3014 AT = AdjustedTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3015 assert(!AT && "Shouldn't be in the map!");
3016
3017 AT = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DecayedType(T, Decayed, Canonical);
3018 Types.push_back(AT);
3019 AdjustedTypes.InsertNode(AT, InsertPos);
3020 return QualType(AT, 0);
3021}
3022
3023/// getBlockPointerType - Return the uniqued reference to the type for
3024/// a pointer to the specified block.
3025QualType ASTContext::getBlockPointerType(QualType T) const {
3026 assert(T->isFunctionType() && "block of function types only");
3027 // Unique pointers, to guarantee there is only one block of a particular
3028 // structure.
3029 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3030 BlockPointerType::Profile(ID, T);
3031
3032 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3033 if (BlockPointerType *PT =
3034 BlockPointerTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
3035 return QualType(PT, 0);
3036
3037 // If the block pointee type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical
3038 // type either so fill in the canonical type field.
3039 QualType Canonical;
3040 if (!T.isCanonical()) {
3041 Canonical = getBlockPointerType(getCanonicalType(T));
3042
3043 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3044 BlockPointerType *NewIP =
3045 BlockPointerTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3046 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
3047 }
3048 auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) BlockPointerType(T, Canonical);
3049 Types.push_back(New);
3050 BlockPointerTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3051 return QualType(New, 0);
3052}
3053
3054/// getLValueReferenceType - Return the uniqued reference to the type for an
3055/// lvalue reference to the specified type.
3056QualType
3057ASTContext::getLValueReferenceType(QualType T, bool SpelledAsLValue, PointerInterpretationKind PIK) const {
3058 assert(getCanonicalType(T) != OverloadTy &&
3059 "Unresolved overloaded function type");
3060
3061 bool isCHERICap = shouldUseCHERICap(PIK);
3062
3063 // Unique pointers, to guarantee there is only one pointer of a particular
3064 // structure.
3065 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3066 ReferenceType::Profile(ID, T, SpelledAsLValue, isCHERICap);
3067
3068 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3069 if (LValueReferenceType *RT =
3070 LValueReferenceTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
3071 return QualType(RT, 0);
3072
3073 const auto *InnerRef = T->getAs<ReferenceType>();
3074
3075 // If the referencee type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type
3076 // either, so fill in the canonical type field.
3077 QualType Canonical;
3078 if (!SpelledAsLValue || InnerRef || !T.isCanonical()) {
3079 QualType PointeeType = (InnerRef ? InnerRef->getPointeeType() : T);
3080 Canonical = getLValueReferenceType(getCanonicalType(PointeeType), true, PIK);
3081
3082 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3083 LValueReferenceType *NewIP =
3084 LValueReferenceTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3085 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
3086 }
3087
3088 auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) LValueReferenceType(T, Canonical,
3089 SpelledAsLValue,
3090 isCHERICap);
3091 Types.push_back(New);
3092 LValueReferenceTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3093
3094 return QualType(New, 0);
3095}
3096
3097/// getRValueReferenceType - Return the uniqued reference to the type for an
3098/// rvalue reference to the specified type.
3099QualType ASTContext::getRValueReferenceType(QualType T, PointerInterpretationKind PIK) const {
3100 // Unique pointers, to guarantee there is only one pointer of a particular
3101 // structure.
3102 bool isCHERICap = shouldUseCHERICap(PIK);
3103
3104 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3105 ReferenceType::Profile(ID, T, false, isCHERICap);
3106
3107 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3108 if (RValueReferenceType *RT =
3109 RValueReferenceTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
3110 return QualType(RT, 0);
3111
3112 const auto *InnerRef = T->getAs<ReferenceType>();
3113
3114 // If the referencee type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type
3115 // either, so fill in the canonical type field.
3116 QualType Canonical;
3117 if (InnerRef || !T.isCanonical()) {
3118 QualType PointeeType = (InnerRef ? InnerRef->getPointeeType() : T);
3119 Canonical = getRValueReferenceType(getCanonicalType(PointeeType), PIK);
3120
3121 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3122 RValueReferenceType *NewIP =
3123 RValueReferenceTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3124 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
3125 }
3126
3127 auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) RValueReferenceType(T, Canonical,
3128 isCHERICap);
3129 Types.push_back(New);
3130 RValueReferenceTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3131 return QualType(New, 0);
3132}
3133
3134/// getMemberPointerType - Return the uniqued reference to the type for a
3135/// member pointer to the specified type, in the specified class.
3136QualType ASTContext::getMemberPointerType(QualType T, const Type *Cls) const {
3137 // Unique pointers, to guarantee there is only one pointer of a particular
3138 // structure.
3139 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3140 MemberPointerType::Profile(ID, T, Cls);
3141
3142 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3143 if (MemberPointerType *PT =
3144 MemberPointerTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
3145 return QualType(PT, 0);
3146
3147 // If the pointee or class type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical
3148 // type either, so fill in the canonical type field.
3149 QualType Canonical;
3150 if (!T.isCanonical() || !Cls->isCanonicalUnqualified()) {
3151 Canonical = getMemberPointerType(getCanonicalType(T),getCanonicalType(Cls));
3152
3153 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3154 MemberPointerType *NewIP =
3155 MemberPointerTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3156 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
3157 }
3158 auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) MemberPointerType(T, Cls, Canonical);
3159 Types.push_back(New);
3160 MemberPointerTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3161 return QualType(New, 0);
3162}
3163
3164/// getConstantArrayType - Return the unique reference to the type for an
3165/// array of the specified element type.
3166QualType ASTContext::getConstantArrayType(QualType EltTy,
3167 const llvm::APInt &ArySizeIn,
3168 ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier ASM,
3169 unsigned IndexTypeQuals) const {
3170 assert((EltTy->isDependentType() ||
3171 EltTy->isIncompleteType() || EltTy->isConstantSizeType()) &&
3172 "Constant array of VLAs is illegal!");
3173
3174 // Convert the array size into a canonical width matching the pointer size for
3175 // the target.
3176 llvm::APInt ArySize(ArySizeIn);
3177 ArySize = ArySize.zextOrTrunc(Target->getMaxPointerRange());
3178
3179 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3180 ConstantArrayType::Profile(ID, EltTy, ArySize, ASM, IndexTypeQuals);
3181
3182 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3183 if (ConstantArrayType *ATP =
3184 ConstantArrayTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
3185 return QualType(ATP, 0);
3186
3187 // If the element type isn't canonical or has qualifiers, this won't
3188 // be a canonical type either, so fill in the canonical type field.
3189 QualType Canon;
3190 if (!EltTy.isCanonical() || EltTy.hasLocalQualifiers()) {
3191 SplitQualType canonSplit = getCanonicalType(EltTy).split();
3192 Canon = getConstantArrayType(QualType(canonSplit.Ty, 0), ArySize,
3193 ASM, IndexTypeQuals);
3194 Canon = getQualifiedType(Canon, canonSplit.Quals);
3195
3196 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3197 ConstantArrayType *NewIP =
3198 ConstantArrayTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3199 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
3200 }
3201
3202 auto *New = new (*this,TypeAlignment)
3203 ConstantArrayType(EltTy, Canon, ArySize, ASM, IndexTypeQuals);
3204 ConstantArrayTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3205 Types.push_back(New);
3206 return QualType(New, 0);
3207}
3208
3209/// getVariableArrayDecayedType - Turns the given type, which may be
3210/// variably-modified, into the corresponding type with all the known
3211/// sizes replaced with [*].
3212QualType ASTContext::getVariableArrayDecayedType(QualType type) const {
3213 // Vastly most common case.
3214 if (!type->isVariablyModifiedType()) return type;
3215
3216 QualType result;
3217
3218 SplitQualType split = type.getSplitDesugaredType();
3219 const Type *ty = split.Ty;
3220 switch (ty->getTypeClass()) {
3221#define TYPE(Class, Base)
3222#define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Class, Base)
3223#define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
3224#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
3225 llvm_unreachable("didn't desugar past all non-canonical types?");
3226
3227 // These types should never be variably-modified.
3228 case Type::Builtin:
3229 case Type::Complex:
3230 case Type::Vector:
3231 case Type::DependentVector:
3232 case Type::ExtVector:
3233 case Type::DependentSizedExtVector:
3234 case Type::DependentAddressSpace:
3235 case Type::ObjCObject:
3236 case Type::ObjCInterface:
3237 case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
3238 case Type::Record:
3239 case Type::Enum:
3240 case Type::UnresolvedUsing:
3241 case Type::TypeOfExpr:
3242 case Type::TypeOf:
3243 case Type::Decltype:
3244 case Type::UnaryTransform:
3245 case Type::DependentName:
3246 case Type::InjectedClassName:
3247 case Type::TemplateSpecialization:
3248 case Type::DependentTemplateSpecialization:
3249 case Type::TemplateTypeParm:
3250 case Type::SubstTemplateTypeParmPack:
3251 case Type::Auto:
3252 case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
3253 case Type::PackExpansion:
3254 llvm_unreachable("type should never be variably-modified");
3255
3256 // These types can be variably-modified but should never need to
3257 // further decay.
3258 case Type::FunctionNoProto:
3259 case Type::FunctionProto:
3260 case Type::BlockPointer:
3261 case Type::MemberPointer:
3262 case Type::Pipe:
3263 return type;
3264
3265 // These types can be variably-modified. All these modifications
3266 // preserve structure except as noted by comments.
3267 // TODO: if we ever care about optimizing VLAs, there are no-op
3268 // optimizations available here.
3269 case Type::Pointer:
3270 result = getPointerType(getVariableArrayDecayedType(
3271 cast<PointerType>(ty)->getPointeeType()));
3272 break;
3273
3274 case Type::LValueReference: {
3275 const auto *lv = cast<LValueReferenceType>(ty);
3276 result = getLValueReferenceType(
3277 getVariableArrayDecayedType(lv->getPointeeType()),
3278 lv->isSpelledAsLValue());
3279 break;
3280 }
3281
3282 case Type::RValueReference: {
3283 const auto *lv = cast<RValueReferenceType>(ty);
3284 result = getRValueReferenceType(
3285 getVariableArrayDecayedType(lv->getPointeeType()));
3286 break;
3287 }
3288
3289 case Type::Atomic: {
3290 const auto *at = cast<AtomicType>(ty);
3291 result = getAtomicType(getVariableArrayDecayedType(at->getValueType()));
3292 break;
3293 }
3294
3295 case Type::ConstantArray: {
3296 const auto *cat = cast<ConstantArrayType>(ty);
3297 result = getConstantArrayType(
3298 getVariableArrayDecayedType(cat->getElementType()),
3299 cat->getSize(),
3300 cat->getSizeModifier(),
3301 cat->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers());
3302 break;
3303 }
3304
3305 case Type::DependentSizedArray: {
3306 const auto *dat = cast<DependentSizedArrayType>(ty);
3307 result = getDependentSizedArrayType(
3308 getVariableArrayDecayedType(dat->getElementType()),
3309 dat->getSizeExpr(),
3310 dat->getSizeModifier(),
3311 dat->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
3312 dat->getBracketsRange());
3313 break;
3314 }
3315
3316 // Turn incomplete types into [*] types.
3317 case Type::IncompleteArray: {
3318 const auto *iat = cast<IncompleteArrayType>(ty);
3319 result = getVariableArrayType(
3320 getVariableArrayDecayedType(iat->getElementType()),
3321 /*size*/ nullptr,
3322 ArrayType::Normal,
3323 iat->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
3324 SourceRange());
3325 break;
3326 }
3327
3328 // Turn VLA types into [*] types.
3329 case Type::VariableArray: {
3330 const auto *vat = cast<VariableArrayType>(ty);
3331 result = getVariableArrayType(
3332 getVariableArrayDecayedType(vat->getElementType()),
3333 /*size*/ nullptr,
3334 ArrayType::Star,
3335 vat->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
3336 vat->getBracketsRange());
3337 break;
3338 }
3339 }
3340
3341 // Apply the top-level qualifiers from the original.
3342 return getQualifiedType(result, split.Quals);
3343}
3344
3345/// getVariableArrayType - Returns a non-unique reference to the type for a
3346/// variable array of the specified element type.
3347QualType ASTContext::getVariableArrayType(QualType EltTy,
3348 Expr *NumElts,
3349 ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier ASM,
3350 unsigned IndexTypeQuals,
3351 SourceRange Brackets) const {
3352 // Since we don't unique expressions, it isn't possible to unique VLA's
3353 // that have an expression provided for their size.
3354 QualType Canon;
3355
3356 // Be sure to pull qualifiers off the element type.
3357 if (!EltTy.isCanonical() || EltTy.hasLocalQualifiers()) {
3358 SplitQualType canonSplit = getCanonicalType(EltTy).split();
3359 Canon = getVariableArrayType(QualType(canonSplit.Ty, 0), NumElts, ASM,
3360 IndexTypeQuals, Brackets);
3361 Canon = getQualifiedType(Canon, canonSplit.Quals);
3362 }
3363
3364 auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3365 VariableArrayType(EltTy, Canon, NumElts, ASM, IndexTypeQuals, Brackets);
3366
3367 VariableArrayTypes.push_back(New);
3368 Types.push_back(New);
3369 return QualType(New, 0);
3370}
3371
3372/// getDependentSizedArrayType - Returns a non-unique reference to
3373/// the type for a dependently-sized array of the specified element
3374/// type.
3375QualType ASTContext::getDependentSizedArrayType(QualType elementType,
3376 Expr *numElements,
3377 ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier ASM,
3378 unsigned elementTypeQuals,
3379 SourceRange brackets) const {
3380 assert((!numElements || numElements->isTypeDependent() ||
3381 numElements->isValueDependent()) &&
3382 "Size must be type- or value-dependent!");
3383
3384 // Dependently-sized array types that do not have a specified number
3385 // of elements will have their sizes deduced from a dependent
3386 // initializer. We do no canonicalization here at all, which is okay
3387 // because they can't be used in most locations.
3388 if (!numElements) {
3389 auto *newType
3390 = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3391 DependentSizedArrayType(*this, elementType, QualType(),
3392 numElements, ASM, elementTypeQuals,
3393 brackets);
3394 Types.push_back(newType);
3395 return QualType(newType, 0);
3396 }
3397
3398 // Otherwise, we actually build a new type every time, but we
3399 // also build a canonical type.
3400
3401 SplitQualType canonElementType = getCanonicalType(elementType).split();
3402
3403 void *insertPos = nullptr;
3404 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3405 DependentSizedArrayType::Profile(ID, *this,
3406 QualType(canonElementType.Ty, 0),
3407 ASM, elementTypeQuals, numElements);
3408
3409 // Look for an existing type with these properties.
3410 DependentSizedArrayType *canonTy =
3411 DependentSizedArrayTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos);
3412
3413 // If we don't have one, build one.
3414 if (!canonTy) {
3415 canonTy = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3416 DependentSizedArrayType(*this, QualType(canonElementType.Ty, 0),
3417 QualType(), numElements, ASM, elementTypeQuals,
3418 brackets);
3419 DependentSizedArrayTypes.InsertNode(canonTy, insertPos);
3420 Types.push_back(canonTy);
3421 }
3422
3423 // Apply qualifiers from the element type to the array.
3424 QualType canon = getQualifiedType(QualType(canonTy,0),
3425 canonElementType.Quals);
3426
3427 // If we didn't need extra canonicalization for the element type or the size
3428 // expression, then just use that as our result.
3429 if (QualType(canonElementType.Ty, 0) == elementType &&
3430 canonTy->getSizeExpr() == numElements)
3431 return canon;
3432
3433 // Otherwise, we need to build a type which follows the spelling
3434 // of the element type.
3435 auto *sugaredType
3436 = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3437 DependentSizedArrayType(*this, elementType, canon, numElements,
3438 ASM, elementTypeQuals, brackets);
3439 Types.push_back(sugaredType);
3440 return QualType(sugaredType, 0);
3441}
3442
3443QualType ASTContext::getIncompleteArrayType(QualType elementType,
3444 ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier ASM,
3445 unsigned elementTypeQuals) const {
3446 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3447 IncompleteArrayType::Profile(ID, elementType, ASM, elementTypeQuals);
3448
3449 void *insertPos = nullptr;
3450 if (IncompleteArrayType *iat =
3451 IncompleteArrayTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos))
3452 return QualType(iat, 0);
3453
3454 // If the element type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type
3455 // either, so fill in the canonical type field. We also have to pull
3456 // qualifiers off the element type.
3457 QualType canon;
3458
3459 if (!elementType.isCanonical() || elementType.hasLocalQualifiers()) {
3460 SplitQualType canonSplit = getCanonicalType(elementType).split();
3461 canon = getIncompleteArrayType(QualType(canonSplit.Ty, 0),
3462 ASM, elementTypeQuals);
3463 canon = getQualifiedType(canon, canonSplit.Quals);
3464
3465 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3466 IncompleteArrayType *existing =
3467 IncompleteArrayTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos);
3468 assert(!existing && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void) existing;
3469 }
3470
3471 auto *newType = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3472 IncompleteArrayType(elementType, canon, ASM, elementTypeQuals);
3473
3474 IncompleteArrayTypes.InsertNode(newType, insertPos);
3475 Types.push_back(newType);
3476 return QualType(newType, 0);
3477}

3479/// getVectorType - Return the unique reference to a vector type of
3480/// the specified element type and size. VectorType must be a built-in type.
3481QualType ASTContext::getVectorType(QualType vecType, unsigned NumElts,
3482 VectorType::VectorKind VecKind) const {
3483 assert(vecType->isBuiltinType());
3484
3485 // Check if we've already instantiated a vector of this type.
3486 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3487 VectorType::Profile(ID, vecType, NumElts, Type::Vector, VecKind);
3488
3489 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3490 if (VectorType *VTP = VectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
3491 return QualType(VTP, 0);
3492
3493 // If the element type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type either,
3494 // so fill in the canonical type field.
3495 QualType Canonical;
3496 if (!vecType.isCanonical()) {
3497 Canonical = getVectorType(getCanonicalType(vecType), NumElts, VecKind);
3498
3499 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3500 VectorType *NewIP = VectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3501 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
3502 }
3503 auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3504 VectorType(vecType, NumElts, Canonical, VecKind);
3505 VectorTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3506 Types.push_back(New);
3507 return QualType(New, 0);
3508}

3510QualType
3511ASTContext::getDependentVectorType(QualType VecType, Expr *SizeExpr,
3512 SourceLocation AttrLoc,
3513 VectorType::VectorKind VecKind) const {
3514 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3515 DependentVectorType::Profile(ID, *this, getCanonicalType(VecType), SizeExpr,
3516 VecKind);
3517 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3518 DependentVectorType *Canon =
3519 DependentVectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3520 DependentVectorType *New;
3521
3522 if (Canon) {
3523 New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentVectorType(
3524 *this, VecType, QualType(Canon, 0), SizeExpr, AttrLoc, VecKind);
3525 } else {
3526 QualType CanonVecTy = getCanonicalType(VecType);
3527 if (CanonVecTy == VecType) {
3528 New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentVectorType(
3529 *this, VecType, QualType(), SizeExpr, AttrLoc, VecKind);
3530
3531 DependentVectorType *CanonCheck =
3532 DependentVectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3533 assert(!CanonCheck &&
3534 "Dependent-sized vector_size canonical type broken");
3535 (void)CanonCheck;
3536 DependentVectorTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3537 } else {
3538 QualType Canon = getDependentSizedExtVectorType(CanonVecTy, SizeExpr,
3539 SourceLocation());
3540 New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentVectorType(
3541 *this, VecType, Canon, SizeExpr, AttrLoc, VecKind);
3542 }
3543 }
3544
3545 Types.push_back(New);
3546 return QualType(New, 0);
3547}

3552ASTContext::getExtVectorType(QualType vecType, unsigned NumElts) const {

3580QualType
3581ASTContext::getDependentSizedExtVectorType(QualType vecType,
3582 Expr *SizeExpr,
3583 SourceLocation AttrLoc) const {
3584 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3585 DependentSizedExtVectorType::Profile(ID, *this, getCanonicalType(vecType),
3586 SizeExpr);
3587
3588 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3589 DependentSizedExtVectorType *Canon
3590 = DependentSizedExtVectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3591 DependentSizedExtVectorType *New;
3592 if (Canon) {
3593 // We already have a canonical version of this array type; use it as
3594 // the canonical type for a newly-built type.
3595 New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3596 DependentSizedExtVectorType(*this, vecType, QualType(Canon, 0),
3597 SizeExpr, AttrLoc);
3598 } else {
3599 QualType CanonVecTy = getCanonicalType(vecType);
3600 if (CanonVecTy == vecType) {
3601 New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3602 DependentSizedExtVectorType(*this, vecType, QualType(), SizeExpr,
3603 AttrLoc);
3604
3605 DependentSizedExtVectorType *CanonCheck
3606 = DependentSizedExtVectorTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3607 assert(!CanonCheck && "Dependent-sized ext_vector canonical type broken");
3608 (void)CanonCheck;
3609 DependentSizedExtVectorTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3610 } else {
3611 QualType Canon = getDependentSizedExtVectorType(CanonVecTy, SizeExpr,
3612 SourceLocation());
3613 New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3614 DependentSizedExtVectorType(*this, vecType, Canon, SizeExpr, AttrLoc);
3615 }
3616 }
3617
3618 Types.push_back(New);
3619 return QualType(New, 0);
3620}

3622QualType ASTContext::getDependentAddressSpaceType(QualType PointeeType,
3623 Expr *AddrSpaceExpr,
3624 SourceLocation AttrLoc) const {
3625 assert(AddrSpaceExpr->isInstantiationDependent());
3626
3627 QualType canonPointeeType = getCanonicalType(PointeeType);
3628
3629 void *insertPos = nullptr;
3630 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3631 DependentAddressSpaceType::Profile(ID, *this, canonPointeeType,
3632 AddrSpaceExpr);
3633
3634 DependentAddressSpaceType *canonTy =
3635 DependentAddressSpaceTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos);
3636
3637 if (!canonTy) {
3638 canonTy = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3639 DependentAddressSpaceType(*this, canonPointeeType,
3640 QualType(), AddrSpaceExpr, AttrLoc);
3641 DependentAddressSpaceTypes.InsertNode(canonTy, insertPos);
3642 Types.push_back(canonTy);
3643 }
3644
3645 if (canonPointeeType == PointeeType &&
3646 canonTy->getAddrSpaceExpr() == AddrSpaceExpr)
3647 return QualType(canonTy, 0);
3648
3649 auto *sugaredType
3650 = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3651 DependentAddressSpaceType(*this, PointeeType, QualType(canonTy, 0),
3652 AddrSpaceExpr, AttrLoc);
3653 Types.push_back(sugaredType);
3654 return QualType(sugaredType, 0);
3655}

3657/// Determine whether \p T is canonical as the result type of a function.
3658static bool isCanonicalResultType(QualType T) {
3659 return T.isCanonical() &&
3660 (T.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_None ||
3661 T.getObjCLifetime() == Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone);
3662}
3663
3664/// getFunctionNoProtoType - Return a K&R style C function type like 'int()'.
3665QualType
3666ASTContext::getFunctionNoProtoType(QualType ResultTy,
3667 const FunctionType::ExtInfo &Info) const {
3668 // Unique functions, to guarantee there is only one function of a particular
3669 // structure.
3670 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3671 FunctionNoProtoType::Profile(ID, ResultTy, Info);
3672
3673 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3674 if (FunctionNoProtoType *FT =
3675 FunctionNoProtoTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
3676 return QualType(FT, 0);
3677
3678 QualType Canonical;
3679 if (!isCanonicalResultType(ResultTy)) {
3680 Canonical =
3681 getFunctionNoProtoType(getCanonicalFunctionResultType(ResultTy), Info);
3682
3683 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3684 FunctionNoProtoType *NewIP =
3685 FunctionNoProtoTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3686 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
3687 }
3688
3689 auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
3690 FunctionNoProtoType(ResultTy, Canonical, Info);
3691 Types.push_back(New);
3692 FunctionNoProtoTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3693 return QualType(New, 0);
3694}
3695
3696CanQualType
3697ASTContext::getCanonicalFunctionResultType(QualType ResultType) const {
3698 CanQualType CanResultType = getCanonicalType(ResultType);
3699
3700 // Canonical result types do not have ARC lifetime qualifiers.
3701 if (CanResultType.getQualifiers().hasObjCLifetime()) {
3702 Qualifiers Qs = CanResultType.getQualifiers();
3703 Qs.removeObjCLifetime();
3704 return CanQualType::CreateUnsafe(
3705 getQualifiedType(CanResultType.getUnqualifiedType(), Qs));
3706 }
3707
3708 return CanResultType;
3709}
3710
3711static bool isCanonicalExceptionSpecification(
3712 const FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo &ESI, bool NoexceptInType) {
3713 if (ESI.Type == EST_None)
3714 return true;
3715 if (!NoexceptInType)
3716 return false;
3717
3718 // C++17 onwards: exception specification is part of the type, as a simple
3719 // boolean "can this function type throw".
3720 if (ESI.Type == EST_BasicNoexcept)
3721 return true;
3722
3723 // A noexcept(expr) specification is (possibly) canonical if expr is
3724 // value-dependent.
3725 if (ESI.Type == EST_DependentNoexcept)
3726 return true;
3727
3728 // A dynamic exception specification is canonical if it only contains pack
3729 // expansions (so we can't tell whether it's non-throwing) and all its
3730 // contained types are canonical.
3731 if (ESI.Type == EST_Dynamic) {
3732 bool AnyPackExpansions = false;
3733 for (QualType ET : ESI.Exceptions) {
3734 if (!ET.isCanonical())
3735 return false;
3736 if (ET->getAs<PackExpansionType>())
3737 AnyPackExpansions = true;
3738 }
3739 return AnyPackExpansions;
3740 }
3741
3742 return false;
3743}
3744
3745QualType ASTContext::getFunctionTypeInternal(
3746 QualType ResultTy, ArrayRef<QualType> ArgArray,
3747 const FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo &EPI, bool OnlyWantCanonical) const {
3748 size_t NumArgs = ArgArray.size();
3749
3750 // Unique functions, to guarantee there is only one function of a particular
3751 // structure.
3752 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3753 FunctionProtoType::Profile(ID, ResultTy, ArgArray.begin(), NumArgs, EPI,
3754 *this, true);
3755
3756 QualType Canonical;
3757 bool Unique = false;
3758
3759 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3760 if (FunctionProtoType *FPT =
3761 FunctionProtoTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos)) {
3762 QualType Existing = QualType(FPT, 0);
3763
3764 // If we find a pre-existing equivalent FunctionProtoType, we can just reuse
3765 // it so long as our exception specification doesn't contain a dependent
3766 // noexcept expression, or we're just looking for a canonical type.
3767 // Otherwise, we're going to need to create a type
3768 // sugar node to hold the concrete expression.
3769 if (OnlyWantCanonical || !isComputedNoexcept(EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type) ||
3770 EPI.ExceptionSpec.NoexceptExpr == FPT->getNoexceptExpr())
3771 return Existing;
3772
3773 // We need a new type sugar node for this one, to hold the new noexcept
3774 // expression. We do no canonicalization here, but that's OK since we don't
3775 // expect to see the same noexcept expression much more than once.
3776 Canonical = getCanonicalType(Existing);
3777 Unique = true;
3778 }
3779
3780 bool NoexceptInType = getLangOpts().CPlusPlus17;
3781 bool IsCanonicalExceptionSpec =
3782 isCanonicalExceptionSpecification(EPI.ExceptionSpec, NoexceptInType);
3783
3784 // Determine whether the type being created is already canonical or not.
3785 bool isCanonical = !Unique && IsCanonicalExceptionSpec &&
3786 isCanonicalResultType(ResultTy) && !EPI.HasTrailingReturn;
3787 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumArgs && isCanonical; ++i)
3788 if (!ArgArray[i].isCanonicalAsParam())
3789 isCanonical = false;
3790
3791 if (OnlyWantCanonical)
3792 assert(isCanonical &&
3793 "given non-canonical parameters constructing canonical type");
3794
3795 // If this type isn't canonical, get the canonical version of it if we don't
3796 // already have it. The exception spec is only partially part of the
3797 // canonical type, and only in C++17 onwards.
3798 if (!isCanonical && Canonical.isNull()) {
3799 SmallVector<QualType, 16> CanonicalArgs;
3800 CanonicalArgs.reserve(NumArgs);
3801 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumArgs; ++i)
3802 CanonicalArgs.push_back(getCanonicalParamType(ArgArray[i]));
3803
3804 llvm::SmallVector<QualType, 8> ExceptionTypeStorage;
3805 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo CanonicalEPI = EPI;
3806 CanonicalEPI.HasTrailingReturn = false;
3807
3808 if (IsCanonicalExceptionSpec) {
3809 // Exception spec is already OK.
3810 } else if (NoexceptInType) {
3811 switch (EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type) {
3812 case EST_Unparsed: case EST_Unevaluated: case EST_Uninstantiated:
3813 // We don't know yet. It shouldn't matter what we pick here; no-one
3814 // should ever look at this.
3815 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
3816 case EST_None: case EST_MSAny: case EST_NoexceptFalse:
3817 CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = EST_None;
3818 break;
3819
3820 // A dynamic exception specification is almost always "not noexcept",
3821 // with the exception that a pack expansion might expand to no types.
3822 case EST_Dynamic: {
3823 bool AnyPacks = false;
3824 for (QualType ET : EPI.ExceptionSpec.Exceptions) {
3825 if (ET->getAs<PackExpansionType>())
3826 AnyPacks = true;
3827 ExceptionTypeStorage.push_back(getCanonicalType(ET));
3828 }
3829 if (!AnyPacks)
3830 CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = EST_None;
3831 else {
3832 CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = EST_Dynamic;
3833 CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec.Exceptions = ExceptionTypeStorage;
3834 }
3835 break;
3836 }
3837
3838 case EST_DynamicNone:
3839 case EST_BasicNoexcept:
3840 case EST_NoexceptTrue:
3841 case EST_NoThrow:
3842 CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec.Type = EST_BasicNoexcept;
3843 break;
3844
3845 case EST_DependentNoexcept:
3846 llvm_unreachable("dependent noexcept is already canonical");
3847 }
3848 } else {
3849 CanonicalEPI.ExceptionSpec = FunctionProtoType::ExceptionSpecInfo();
3850 }
3851
3852 // Adjust the canonical function result type.
3853 CanQualType CanResultTy = getCanonicalFunctionResultType(ResultTy);
3854 Canonical =
3855 getFunctionTypeInternal(CanResultTy, CanonicalArgs, CanonicalEPI, true);
3856
3857 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3858 FunctionProtoType *NewIP =
3859 FunctionProtoTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3860 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
3861 }
3862
3863 // Compute the needed size to hold this FunctionProtoType and the
3864 // various trailing objects.
3865 auto ESH = FunctionProtoType::getExceptionSpecSize(
3866 EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type, EPI.ExceptionSpec.Exceptions.size());
3867 size_t Size = FunctionProtoType::totalSizeToAlloc<
3868 QualType, FunctionType::FunctionTypeExtraBitfields,
3869 FunctionType::ExceptionType, Expr *, FunctionDecl *,
3870 FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, Qualifiers>(
3871 NumArgs, FunctionProtoType::hasExtraBitfields(EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type),
3872 ESH.NumExceptionType, ESH.NumExprPtr, ESH.NumFunctionDeclPtr,
3873 EPI.ExtParameterInfos ? NumArgs : 0,
3874 EPI.TypeQuals.hasNonFastQualifiers() ? 1 : 0);
3875
3876 auto *FTP = (FunctionProtoType *)Allocate(Size, TypeAlignment);
3877 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo newEPI = EPI;
3878 new (FTP) FunctionProtoType(ResultTy, ArgArray, Canonical, newEPI);
3879 Types.push_back(FTP);
3880 if (!Unique)
3881 FunctionProtoTypes.InsertNode(FTP, InsertPos);
3882 return QualType(FTP, 0);
3883}
3884
3885QualType ASTContext::getPipeType(QualType T, bool ReadOnly) const {
3886 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
3887 PipeType::Profile(ID, T, ReadOnly);
3888
3889 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
3890 if (PipeType *PT = PipeTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
3891 return QualType(PT, 0);
3892
3893 // If the pipe element type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type
3894 // either, so fill in the canonical type field.
3895 QualType Canonical;
3896 if (!T.isCanonical()) {
3897 Canonical = getPipeType(getCanonicalType(T), ReadOnly);
3898
3899 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
3900 PipeType *NewIP = PipeTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
3901 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!");
3902 (void)NewIP;
3903 }
3904 auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) PipeType(T, Canonical, ReadOnly);
3905 Types.push_back(New);
3906 PipeTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
3907 return QualType(New, 0);
3908}
3909
3910QualType ASTContext::adjustStringLiteralBaseType(QualType Ty) const {
3911 // OpenCL v1.1 s6.5.3: a string literal is in the constant address space.
3912 return LangOpts.OpenCL ? getAddrSpaceQualType(Ty, LangAS::opencl_constant)
3913 : Ty;
3914}
3915
3916QualType ASTContext::getReadPipeType(QualType T) const {
3917 return getPipeType(T, true);
3918}
3919
3920QualType ASTContext::getWritePipeType(QualType T) const {
3921 return getPipeType(T, false);
3922}

3924#ifndef NDEBUG
3925static bool NeedsInjectedClassNameType(const RecordDecl *D) {
3926 if (!isa<CXXRecordDecl>(D)) return false;
3927 const auto *RD = cast<CXXRecordDecl>(D);
3928 if (isa<ClassTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(RD))
3929 return true;
3930 if (RD->getDescribedClassTemplate() &&
3931 !isa<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RD))
3932 return true;
3933 return false;
3934}
3935#endif
3936
3937/// getInjectedClassNameType - Return the unique reference to the
3938/// injected class name type for the specified templated declaration.
3939QualType ASTContext::getInjectedClassNameType(CXXRecordDecl *Decl,
3940 QualType TST) const {
3941 assert(NeedsInjectedClassNameType(Decl));
3942 if (Decl->TypeForDecl) {
3943 assert(isa<InjectedClassNameType>(Decl->TypeForDecl));
3944 } else if (CXXRecordDecl *PrevDecl = Decl->getPreviousDecl()) {
3945 assert(PrevDecl->TypeForDecl && "previous declaration has no type");
3946 Decl->TypeForDecl = PrevDecl->TypeForDecl;
3947 assert(isa<InjectedClassNameType>(Decl->TypeForDecl));
3948 } else {
3949 Type *newType =
3950 new (*this, TypeAlignment) InjectedClassNameType(Decl, TST);
3951 Decl->TypeForDecl = newType;
3952 Types.push_back(newType);
3953 }
3954 return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl, 0);
3955}
3956
3957/// getTypeDeclType - Return the unique reference to the type for the
3958/// specified type declaration.
3959QualType ASTContext::getTypeDeclTypeSlow(const TypeDecl *Decl) const {
3960 assert(Decl && "Passed null for Decl param");
3961 assert(!Decl->TypeForDecl && "TypeForDecl present in slow case");
3962
3963 if (const auto *Typedef = dyn_cast<TypedefNameDecl>(Decl))
3964 return getTypedefType(Typedef);
3965
3966 assert(!isa<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(Decl) &&
3967 "Template type parameter types are always available.");
3968
3969 if (const auto *Record = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(Decl)) {
3970 assert(Record->isFirstDecl() && "struct/union has previous declaration");
3971 assert(!NeedsInjectedClassNameType(Record));
3972 return getRecordType(Record);
3973 } else if (const auto *Enum = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(Decl)) {
3974 assert(Enum->isFirstDecl() && "enum has previous declaration");
3975 return getEnumType(Enum);
3976 } else if (const auto *Using = dyn_cast<UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl>(Decl)) {
3977 Type *newType = new (*this, TypeAlignment) UnresolvedUsingType(Using);
3978 Decl->TypeForDecl = newType;
3979 Types.push_back(newType);
3980 } else
3981 llvm_unreachable("TypeDecl without a type?");
3982
3983 return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl, 0);
3984}
3985
3986/// getTypedefType - Return the unique reference to the type for the
3987/// specified typedef name decl.
3988QualType
3989ASTContext::getTypedefType(const TypedefNameDecl *Decl,
3990 QualType Canonical,
3991 bool IsCHERICap) const {
3992 if (IsCHERICap && Decl->CHERICapTypeForDecl) return QualType(Decl->CHERICapTypeForDecl, 0);
3993 if (!IsCHERICap && Decl->TypeForDecl) return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl, 0);
3994
3995 if (Canonical.isNull())
3996 Canonical = getCanonicalType(Decl->getUnderlyingType());
3997 if (IsCHERICap) {
3998 if (const PointerType *PT = Canonical->getAs<PointerType>()) {
3999 // Create a copy of the typedef whose name is prefixed by "__chericap_"
4000 // and whose underlying type is the cheri_capability qualified version of
4001 // the pointer type
4002 Canonical = getPointerType(PT->getPointeeType(), ASTContext::PIK_Capability);
4003 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = getTrivialTypeSourceInfo(Canonical, Decl->getBeginLoc());
4004 DeclContext *DC = const_cast<DeclContext *>(Decl->getDeclContext());
4005 std::string typedefName = "__chericap_" + Decl->getNameAsString();
4006 TypedefDecl *NewDecl = TypedefDecl::Create(
4007 const_cast<ASTContext &>(*this),
4008 DC,
4009 Decl->getBeginLoc(),
4010 Decl->getLocation(),
4011 &Idents.get(typedefName),
4012 TInfo);
4013 DC->addDecl(NewDecl);
4014 Decl = NewDecl;
4015 }
4016 }
4017 auto *newType = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4018 TypedefType(Type::Typedef, Decl, Canonical);
4019 if (IsCHERICap)
4020 Decl->CHERICapTypeForDecl = newType;
4021 else
4022 Decl->TypeForDecl = newType;
4023 Types.push_back(newType);
4024 return QualType(newType, 0);
4025}
4026
4027QualType ASTContext::getRecordType(const RecordDecl *Decl) const {
4028 if (Decl->TypeForDecl) return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl, 0);
4029
4030 if (const RecordDecl *PrevDecl = Decl->getPreviousDecl())
4031 if (PrevDecl->TypeForDecl)
4032 return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl = PrevDecl->TypeForDecl, 0);
4033
4034 auto *newType = new (*this, TypeAlignment) RecordType(Decl);
4035 Decl->TypeForDecl = newType;
4036 Types.push_back(newType);
4037 return QualType(newType, 0);
4038}
4039
4040QualType ASTContext::getEnumType(const EnumDecl *Decl) const {
4041 if (Decl->TypeForDecl) return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl, 0);
4042
4043 if (const EnumDecl *PrevDecl = Decl->getPreviousDecl())
4044 if (PrevDecl->TypeForDecl)
4045 return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl = PrevDecl->TypeForDecl, 0);
4046
4047 auto *newType = new (*this, TypeAlignment) EnumType(Decl);
4048 Decl->TypeForDecl = newType;
4049 Types.push_back(newType);
4050 return QualType(newType, 0);
4051}
4052
4053QualType ASTContext::getAttributedType(attr::Kind attrKind,
4054 QualType modifiedType,
4055 QualType equivalentType) {
4056 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID id;
4057 AttributedType::Profile(id, attrKind, modifiedType, equivalentType);
4058
4059 void *insertPos = nullptr;
4060 AttributedType *type = AttributedTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(id, insertPos);
4061 if (type) return QualType(type, 0);
4062
4063 QualType canon = getCanonicalType(equivalentType);
4064 type = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4065 AttributedType(canon, attrKind, modifiedType, equivalentType);
4066
4067 Types.push_back(type);
4068 AttributedTypes.InsertNode(type, insertPos);
4069
4070 return QualType(type, 0);
4071}

4073/// Retrieve a substitution-result type.
4074QualType
4075ASTContext::getSubstTemplateTypeParmType(const TemplateTypeParmType *Parm,
4076 QualType Replacement) const {
4077 assert(Replacement.isCanonical()
4078 && "replacement types must always be canonical");
4079
4080 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4081 SubstTemplateTypeParmType::Profile(ID, Parm, Replacement);
4082 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4083 SubstTemplateTypeParmType *SubstParm
4084 = SubstTemplateTypeParmTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4085
4086 if (!SubstParm) {
4087 SubstParm = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4088 SubstTemplateTypeParmType(Parm, Replacement);
4089 Types.push_back(SubstParm);
4090 SubstTemplateTypeParmTypes.InsertNode(SubstParm, InsertPos);
4091 }
4092
4093 return QualType(SubstParm, 0);
4094}
4095
4096/// Retrieve a
4097QualType ASTContext::getSubstTemplateTypeParmPackType(
4098 const TemplateTypeParmType *Parm,
4099 const TemplateArgument &ArgPack) {
4100#ifndef NDEBUG
4101 for (const auto &P : ArgPack.pack_elements()) {
4102 assert(P.getKind() == TemplateArgument::Type &&"Pack contains a non-type");
4103 assert(P.getAsType().isCanonical() && "Pack contains non-canonical type");
4104 }
4105#endif
4106
4107 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4108 SubstTemplateTypeParmPackType::Profile(ID, Parm, ArgPack);
4109 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4110 if (SubstTemplateTypeParmPackType *SubstParm
4111 = SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
4112 return QualType(SubstParm, 0);
4113
4114 QualType Canon;
4115 if (!Parm->isCanonicalUnqualified()) {
4116 Canon = getCanonicalType(QualType(Parm, 0));
4117 Canon = getSubstTemplateTypeParmPackType(cast<TemplateTypeParmType>(Canon),
4118 ArgPack);
4119 SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4120 }
4121
4122 auto *SubstParm
4123 = new (*this, TypeAlignment) SubstTemplateTypeParmPackType(Parm, Canon,
4124 ArgPack);
4125 Types.push_back(SubstParm);
4126 SubstTemplateTypeParmPackTypes.InsertNode(SubstParm, InsertPos);
4127 return QualType(SubstParm, 0);
4128}
4129
4130/// Retrieve the template type parameter type for a template
4131/// parameter or parameter pack with the given depth, index, and (optionally)
4132/// name.
4133QualType ASTContext::getTemplateTypeParmType(unsigned Depth, unsigned Index,
4134 bool ParameterPack,
4135 TemplateTypeParmDecl *TTPDecl) const {
4136 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4137 TemplateTypeParmType::Profile(ID, Depth, Index, ParameterPack, TTPDecl);
4138 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4139 TemplateTypeParmType *TypeParm
4140 = TemplateTypeParmTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4141
4142 if (TypeParm)
4143 return QualType(TypeParm, 0);
4144
4145 if (TTPDecl) {
4146 QualType Canon = getTemplateTypeParmType(Depth, Index, ParameterPack);
4147 TypeParm = new (*this, TypeAlignment) TemplateTypeParmType(TTPDecl, Canon);
4148
4149 TemplateTypeParmType *TypeCheck
4150 = TemplateTypeParmTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4151 assert(!TypeCheck && "Template type parameter canonical type broken");
4152 (void)TypeCheck;
4153 } else
4154 TypeParm = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4155 TemplateTypeParmType(Depth, Index, ParameterPack);
4156
4157 Types.push_back(TypeParm);
4158 TemplateTypeParmTypes.InsertNode(TypeParm, InsertPos);
4159
4160 return QualType(TypeParm, 0);
4161}
4162
4163TypeSourceInfo *
4164ASTContext::getTemplateSpecializationTypeInfo(TemplateName Name,
4165 SourceLocation NameLoc,
4166 const TemplateArgumentListInfo &Args,
4167 QualType Underlying) const {
4168 assert(!Name.getAsDependentTemplateName() &&
4169 "No dependent template names here!");
4170 QualType TST = getTemplateSpecializationType(Name, Args, Underlying);
4171
4172 TypeSourceInfo *DI = CreateTypeSourceInfo(TST);
4173 TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc TL =
4174 DI->getTypeLoc().castAs<TemplateSpecializationTypeLoc>();
4175 TL.setTemplateKeywordLoc(SourceLocation());
4176 TL.setTemplateNameLoc(NameLoc);
4177 TL.setLAngleLoc(Args.getLAngleLoc());
4178 TL.setRAngleLoc(Args.getRAngleLoc());
4179 for (unsigned i = 0, e = TL.getNumArgs(); i != e; ++i)
4180 TL.setArgLocInfo(i, Args[i].getLocInfo());
4181 return DI;
4182}
4183
4184QualType
4185ASTContext::getTemplateSpecializationType(TemplateName Template,
4186 const TemplateArgumentListInfo &Args,
4187 QualType Underlying) const {
4188 assert(!Template.getAsDependentTemplateName() &&
4189 "No dependent template names here!");
4190
4191 SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 4> ArgVec;
4192 ArgVec.reserve(Args.size());
4193 for (const TemplateArgumentLoc &Arg : Args.arguments())
4194 ArgVec.push_back(Arg.getArgument());
4195
4196 return getTemplateSpecializationType(Template, ArgVec, Underlying);
4197}
4198
4199#ifndef NDEBUG
4200static bool hasAnyPackExpansions(ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) {
4201 for (const TemplateArgument &Arg : Args)
4202 if (Arg.isPackExpansion())
4203 return true;
4204
4205 return true;
4206}
4207#endif
4208
4209QualType
4210ASTContext::getTemplateSpecializationType(TemplateName Template,
4211 ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args,
4212 QualType Underlying) const {
4213 assert(!Template.getAsDependentTemplateName() &&
4214 "No dependent template names here!");
4215 // Look through qualified template names.
4216 if (QualifiedTemplateName *QTN = Template.getAsQualifiedTemplateName())
4217 Template = TemplateName(QTN->getTemplateDecl());
4218
4219 bool IsTypeAlias =
4220 Template.getAsTemplateDecl() &&
4221 isa<TypeAliasTemplateDecl>(Template.getAsTemplateDecl());
4222 QualType CanonType;
4223 if (!Underlying.isNull())
4224 CanonType = getCanonicalType(Underlying);
4225 else {
4226 // We can get here with an alias template when the specialization contains
4227 // a pack expansion that does not match up with a parameter pack.
4228 assert((!IsTypeAlias || hasAnyPackExpansions(Args)) &&
4229 "Caller must compute aliased type");
4230 IsTypeAlias = false;
4231 CanonType = getCanonicalTemplateSpecializationType(Template, Args);
4232 }
4233
4234 // Allocate the (non-canonical) template specialization type, but don't
4235 // try to unique it: these types typically have location information that
4236 // we don't unique and don't want to lose.
4237 void *Mem = Allocate(sizeof(TemplateSpecializationType) +
4238 sizeof(TemplateArgument) * Args.size() +
4239 (IsTypeAlias? sizeof(QualType) : 0),
4240 TypeAlignment);
4241 auto *Spec
4242 = new (Mem) TemplateSpecializationType(Template, Args, CanonType,
4243 IsTypeAlias ? Underlying : QualType());
4244
4245 Types.push_back(Spec);
4246 return QualType(Spec, 0);
4247}
4248
4249QualType ASTContext::getCanonicalTemplateSpecializationType(
4250 TemplateName Template, ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) const {
4251 assert(!Template.getAsDependentTemplateName() &&
4252 "No dependent template names here!");
4253
4254 // Look through qualified template names.
4255 if (QualifiedTemplateName *QTN = Template.getAsQualifiedTemplateName())
4256 Template = TemplateName(QTN->getTemplateDecl());
4257
4258 // Build the canonical template specialization type.
4259 TemplateName CanonTemplate = getCanonicalTemplateName(Template);
4260 SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 4> CanonArgs;
4261 unsigned NumArgs = Args.size();
4262 CanonArgs.reserve(NumArgs);
4263 for (const TemplateArgument &Arg : Args)
4264 CanonArgs.push_back(getCanonicalTemplateArgument(Arg));
4265
4266 // Determine whether this canonical template specialization type already
4267 // exists.
4268 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4269 TemplateSpecializationType::Profile(ID, CanonTemplate,
4270 CanonArgs, *this);
4271
4272 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4273 TemplateSpecializationType *Spec
4274 = TemplateSpecializationTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4275
4276 if (!Spec) {
4277 // Allocate a new canonical template specialization type.
4278 void *Mem = Allocate((sizeof(TemplateSpecializationType) +
4279 sizeof(TemplateArgument) * NumArgs),
4280 TypeAlignment);
4281 Spec = new (Mem) TemplateSpecializationType(CanonTemplate,
4282 CanonArgs,
4283 QualType(), QualType());
4284 Types.push_back(Spec);
4285 TemplateSpecializationTypes.InsertNode(Spec, InsertPos);
4286 }
4287
4288 assert(Spec->isDependentType() &&
4289 "Non-dependent template-id type must have a canonical type");
4290 return QualType(Spec, 0);
4291}
4292
4293QualType ASTContext::getElaboratedType(ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
4294 NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
4295 QualType NamedType,
4296 TagDecl *OwnedTagDecl) const {
4297 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4298 ElaboratedType::Profile(ID, Keyword, NNS, NamedType, OwnedTagDecl);
4299
4300 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4301 ElaboratedType *T = ElaboratedTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4302 if (T)
4303 return QualType(T, 0);
4304
4305 QualType Canon = NamedType;
4306 if (!Canon.isCanonical()) {
4307 Canon = getCanonicalType(NamedType);
4308 ElaboratedType *CheckT = ElaboratedTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4309 assert(!CheckT && "Elaborated canonical type broken");
4310 (void)CheckT;
4311 }
4312
4313 void *Mem = Allocate(ElaboratedType::totalSizeToAlloc<TagDecl *>(!!OwnedTagDecl),
4314 TypeAlignment);
4315 T = new (Mem) ElaboratedType(Keyword, NNS, NamedType, Canon, OwnedTagDecl);
4316
4317 Types.push_back(T);
4318 ElaboratedTypes.InsertNode(T, InsertPos);
4319 return QualType(T, 0);
4320}

4322QualType
4323ASTContext::getParenType(QualType InnerType) const {
4324 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4325 ParenType::Profile(ID, InnerType);
4326
4327 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4328 ParenType *T = ParenTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4329 if (T)
4330 return QualType(T, 0);
4331
4332 QualType Canon = InnerType;
4333 if (!Canon.isCanonical()) {
4334 Canon = getCanonicalType(InnerType);
4335 ParenType *CheckT = ParenTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4336 assert(!CheckT && "Paren canonical type broken");
4337 (void)CheckT;
4338 }
4339
4340 T = new (*this, TypeAlignment) ParenType(InnerType, Canon);
4341 Types.push_back(T);
4342 ParenTypes.InsertNode(T, InsertPos);
4343 return QualType(T, 0);
4344}

4346QualType
4347ASTContext::getMacroQualifiedType(QualType UnderlyingTy,

4351 Canon = getCanonicalType(UnderlyingTy);
4352

4358
4359QualType ASTContext::getDependentNameType(ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
4360 NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
4361 const IdentifierInfo *Name,
4362 QualType Canon) const {
4363 if (Canon.isNull()) {
4364 NestedNameSpecifier *CanonNNS = getCanonicalNestedNameSpecifier(NNS);
4365 if (CanonNNS != NNS)
4366 Canon = getDependentNameType(Keyword, CanonNNS, Name);
4367 }

4370 DependentNameType::Profile(ID, Keyword, NNS, Name);
4371
4372 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4373 DependentNameType *T
4374 = DependentNameTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4375 if (T)
4376 return QualType(T, 0);

4378 T = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentNameType(Keyword, NNS, Name, Canon);
4379 Types.push_back(T);
4380 DependentNameTypes.InsertNode(T, InsertPos);
