4383
4384QualType
4385ASTContext::getDependentTemplateSpecializationType(
4386 ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
4387 NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
4388 const IdentifierInfo *Name,
4389 const TemplateArgumentListInfo &Args) const {
4390 // TODO: avoid this copy
4391 SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 16> ArgCopy;
4392 for (unsigned I = 0, E = Args.size(); I != E; ++I)
4393 ArgCopy.push_back(Args[I].getArgument());
4394 return getDependentTemplateSpecializationType(Keyword, NNS, Name, ArgCopy);
4395}
4396
4397QualType
4398ASTContext::getDependentTemplateSpecializationType(
4399 ElaboratedTypeKeyword Keyword,
4400 NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
4401 const IdentifierInfo *Name,
4402 ArrayRef<TemplateArgument> Args) const {
4403 assert((!NNS || NNS->isDependent()) &&
4404 "nested-name-specifier must be dependent");
4405
4406 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4407 DependentTemplateSpecializationType::Profile(ID, *this, Keyword, NNS,
4408 Name, Args);
4409
4410 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4411 DependentTemplateSpecializationType *T
4412 = DependentTemplateSpecializationTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4413 if (T)
4414 return QualType(T, 0);
4415
4416 NestedNameSpecifier *CanonNNS = getCanonicalNestedNameSpecifier(NNS);
4417
4418 ElaboratedTypeKeyword CanonKeyword = Keyword;
4419 if (Keyword == ETK_None) CanonKeyword = ETK_Typename;
4420
4421 bool AnyNonCanonArgs = false;
4422 unsigned NumArgs = Args.size();
4423 SmallVector<TemplateArgument, 16> CanonArgs(NumArgs);
4424 for (unsigned I = 0; I != NumArgs; ++I) {
4425 CanonArgs[I] = getCanonicalTemplateArgument(Args[I]);
4426 if (!CanonArgs[I].structurallyEquals(Args[I]))
4427 AnyNonCanonArgs = true;
4428 }
4429
4430 QualType Canon;
4431 if (AnyNonCanonArgs || CanonNNS != NNS || CanonKeyword != Keyword) {
4432 Canon = getDependentTemplateSpecializationType(CanonKeyword, CanonNNS,
4433 Name,
4434 CanonArgs);
4435
4436 // Find the insert position again.
4437 DependentTemplateSpecializationTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4438 }
4439
4440 void *Mem = Allocate((sizeof(DependentTemplateSpecializationType) +
4441 sizeof(TemplateArgument) * NumArgs),
4442 TypeAlignment);
4443 T = new (Mem) DependentTemplateSpecializationType(Keyword, NNS,
4444 Name, Args, Canon);
4445 Types.push_back(T);
4446 DependentTemplateSpecializationTypes.InsertNode(T, InsertPos);
4447 return QualType(T, 0);
4448}
4449
4450TemplateArgument ASTContext::getInjectedTemplateArg(NamedDecl *Param) {
4451 TemplateArgument Arg;
4452 if (const auto *TTP = dyn_cast<TemplateTypeParmDecl>(Param)) {
4453 QualType ArgType = getTypeDeclType(TTP);
4454 if (TTP->isParameterPack())
4455 ArgType = getPackExpansionType(ArgType, None);
4456
4457 Arg = TemplateArgument(ArgType);
4458 } else if (auto *NTTP = dyn_cast<NonTypeTemplateParmDecl>(Param)) {
4459 Expr *E = new (*this) DeclRefExpr(
4460 *this, NTTP, /*enclosing*/ false,
4461 NTTP->getType().getNonLValueExprType(*this),
4462 Expr::getValueKindForType(NTTP->getType()), NTTP->getLocation());
4463
4464 if (NTTP->isParameterPack())
4465 E = new (*this) PackExpansionExpr(DependentTy, E, NTTP->getLocation(),
4466 None);
4467 Arg = TemplateArgument(E);
4468 } else {
4469 auto *TTP = cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Param);
4470 if (TTP->isParameterPack())
4471 Arg = TemplateArgument(TemplateName(TTP), Optional<unsigned>());
4472 else
4473 Arg = TemplateArgument(TemplateName(TTP));
4474 }
4475
4476 if (Param->isTemplateParameterPack())
4477 Arg = TemplateArgument::CreatePackCopy(*this, Arg);
4478
4479 return Arg;
4480}
4481
4482void
4483ASTContext::getInjectedTemplateArgs(const TemplateParameterList *Params,
4484 SmallVectorImpl<TemplateArgument> &Args) {
4485 Args.reserve(Args.size() + Params->size());
4486
4487 for (NamedDecl *Param : *Params)
4488 Args.push_back(getInjectedTemplateArg(Param));
4489}
4490
4491QualType ASTContext::getPackExpansionType(QualType Pattern,
4492 Optional<unsigned> NumExpansions) {
4493 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4494 PackExpansionType::Profile(ID, Pattern, NumExpansions);
4495
4496 // A deduced type can deduce to a pack, eg
4497 // auto ...x = some_pack;
4498 // That declaration isn't (yet) valid, but is created as part of building an
4499 // init-capture pack:
4500 // [...x = some_pack] {}
4501 assert((Pattern->containsUnexpandedParameterPack() ||
4502 Pattern->getContainedDeducedType()) &&
4503 "Pack expansions must expand one or more parameter packs");
4504 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4505 PackExpansionType *T
4506 = PackExpansionTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4507 if (T)
4508 return QualType(T, 0);
4509
4510 QualType Canon;
4511 if (!Pattern.isCanonical()) {
4512 Canon = getCanonicalType(Pattern);
4513 // The canonical type might not contain an unexpanded parameter pack, if it
4514 // contains an alias template specialization which ignores one of its
4515 // parameters.
4516 if (Canon->containsUnexpandedParameterPack()) {
4517 Canon = getPackExpansionType(Canon, NumExpansions);
4518
4519 // Find the insert position again, in case we inserted an element into
4520 // PackExpansionTypes and invalidated our insert position.
4521 PackExpansionTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4522 }
4523 }
4524
4525 T = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4526 PackExpansionType(Pattern, Canon, NumExpansions);
4527 Types.push_back(T);
4528 PackExpansionTypes.InsertNode(T, InsertPos);
4529 return QualType(T, 0);
4530}
4531
4532/// CmpProtocolNames - Comparison predicate for sorting protocols
4533/// alphabetically.
4534static int CmpProtocolNames(ObjCProtocolDecl *const *LHS,
4535 ObjCProtocolDecl *const *RHS) {
4536 return DeclarationName::compare((*LHS)->getDeclName(), (*RHS)->getDeclName());
4537}
4538
4539static bool areSortedAndUniqued(ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> Protocols) {
4540 if (Protocols.empty()) return true;
4541
4542 if (Protocols[0]->getCanonicalDecl() != Protocols[0])
4543 return false;
4544
4545 for (unsigned i = 1; i != Protocols.size(); ++i)
4546 if (CmpProtocolNames(&Protocols[i - 1], &Protocols[i]) >= 0 ||
4547 Protocols[i]->getCanonicalDecl() != Protocols[i])
4548 return false;
4549 return true;
4550}
4551
4552static void
4553SortAndUniqueProtocols(SmallVectorImpl<ObjCProtocolDecl *> &Protocols) {
4554 // Sort protocols, keyed by name.
4555 llvm::array_pod_sort(Protocols.begin(), Protocols.end(), CmpProtocolNames);
4556
4557 // Canonicalize.
4558 for (ObjCProtocolDecl *&P : Protocols)
4559 P = P->getCanonicalDecl();
4560
4561 // Remove duplicates.
4562 auto ProtocolsEnd = std::unique(Protocols.begin(), Protocols.end());
4563 Protocols.erase(ProtocolsEnd, Protocols.end());
4564}
4565
4566QualType ASTContext::getObjCObjectType(QualType BaseType,
4567 ObjCProtocolDecl * const *Protocols,
4568 unsigned NumProtocols) const {
4569 return getObjCObjectType(BaseType, {},
4570 llvm::makeArrayRef(Protocols, NumProtocols),
4571 /*isKindOf=*/false);
4572}
4573
4574QualType ASTContext::getObjCObjectType(
4575 QualType baseType,
4576 ArrayRef<QualType> typeArgs,
4577 ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> protocols,
4578 bool isKindOf) const {
4579 // If the base type is an interface and there aren't any protocols or
4580 // type arguments to add, then the interface type will do just fine.
4581 if (typeArgs.empty() && protocols.empty() && !isKindOf &&
4582 isa<ObjCInterfaceType>(baseType))
4583 return baseType;
4584
4585 // Look in the folding set for an existing type.
4586 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4587 ObjCObjectTypeImpl::Profile(ID, baseType, typeArgs, protocols, isKindOf);
4588 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4589 if (ObjCObjectType *QT = ObjCObjectTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
4590 return QualType(QT, 0);
4591
4592 // Determine the type arguments to be used for canonicalization,
4593 // which may be explicitly specified here or written on the base
4594 // type.
4595 ArrayRef<QualType> effectiveTypeArgs = typeArgs;
4596 if (effectiveTypeArgs.empty()) {
4597 if (const auto *baseObject = baseType->getAs<ObjCObjectType>())
4598 effectiveTypeArgs = baseObject->getTypeArgs();
4599 }
4600
4601 // Build the canonical type, which has the canonical base type and a
4602 // sorted-and-uniqued list of protocols and the type arguments
4603 // canonicalized.
4604 QualType canonical;
4605 bool typeArgsAreCanonical = std::all_of(effectiveTypeArgs.begin(),
4606 effectiveTypeArgs.end(),
4607 [&](QualType type) {
4608 return type.isCanonical();
4609 });
4610 bool protocolsSorted = areSortedAndUniqued(protocols);
4611 if (!typeArgsAreCanonical || !protocolsSorted || !baseType.isCanonical()) {
4612 // Determine the canonical type arguments.
4613 ArrayRef<QualType> canonTypeArgs;
4614 SmallVector<QualType, 4> canonTypeArgsVec;
4615 if (!typeArgsAreCanonical) {
4616 canonTypeArgsVec.reserve(effectiveTypeArgs.size());
4617 for (auto typeArg : effectiveTypeArgs)
4618 canonTypeArgsVec.push_back(getCanonicalType(typeArg));
4619 canonTypeArgs = canonTypeArgsVec;
4620 } else {
4621 canonTypeArgs = effectiveTypeArgs;
4622 }
4623
4624 ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> canonProtocols;
4625 SmallVector<ObjCProtocolDecl*, 8> canonProtocolsVec;
4626 if (!protocolsSorted) {
4627 canonProtocolsVec.append(protocols.begin(), protocols.end());
4628 SortAndUniqueProtocols(canonProtocolsVec);
4629 canonProtocols = canonProtocolsVec;
4630 } else {
4631 canonProtocols = protocols;
4632 }
4633
4634 canonical = getObjCObjectType(getCanonicalType(baseType), canonTypeArgs,
4635 canonProtocols, isKindOf);
4636
4637 // Regenerate InsertPos.
4638 ObjCObjectTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4639 }
4640
4641 unsigned size = sizeof(ObjCObjectTypeImpl);
4642 size += typeArgs.size() * sizeof(QualType);
4643 size += protocols.size() * sizeof(ObjCProtocolDecl *);
4644 void *mem = Allocate(size, TypeAlignment);
4645 auto *T =
4646 new (mem) ObjCObjectTypeImpl(canonical, baseType, typeArgs, protocols,
4647 isKindOf);
4648
4649 Types.push_back(T);
4650 ObjCObjectTypes.InsertNode(T, InsertPos);
4651 return QualType(T, 0);
4652}
4653
4654/// Apply Objective-C protocol qualifiers to the given type.
4655/// If this is for the canonical type of a type parameter, we can apply
4656/// protocol qualifiers on the ObjCObjectPointerType.
4657QualType
4658ASTContext::applyObjCProtocolQualifiers(QualType type,
4659 ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> protocols, bool &hasError,
4660 bool allowOnPointerType) const {
4661 hasError = false;
4662
4663 if (const auto *objT = dyn_cast<ObjCTypeParamType>(type.getTypePtr())) {
4664 return getObjCTypeParamType(objT->getDecl(), protocols);
4665 }
4666
4667 // Apply protocol qualifiers to ObjCObjectPointerType.
4668 if (allowOnPointerType) {
4669 if (const auto *objPtr =
4670 dyn_cast<ObjCObjectPointerType>(type.getTypePtr())) {
4671 const ObjCObjectType *objT = objPtr->getObjectType();
4672 // Merge protocol lists and construct ObjCObjectType.
4673 SmallVector<ObjCProtocolDecl*, 8> protocolsVec;
4674 protocolsVec.append(objT->qual_begin(),
4675 objT->qual_end());
4676 protocolsVec.append(protocols.begin(), protocols.end());
4677 ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> protocols = protocolsVec;
4678 type = getObjCObjectType(
4679 objT->getBaseType(),
4680 objT->getTypeArgsAsWritten(),
4681 protocols,
4682 objT->isKindOfTypeAsWritten());
4683 return getObjCObjectPointerType(type);
4684 }
4685 }
4686
4687 // Apply protocol qualifiers to ObjCObjectType.
4688 if (const auto *objT = dyn_cast<ObjCObjectType>(type.getTypePtr())){
4689 // FIXME: Check for protocols to which the class type is already
4690 // known to conform.
4691
4692 return getObjCObjectType(objT->getBaseType(),
4693 objT->getTypeArgsAsWritten(),
4694 protocols,
4695 objT->isKindOfTypeAsWritten());
4696 }
4697
4698 // If the canonical type is ObjCObjectType, ...
4699 if (type->isObjCObjectType()) {
4700 // Silently overwrite any existing protocol qualifiers.
4701 // TODO: determine whether that's the right thing to do.
4702
4703 // FIXME: Check for protocols to which the class type is already
4704 // known to conform.
4705 return getObjCObjectType(type, {}, protocols, false);
4706 }
4707
4708 // id<protocol-list>
4709 if (type->isObjCIdType()) {
4710 const auto *objPtr = type->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
4711 type = getObjCObjectType(ObjCBuiltinIdTy, {}, protocols,
4712 objPtr->isKindOfType());
4713 return getObjCObjectPointerType(type);
4714 }
4715
4716 // Class<protocol-list>
4717 if (type->isObjCClassType()) {
4718 const auto *objPtr = type->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
4719 type = getObjCObjectType(ObjCBuiltinClassTy, {}, protocols,
4720 objPtr->isKindOfType());
4721 return getObjCObjectPointerType(type);
4722 }
4723
4724 hasError = true;
4725 return type;
4726}
4727
4728QualType
4729ASTContext::getObjCTypeParamType(const ObjCTypeParamDecl *Decl,
4730 ArrayRef<ObjCProtocolDecl *> protocols,
4731 QualType Canonical) const {
4732 // Look in the folding set for an existing type.
4733 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4734 ObjCTypeParamType::Profile(ID, Decl, protocols);
4735 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4736 if (ObjCTypeParamType *TypeParam =
4737 ObjCTypeParamTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
4738 return QualType(TypeParam, 0);
4739
4740 if (Canonical.isNull()) {
4741 // We canonicalize to the underlying type.
4742 Canonical = getCanonicalType(Decl->getUnderlyingType());
4743 if (!protocols.empty()) {
4744 // Apply the protocol qualifers.
4745 bool hasError;
4746 Canonical = getCanonicalType(applyObjCProtocolQualifiers(
4747 Canonical, protocols, hasError, true /*allowOnPointerType*/));
4748 assert(!hasError && "Error when apply protocol qualifier to bound type");
4749 }
4750 }
4751
4752 unsigned size = sizeof(ObjCTypeParamType);
4753 size += protocols.size() * sizeof(ObjCProtocolDecl *);
4754 void *mem = Allocate(size, TypeAlignment);
4755 auto *newType = new (mem) ObjCTypeParamType(Decl, Canonical, protocols);
4756
4757 Types.push_back(newType);
4758 ObjCTypeParamTypes.InsertNode(newType, InsertPos);
4759 return QualType(newType, 0);
4760}
4761
4762/// ObjCObjectAdoptsQTypeProtocols - Checks that protocols in IC's
4763/// protocol list adopt all protocols in QT's qualified-id protocol
4764/// list.
4765bool ASTContext::ObjCObjectAdoptsQTypeProtocols(QualType QT,
4766 ObjCInterfaceDecl *IC) {
4767 if (!QT->isObjCQualifiedIdType())
4768 return false;
4769
4770 if (const auto *OPT = QT->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()) {
4771 // If both the right and left sides have qualifiers.
4772 for (auto *Proto : OPT->quals()) {
4773 if (!IC->ClassImplementsProtocol(Proto, false))
4774 return false;
4775 }
4776 return true;
4777 }
4778 return false;
4779}
4780
4781/// QIdProtocolsAdoptObjCObjectProtocols - Checks that protocols in
4782/// QT's qualified-id protocol list adopt all protocols in IDecl's list
4783/// of protocols.
4784bool ASTContext::QIdProtocolsAdoptObjCObjectProtocols(QualType QT,
4785 ObjCInterfaceDecl *IDecl) {
4786 if (!QT->isObjCQualifiedIdType())
4787 return false;
4788 const auto *OPT = QT->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
4789 if (!OPT)
4790 return false;
4791 if (!IDecl->hasDefinition())
4792 return false;
4793 llvm::SmallPtrSet<ObjCProtocolDecl *, 8> InheritedProtocols;
4794 CollectInheritedProtocols(IDecl, InheritedProtocols);
4795 if (InheritedProtocols.empty())
4796 return false;
4797 // Check that if every protocol in list of id<plist> conforms to a protocol
4798 // of IDecl's, then bridge casting is ok.
4799 bool Conforms = false;
4800 for (auto *Proto : OPT->quals()) {
4801 Conforms = false;
4802 for (auto *PI : InheritedProtocols) {
4803 if (ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(Proto, PI)) {
4804 Conforms = true;
4805 break;
4806 }
4807 }
4808 if (!Conforms)
4809 break;
4810 }
4811 if (Conforms)
4812 return true;
4813
4814 for (auto *PI : InheritedProtocols) {
4815 // If both the right and left sides have qualifiers.
4816 bool Adopts = false;
4817 for (auto *Proto : OPT->quals()) {
4818 // return 'true' if 'PI' is in the inheritance hierarchy of Proto
4819 if ((Adopts = ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(PI, Proto)))
4820 break;
4821 }
4822 if (!Adopts)
4823 return false;
4824 }
4825 return true;
4826}
4827
4828/// getObjCObjectPointerType - Return a ObjCObjectPointerType type for
4829/// the given object type.
4830QualType ASTContext::getObjCObjectPointerType(QualType ObjectT) const {
4831 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4832 ObjCObjectPointerType::Profile(ID, ObjectT);
4833
4834 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4835 if (ObjCObjectPointerType *QT =
4836 ObjCObjectPointerTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
4837 return QualType(QT, 0);
4838
4839 // Find the canonical object type.
4840 QualType Canonical;
4841 if (!ObjectT.isCanonical()) {
4842 Canonical = getObjCObjectPointerType(getCanonicalType(ObjectT));
4843
4844 // Regenerate InsertPos.
4845 ObjCObjectPointerTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4846 }
4847
4848 // No match.
4849 void *Mem = Allocate(sizeof(ObjCObjectPointerType), TypeAlignment);
4850 auto *QType =
4851 new (Mem) ObjCObjectPointerType(Canonical, ObjectT);
4852
4853 Types.push_back(QType);
4854 ObjCObjectPointerTypes.InsertNode(QType, InsertPos);
4855 return QualType(QType, 0);
4856}
4857
4858/// getObjCInterfaceType - Return the unique reference to the type for the
4859/// specified ObjC interface decl. The list of protocols is optional.
4860QualType ASTContext::getObjCInterfaceType(const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Decl,
4861 ObjCInterfaceDecl *PrevDecl) const {
4862 if (Decl->TypeForDecl)
4863 return QualType(Decl->TypeForDecl, 0);
4864
4865 if (PrevDecl) {
4866 assert(PrevDecl->TypeForDecl && "previous decl has no TypeForDecl");
4867 Decl->TypeForDecl = PrevDecl->TypeForDecl;
4868 return QualType(PrevDecl->TypeForDecl, 0);
4869 }
4870
4871 // Prefer the definition, if there is one.
4872 if (const ObjCInterfaceDecl *Def = Decl->getDefinition())
4873 Decl = Def;
4874
4875 void *Mem = Allocate(sizeof(ObjCInterfaceType), TypeAlignment);
4876 auto *T = new (Mem) ObjCInterfaceType(Decl);
4877 Decl->TypeForDecl = T;
4878 Types.push_back(T);
4879 return QualType(T, 0);
4880}
4881
4882/// getTypeOfExprType - Unlike many "get<Type>" functions, we can't unique
4883/// TypeOfExprType AST's (since expression's are never shared). For example,
4884/// multiple declarations that refer to "typeof(x)" all contain different
4885/// DeclRefExpr's. This doesn't effect the type checker, since it operates
4886/// on canonical type's (which are always unique).
4887QualType ASTContext::getTypeOfExprType(Expr *tofExpr) const {
4888 TypeOfExprType *toe;
4889 if (tofExpr->isTypeDependent()) {
4890 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4891 DependentTypeOfExprType::Profile(ID, *this, tofExpr);
4892
4893 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4894 DependentTypeOfExprType *Canon
4895 = DependentTypeOfExprTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4896 if (Canon) {
4897 // We already have a "canonical" version of an identical, dependent
4898 // typeof(expr) type. Use that as our canonical type.
4899 toe = new (*this, TypeAlignment) TypeOfExprType(tofExpr,
4900 QualType((TypeOfExprType*)Canon, 0));
4901 } else {
4902 // Build a new, canonical typeof(expr) type.
4903 Canon
4904 = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentTypeOfExprType(*this, tofExpr);
4905 DependentTypeOfExprTypes.InsertNode(Canon, InsertPos);
4906 toe = Canon;
4907 }
4908 } else {
4909 QualType Canonical = getCanonicalType(tofExpr->getType());
4910 toe = new (*this, TypeAlignment) TypeOfExprType(tofExpr, Canonical);
4911 }
4912 Types.push_back(toe);
4913 return QualType(toe, 0);
4914}
4915
4916/// getTypeOfType - Unlike many "get<Type>" functions, we don't unique
4917/// TypeOfType nodes. The only motivation to unique these nodes would be
4918/// memory savings. Since typeof(t) is fairly uncommon, space shouldn't be
4919/// an issue. This doesn't affect the type checker, since it operates
4920/// on canonical types (which are always unique).
4921QualType ASTContext::getTypeOfType(QualType tofType) const {
4922 QualType Canonical = getCanonicalType(tofType);
4923 auto *tot = new (*this, TypeAlignment) TypeOfType(tofType, Canonical);
4924 Types.push_back(tot);
4925 return QualType(tot, 0);
4926}
4927
4928/// Unlike many "get<Type>" functions, we don't unique DecltypeType
4929/// nodes. This would never be helpful, since each such type has its own
4930/// expression, and would not give a significant memory saving, since there
4931/// is an Expr tree under each such type.
4932QualType ASTContext::getDecltypeType(Expr *e, QualType UnderlyingType) const {
4933 DecltypeType *dt;
4934
4935 // C++11 [temp.type]p2:
4936 // If an expression e involves a template parameter, decltype(e) denotes a
4937 // unique dependent type. Two such decltype-specifiers refer to the same
4938 // type only if their expressions are equivalent (14.5.6.1).
4939 if (e->isInstantiationDependent()) {
4940 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4941 DependentDecltypeType::Profile(ID, *this, e);
4942
4943 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4944 DependentDecltypeType *Canon
4945 = DependentDecltypeTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4946 if (!Canon) {
4947 // Build a new, canonical decltype(expr) type.
4948 Canon = new (*this, TypeAlignment) DependentDecltypeType(*this, e);
4949 DependentDecltypeTypes.InsertNode(Canon, InsertPos);
4950 }
4951 dt = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4952 DecltypeType(e, UnderlyingType, QualType((DecltypeType *)Canon, 0));
4953 } else {
4954 dt = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4955 DecltypeType(e, UnderlyingType, getCanonicalType(UnderlyingType));
4956 }
4957 Types.push_back(dt);
4958 return QualType(dt, 0);
4959}
4960
4961/// getUnaryTransformationType - We don't unique these, since the memory
4962/// savings are minimal and these are rare.
4963QualType ASTContext::getUnaryTransformType(QualType BaseType,
4964 QualType UnderlyingType,
4965 UnaryTransformType::UTTKind Kind)
4966 const {
4967 UnaryTransformType *ut = nullptr;
4968
4969 if (BaseType->isDependentType()) {
4970 // Look in the folding set for an existing type.
4971 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
4972 DependentUnaryTransformType::Profile(ID, getCanonicalType(BaseType), Kind);
4973
4974 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
4975 DependentUnaryTransformType *Canon
4976 = DependentUnaryTransformTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
4977
4978 if (!Canon) {
4979 // Build a new, canonical __underlying_type(type) type.
4980 Canon = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
4981 DependentUnaryTransformType(*this, getCanonicalType(BaseType),
4982 Kind);
4983 DependentUnaryTransformTypes.InsertNode(Canon, InsertPos);
4984 }
4985 ut = new (*this, TypeAlignment) UnaryTransformType (BaseType,
4986 QualType(), Kind,
4987 QualType(Canon, 0));
4988 } else {
4989 QualType CanonType = getCanonicalType(UnderlyingType);
4990 ut = new (*this, TypeAlignment) UnaryTransformType (BaseType,
4991 UnderlyingType, Kind,
4992 CanonType);
4993 }
4994 Types.push_back(ut);
4995 return QualType(ut, 0);
4996}
4997
4998/// getAutoType - Return the uniqued reference to the 'auto' type which has been
4999/// deduced to the given type, or to the canonical undeduced 'auto' type, or the
5000/// canonical deduced-but-dependent 'auto' type.
5001QualType ASTContext::getAutoType(QualType DeducedType, AutoTypeKeyword Keyword,
5002 bool IsDependent, bool IsPack) const {
5003 assert((!IsPack || IsDependent) && "only use IsPack for a dependent pack");
5004 if (DeducedType.isNull() && Keyword == AutoTypeKeyword::Auto && !IsDependent)
5005 return getAutoDeductType();
5006
5007 // Look in the folding set for an existing type.
5008 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5009 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5010 AutoType::Profile(ID, DeducedType, Keyword, IsDependent, IsPack);
5011 if (AutoType *AT = AutoTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
5012 return QualType(AT, 0);
5013
5014 auto *AT = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
5015 AutoType(DeducedType, Keyword, IsDependent, IsPack);
5016 Types.push_back(AT);
5017 if (InsertPos)
5018 AutoTypes.InsertNode(AT, InsertPos);
5019 return QualType(AT, 0);
5020}
5021
5022/// Return the uniqued reference to the deduced template specialization type
5023/// which has been deduced to the given type, or to the canonical undeduced
5024/// such type, or the canonical deduced-but-dependent such type.
5025QualType ASTContext::getDeducedTemplateSpecializationType(
5026 TemplateName Template, QualType DeducedType, bool IsDependent) const {
5027 // Look in the folding set for an existing type.
5028 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5029 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5030 DeducedTemplateSpecializationType::Profile(ID, Template, DeducedType,
5031 IsDependent);
5032 if (DeducedTemplateSpecializationType *DTST =
5033 DeducedTemplateSpecializationTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
5034 return QualType(DTST, 0);
5035
5036 auto *DTST = new (*this, TypeAlignment)
5037 DeducedTemplateSpecializationType(Template, DeducedType, IsDependent);
5038 Types.push_back(DTST);
5039 if (InsertPos)
5040 DeducedTemplateSpecializationTypes.InsertNode(DTST, InsertPos);
5041 return QualType(DTST, 0);
5042}
5043
5044/// getAtomicType - Return the uniqued reference to the atomic type for
5045/// the given value type.
5046QualType ASTContext::getAtomicType(QualType T) const {
5047 // Unique pointers, to guarantee there is only one pointer of a particular
5048 // structure.
5049 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
5050 AtomicType::Profile(ID, T);
5051
5052 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
5053 if (AtomicType *AT = AtomicTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos))
5054 return QualType(AT, 0);
5055
5056 // If the atomic value type isn't canonical, this won't be a canonical type
5057 // either, so fill in the canonical type field.
5058 QualType Canonical;
5059 if (!T.isCanonical()) {
5060 Canonical = getAtomicType(getCanonicalType(T));
5061
5062 // Get the new insert position for the node we care about.
5063 AtomicType *NewIP = AtomicTypes.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
5064 assert(!NewIP && "Shouldn't be in the map!"); (void)NewIP;
5065 }
5066 auto *New = new (*this, TypeAlignment) AtomicType(T, Canonical);
5067 Types.push_back(New);
5068 AtomicTypes.InsertNode(New, InsertPos);
5069 return QualType(New, 0);
5070}

5074 if (AutoDeductTy.isNull())
5075 AutoDeductTy = QualType(
5076 new (*this, TypeAlignment) AutoType(QualType(), AutoTypeKeyword::Auto,
5077 /*dependent*/false, /*pack*/false),
5078 0);
5079 return AutoDeductTy;
5080}

5163//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5164// Type Operators
5165//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5166
5167CanQualType ASTContext::getCanonicalParamType(QualType T) const {
5168 // Push qualifiers into arrays, and then discard any remaining
5169 // qualifiers.
5170 T = getCanonicalType(T);
5171 T = getVariableArrayDecayedType(T);
5172 const Type *Ty = T.getTypePtr();
5173 QualType Result;
5174 if (isa<ArrayType>(Ty)) {
5175 Result = getArrayDecayedType(QualType(Ty,0));
5176 } else if (isa<FunctionType>(Ty)) {
5177 Result = getPointerType(QualType(Ty, 0));
5178 } else {
5179 Result = QualType(Ty, 0);
5180 }
5181
5182 return CanQualType::CreateUnsafe(Result);
5183}
5184
5185QualType ASTContext::getUnqualifiedArrayType(QualType type,
5186 Qualifiers &quals) {
5187 SplitQualType splitType = type.getSplitUnqualifiedType();
5188
5189 // FIXME: getSplitUnqualifiedType() actually walks all the way to
5190 // the unqualified desugared type and then drops it on the floor.
5191 // We then have to strip that sugar back off with
5192 // getUnqualifiedDesugaredType(), which is silly.
5193 const auto *AT =
5194 dyn_cast<ArrayType>(splitType.Ty->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType());
5195
5196 // If we don't have an array, just use the results in splitType.
5197 if (!AT) {
5198 quals = splitType.Quals;
5199 return QualType(splitType.Ty, 0);
5200 }
5201
5202 // Otherwise, recurse on the array's element type.
5203 QualType elementType = AT->getElementType();
5204 QualType unqualElementType = getUnqualifiedArrayType(elementType, quals);
5205
5206 // If that didn't change the element type, AT has no qualifiers, so we
5207 // can just use the results in splitType.
5208 if (elementType == unqualElementType) {
5209 assert(quals.empty()); // from the recursive call
5210 quals = splitType.Quals;
5211 return QualType(splitType.Ty, 0);
5212 }
5213
5214 // Otherwise, add in the qualifiers from the outermost type, then
5215 // build the type back up.
5216 quals.addConsistentQualifiers(splitType.Quals);
5217
5218 if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT)) {
5219 return getConstantArrayType(unqualElementType, CAT->getSize(),
5220 CAT->getSizeModifier(), 0);
5221 }
5222
5223 if (const auto *IAT = dyn_cast<IncompleteArrayType>(AT)) {
5224 return getIncompleteArrayType(unqualElementType, IAT->getSizeModifier(), 0);
5225 }
5226
5227 if (const auto *VAT = dyn_cast<VariableArrayType>(AT)) {
5228 return getVariableArrayType(unqualElementType,
5229 VAT->getSizeExpr(),
5230 VAT->getSizeModifier(),
5231 VAT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
5232 VAT->getBracketsRange());
5233 }
5234
5235 const auto *DSAT = cast<DependentSizedArrayType>(AT);
5236 return getDependentSizedArrayType(unqualElementType, DSAT->getSizeExpr(),
5237 DSAT->getSizeModifier(), 0,
5238 SourceRange());
5239}
5240
5241/// Attempt to unwrap two types that may both be array types with the same bound
5242/// (or both be array types of unknown bound) for the purpose of comparing the
5243/// cv-decomposition of two types per C++ [conv.qual].
5244bool ASTContext::UnwrapSimilarArrayTypes(QualType &T1, QualType &T2) {
5245 bool UnwrappedAny = false;
5246 while (true) {
5247 auto *AT1 = getAsArrayType(T1);
5248 if (!AT1) return UnwrappedAny;
5249
5250 auto *AT2 = getAsArrayType(T2);
5251 if (!AT2) return UnwrappedAny;
5252
5253 // If we don't have two array types with the same constant bound nor two
5254 // incomplete array types, we've unwrapped everything we can.
5255 if (auto *CAT1 = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT1)) {
5256 auto *CAT2 = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT2);
5257 if (!CAT2 || CAT1->getSize() != CAT2->getSize())
5258 return UnwrappedAny;
5259 } else if (!isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT1) ||
5260 !isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT2)) {
5261 return UnwrappedAny;
5262 }
5263
5264 T1 = AT1->getElementType();
5265 T2 = AT2->getElementType();
5266 UnwrappedAny = true;
5267 }
5268}
5269
5270/// Attempt to unwrap two types that may be similar (C++ [conv.qual]).
5271///
5272/// If T1 and T2 are both pointer types of the same kind, or both array types
5273/// with the same bound, unwraps layers from T1 and T2 until a pointer type is
5274/// unwrapped. Top-level qualifiers on T1 and T2 are ignored.
5275///
5276/// This function will typically be called in a loop that successively
5277/// "unwraps" pointer and pointer-to-member types to compare them at each
5278/// level.
5279///
5280/// \return \c true if a pointer type was unwrapped, \c false if we reached a
5281/// pair of types that can't be unwrapped further.
5282bool ASTContext::UnwrapSimilarTypes(QualType &T1, QualType &T2) {
5283 UnwrapSimilarArrayTypes(T1, T2);
5284
5285 const auto *T1PtrType = T1->getAs<PointerType>();
5286 const auto *T2PtrType = T2->getAs<PointerType>();
5287 if (T1PtrType && T2PtrType) {
5288 T1 = T1PtrType->getPointeeType();
5289 T2 = T2PtrType->getPointeeType();
5290 return true;
5291 }
5292
5293 const auto *T1MPType = T1->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
5294 const auto *T2MPType = T2->getAs<MemberPointerType>();
5295 if (T1MPType && T2MPType &&
5296 hasSameUnqualifiedType(QualType(T1MPType->getClass(), 0),
5297 QualType(T2MPType->getClass(), 0))) {
5298 T1 = T1MPType->getPointeeType();
5299 T2 = T2MPType->getPointeeType();
5300 return true;
5301 }
5302
5303 if (getLangOpts().ObjC) {
5304 const auto *T1OPType = T1->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
5305 const auto *T2OPType = T2->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
5306 if (T1OPType && T2OPType) {
5307 T1 = T1OPType->getPointeeType();
5308 T2 = T2OPType->getPointeeType();
5309 return true;
5310 }
5311 }
5312
5313 // FIXME: Block pointers, too?
5314
5315 return false;
5316}
5317
5318bool ASTContext::hasSimilarType(QualType T1, QualType T2) {
5319 while (true) {
5320 Qualifiers Quals;
5321 T1 = getUnqualifiedArrayType(T1, Quals);
5322 T2 = getUnqualifiedArrayType(T2, Quals);
5323 if (hasSameType(T1, T2))
5324 return true;
5325 if (!UnwrapSimilarTypes(T1, T2))
5326 return false;
5327 }
5328}
5329
5330bool ASTContext::hasCvrSimilarType(QualType T1, QualType T2) {
5331 while (true) {
5332 Qualifiers Quals1, Quals2;
5333 T1 = getUnqualifiedArrayType(T1, Quals1);
5334 T2 = getUnqualifiedArrayType(T2, Quals2);
5335
5336 Quals1.removeCVRQualifiers();
5337 Quals2.removeCVRQualifiers();
5338 if (Quals1 != Quals2)
5339 return false;
5340
5341 // We also need to check if the capability qualifier matches since otherwise
5342 // we return true for `int*__capability*` and `int**` and then generate
5343 // CK_NoOp casts that will crash during CodeGen
5344 if (T1->isCHERICapabilityType(*this, false) !=
5345 T2->isCHERICapabilityType(*this, false)) {
5346 return false;
5347 }
5348
5349 if (hasSameType(T1, T2))
5350 return true;
5351
5352 if (!UnwrapSimilarTypes(T1, T2))
5353 return false;
5354 }
5355}
5356
5357DeclarationNameInfo
5358ASTContext::getNameForTemplate(TemplateName Name,
5359 SourceLocation NameLoc) const {
5360 switch (Name.getKind()) {
5361 case TemplateName::QualifiedTemplate:
5362 case TemplateName::Template:
5363 // DNInfo work in progress: CHECKME: what about DNLoc?
5364 return DeclarationNameInfo(Name.getAsTemplateDecl()->getDeclName(),
5365 NameLoc);
5366
5367 case TemplateName::OverloadedTemplate: {
5368 OverloadedTemplateStorage *Storage = Name.getAsOverloadedTemplate();
5369 // DNInfo work in progress: CHECKME: what about DNLoc?
5370 return DeclarationNameInfo((*Storage->begin())->getDeclName(), NameLoc);
5371 }
5372
5373 case TemplateName::AssumedTemplate: {
5374 AssumedTemplateStorage *Storage = Name.getAsAssumedTemplateName();
5375 return DeclarationNameInfo(Storage->getDeclName(), NameLoc);
5376 }
5377
5378 case TemplateName::DependentTemplate: {
5379 DependentTemplateName *DTN = Name.getAsDependentTemplateName();
5380 DeclarationName DName;
5381 if (DTN->isIdentifier()) {
5382 DName = DeclarationNames.getIdentifier(DTN->getIdentifier());
5383 return DeclarationNameInfo(DName, NameLoc);
5384 } else {
5385 DName = DeclarationNames.getCXXOperatorName(DTN->getOperator());
5386 // DNInfo work in progress: FIXME: source locations?
5387 DeclarationNameLoc DNLoc;
5388 DNLoc.CXXOperatorName.BeginOpNameLoc = SourceLocation().getRawEncoding();
5389 DNLoc.CXXOperatorName.EndOpNameLoc = SourceLocation().getRawEncoding();
5390 return DeclarationNameInfo(DName, NameLoc, DNLoc);
5391 }
5392 }
5393
5394 case TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParm: {
5395 SubstTemplateTemplateParmStorage *subst
5396 = Name.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParm();
5397 return DeclarationNameInfo(subst->getParameter()->getDeclName(),
5398 NameLoc);
5399 }
5400
5401 case TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParmPack: {
5402 SubstTemplateTemplateParmPackStorage *subst
5403 = Name.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParmPack();
5404 return DeclarationNameInfo(subst->getParameterPack()->getDeclName(),
5405 NameLoc);
5406 }
5407 }
5408
5409 llvm_unreachable("bad template name kind!");
5410}
5411
5412TemplateName ASTContext::getCanonicalTemplateName(TemplateName Name) const {
5413 switch (Name.getKind()) {
5414 case TemplateName::QualifiedTemplate:
5415 case TemplateName::Template: {
5416 TemplateDecl *Template = Name.getAsTemplateDecl();
5417 if (auto *TTP = dyn_cast<TemplateTemplateParmDecl>(Template))
5418 Template = getCanonicalTemplateTemplateParmDecl(TTP);
5419
5420 // The canonical template name is the canonical template declaration.
5421 return TemplateName(cast<TemplateDecl>(Template->getCanonicalDecl()));
5422 }
5423
5424 case TemplateName::OverloadedTemplate:
5425 case TemplateName::AssumedTemplate:
5426 llvm_unreachable("cannot canonicalize unresolved template");
5427
5428 case TemplateName::DependentTemplate: {
5429 DependentTemplateName *DTN = Name.getAsDependentTemplateName();
5430 assert(DTN && "Non-dependent template names must refer to template decls.");
5431 return DTN->CanonicalTemplateName;
5432 }
5433
5434 case TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParm: {
5435 SubstTemplateTemplateParmStorage *subst
5436 = Name.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParm();
5437 return getCanonicalTemplateName(subst->getReplacement());
5438 }
5439
5440 case TemplateName::SubstTemplateTemplateParmPack: {
5441 SubstTemplateTemplateParmPackStorage *subst
5442 = Name.getAsSubstTemplateTemplateParmPack();
5443 TemplateTemplateParmDecl *canonParameter
5444 = getCanonicalTemplateTemplateParmDecl(subst->getParameterPack());
5445 TemplateArgument canonArgPack
5446 = getCanonicalTemplateArgument(subst->getArgumentPack());
5447 return getSubstTemplateTemplateParmPack(canonParameter, canonArgPack);
5448 }
5449 }
5450
5451 llvm_unreachable("bad template name!");
5452}
5453
5454bool ASTContext::hasSameTemplateName(TemplateName X, TemplateName Y) {
5455 X = getCanonicalTemplateName(X);
5456 Y = getCanonicalTemplateName(Y);
5457 return X.getAsVoidPointer() == Y.getAsVoidPointer();
5458}
5459
5460TemplateArgument
5461ASTContext::getCanonicalTemplateArgument(const TemplateArgument &Arg) const {
5462 switch (Arg.getKind()) {
5463 case TemplateArgument::Null:
5464 return Arg;
5465
5466 case TemplateArgument::Expression:
5467 return Arg;
5468
5469 case TemplateArgument::Declaration: {
5470 auto *D = cast<ValueDecl>(Arg.getAsDecl()->getCanonicalDecl());
5471 return TemplateArgument(D, Arg.getParamTypeForDecl());
5472 }
5473
5474 case TemplateArgument::NullPtr:
5475 return TemplateArgument(getCanonicalType(Arg.getNullPtrType()),
5476 /*isNullPtr*/true);
5477
5478 case TemplateArgument::Template:
5479 return TemplateArgument(getCanonicalTemplateName(Arg.getAsTemplate()));
5480
5481 case TemplateArgument::TemplateExpansion:
5482 return TemplateArgument(getCanonicalTemplateName(
5483 Arg.getAsTemplateOrTemplatePattern()),
5484 Arg.getNumTemplateExpansions());
5485
5486 case TemplateArgument::Integral:
5487 return TemplateArgument(Arg, getCanonicalType(Arg.getIntegralType()));
5488
5489 case TemplateArgument::Type:
5490 return TemplateArgument(getCanonicalType(Arg.getAsType()));
5491
5492 case TemplateArgument::Pack: {
5493 if (Arg.pack_size() == 0)
5494 return Arg;
5495
5496 auto *CanonArgs = new (*this) TemplateArgument[Arg.pack_size()];
5497 unsigned Idx = 0;
5498 for (TemplateArgument::pack_iterator A = Arg.pack_begin(),
5499 AEnd = Arg.pack_end();
5500 A != AEnd; (void)++A, ++Idx)
5501 CanonArgs[Idx] = getCanonicalTemplateArgument(*A);
5502
5503 return TemplateArgument(llvm::makeArrayRef(CanonArgs, Arg.pack_size()));
5504 }
5505 }
5506
5507 // Silence GCC warning
5508 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled template argument kind");
5509}
5510
5511NestedNameSpecifier *
5512ASTContext::getCanonicalNestedNameSpecifier(NestedNameSpecifier *NNS) const {
5513 if (!NNS)
5514 return nullptr;
5515
5516 switch (NNS->getKind()) {
5517 case NestedNameSpecifier::Identifier:
5518 // Canonicalize the prefix but keep the identifier the same.
5519 return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(*this,
5520 getCanonicalNestedNameSpecifier(NNS->getPrefix()),
5521 NNS->getAsIdentifier());
5522
5523 case NestedNameSpecifier::Namespace:
5524 // A namespace is canonical; build a nested-name-specifier with
5525 // this namespace and no prefix.
5526 return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(*this, nullptr,
5527 NNS->getAsNamespace()->getOriginalNamespace());
5528
5529 case NestedNameSpecifier::NamespaceAlias:
5530 // A namespace is canonical; build a nested-name-specifier with
5531 // this namespace and no prefix.
5532 return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(*this, nullptr,
5533 NNS->getAsNamespaceAlias()->getNamespace()
5534 ->getOriginalNamespace());
5535
5536 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpec:
5537 case NestedNameSpecifier::TypeSpecWithTemplate: {
5538 QualType T = getCanonicalType(QualType(NNS->getAsType(), 0));
5539
5540 // If we have some kind of dependent-named type (e.g., "typename T::type"),
5541 // break it apart into its prefix and identifier, then reconsititute those
5542 // as the canonical nested-name-specifier. This is required to canonicalize
5543 // a dependent nested-name-specifier involving typedefs of dependent-name
5544 // types, e.g.,
5545 // typedef typename T::type T1;
5546 // typedef typename T1::type T2;
5547 if (const auto *DNT = T->getAs<DependentNameType>())
5548 return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(*this, DNT->getQualifier(),
5549 const_cast<IdentifierInfo *>(DNT->getIdentifier()));
5550
5551 // Otherwise, just canonicalize the type, and force it to be a TypeSpec.
5552 // FIXME: Why are TypeSpec and TypeSpecWithTemplate distinct in the
5553 // first place?
5554 return NestedNameSpecifier::Create(*this, nullptr, false,
5555 const_cast<Type *>(T.getTypePtr()));
5556 }
5557
5558 case NestedNameSpecifier::Global:
5559 case NestedNameSpecifier::Super:
5560 // The global specifier and __super specifer are canonical and unique.
5561 return NNS;
5562 }
5563
5564 llvm_unreachable("Invalid NestedNameSpecifier::Kind!");
5565}
5566
5567const ArrayType *ASTContext::getAsArrayType(QualType T) const {
5568 // Handle the non-qualified case efficiently.
5569 if (!T.hasLocalQualifiers()) {
5570 // Handle the common positive case fast.
5571 if (const auto *AT = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(T))
5572 return AT;
5573 }
5574
5575 // Handle the common negative case fast.
5576 if (!isa<ArrayType>(T.getCanonicalType()))
5577 return nullptr;
5578
5579 // Apply any qualifiers from the array type to the element type. This
5580 // implements C99 6.7.3p8: "If the specification of an array type includes
5581 // any type qualifiers, the element type is so qualified, not the array type."
5582
5583 // If we get here, we either have type qualifiers on the type, or we have
5584 // sugar such as a typedef in the way. If we have type qualifiers on the type
5585 // we must propagate them down into the element type.
5586
5587 SplitQualType split = T.getSplitDesugaredType();
5588 Qualifiers qs = split.Quals;
5589
5590 // If we have a simple case, just return now.
5591 const auto *ATy = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(split.Ty);
5592 if (!ATy || qs.empty())
5593 return ATy;
5594
5595 // Otherwise, we have an array and we have qualifiers on it. Push the
5596 // qualifiers into the array element type and return a new array type.
5597 QualType NewEltTy = getQualifiedType(ATy->getElementType(), qs);
5598
5599 if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(ATy))
5600 return cast<ArrayType>(getConstantArrayType(NewEltTy, CAT->getSize(),
5601 CAT->getSizeModifier(),
5602 CAT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers()));
5603 if (const auto *IAT = dyn_cast<IncompleteArrayType>(ATy))
5604 return cast<ArrayType>(getIncompleteArrayType(NewEltTy,
5605 IAT->getSizeModifier(),
5606 IAT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers()));
5607
5608 if (const auto *DSAT = dyn_cast<DependentSizedArrayType>(ATy))
5609 return cast<ArrayType>(
5610 getDependentSizedArrayType(NewEltTy,
5611 DSAT->getSizeExpr(),
5612 DSAT->getSizeModifier(),
5613 DSAT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
5614 DSAT->getBracketsRange()));
5615
5616 const auto *VAT = cast<VariableArrayType>(ATy);
5617 return cast<ArrayType>(getVariableArrayType(NewEltTy,
5618 VAT->getSizeExpr(),
5619 VAT->getSizeModifier(),
5620 VAT->getIndexTypeCVRQualifiers(),
5621 VAT->getBracketsRange()));
5622}
5623
5624QualType ASTContext::getAdjustedParameterType(QualType T) const {
5625 if (T->isFunctionType() || T->isArrayType())
5626 return getDecayedType(T);
5627 return T;
5628}
5629
5630QualType ASTContext::getSignatureParameterType(QualType T) const {
5631 T = getVariableArrayDecayedType(T);
5632 T = getAdjustedParameterType(T);
5633 return T.getUnqualifiedType();
5634}
5635
5636QualType ASTContext::getExceptionObjectType(QualType T) const {
5637 // C++ [except.throw]p3:
5638 // A throw-expression initializes a temporary object, called the exception
5639 // object, the type of which is determined by removing any top-level
5640 // cv-qualifiers from the static type of the operand of throw and adjusting
5641 // the type from "array of T" or "function returning T" to "pointer to T"
5642 // or "pointer to function returning T", [...]
5643 T = getVariableArrayDecayedType(T);
5644 if (T->isArrayType() || T->isFunctionType())
5645 T = getDecayedType(T);
5646 return T.getUnqualifiedType();
5647}
5648
5649/// getArrayDecayedType - Return the properly qualified result of decaying the
5650/// specified array type to a pointer. This operation is non-trivial when
5651/// handling typedefs etc. The canonical type of "T" must be an array type,
5652/// this returns a pointer to a properly qualified element of the array.
5653///
5654/// See C99 6.7.5.3p7 and C99 6.3.2.1p3.
5655QualType ASTContext::getArrayDecayedType(QualType Ty) const {
5656 // Get the element type with 'getAsArrayType' so that we don't lose any
5657 // typedefs in the element type of the array. This also handles propagation
5658 // of type qualifiers from the array type into the element type if present
5659 // (C99 6.7.3p8).
5660 const ArrayType *PrettyArrayType = getAsArrayType(Ty);
5661 assert(PrettyArrayType && "Not an array type!");
5662
5663 QualType PtrTy = getPointerType(PrettyArrayType->getElementType());
5664
5665 // int x[restrict 4] -> int *restrict
5666 QualType Result = getQualifiedType(PtrTy,
5667 PrettyArrayType->getIndexTypeQualifiers());
5668
5669 // int x[_Nullable] -> int * _Nullable
5670 if (auto Nullability = Ty->getNullability(*this)) {
5671 Result = const_cast<ASTContext *>(this)->getAttributedType(
5672 AttributedType::getNullabilityAttrKind(*Nullability), Result, Result);
5673 }
5674 return Result;
5675}
5676
5677QualType ASTContext::getBaseElementType(const ArrayType *array) const {
5678 return getBaseElementType(array->getElementType());
5679}
5680
5681QualType ASTContext::getBaseElementType(QualType type) const {
5682 Qualifiers qs;
5683 while (true) {
5684 SplitQualType split = type.getSplitDesugaredType();
5685 const ArrayType *array = split.Ty->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe();
5686 if (!array) break;
5687
5688 type = array->getElementType();
5689 qs.addConsistentQualifiers(split.Quals);
5690 }
5691
5692 return getQualifiedType(type, qs);
5693}
5694
5695/// getConstantArrayElementCount - Returns number of constant array elements.
5696uint64_t
5697ASTContext::getConstantArrayElementCount(const ConstantArrayType *CA) const {
5698 uint64_t ElementCount = 1;
5699 do {
5700 ElementCount *= CA->getSize().getZExtValue();
5701 CA = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantArrayType>(
5702 CA->getElementType()->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe());
5703 } while (CA);
5704 return ElementCount;
5705}
5706
5707/// getFloatingRank - Return a relative rank for floating point types.
5708/// This routine will assert if passed a built-in type that isn't a float.
5709static FloatingRank getFloatingRank(QualType T) {
5710 if (const auto *CT = T->getAs<ComplexType>())
5711 return getFloatingRank(CT->getElementType());
5712
5713 assert(T->getAs<BuiltinType>() && "getFloatingRank(): not a floating type");
5714 switch (T->getAs<BuiltinType>()->getKind()) {
5715 default: llvm_unreachable("getFloatingRank(): not a floating type");
5716 case BuiltinType::Float16: return Float16Rank;
5717 case BuiltinType::Half: return HalfRank;
5718 case BuiltinType::Float: return FloatRank;
5719 case BuiltinType::Double: return DoubleRank;
5720 case BuiltinType::LongDouble: return LongDoubleRank;
5721 case BuiltinType::Float128: return Float128Rank;
5722 }
5723}
5724
5725/// getFloatingTypeOfSizeWithinDomain - Returns a real floating
5726/// point or a complex type (based on typeDomain/typeSize).
5727/// 'typeDomain' is a real floating point or complex type.
5728/// 'typeSize' is a real floating point or complex type.
5729QualType ASTContext::getFloatingTypeOfSizeWithinDomain(QualType Size,
5730 QualType Domain) const {
5731 FloatingRank EltRank = getFloatingRank(Size);
5732 if (Domain->isComplexType()) {
5733 switch (EltRank) {
5734 case Float16Rank:
5735 case HalfRank: llvm_unreachable("Complex half is not supported");
5736 case FloatRank: return FloatComplexTy;
5737 case DoubleRank: return DoubleComplexTy;
5738 case LongDoubleRank: return LongDoubleComplexTy;
5739 case Float128Rank: return Float128ComplexTy;
5740 }
5741 }
5742
5743 assert(Domain->isRealFloatingType() && "Unknown domain!");
5744 switch (EltRank) {
5745 case Float16Rank: return HalfTy;
5746 case HalfRank: return HalfTy;
5747 case FloatRank: return FloatTy;
5748 case DoubleRank: return DoubleTy;
5749 case LongDoubleRank: return LongDoubleTy;
5750 case Float128Rank: return Float128Ty;
5751 }
5752 llvm_unreachable("getFloatingRank(): illegal value for rank");
5753}
5754
5755/// getFloatingTypeOrder - Compare the rank of the two specified floating
5756/// point types, ignoring the domain of the type (i.e. 'double' ==
5757/// '_Complex double'). If LHS > RHS, return 1. If LHS == RHS, return 0. If
5758/// LHS < RHS, return -1.
5759int ASTContext::getFloatingTypeOrder(QualType LHS, QualType RHS) const {
5760 FloatingRank LHSR = getFloatingRank(LHS);
5761 FloatingRank RHSR = getFloatingRank(RHS);
5762
5763 if (LHSR == RHSR)
5764 return 0;
5765 if (LHSR > RHSR)
5766 return 1;
5767 return -1;
5768}
5769
5770int ASTContext::getFloatingTypeSemanticOrder(QualType LHS, QualType RHS) const {
5771 if (&getFloatTypeSemantics(LHS) == &getFloatTypeSemantics(RHS))
5772 return 0;
5773 return getFloatingTypeOrder(LHS, RHS);
5774}
5775
5776/// getIntegerRank - Return an integer conversion rank (C99 6.3.1.1p1). This
5777/// routine will assert if passed a built-in type that isn't an integer or enum,
5778/// or if it is not canonicalized.
5779unsigned ASTContext::getIntegerRank(const Type *T) const {
5780 assert(T->isCanonicalUnqualified() && "T should be canonicalized");
5781
5782 switch (cast<BuiltinType>(T)->getKind()) {
5783 default: llvm_unreachable("getIntegerRank(): not a built-in integer");
5784 case BuiltinType::Bool:
5785 return 1 + (getIntWidth(BoolTy) << 3);
5786 case BuiltinType::Char_S:
5787 case BuiltinType::Char_U:
5788 case BuiltinType::SChar:
5789 case BuiltinType::UChar:
5790 return 2 + (getIntWidth(CharTy) << 3);
5791 case BuiltinType::Short:
5792 case BuiltinType::UShort:
5793 return 3 + (getIntWidth(ShortTy) << 3);
5794 case BuiltinType::Int:
5795 case BuiltinType::UInt:
5796 return 4 + (getIntWidth(IntTy) << 3);
5797 case BuiltinType::Long:
5798 case BuiltinType::ULong:
5799 return 5 + (getIntWidth(LongTy) << 3);
5800 case BuiltinType::LongLong:
5801 case BuiltinType::ULongLong:
5802 return 6 + (getIntWidth(LongLongTy) << 3);
5803 // Does this make sense?
5804 case BuiltinType::IntCap:
5805 case BuiltinType::UIntCap:
5806 return 6 + (getIntWidth(IntCapTy) << 3);
5807 case BuiltinType::Int128:
5808 case BuiltinType::UInt128:
5809 return 7 + (getIntWidth(Int128Ty) << 3);
5810 }
5811}
5812
5813/// Whether this is a promotable bitfield reference according
5814/// to C99 6.3.1.1p2, bullet 2 (and GCC extensions).
5815///
5816/// \returns the type this bit-field will promote to, or NULL if no
5817/// promotion occurs.
5818QualType ASTContext::isPromotableBitField(Expr *E) const {
5819 if (E->isTypeDependent() || E->isValueDependent())
5820 return {};
5821
5822 // C++ [conv.prom]p5:
5823 // If the bit-field has an enumerated type, it is treated as any other
5824 // value of that type for promotion purposes.
5825 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && E->getType()->isEnumeralType())
5826 return {};
5827
5828 // FIXME: We should not do this unless E->refersToBitField() is true. This
5829 // matters in C where getSourceBitField() will find bit-fields for various
5830 // cases where the source expression is not a bit-field designator.
5831
5832 FieldDecl *Field = E->getSourceBitField(); // FIXME: conditional bit-fields?
5833 if (!Field)
5834 return {};
5835
5836 QualType FT = Field->getType();
5837
5838 uint64_t BitWidth = Field->getBitWidthValue(*this);
5839 uint64_t IntSize = getTypeSize(IntTy);
5840 // C++ [conv.prom]p5:
5841 // A prvalue for an integral bit-field can be converted to a prvalue of type
5842 // int if int can represent all the values of the bit-field; otherwise, it
5843 // can be converted to unsigned int if unsigned int can represent all the
5844 // values of the bit-field. If the bit-field is larger yet, no integral
5845 // promotion applies to it.
5846 // C11 6.3.1.1/2:
5847 // [For a bit-field of type _Bool, int, signed int, or unsigned int:]
5848 // If an int can represent all values of the original type (as restricted by
5849 // the width, for a bit-field), the value is converted to an int; otherwise,
5850 // it is converted to an unsigned int.
5851 //
5852 // FIXME: C does not permit promotion of a 'long : 3' bitfield to int.
5853 // We perform that promotion here to match GCC and C++.
5854 // FIXME: C does not permit promotion of an enum bit-field whose rank is
5855 // greater than that of 'int'. We perform that promotion to match GCC.
5856 if (BitWidth < IntSize)
5857 return IntTy;
5858
5859 if (BitWidth == IntSize)
5860 return FT->isSignedIntegerType() ? IntTy : UnsignedIntTy;
5861
5862 // Bit-fields wider than int are not subject to promotions, and therefore act
5863 // like the base type. GCC has some weird bugs in this area that we
5864 // deliberately do not follow (GCC follows a pre-standard resolution to
5865 // C's DR315 which treats bit-width as being part of the type, and this leaks
5866 // into their semantics in some cases).
5867 return {};
5868}
5869
5870/// getPromotedIntegerType - Returns the type that Promotable will
5871/// promote to: C99 6.3.1.1p2, assuming that Promotable is a promotable
5872/// integer type.
5873QualType ASTContext::getPromotedIntegerType(QualType Promotable) const {
5874 assert(!Promotable.isNull());
5875 assert(Promotable->isPromotableIntegerType());
5876 if (const auto *ET = Promotable->getAs<EnumType>())
5877 return ET->getDecl()->getPromotionType();
5878
5879 if (const auto *BT = Promotable->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
5880 // C++ [conv.prom]: A prvalue of type char16_t, char32_t, or wchar_t
5881 // (3.9.1) can be converted to a prvalue of the first of the following
5882 // types that can represent all the values of its underlying type:
5883 // int, unsigned int, long int, unsigned long int, long long int, or
5884 // unsigned long long int [...]
5885 // FIXME: Is there some better way to compute this?
5886 if (BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::WChar_S ||
5887 BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::WChar_U ||
5888 BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Char8 ||
5889 BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Char16 ||
5890 BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Char32) {
5891 bool FromIsSigned = BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::WChar_S;
5892 uint64_t FromSize = getTypeSize(BT);
5893 QualType PromoteTypes[] = { IntTy, UnsignedIntTy, LongTy, UnsignedLongTy,
5894 LongLongTy, UnsignedLongLongTy };
5895 for (size_t Idx = 0; Idx < llvm::array_lengthof(PromoteTypes); ++Idx) {
5896 uint64_t ToSize = getTypeSize(PromoteTypes[Idx]);
5897 if (FromSize < ToSize ||
5898 (FromSize == ToSize &&
5899 FromIsSigned == PromoteTypes[Idx]->isSignedIntegerType()))
5900 return PromoteTypes[Idx];
5901 }
5902 llvm_unreachable("char type should fit into long long");
5903 }
5904 }
5905
5906 // At this point, we should have a signed or unsigned integer type.
5907 if (Promotable->isSignedIntegerType())
5908 return IntTy;
5909 uint64_t PromotableSize = getIntWidth(Promotable);
5910 uint64_t IntSize = getIntWidth(IntTy);
5911 assert(Promotable->isUnsignedIntegerType() && PromotableSize <= IntSize);
5912 return (PromotableSize != IntSize) ? IntTy : UnsignedIntTy;
5913}
5914
5915/// Recurses in pointer/array types until it finds an objc retainable
5916/// type and returns its ownership.
5917Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime ASTContext::getInnerObjCOwnership(QualType T) const {
5918 while (!T.isNull()) {
5919 if (T.getObjCLifetime() != Qualifiers::OCL_None)
5920 return T.getObjCLifetime();
5921 if (T->isArrayType())
5922 T = getBaseElementType(T);
5923 else if (const auto *PT = T->getAs<PointerType>())
5924 T = PT->getPointeeType();
5925 else if (const auto *RT = T->getAs<ReferenceType>())
5926 T = RT->getPointeeType();
5927 else
5928 break;
5929 }
5930
5931 return Qualifiers::OCL_None;
5932}
5933
5934static const Type *getIntegerTypeForEnum(const EnumType *ET) {
5935 // Incomplete enum types are not treated as integer types.
5936 // FIXME: In C++, enum types are never integer types.
5937 if (ET->getDecl()->isComplete() && !ET->getDecl()->isScoped())
5938 return ET->getDecl()->getIntegerType().getTypePtr();
5939 return nullptr;
5940}
5941
5942/// getIntegerTypeOrder - Returns the highest ranked integer type:
5943/// C99 6.3.1.8p1. If LHS > RHS, return 1. If LHS == RHS, return 0. If
5944/// LHS < RHS, return -1.
5945int ASTContext::getIntegerTypeOrder(QualType LHS, QualType RHS) const {
5946 const Type *LHSC = getCanonicalType(LHS).getTypePtr();
5947 const Type *RHSC = getCanonicalType(RHS).getTypePtr();
5948
5949 // Unwrap enums to their underlying type.
5950 if (const auto *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(LHSC))
5951 LHSC = getIntegerTypeForEnum(ET);
5952 if (const auto *ET = dyn_cast<EnumType>(RHSC))
5953 RHSC = getIntegerTypeForEnum(ET);
5954
5955 if (LHSC == RHSC) return 0;
5956
5957 bool LHSUnsigned = LHSC->isUnsignedIntegerType();
5958 bool RHSUnsigned = RHSC->isUnsignedIntegerType();
5959
5960 unsigned LHSRank = getIntegerRank(LHSC);
5961 unsigned RHSRank = getIntegerRank(RHSC);
5962
5963 if (LHSUnsigned == RHSUnsigned) { // Both signed or both unsigned.
5964 if (LHSRank == RHSRank) return 0;
5965 return LHSRank > RHSRank ? 1 : -1;
5966 }
5967
5968 // Otherwise, the LHS is signed and the RHS is unsigned or visa versa.
5969 if (LHSUnsigned) {
5970 // If the unsigned [LHS] type is larger, return it.
5971 if (LHSRank >= RHSRank)
5972 return 1;
5973
5974 // If the signed type can represent all values of the unsigned type, it
5975 // wins. Because we are dealing with 2's complement and types that are
5976 // powers of two larger than each other, this is always safe.
5977 return -1;
5978 }
5979
5980 // If the unsigned [RHS] type is larger, return it.
5981 if (RHSRank >= LHSRank)
5982 return -1;
5983
5984 // If the signed type can represent all values of the unsigned type, it
5985 // wins. Because we are dealing with 2's complement and types that are
5986 // powers of two larger than each other, this is always safe.
5987 return 1;
5988}
5989
5990TypedefDecl *ASTContext::getCFConstantStringDecl() const {
5991 if (CFConstantStringTypeDecl)
5992 return CFConstantStringTypeDecl;
5993
5994 assert(!CFConstantStringTagDecl &&
5995 "tag and typedef should be initialized together");
5996 CFConstantStringTagDecl = buildImplicitRecord("__NSConstantString_tag");
5997 CFConstantStringTagDecl->startDefinition();
5998
5999 struct {
6000 QualType Type;
6001 const char *Name;
6002 } Fields[5];
6003 unsigned Count = 0;
6004
6005 /// Objective-C ABI
6006 ///
6007 /// typedef struct __NSConstantString_tag {
6008 /// const int *isa;
6009 /// int flags;
6010 /// const char *str;
6011 /// long length;
6012 /// } __NSConstantString;
6013 ///
6014 /// Swift ABI (4.1, 4.2)
6015 ///
6016 /// typedef struct __NSConstantString_tag {
6017 /// uintptr_t _cfisa;
6018 /// uintptr_t _swift_rc;
6019 /// _Atomic(uint64_t) _cfinfoa;
6020 /// const char *_ptr;
6021 /// uint32_t _length;
6022 /// } __NSConstantString;
6023 ///
6024 /// Swift ABI (5.0)
6025 ///
6026 /// typedef struct __NSConstantString_tag {
6027 /// uintptr_t _cfisa;
6028 /// uintptr_t _swift_rc;
6029 /// _Atomic(uint64_t) _cfinfoa;
6030 /// const char *_ptr;
6031 /// uintptr_t _length;
6032 /// } __NSConstantString;
6033
6034 const auto CFRuntime = getLangOpts().CFRuntime;
6035 if (static_cast<unsigned>(CFRuntime) <
6036 static_cast<unsigned>(LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift)) {
6037 Fields[Count++] = { getPointerType(IntTy.withConst()), "isa" };
6038 Fields[Count++] = { IntTy, "flags" };
6039 Fields[Count++] = { getPointerType(CharTy.withConst()), "str" };
6040 Fields[Count++] = { LongTy, "length" };
6041 } else {
6042 Fields[Count++] = { getUIntPtrType(), "_cfisa" };
6043 Fields[Count++] = { getUIntPtrType(), "_swift_rc" };
6044 Fields[Count++] = { getFromTargetType(Target->getUInt64Type()), "_swift_rc" };
6045 Fields[Count++] = { getPointerType(CharTy.withConst()), "_ptr" };
6046 if (CFRuntime == LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_1 ||
6047 CFRuntime == LangOptions::CoreFoundationABI::Swift4_2)
6048 Fields[Count++] = { IntTy, "_ptr" };
6049 else
6050 Fields[Count++] = { getUIntPtrType(), "_ptr" };
6051 }
6052
6053 // Create fields
6054 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Count; ++i) {
6055 FieldDecl *Field =
6056 FieldDecl::Create(*this, CFConstantStringTagDecl, SourceLocation(),
6057 SourceLocation(), &Idents.get(Fields[i].Name),
6058 Fields[i].Type, /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
6059 /*BitWidth=*/nullptr, /*Mutable=*/false, ICIS_NoInit);
6060 Field->setAccess(AS_public);
6061 CFConstantStringTagDecl->addDecl(Field);
6062 }
6063
6064 CFConstantStringTagDecl->completeDefinition();
6065 // This type is designed to be compatible with NSConstantString, but cannot
6066 // use the same name, since NSConstantString is an interface.
6067 auto tagType = getTagDeclType(CFConstantStringTagDecl);
6068 CFConstantStringTypeDecl =
6069 buildImplicitTypedef(tagType, "__NSConstantString");
6070
6071 return CFConstantStringTypeDecl;
6072}
6073
6074RecordDecl *ASTContext::getCFConstantStringTagDecl() const {
6075 if (!CFConstantStringTagDecl)
6076 getCFConstantStringDecl(); // Build the tag and the typedef.
6077 return CFConstantStringTagDecl;
6078}
6079
6080// getCFConstantStringType - Return the type used for constant CFStrings.
6081QualType ASTContext::getCFConstantStringType() const {
6082 return getTypedefType(getCFConstantStringDecl());
6083}
6084
6085QualType ASTContext::getObjCSuperType() const {
6086 if (ObjCSuperType.isNull()) {
6087 RecordDecl *ObjCSuperTypeDecl = buildImplicitRecord("objc_super");
6088 TUDecl->addDecl(ObjCSuperTypeDecl);
6089 ObjCSuperType = getTagDeclType(ObjCSuperTypeDecl);
6090 }
6091 return ObjCSuperType;
6092}
6093
6094void ASTContext::setCFConstantStringType(QualType T) {
6095 const auto *TD = T->getAs<TypedefType>();
6096 assert(TD && "Invalid CFConstantStringType");
6097 CFConstantStringTypeDecl = cast<TypedefDecl>(TD->getDecl());
6098 const auto *TagType =
6099 CFConstantStringTypeDecl->getUnderlyingType()->getAs<RecordType>();
6100 assert(TagType && "Invalid CFConstantStringType");
6101 CFConstantStringTagDecl = TagType->getDecl();
6102}

6104QualType ASTContext::getBlockDescriptorType() const {
6105 if (BlockDescriptorType)
6106 return getTagDeclType(BlockDescriptorType);
6107
6108 RecordDecl *RD;
6109 // FIXME: Needs the FlagAppleBlock bit.
6110 RD = buildImplicitRecord("__block_descriptor");
6111 RD->startDefinition();
6112
6113 QualType FieldTypes[] = {
6114 UnsignedLongTy,
6115 UnsignedLongTy,
6116 };
6117

6119 "reserved",
6120 "Size"
6121 };
6122

6124 FieldDecl *Field = FieldDecl::Create(
6125 *this, RD, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
6126 &Idents.get(FieldNames[i]), FieldTypes[i], /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
6127 /*BitWidth=*/nullptr, /*Mutable=*/false, ICIS_NoInit);
