6178TargetInfo::OpenCLTypeKind ASTContext::getOpenCLTypeKind(const Type *T) const {
6179 const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(T);
6180
6181 if (!BT) {
6182 if (isa<PipeType>(T))
6183 return TargetInfo::OCLTK_Pipe;
6184
6185 return TargetInfo::OCLTK_Default;
6186 }
6187
6188 switch (BT->getKind()) {
6189#define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
6190 case BuiltinType::Id: \
6191 return TargetInfo::OCLTK_Image;
6192#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
6193
6194 case BuiltinType::OCLClkEvent:
6195 return TargetInfo::OCLTK_ClkEvent;
6196
6197 case BuiltinType::OCLEvent:
6198 return TargetInfo::OCLTK_Event;
6199
6200 case BuiltinType::OCLQueue:
6201 return TargetInfo::OCLTK_Queue;
6202
6203 case BuiltinType::OCLReserveID:
6204 return TargetInfo::OCLTK_ReserveID;
6205
6206 case BuiltinType::OCLSampler:
6207 return TargetInfo::OCLTK_Sampler;
6208
6209 default:
6210 return TargetInfo::OCLTK_Default;
6211 }
6212}
6213
6214LangAS ASTContext::getOpenCLTypeAddrSpace(const Type *T) const {
6215 return Target->getOpenCLTypeAddrSpace(getOpenCLTypeKind(T));
6216}
6217
6218/// BlockRequiresCopying - Returns true if byref variable "D" of type "Ty"
6219/// requires copy/dispose. Note that this must match the logic
6220/// in buildByrefHelpers.
6221bool ASTContext::BlockRequiresCopying(QualType Ty,
6222 const VarDecl *D) {
6223 if (const CXXRecordDecl *record = Ty->getAsCXXRecordDecl()) {
6224 const Expr *copyExpr = getBlockVarCopyInit(D).getCopyExpr();
6225 if (!copyExpr && record->hasTrivialDestructor()) return false;
6226
6227 return true;
6228 }
6229
6230 // The block needs copy/destroy helpers if Ty is non-trivial to destructively
6231 // move or destroy.
6232 if (Ty.isNonTrivialToPrimitiveDestructiveMove() || Ty.isDestructedType())
6233 return true;
6234
6235 if (!Ty->isObjCRetainableType()) return false;
6236
6237 Qualifiers qs = Ty.getQualifiers();
6238
6239 // If we have lifetime, that dominates.
6240 if (Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime lifetime = qs.getObjCLifetime()) {
6241 switch (lifetime) {
6242 case Qualifiers::OCL_None: llvm_unreachable("impossible");
6243
6244 // These are just bits as far as the runtime is concerned.
6245 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
6246 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
6247 return false;
6248
6249 // These cases should have been taken care of when checking the type's
6250 // non-triviality.
6251 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
6252 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
6253 llvm_unreachable("impossible");
6254 }
6255 llvm_unreachable("fell out of lifetime switch!");
6256 }
6257 return (Ty->isBlockPointerType() || isObjCNSObjectType(Ty) ||
6258 Ty->isObjCObjectPointerType());
6259}
6260
6261bool ASTContext::getByrefLifetime(QualType Ty,
6262 Qualifiers::ObjCLifetime &LifeTime,
6263 bool &HasByrefExtendedLayout) const {
6264 if (!getLangOpts().ObjC ||
6265 getLangOpts().getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC)
6266 return false;
6267
6268 HasByrefExtendedLayout = false;
6269 if (Ty->isRecordType()) {
6270 HasByrefExtendedLayout = true;
6271 LifeTime = Qualifiers::OCL_None;
6272 } else if ((LifeTime = Ty.getObjCLifetime())) {
6273 // Honor the ARC qualifiers.
6274 } else if (Ty->isObjCObjectPointerType() || Ty->isBlockPointerType()) {
6275 // The MRR rule.
6276 LifeTime = Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone;
6277 } else {
6278 LifeTime = Qualifiers::OCL_None;
6279 }
6280 return true;
6281}
6282
6283TypedefDecl *ASTContext::getObjCInstanceTypeDecl() {
6284 if (!ObjCInstanceTypeDecl)
6285 ObjCInstanceTypeDecl =
6286 buildImplicitTypedef(getObjCIdType(), "instancetype");
6287 return ObjCInstanceTypeDecl;
6288}
6289
6290// This returns true if a type has been typedefed to BOOL:
6291// typedef <type> BOOL;
6292static bool isTypeTypedefedAsBOOL(QualType T) {
6293 if (const auto *TT = dyn_cast<TypedefType>(T))
6294 if (IdentifierInfo *II = TT->getDecl()->getIdentifier())
6295 return II->isStr("BOOL");
6296
6297 return false;
6298}
6299
6300/// getObjCEncodingTypeSize returns size of type for objective-c encoding
6301/// purpose.
6302CharUnits ASTContext::getObjCEncodingTypeSize(QualType type) const {
6303 if (!type->isIncompleteArrayType() && type->isIncompleteType())
6304 return CharUnits::Zero();
6305
6306 CharUnits sz = getTypeSizeInChars(type);
6307
6308 // Make all integer and enum types at least as large as an int
6309 if (sz.isPositive() && type->isIntegralOrEnumerationType())
6310 sz = std::max(sz, getTypeSizeInChars(IntTy));
6311 // Treat arrays as pointers, since that's how they're passed in.
6312 else if (type->isArrayType())
6313 sz = getTypeSizeInChars(VoidPtrTy);
6314 return sz;
6315}
6316
6317bool ASTContext::isMSStaticDataMemberInlineDefinition(const VarDecl *VD) const {
6318 return getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() &&
6319 VD->isStaticDataMember() &&
6320 VD->getType()->isIntegralOrEnumerationType() &&
6321 !VD->getFirstDecl()->isOutOfLine() && VD->getFirstDecl()->hasInit();
6322}
6323
6324ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind
6325ASTContext::getInlineVariableDefinitionKind(const VarDecl *VD) const {
6326 if (!VD->isInline())
6327 return InlineVariableDefinitionKind::None;
6328
6329 // In almost all cases, it's a weak definition.
6330 auto *First = VD->getFirstDecl();
6331 if (First->isInlineSpecified() || !First->isStaticDataMember())
6332 return InlineVariableDefinitionKind::Weak;
6333
6334 // If there's a file-context declaration in this translation unit, it's a
6335 // non-discardable definition.
6336 for (auto *D : VD->redecls())
6337 if (D->getLexicalDeclContext()->isFileContext() &&
6338 !D->isInlineSpecified() && (D->isConstexpr() || First->isConstexpr()))
6339 return InlineVariableDefinitionKind::Strong;
6340
6341 // If we've not seen one yet, we don't know.
6342 return InlineVariableDefinitionKind::WeakUnknown;
6343}
6344
6345static std::string charUnitsToString(const CharUnits &CU) {
6346 return llvm::itostr(CU.getQuantity());
6347}
6348
6349/// getObjCEncodingForBlock - Return the encoded type for this block
6350/// declaration.
6351std::string ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForBlock(const BlockExpr *Expr) const {
6352 std::string S;
6353
6354 const BlockDecl *Decl = Expr->getBlockDecl();
6355 QualType BlockTy =
6356 Expr->getType()->getAs<BlockPointerType>()->getPointeeType();
6357 // Encode result type.
6358 if (getLangOpts().EncodeExtendedBlockSig)
6359 getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter(
6360 Decl::OBJC_TQ_None, BlockTy->getAs<FunctionType>()->getReturnType(), S,
6361 true /*Extended*/);
6362 else
6363 getObjCEncodingForType(BlockTy->getAs<FunctionType>()->getReturnType(), S);
6364 // Compute size of all parameters.
6365 // Start with computing size of a pointer in number of bytes.
6366 // FIXME: There might(should) be a better way of doing this computation!
6367 CharUnits PtrSize = getTypeSizeInChars(VoidPtrTy);
6368 CharUnits ParmOffset = PtrSize;
6369 for (auto PI : Decl->parameters()) {
6370 QualType PType = PI->getType();
6371 CharUnits sz = getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
6372 if (sz.isZero())
6373 continue;
6374 assert(sz.isPositive() && "BlockExpr - Incomplete param type");
6375 ParmOffset += sz;
6376 }
6377 // Size of the argument frame
6378 S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
6379 // Block pointer and offset.
6380 S += "@?0";
6381
6382 // Argument types.
6383 ParmOffset = PtrSize;
6384 for (auto PVDecl : Decl->parameters()) {
6385 QualType PType = PVDecl->getOriginalType();
6386 if (const auto *AT =
6387 dyn_cast<ArrayType>(PType->getCanonicalTypeInternal())) {
6388 // Use array's original type only if it has known number of
6389 // elements.
6390 if (!isa<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
6391 PType = PVDecl->getType();
6392 } else if (PType->isFunctionType())
6393 PType = PVDecl->getType();
6394 if (getLangOpts().EncodeExtendedBlockSig)
6395 getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter(Decl::OBJC_TQ_None, PType,
6396 S, true /*Extended*/);
6397 else
6398 getObjCEncodingForType(PType, S);
6399 S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
6400 ParmOffset += getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
6401 }
6402
6403 return S;
6404}
6405
6406std::string
6407ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForFunctionDecl(const FunctionDecl *Decl) const {
6408 std::string S;
6409 // Encode result type.
6410 getObjCEncodingForType(Decl->getReturnType(), S);
6411 CharUnits ParmOffset;
6412 // Compute size of all parameters.
6413 for (auto PI : Decl->parameters()) {
6414 QualType PType = PI->getType();
6415 CharUnits sz = getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
6416 if (sz.isZero())
6417 continue;
6418
6419 assert(sz.isPositive() &&
6420 "getObjCEncodingForFunctionDecl - Incomplete param type");
6421 ParmOffset += sz;
6422 }
6423 S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
6424 ParmOffset = CharUnits::Zero();
6425
6426 // Argument types.
6427 for (auto PVDecl : Decl->parameters()) {
6428 QualType PType = PVDecl->getOriginalType();
6429 if (const auto *AT =
6430 dyn_cast<ArrayType>(PType->getCanonicalTypeInternal())) {
6431 // Use array's original type only if it has known number of
6432 // elements.
6433 if (!isa<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
6434 PType = PVDecl->getType();
6435 } else if (PType->isFunctionType())
6436 PType = PVDecl->getType();
6437 getObjCEncodingForType(PType, S);
6438 S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
6439 ParmOffset += getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
6440 }
6441
6442 return S;
6443}
6444
6445/// getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter - Return the encoded type for a single
6446/// method parameter or return type. If Extended, include class names and
6447/// block object types.
6448void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter(Decl::ObjCDeclQualifier QT,
6449 QualType T, std::string& S,
6450 bool Extended) const {
6451 // Encode type qualifer, 'in', 'inout', etc. for the parameter.
6452 getObjCEncodingForTypeQualifier(QT, S);
6453 // Encode parameter type.
6454 ObjCEncOptions Options = ObjCEncOptions()
6455 .setExpandPointedToStructures()
6456 .setExpandStructures()
6457 .setIsOutermostType();
6458 if (Extended)
6459 Options.setEncodeBlockParameters().setEncodeClassNames();
6460 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(T, S, Options, /*Field=*/nullptr);
6461}
6462
6463/// getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl - Return the encoded type for this method
6464/// declaration.
6465std::string ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl(const ObjCMethodDecl *Decl,
6466 bool Extended) const {
6467 // FIXME: This is not very efficient.
6468 // Encode return type.
6469 std::string S;
6470 getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter(Decl->getObjCDeclQualifier(),
6471 Decl->getReturnType(), S, Extended);
6472 // Compute size of all parameters.
6473 // Start with computing size of a pointer in number of bytes.
6474 // FIXME: There might(should) be a better way of doing this computation!
6475 CharUnits PtrSize = getTypeSizeInChars(VoidPtrTy);
6476 // The first two arguments (self and _cmd) are pointers; account for
6477 // their size.
6478 CharUnits ParmOffset = 2 * PtrSize;
6479 for (ObjCMethodDecl::param_const_iterator PI = Decl->param_begin(),
6480 E = Decl->sel_param_end(); PI != E; ++PI) {
6481 QualType PType = (*PI)->getType();
6482 CharUnits sz = getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
6483 if (sz.isZero())
6484 continue;
6485
6486 assert(sz.isPositive() &&
6487 "getObjCEncodingForMethodDecl - Incomplete param type");
6488 ParmOffset += sz;
6489 }
6490 S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
6491 S += "@0:";
6492 S += charUnitsToString(PtrSize);
6493
6494 // Argument types.
6495 ParmOffset = 2 * PtrSize;
6496 for (ObjCMethodDecl::param_const_iterator PI = Decl->param_begin(),
6497 E = Decl->sel_param_end(); PI != E; ++PI) {
6498 const ParmVarDecl *PVDecl = *PI;
6499 QualType PType = PVDecl->getOriginalType();
6500 if (const auto *AT =
6501 dyn_cast<ArrayType>(PType->getCanonicalTypeInternal())) {
6502 // Use array's original type only if it has known number of
6503 // elements.
6504 if (!isa<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
6505 PType = PVDecl->getType();
6506 } else if (PType->isFunctionType())
6507 PType = PVDecl->getType();
6508 getObjCEncodingForMethodParameter(PVDecl->getObjCDeclQualifier(),
6509 PType, S, Extended);
6510 S += charUnitsToString(ParmOffset);
6511 ParmOffset += getObjCEncodingTypeSize(PType);
6512 }
6513
6514 return S;
6515}
6516
6517ObjCPropertyImplDecl *
6518ASTContext::getObjCPropertyImplDeclForPropertyDecl(
6519 const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD,
6520 const Decl *Container) const {
6521 if (!Container)
6522 return nullptr;
6523 if (const auto *CID = dyn_cast<ObjCCategoryImplDecl>(Container)) {
6524 for (auto *PID : CID->property_impls())
6525 if (PID->getPropertyDecl() == PD)
6526 return PID;
6527 } else {
6528 const auto *OID = cast<ObjCImplementationDecl>(Container);
6529 for (auto *PID : OID->property_impls())
6530 if (PID->getPropertyDecl() == PD)
6531 return PID;
6532 }
6533 return nullptr;
6534}
6535
6536/// getObjCEncodingForPropertyDecl - Return the encoded type for this
6537/// property declaration. If non-NULL, Container must be either an
6538/// ObjCCategoryImplDecl or ObjCImplementationDecl; it should only be
6539/// NULL when getting encodings for protocol properties.
6540/// Property attributes are stored as a comma-delimited C string. The simple
6541/// attributes readonly and bycopy are encoded as single characters. The
6542/// parametrized attributes, getter=name, setter=name, and ivar=name, are
6543/// encoded as single characters, followed by an identifier. Property types
6544/// are also encoded as a parametrized attribute. The characters used to encode
6545/// these attributes are defined by the following enumeration:
6546/// @code
6547/// enum PropertyAttributes {
6548/// kPropertyReadOnly = 'R', // property is read-only.
6549/// kPropertyBycopy = 'C', // property is a copy of the value last assigned
6550/// kPropertyByref = '&', // property is a reference to the value last assigned
6551/// kPropertyDynamic = 'D', // property is dynamic
6552/// kPropertyGetter = 'G', // followed by getter selector name
6553/// kPropertySetter = 'S', // followed by setter selector name
6554/// kPropertyInstanceVariable = 'V' // followed by instance variable name
6555/// kPropertyType = 'T' // followed by old-style type encoding.
6556/// kPropertyWeak = 'W' // 'weak' property
6557/// kPropertyStrong = 'P' // property GC'able
6558/// kPropertyNonAtomic = 'N' // property non-atomic
6559/// };
6560/// @endcode
6561std::string
6562ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForPropertyDecl(const ObjCPropertyDecl *PD,
6563 const Decl *Container) const {
6564 // Collect information from the property implementation decl(s).
6565 bool Dynamic = false;
6566 ObjCPropertyImplDecl *SynthesizePID = nullptr;
6567
6568 if (ObjCPropertyImplDecl *PropertyImpDecl =
6569 getObjCPropertyImplDeclForPropertyDecl(PD, Container)) {
6570 if (PropertyImpDecl->getPropertyImplementation() == ObjCPropertyImplDecl::Dynamic)
6571 Dynamic = true;
6572 else
6573 SynthesizePID = PropertyImpDecl;
6574 }
6575
6576 // FIXME: This is not very efficient.
6577 std::string S = "T";
6578
6579 // Encode result type.
6580 // GCC has some special rules regarding encoding of properties which
6581 // closely resembles encoding of ivars.
6582 getObjCEncodingForPropertyType(PD->getType(), S);
6583
6584 if (PD->isReadOnly()) {
6585 S += ",R";
6586 if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyDecl::OBJC_PR_copy)
6587 S += ",C";
6588 if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyDecl::OBJC_PR_retain)
6589 S += ",&";
6590 if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyDecl::OBJC_PR_weak)
6591 S += ",W";
6592 } else {
6593 switch (PD->getSetterKind()) {
6594 case ObjCPropertyDecl::Assign: break;
6595 case ObjCPropertyDecl::Copy: S += ",C"; break;
6596 case ObjCPropertyDecl::Retain: S += ",&"; break;
6597 case ObjCPropertyDecl::Weak: S += ",W"; break;
6598 }
6599 }
6600
6601 // It really isn't clear at all what this means, since properties
6602 // are "dynamic by default".
6603 if (Dynamic)
6604 S += ",D";
6605
6606 if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyDecl::OBJC_PR_nonatomic)
6607 S += ",N";
6608
6609 if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyDecl::OBJC_PR_getter) {
6610 S += ",G";
6611 S += PD->getGetterName().getAsString();
6612 }
6613
6614 if (PD->getPropertyAttributes() & ObjCPropertyDecl::OBJC_PR_setter) {
6615 S += ",S";
6616 S += PD->getSetterName().getAsString();
6617 }
6618
6619 if (SynthesizePID) {
6620 const ObjCIvarDecl *OID = SynthesizePID->getPropertyIvarDecl();
6621 S += ",V";
6622 S += OID->getNameAsString();
6623 }
6624
6625 // FIXME: OBJCGC: weak & strong
6626 return S;
6627}
6628
6629/// getLegacyIntegralTypeEncoding -
6630/// Another legacy compatibility encoding: 32-bit longs are encoded as
6631/// 'l' or 'L' , but not always. For typedefs, we need to use
6632/// 'i' or 'I' instead if encoding a struct field, or a pointer!
6633void ASTContext::getLegacyIntegralTypeEncoding (QualType &PointeeTy) const {
6634 if (isa<TypedefType>(PointeeTy.getTypePtr())) {
6635 if (const auto *BT = PointeeTy->getAs<BuiltinType>()) {
6636 if (BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::ULong && getIntWidth(PointeeTy) == 32)
6637 PointeeTy = UnsignedIntTy;
6638 else
6639 if (BT->getKind() == BuiltinType::Long && getIntWidth(PointeeTy) == 32)
6640 PointeeTy = IntTy;
6641 }
6642 }
6643}
6644
6645void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForType(QualType T, std::string& S,
6646 const FieldDecl *Field,
6647 QualType *NotEncodedT) const {
6648 // We follow the behavior of gcc, expanding structures which are
6649 // directly pointed to, and expanding embedded structures. Note that
6650 // these rules are sufficient to prevent recursive encoding of the
6651 // same type.
6652 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(T, S,
6653 ObjCEncOptions()
6654 .setExpandPointedToStructures()
6655 .setExpandStructures()
6656 .setIsOutermostType(),
6657 Field, NotEncodedT);
6658}
6659
6660void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForPropertyType(QualType T,
6661 std::string& S) const {
6662 // Encode result type.
6663 // GCC has some special rules regarding encoding of properties which
6664 // closely resembles encoding of ivars.
6665 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(T, S,
6666 ObjCEncOptions()
6667 .setExpandPointedToStructures()
6668 .setExpandStructures()
6669 .setIsOutermostType()
6670 .setEncodingProperty(),
6671 /*Field=*/nullptr);
6672}
6673
6674static char getObjCEncodingForPrimitiveKind(const ASTContext *C,
6675 BuiltinType::Kind kind) {
6676 switch (kind) {
6677 case BuiltinType::Void: return 'v';
6678 case BuiltinType::Bool: return 'B';
6679 case BuiltinType::Char8:
6680 case BuiltinType::Char_U:
6681 case BuiltinType::UChar: return 'C';
6682 case BuiltinType::Char16:
6683 case BuiltinType::UShort: return 'S';
6684 case BuiltinType::Char32:
6685 case BuiltinType::UInt: return 'I';
6686 case BuiltinType::ULong:
6687 return C->getTargetInfo().getLongWidth() == 32 ? 'L' : 'Q';
6688 case BuiltinType::UInt128: return 'T';
6689 case BuiltinType::UIntCap: return 'Y';
6690 case BuiltinType::ULongLong: return 'Q';
6691 case BuiltinType::Char_S:
6692 case BuiltinType::SChar: return 'c';
6693 case BuiltinType::Short: return 's';
6694 case BuiltinType::WChar_S:
6695 case BuiltinType::WChar_U:
6696 case BuiltinType::Int: return 'i';
6697 case BuiltinType::Long:
6698 return C->getTargetInfo().getLongWidth() == 32 ? 'l' : 'q';
6699 case BuiltinType::LongLong: return 'q';
6700 case BuiltinType::Int128: return 't';
6701 case BuiltinType::IntCap: return 'y';
6702 case BuiltinType::Float: return 'f';
6703 case BuiltinType::Double: return 'd';
6704 case BuiltinType::LongDouble: return 'D';
6705 case BuiltinType::NullPtr: return '*'; // like char*
6706
6707 case BuiltinType::Float16:
6708 case BuiltinType::Float128:
6709 case BuiltinType::Half:
6710 case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
6711 case BuiltinType::Accum:
6712 case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
6713 case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
6714 case BuiltinType::UAccum:
6715 case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
6716 case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
6717 case BuiltinType::Fract:
6718 case BuiltinType::LongFract:
6719 case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
6720 case BuiltinType::UFract:
6721 case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
6722 case BuiltinType::SatShortAccum:
6723 case BuiltinType::SatAccum:
6724 case BuiltinType::SatLongAccum:
6725 case BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum:
6726 case BuiltinType::SatUAccum:
6727 case BuiltinType::SatULongAccum:
6728 case BuiltinType::SatShortFract:
6729 case BuiltinType::SatFract:
6730 case BuiltinType::SatLongFract:
6731 case BuiltinType::SatUShortFract:
6732 case BuiltinType::SatUFract:
6733 case BuiltinType::SatULongFract:
6734 // FIXME: potentially need @encodes for these!
6735 return ' ';
6736
6737 case BuiltinType::ObjCId:
6738 case BuiltinType::ObjCClass:
6739 case BuiltinType::ObjCSel:
6740 llvm_unreachable("@encoding ObjC primitive type");
6741
6742 // OpenCL and placeholder types don't need @encodings.
6743#define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
6744 case BuiltinType::Id:
6745#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
6746#define EXT_OPAQUE_TYPE(ExtType, Id, Ext) \
6747 case BuiltinType::Id:
6748#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLExtensionTypes.def"
6749 case BuiltinType::OCLEvent:
6750 case BuiltinType::OCLClkEvent:
6751 case BuiltinType::OCLQueue:
6752 case BuiltinType::OCLReserveID:
6753 case BuiltinType::OCLSampler:
6754 case BuiltinType::Dependent:
6755#define BUILTIN_TYPE(KIND, ID)
6756#define PLACEHOLDER_TYPE(KIND, ID) \
6757 case BuiltinType::KIND:
6758#include "clang/AST/BuiltinTypes.def"
6759 llvm_unreachable("invalid builtin type for @encode");
6760 }
6761 llvm_unreachable("invalid BuiltinType::Kind value");
6762}
6763
6764static char ObjCEncodingForEnumType(const ASTContext *C, const EnumType *ET) {
6765 EnumDecl *Enum = ET->getDecl();
6766
6767 // The encoding of an non-fixed enum type is always 'i', regardless of size.
6768 if (!Enum->isFixed())
6769 return 'i';
6770
6771 // The encoding of a fixed enum type matches its fixed underlying type.
6772 const auto *BT = Enum->getIntegerType()->castAs<BuiltinType>();
6773 return getObjCEncodingForPrimitiveKind(C, BT->getKind());
6774}
6775
6776static void EncodeBitField(const ASTContext *Ctx, std::string& S,
6777 QualType T, const FieldDecl *FD) {
6778 assert(FD->isBitField() && "not a bitfield - getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl");
6779 S += 'b';
6780 // The NeXT runtime encodes bit fields as b followed by the number of bits.
6781 // The GNU runtime requires more information; bitfields are encoded as b,
6782 // then the offset (in bits) of the first element, then the type of the
6783 // bitfield, then the size in bits. For example, in this structure:
6784 //
6785 // struct
6786 // {
6787 // int integer;
6788 // int flags:2;
6789 // };
6790 // On a 32-bit system, the encoding for flags would be b2 for the NeXT
6791 // runtime, but b32i2 for the GNU runtime. The reason for this extra
6792 // information is not especially sensible, but we're stuck with it for
6793 // compatibility with GCC, although providing it breaks anything that
6794 // actually uses runtime introspection and wants to work on both runtimes...
6795 if (Ctx->getLangOpts().ObjCRuntime.isGNUFamily()) {
6796 uint64_t Offset;
6797
6798 if (const auto *IVD = dyn_cast<ObjCIvarDecl>(FD)) {
6799 Offset = Ctx->lookupFieldBitOffset(IVD->getContainingInterface(), nullptr,
6800 IVD);
6801 } else {
6802 const RecordDecl *RD = FD->getParent();
6803 const ASTRecordLayout &RL = Ctx->getASTRecordLayout(RD);
6804 Offset = RL.getFieldOffset(FD->getFieldIndex());
6805 }
6806
6807 S += llvm::utostr(Offset);
6808
6809 if (const auto *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>())
6810 S += ObjCEncodingForEnumType(Ctx, ET);
6811 else {
6812 const auto *BT = T->castAs<BuiltinType>();
6813 S += getObjCEncodingForPrimitiveKind(Ctx, BT->getKind());
6814 }
6815 }
6816 S += llvm::utostr(FD->getBitWidthValue(*Ctx));
6817}
6818
6819// FIXME: Use SmallString for accumulating string.
6820void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(QualType T, std::string &S,
6821 const ObjCEncOptions Options,
6822 const FieldDecl *FD,
6823 QualType *NotEncodedT) const {
6824 CanQualType CT = getCanonicalType(T);
6825 switch (CT->getTypeClass()) {
6826 case Type::Builtin:
6827 case Type::Enum:
6828 if (FD && FD->isBitField())
6829 return EncodeBitField(this, S, T, FD);
6830 if (const auto *BT = dyn_cast<BuiltinType>(CT))
6831 S += getObjCEncodingForPrimitiveKind(this, BT->getKind());
6832 else
6833 S += ObjCEncodingForEnumType(this, cast<EnumType>(CT));
6834 return;
6835
6836 case Type::Complex: {
6837 const auto *CT = T->castAs<ComplexType>();
6838 S += 'j';
6839 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(CT->getElementType(), S, ObjCEncOptions(),
6840 /*Field=*/nullptr);
6841 return;
6842 }
6843
6844 case Type::Atomic: {
6845 const auto *AT = T->castAs<AtomicType>();
6846 S += 'A';
6847 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(AT->getValueType(), S, ObjCEncOptions(),
6848 /*Field=*/nullptr);
6849 return;
6850 }
6851
6852 // encoding for pointer or reference types.
6853 case Type::Pointer:
6854 case Type::LValueReference:
6855 case Type::RValueReference: {
6856 QualType PointeeTy;
6857 if (isa<PointerType>(CT)) {
6858 const auto *PT = T->castAs<PointerType>();
6859 if (PT->isObjCSelType()) {
6860 S += ':';
6861 return;
6862 }
6863 PointeeTy = PT->getPointeeType();
6864 } else {
6865 PointeeTy = T->castAs<ReferenceType>()->getPointeeType();
6866 }
6867
6868 bool isReadOnly = false;
6869 // For historical/compatibility reasons, the read-only qualifier of the
6870 // pointee gets emitted _before_ the '^'. The read-only qualifier of
6871 // the pointer itself gets ignored, _unless_ we are looking at a typedef!
6872 // Also, do not emit the 'r' for anything but the outermost type!
6873 if (isa<TypedefType>(T.getTypePtr())) {
6874 if (Options.IsOutermostType() && T.isConstQualified()) {
6875 isReadOnly = true;
6876 S += 'r';
6877 }
6878 } else if (Options.IsOutermostType()) {
6879 QualType P = PointeeTy;
6880 while (P->getAs<PointerType>())
6881 P = P->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
6882 if (P.isConstQualified()) {
6883 isReadOnly = true;
6884 S += 'r';
6885 }
6886 }
6887 if (isReadOnly) {
6888 // Another legacy compatibility encoding. Some ObjC qualifier and type
6889 // combinations need to be rearranged.
6890 // Rewrite "in const" from "nr" to "rn"
6891 if (StringRef(S).endswith("nr"))
6892 S.replace(S.end()-2, S.end(), "rn");
6893 }
6894
6895 if (PointeeTy->isCharType()) {
6896 // char pointer types should be encoded as '*' unless it is a
6897 // type that has been typedef'd to 'BOOL'.
6898 if (!isTypeTypedefedAsBOOL(PointeeTy)) {
6899 S += '*';
6900 return;
6901 }
6902 } else if (const auto *RTy = PointeeTy->getAs<RecordType>()) {
6903 // GCC binary compat: Need to convert "struct objc_class *" to "#".
6904 if (RTy->getDecl()->getIdentifier() == &Idents.get("objc_class")) {
6905 S += '#';
6906 return;
6907 }
6908 // GCC binary compat: Need to convert "struct objc_object *" to "@".
6909 if (RTy->getDecl()->getIdentifier() == &Idents.get("objc_object")) {
6910 S += '@';
6911 return;
6912 }
6913 // fall through...
6914 }
6915 S += '^';
6916 getLegacyIntegralTypeEncoding(PointeeTy);
6917
6918 ObjCEncOptions NewOptions;
6919 if (Options.ExpandPointedToStructures())
6920 NewOptions.setExpandStructures();
6921 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(PointeeTy, S, NewOptions,
6922 /*Field=*/nullptr, NotEncodedT);
6923 return;
6924 }
6925
6926 case Type::ConstantArray:
6927 case Type::IncompleteArray:
6928 case Type::VariableArray: {
6929 const auto *AT = cast<ArrayType>(CT);
6930
6931 if (isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT) && !Options.IsStructField()) {
6932 // Incomplete arrays are encoded as a pointer to the array element.
6933 S += '^';
6934
6935 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(
6936 AT->getElementType(), S,
6937 Options.keepingOnly(ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures()), FD);
6938 } else {
6939 S += '[';
6940
6941 if (const auto *CAT = dyn_cast<ConstantArrayType>(AT))
6942 S += llvm::utostr(CAT->getSize().getZExtValue());
6943 else {
6944 //Variable length arrays are encoded as a regular array with 0 elements.
6945 assert((isa<VariableArrayType>(AT) || isa<IncompleteArrayType>(AT)) &&
6946 "Unknown array type!");
6947 S += '0';
6948 }
6949
6950 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(
6951 AT->getElementType(), S,
6952 Options.keepingOnly(ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures()), FD,
6953 NotEncodedT);
6954 S += ']';
6955 }
6956 return;
6957 }
6958
6959 case Type::FunctionNoProto:
6960 case Type::FunctionProto:
6961 S += '?';
6962 return;
6963
6964 case Type::Record: {
6965 RecordDecl *RDecl = cast<RecordType>(CT)->getDecl();
6966 S += RDecl->isUnion() ? '(' : '{';
6967 // Anonymous structures print as '?'
6968 if (const IdentifierInfo *II = RDecl->getIdentifier()) {
6969 S += II->getName();
6970 if (const auto *Spec = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>(RDecl)) {
6971 const TemplateArgumentList &TemplateArgs = Spec->getTemplateArgs();
6972 llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(S);
6973 printTemplateArgumentList(OS, TemplateArgs.asArray(),
6974 getPrintingPolicy());
6975 }
6976 } else {
6977 S += '?';
6978 }
6979 if (Options.ExpandStructures()) {
6980 S += '=';
6981 if (!RDecl->isUnion()) {
6982 getObjCEncodingForStructureImpl(RDecl, S, FD, true, NotEncodedT);
6983 } else {
6984 for (const auto *Field : RDecl->fields()) {
6985 if (FD) {
6986 S += '"';
6987 S += Field->getNameAsString();
6988 S += '"';
6989 }
6990
6991 // Special case bit-fields.
6992 if (Field->isBitField()) {
6993 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(Field->getType(), S,
6994 ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures(),
6995 Field);
6996 } else {
6997 QualType qt = Field->getType();
6998 getLegacyIntegralTypeEncoding(qt);
6999 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(
7000 qt, S,
7001 ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures().setIsStructField(), FD,
7002 NotEncodedT);
7003 }
7004 }
7005 }
7006 }
7007 S += RDecl->isUnion() ? ')' : '}';
7008 return;
7009 }
7010
7011 case Type::BlockPointer: {
7012 const auto *BT = T->castAs<BlockPointerType>();
7013 S += "@?"; // Unlike a pointer-to-function, which is "^?".
7014 if (Options.EncodeBlockParameters()) {
7015 const auto *FT = BT->getPointeeType()->castAs<FunctionType>();
7016
7017 S += '<';
7018 // Block return type
7019 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(FT->getReturnType(), S,
7020 Options.forComponentType(), FD, NotEncodedT);
7021 // Block self
7022 S += "@?";
7023 // Block parameters
7024 if (const auto *FPT = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(FT)) {
7025 for (const auto &I : FPT->param_types())
7026 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(I, S, Options.forComponentType(), FD,
7027 NotEncodedT);
7028 }
7029 S += '>';
7030 }
7031 return;
7032 }
7033
7034 case Type::ObjCObject: {
7035 // hack to match legacy encoding of *id and *Class
7036 QualType Ty = getObjCObjectPointerType(CT);
7037 if (Ty->isObjCIdType()) {
7038 S += "{objc_object=}";
7039 return;
7040 }
7041 else if (Ty->isObjCClassType()) {
7042 S += "{objc_class=}";
7043 return;
7044 }
7045 // TODO: Double check to make sure this intentionally falls through.
7046 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
7047 }
7048
7049 case Type::ObjCInterface: {
7050 // Ignore protocol qualifiers when mangling at this level.
7051 // @encode(class_name)
7052 ObjCInterfaceDecl *OI = T->castAs<ObjCObjectType>()->getInterface();
7053 S += '{';
7054 S += OI->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
7055 if (Options.ExpandStructures()) {
7056 S += '=';
7057 SmallVector<const ObjCIvarDecl*, 32> Ivars;
7058 DeepCollectObjCIvars(OI, true, Ivars);
7059 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Ivars.size(); i != e; ++i) {
7060 const FieldDecl *Field = Ivars[i];
7061 if (Field->isBitField())
7062 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(Field->getType(), S,
7063 ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures(),
7064 Field);
7065 else
7066 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(Field->getType(), S,
7067 ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures(), FD,
7068 NotEncodedT);
7069 }
7070 }
7071 S += '}';
7072 return;
7073 }
7074
7075 case Type::ObjCObjectPointer: {
7076 const auto *OPT = T->castAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
7077 if (OPT->isObjCIdType()) {
7078 S += '@';
7079 return;
7080 }
7081
7082 if (OPT->isObjCClassType() || OPT->isObjCQualifiedClassType()) {
7083 // FIXME: Consider if we need to output qualifiers for 'Class<p>'.
7084 // Since this is a binary compatibility issue, need to consult with
7085 // runtime folks. Fortunately, this is a *very* obscure construct.
7086 S += '#';
7087 return;
7088 }
7089
7090 if (OPT->isObjCQualifiedIdType()) {
7091 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(
7092 getObjCIdType(), S,
7093 Options.keepingOnly(ObjCEncOptions()
7094 .setExpandPointedToStructures()
7095 .setExpandStructures()),
7096 FD);
7097 if (FD || Options.EncodingProperty() || Options.EncodeClassNames()) {
7098 // Note that we do extended encoding of protocol qualifer list
7099 // Only when doing ivar or property encoding.
7100 S += '"';
7101 for (const auto *I : OPT->quals()) {
7102 S += '<';
7103 S += I->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
7104 S += '>';
7105 }
7106 S += '"';
7107 }
7108 return;
7109 }
7110
7111 S += '@';
7112 if (OPT->getInterfaceDecl() &&
7113 (FD || Options.EncodingProperty() || Options.EncodeClassNames())) {
7114 S += '"';
7115 S += OPT->getInterfaceDecl()->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
7116 for (const auto *I : OPT->quals()) {
7117 S += '<';
7118 S += I->getObjCRuntimeNameAsString();
7119 S += '>';
7120 }
7121 S += '"';
7122 }
7123 return;
7124 }
7125
7126 // gcc just blithely ignores member pointers.
7127 // FIXME: we should do better than that. 'M' is available.
7128 case Type::MemberPointer:
7129 // This matches gcc's encoding, even though technically it is insufficient.
7130 //FIXME. We should do a better job than gcc.
7131 case Type::Vector:
7132 case Type::ExtVector:
7133 // Until we have a coherent encoding of these three types, issue warning.
7134 if (NotEncodedT)
7135 *NotEncodedT = T;
7136 return;
7137
7138 // We could see an undeduced auto type here during error recovery.
7139 // Just ignore it.
7140 case Type::Auto:
7141 case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
7142 return;
7143
7144 case Type::Pipe:
7145#define ABSTRACT_TYPE(KIND, BASE)
7146#define TYPE(KIND, BASE)
7147#define DEPENDENT_TYPE(KIND, BASE) \
7148 case Type::KIND:
7149#define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(KIND, BASE) \
7150 case Type::KIND:
7151#define NON_CANONICAL_UNLESS_DEPENDENT_TYPE(KIND, BASE) \
7152 case Type::KIND:
7153#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
7154 llvm_unreachable("@encode for dependent type!");
7155 }
7156 llvm_unreachable("bad type kind!");
7157}
7158
7159void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForStructureImpl(RecordDecl *RDecl,
7160 std::string &S,
7161 const FieldDecl *FD,
7162 bool includeVBases,
7163 QualType *NotEncodedT) const {
7164 assert(RDecl && "Expected non-null RecordDecl");
7165 assert(!RDecl->isUnion() && "Should not be called for unions");
7166 if (!RDecl->getDefinition() || RDecl->getDefinition()->isInvalidDecl())
7167 return;
7168
7169 const auto *CXXRec = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RDecl);
7170 std::multimap<uint64_t, NamedDecl *> FieldOrBaseOffsets;
7171 const ASTRecordLayout &layout = getASTRecordLayout(RDecl);
7172
7173 if (CXXRec) {
7174 for (const auto &BI : CXXRec->bases()) {
7175 if (!BI.isVirtual()) {
7176 CXXRecordDecl *base = BI.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
7177 if (base->isEmpty())
7178 continue;
7179 uint64_t offs = toBits(layout.getBaseClassOffset(base));
7180 FieldOrBaseOffsets.insert(FieldOrBaseOffsets.upper_bound(offs),
7181 std::make_pair(offs, base));
7182 }
7183 }
7184 }
7185
7186 unsigned i = 0;
7187 for (auto *Field : RDecl->fields()) {
7188 uint64_t offs = layout.getFieldOffset(i);
7189 FieldOrBaseOffsets.insert(FieldOrBaseOffsets.upper_bound(offs),
7190 std::make_pair(offs, Field));
7191 ++i;
7192 }
7193
7194 if (CXXRec && includeVBases) {
7195 for (const auto &BI : CXXRec->vbases()) {
7196 CXXRecordDecl *base = BI.getType()->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
7197 if (base->isEmpty())
7198 continue;
7199 uint64_t offs = toBits(layout.getVBaseClassOffset(base));
7200 if (offs >= uint64_t(toBits(layout.getNonVirtualSize())) &&
7201 FieldOrBaseOffsets.find(offs) == FieldOrBaseOffsets.end())
7202 FieldOrBaseOffsets.insert(FieldOrBaseOffsets.end(),
7203 std::make_pair(offs, base));
7204 }
7205 }
7206
7207 CharUnits size;
7208 if (CXXRec) {
7209 size = includeVBases ? layout.getSize() : layout.getNonVirtualSize();
7210 } else {
7211 size = layout.getSize();
7212 }
7213
7214#ifndef NDEBUG
7215 uint64_t CurOffs = 0;
7216#endif
7217 std::multimap<uint64_t, NamedDecl *>::iterator
7218 CurLayObj = FieldOrBaseOffsets.begin();
7219
7220 if (CXXRec && CXXRec->isDynamicClass() &&
7221 (CurLayObj == FieldOrBaseOffsets.end() || CurLayObj->first != 0)) {
7222 if (FD) {
7223 S += "\"_vptr$";
7224 std::string recname = CXXRec->getNameAsString();
7225 if (recname.empty()) recname = "?";
7226 S += recname;
7227 S += '"';
7228 }
7229 S += "^^?";
7230#ifndef NDEBUG
7231 CurOffs += getTypeSize(VoidPtrTy);
7232#endif
7233 }
7234
7235 if (!RDecl->hasFlexibleArrayMember()) {
7236 // Mark the end of the structure.
7237 uint64_t offs = toBits(size);
7238 FieldOrBaseOffsets.insert(FieldOrBaseOffsets.upper_bound(offs),
7239 std::make_pair(offs, nullptr));
7240 }
7241
7242 for (; CurLayObj != FieldOrBaseOffsets.end(); ++CurLayObj) {
7243#ifndef NDEBUG
7244 assert(CurOffs <= CurLayObj->first);
7245 if (CurOffs < CurLayObj->first) {
7246 uint64_t padding = CurLayObj->first - CurOffs;
7247 // FIXME: There doesn't seem to be a way to indicate in the encoding that
7248 // packing/alignment of members is different that normal, in which case
7249 // the encoding will be out-of-sync with the real layout.
7250 // If the runtime switches to just consider the size of types without
7251 // taking into account alignment, we could make padding explicit in the
7252 // encoding (e.g. using arrays of chars). The encoding strings would be
7253 // longer then though.
7254 CurOffs += padding;
7255 }
7256#endif
7257
7258 NamedDecl *dcl = CurLayObj->second;
7259 if (!dcl)
7260 break; // reached end of structure.
7261
7262 if (auto *base = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(dcl)) {
7263 // We expand the bases without their virtual bases since those are going
7264 // in the initial structure. Note that this differs from gcc which
7265 // expands virtual bases each time one is encountered in the hierarchy,
7266 // making the encoding type bigger than it really is.
7267 getObjCEncodingForStructureImpl(base, S, FD, /*includeVBases*/false,
7268 NotEncodedT);
7269 assert(!base->isEmpty());
7270#ifndef NDEBUG
7271 CurOffs += toBits(getASTRecordLayout(base).getNonVirtualSize());
7272#endif
7273 } else {
7274 const auto *field = cast<FieldDecl>(dcl);
7275 if (FD) {
7276 S += '"';
7277 S += field->getNameAsString();
7278 S += '"';
7279 }
7280
7281 if (field->isBitField()) {
7282 EncodeBitField(this, S, field->getType(), field);
7283#ifndef NDEBUG
7284 CurOffs += field->getBitWidthValue(*this);
7285#endif
7286 } else {
7287 QualType qt = field->getType();
7288 getLegacyIntegralTypeEncoding(qt);
7289 getObjCEncodingForTypeImpl(
7290 qt, S, ObjCEncOptions().setExpandStructures().setIsStructField(),
7291 FD, NotEncodedT);
7292#ifndef NDEBUG
7293 CurOffs += getTypeSize(field->getType());
7294#endif
7295 }
7296 }
7297 }
7298}
7299
7300void ASTContext::getObjCEncodingForTypeQualifier(Decl::ObjCDeclQualifier QT,
7301 std::string& S) const {
7302 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_In)
7303 S += 'n';
7304 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Inout)
7305 S += 'N';
7306 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Out)
7307 S += 'o';
7308 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Bycopy)
7309 S += 'O';
7310 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Byref)
7311 S += 'R';
7312 if (QT & Decl::OBJC_TQ_Oneway)
7313 S += 'V';
7314}
7315
7316TypedefDecl *ASTContext::getObjCIdDecl() const {
7317 if (!ObjCIdDecl) {
7318 QualType T = getObjCObjectType(ObjCBuiltinIdTy, {}, {});
7319 T = getObjCObjectPointerType(T);
7320 ObjCIdDecl = buildImplicitTypedef(T, "id");
7321 }
7322 return ObjCIdDecl;
7323}
7324
7325TypedefDecl *ASTContext::getObjCSelDecl() const {
7326 if (!ObjCSelDecl) {
7327 QualType T = getPointerType(ObjCBuiltinSelTy);
7328 ObjCSelDecl = buildImplicitTypedef(T, "SEL");
7329 }
7330 return ObjCSelDecl;
7331}
7332
7333TypedefDecl *ASTContext::getObjCClassDecl() const {
7334 if (!ObjCClassDecl) {
7335 QualType T = getObjCObjectType(ObjCBuiltinClassTy, {}, {});
7336 T = getObjCObjectPointerType(T);
7337 ObjCClassDecl = buildImplicitTypedef(T, "Class");
7338 }
7339 return ObjCClassDecl;
7340}
7341
7342RecordDecl *ASTContext::getCHERIClassDecl() const {
7343 if (!CHERIClassDecl) {
7344 RecordDecl *RD;
7345 RD = buildImplicitRecord("cheri_object");
7346 RD->startDefinition();
7347
7348 QualType CapTy = getPointerType(VoidTy, ASTContext::PIK_Capability);
7349
7350 QualType FieldTypes[] = { CapTy, CapTy };
7351 static const char *const FieldNames[] = { "co_codecap", "co_datacap" };
7352
7353 for (size_t i = 0; i < 2; ++i) {
7354 FieldDecl *Field = FieldDecl::Create(
7355 *this, RD, SourceLocation(), SourceLocation(),
7356 &Idents.get(FieldNames[i]), FieldTypes[i], /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
7357 /*BitWidth=*/nullptr, /*Mutable=*/false, ICIS_NoInit);
7358 Field->setAccess(AS_public);
7359 RD->addDecl(Field);
7360 }
7361
7362 RD->completeDefinition();
7363 RD->setImplicit();
7364 CHERIClassDecl = RD;
7365 }
7366 return CHERIClassDecl;
7367}
7368
7369ObjCInterfaceDecl *ASTContext::getObjCProtocolDecl() const {
7370 if (!ObjCProtocolClassDecl) {
7371 ObjCProtocolClassDecl
7372 = ObjCInterfaceDecl::Create(*this, getTranslationUnitDecl(),
7373 SourceLocation(),
7374 &Idents.get("Protocol"),
7375 /*typeParamList=*/nullptr,
7376 /*PrevDecl=*/nullptr,
7377 SourceLocation(), true);
7378 }
7379
7380 return ObjCProtocolClassDecl;
7381}

7387static TypedefDecl *CreateCharPtrNamedVaListDecl(const ASTContext *Context,
7388 StringRef Name) {
7389 // typedef char* __builtin[_ms]_va_list;
7390 QualType T = Context->getPointerType(Context->CharTy);
7391 return Context->buildImplicitTypedef(T, Name);
7392}

7396}

7399 return CreateCharPtrNamedVaListDecl(Context, "__builtin_va_list");
7400}

7402static TypedefDecl *CreateVoidPtrBuiltinVaListDecl(const ASTContext *Context) {
7403 // typedef void* __builtin_va_list;
7404 QualType T = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
7405 return Context->buildImplicitTypedef(T, "__builtin_va_list");

7407
7408static TypedefDecl *
7409CreateAArch64ABIBuiltinVaListDecl(const ASTContext *Context) {
7410 // struct __va_list
7411 RecordDecl *VaListTagDecl = Context->buildImplicitRecord("__va_list");
7412 if (Context->getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
7413 // namespace std { struct __va_list {
7414 NamespaceDecl *NS;
7415 NS = NamespaceDecl::Create(const_cast<ASTContext &>(*Context),
7416 Context->getTranslationUnitDecl(),
7417 /*Inline*/ false, SourceLocation(),
7418 SourceLocation(), &Context->Idents.get("std"),
7419 /*PrevDecl*/ nullptr);
7420 NS->setImplicit();
7421 VaListTagDecl->setDeclContext(NS);
7422 }
7423
7424 VaListTagDecl->startDefinition();
7425
7426 const size_t NumFields = 5;
7427 QualType FieldTypes[NumFields];
7428 const char *FieldNames[NumFields];
7429
7430 // void *__stack;
7431 FieldTypes[0] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
7432 FieldNames[0] = "__stack";
7433
7434 // void *__gr_top;
7435 FieldTypes[1] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
7436 FieldNames[1] = "__gr_top";
7437
7438 // void *__vr_top;
7439 FieldTypes[2] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
7440 FieldNames[2] = "__vr_top";
7441
7442 // int __gr_offs;
7443 FieldTypes[3] = Context->IntTy;
7444 FieldNames[3] = "__gr_offs";
7445
7446 // int __vr_offs;
7447 FieldTypes[4] = Context->IntTy;
7448 FieldNames[4] = "__vr_offs";
7449
7450 // Create fields
7451 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumFields; ++i) {
7452 FieldDecl *Field = FieldDecl::Create(const_cast<ASTContext &>(*Context),
7453 VaListTagDecl,
7454 SourceLocation(),
7455 SourceLocation(),
7456 &Context->Idents.get(FieldNames[i]),
7457 FieldTypes[i], /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
7458 /*BitWidth=*/nullptr,
7459 /*Mutable=*/false,
7460 ICIS_NoInit);
7461 Field->setAccess(AS_public);
7462 VaListTagDecl->addDecl(Field);
7463 }
7464 VaListTagDecl->completeDefinition();
7465 Context->VaListTagDecl = VaListTagDecl;
7466 QualType VaListTagType = Context->getRecordType(VaListTagDecl);
7467
7468 // } __builtin_va_list;
7469 return Context->buildImplicitTypedef(VaListTagType, "__builtin_va_list");
7470}
7471
7472static TypedefDecl *CreatePowerABIBuiltinVaListDecl(const ASTContext *Context) {
7473 // typedef struct __va_list_tag {
7474 RecordDecl *VaListTagDecl;
7475
7476 VaListTagDecl = Context->buildImplicitRecord("__va_list_tag");
7477 VaListTagDecl->startDefinition();
7478
7479 const size_t NumFields = 5;
7480 QualType FieldTypes[NumFields];
7481 const char *FieldNames[NumFields];
7482
7483 // unsigned char gpr;
7484 FieldTypes[0] = Context->UnsignedCharTy;
7485 FieldNames[0] = "gpr";
7486
7487 // unsigned char fpr;
7488 FieldTypes[1] = Context->UnsignedCharTy;
7489 FieldNames[1] = "fpr";
7490
7491 // unsigned short reserved;
7492 FieldTypes[2] = Context->UnsignedShortTy;
7493 FieldNames[2] = "reserved";
7494
7495 // void* overflow_arg_area;
7496 FieldTypes[3] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
7497 FieldNames[3] = "overflow_arg_area";
7498
7499 // void* reg_save_area;
7500 FieldTypes[4] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
7501 FieldNames[4] = "reg_save_area";
7502
7503 // Create fields
7504 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumFields; ++i) {
7505 FieldDecl *Field = FieldDecl::Create(*Context, VaListTagDecl,
7506 SourceLocation(),
7507 SourceLocation(),
7508 &Context->Idents.get(FieldNames[i]),
7509 FieldTypes[i], /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
7510 /*BitWidth=*/nullptr,
7511 /*Mutable=*/false,
7512 ICIS_NoInit);
7513 Field->setAccess(AS_public);
7514 VaListTagDecl->addDecl(Field);
7515 }
7516 VaListTagDecl->completeDefinition();
7517 Context->VaListTagDecl = VaListTagDecl;
7518 QualType VaListTagType = Context->getRecordType(VaListTagDecl);
7519
7520 // } __va_list_tag;
7521 TypedefDecl *VaListTagTypedefDecl =
7522 Context->buildImplicitTypedef(VaListTagType, "__va_list_tag");
7523
7524 QualType VaListTagTypedefType =
7525 Context->getTypedefType(VaListTagTypedefDecl);
7526
7527 // typedef __va_list_tag __builtin_va_list[1];
7528 llvm::APInt Size(Context->getTypeSize(Context->getSizeType()), 1);
7529 QualType VaListTagArrayType
7530 = Context->getConstantArrayType(VaListTagTypedefType,
7531 Size, ArrayType::Normal, 0);
7532 return Context->buildImplicitTypedef(VaListTagArrayType, "__builtin_va_list");
7533}
7534
7535static TypedefDecl *
7536CreateX86_64ABIBuiltinVaListDecl(const ASTContext *Context) {
7537 // struct __va_list_tag {
7538 RecordDecl *VaListTagDecl;
7539 VaListTagDecl = Context->buildImplicitRecord("__va_list_tag");
7540 VaListTagDecl->startDefinition();
7541
7542 const size_t NumFields = 4;
7543 QualType FieldTypes[NumFields];
7544 const char *FieldNames[NumFields];
7545
7546 // unsigned gp_offset;
7547 FieldTypes[0] = Context->UnsignedIntTy;
7548 FieldNames[0] = "gp_offset";
7549
7550 // unsigned fp_offset;
7551 FieldTypes[1] = Context->UnsignedIntTy;
7552 FieldNames[1] = "fp_offset";
7553
7554 // void* overflow_arg_area;
7555 FieldTypes[2] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
7556 FieldNames[2] = "overflow_arg_area";
7557
7558 // void* reg_save_area;
7559 FieldTypes[3] = Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy);
7560 FieldNames[3] = "reg_save_area";
7561
7562 // Create fields
7563 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumFields; ++i) {
7564 FieldDecl *Field = FieldDecl::Create(const_cast<ASTContext &>(*Context),
7565 VaListTagDecl,
7566 SourceLocation(),
7567 SourceLocation(),
7568 &Context->Idents.get(FieldNames[i]),
7569 FieldTypes[i], /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
7570 /*BitWidth=*/nullptr,
7571 /*Mutable=*/false,
7572 ICIS_NoInit);
7573 Field->setAccess(AS_public);
7574 VaListTagDecl->addDecl(Field);
7575 }
7576 VaListTagDecl->completeDefinition();
7577 Context->VaListTagDecl = VaListTagDecl;
7578 QualType VaListTagType = Context->getRecordType(VaListTagDecl);
7579
7580 // };
7581
7582 // typedef struct __va_list_tag __builtin_va_list[1];
7583 llvm::APInt Size(Context->getTypeSize(Context->getSizeType()), 1);
7584 QualType VaListTagArrayType =
7585 Context->getConstantArrayType(VaListTagType, Size, ArrayType::Normal, 0);
7586 return Context->buildImplicitTypedef(VaListTagArrayType, "__builtin_va_list");
7587}

7597static TypedefDecl *
7598CreateAAPCSABIBuiltinVaListDecl(const ASTContext *Context) {
7599 // struct __va_list
7600 RecordDecl *VaListDecl = Context->buildImplicitRecord("__va_list");
7601 if (Context->getLangOpts().CPlusPlus) {
7602 // namespace std { struct __va_list {
7603 NamespaceDecl *NS;
7604 NS = NamespaceDecl::Create(const_cast<ASTContext &>(*Context),
7605 Context->getTranslationUnitDecl(),
7606 /*Inline*/false, SourceLocation(),
7607 SourceLocation(), &Context->Idents.get("std"),
7608 /*PrevDecl*/ nullptr);
7609 NS->setImplicit();
7610 VaListDecl->setDeclContext(NS);
7611 }
7612
7613 VaListDecl->startDefinition();
7614
7615 // void * __ap;
7616 FieldDecl *Field = FieldDecl::Create(const_cast<ASTContext &>(*Context),
7617 VaListDecl,
7618 SourceLocation(),
7619 SourceLocation(),
7620 &Context->Idents.get("__ap"),
7621 Context->getPointerType(Context->VoidTy),
7622 /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
7623 /*BitWidth=*/nullptr,
7624 /*Mutable=*/false,
7625 ICIS_NoInit);
7626 Field->setAccess(AS_public);
7627 VaListDecl->addDecl(Field);
7628
7629 // };
7630 VaListDecl->completeDefinition();
7631 Context->VaListTagDecl = VaListDecl;
7632
7633 // typedef struct __va_list __builtin_va_list;
7634 QualType T = Context->getRecordType(VaListDecl);
7635 return Context->buildImplicitTypedef(T, "__builtin_va_list");
7636}

7659 FieldNames[2] = "__overflow_arg_area";

7663 FieldNames[3] = "__reg_save_area";

7668 VaListTagDecl,
7669 SourceLocation(),
7670 SourceLocation(),
7671 &Context->Idents.get(FieldNames[i]),
7672 FieldTypes[i], /*TInfo=*/nullptr,
7673 /*BitWidth=*/nullptr,
7674 /*Mutable=*/false,

7692
7693static TypedefDecl *CreateVaListDecl(const ASTContext *Context,
7694 TargetInfo::BuiltinVaListKind Kind) {
7695 switch (Kind) {
7696 case TargetInfo::CharPtrBuiltinVaList:
7697 return CreateCharPtrBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
7698 case TargetInfo::VoidPtrBuiltinVaList:
7699 return CreateVoidPtrBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
7700 case TargetInfo::AArch64ABIBuiltinVaList:
7701 return CreateAArch64ABIBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
7702 case TargetInfo::PowerABIBuiltinVaList:
7703 return CreatePowerABIBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
7704 case TargetInfo::X86_64ABIBuiltinVaList:
7705 return CreateX86_64ABIBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
7706 case TargetInfo::PNaClABIBuiltinVaList:
7707 return CreatePNaClABIBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
7708 case TargetInfo::AAPCSABIBuiltinVaList:
7709 return CreateAAPCSABIBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
7710 case TargetInfo::SystemZBuiltinVaList:
7711 return CreateSystemZBuiltinVaListDecl(Context);
7712 }
7713
7714 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled __builtin_va_list type kind");
7715}
7716
7717TypedefDecl *ASTContext::getBuiltinVaListDecl() const {
7718 if (!BuiltinVaListDecl) {
7719 BuiltinVaListDecl = CreateVaListDecl(this, Target->getBuiltinVaListKind());
7720 assert(BuiltinVaListDecl->isImplicit());
7721 }
7722
7723 return BuiltinVaListDecl;
7724}
7725
7726Decl *ASTContext::getVaListTagDecl() const {
7727 // Force the creation of VaListTagDecl by building the __builtin_va_list
7728 // declaration.
7729 if (!VaListTagDecl)
7730 (void)getBuiltinVaListDecl();
7731
7732 return VaListTagDecl;
7733}
7734
7735TypedefDecl *ASTContext::getBuiltinMSVaListDecl() const {
7736 if (!BuiltinMSVaListDecl)
7737 BuiltinMSVaListDecl = CreateMSVaListDecl(this);
7738
7739 return BuiltinMSVaListDecl;
7740}

7752
7753/// Retrieve the template name that corresponds to a non-empty
7754/// lookup.
7755TemplateName
7756ASTContext::getOverloadedTemplateName(UnresolvedSetIterator Begin,
7757 UnresolvedSetIterator End) const {
7758 unsigned size = End - Begin;
7759 assert(size > 1 && "set is not overloaded!");
7760
7761 void *memory = Allocate(sizeof(OverloadedTemplateStorage) +
7762 size * sizeof(FunctionTemplateDecl*));
7763 auto *OT = new (memory) OverloadedTemplateStorage(size);
7764
7765 NamedDecl **Storage = OT->getStorage();
7766 for (UnresolvedSetIterator I = Begin; I != End; ++I) {
7767 NamedDecl *D = *I;
7768 assert(isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D) ||
7769 isa<UnresolvedUsingValueDecl>(D) ||
7770 (isa<UsingShadowDecl>(D) &&
7771 isa<FunctionTemplateDecl>(D->getUnderlyingDecl())));
7772 *Storage++ = D;
7773 }
7774
7775 return TemplateName(OT);
7776}
7777
7778/// Retrieve a template name representing an unqualified-id that has been
7779/// assumed to name a template for ADL purposes.
7780TemplateName ASTContext::getAssumedTemplateName(DeclarationName Name) const {
7781 auto *OT = new (*this) AssumedTemplateStorage(Name);
7782 return TemplateName(OT);
7783}
7784
7785/// Retrieve the template name that represents a qualified
7786/// template name such as \c std::vector.
7787TemplateName
7788ASTContext::getQualifiedTemplateName(NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
7789 bool TemplateKeyword,
7790 TemplateDecl *Template) const {
7791 assert(NNS && "Missing nested-name-specifier in qualified template name");
7792
7793 // FIXME: Canonicalization?
7794 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
7795 QualifiedTemplateName::Profile(ID, NNS, TemplateKeyword, Template);
7796
7797 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
7798 QualifiedTemplateName *QTN =
7799 QualifiedTemplateNames.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
7800 if (!QTN) {
7801 QTN = new (*this, alignof(QualifiedTemplateName))
7802 QualifiedTemplateName(NNS, TemplateKeyword, Template);
7803 QualifiedTemplateNames.InsertNode(QTN, InsertPos);
7804 }
7805
7806 return TemplateName(QTN);
7807}
7808
7809/// Retrieve the template name that represents a dependent
7810/// template name such as \c MetaFun::template apply.
7811TemplateName
7812ASTContext::getDependentTemplateName(NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
7813 const IdentifierInfo *Name) const {
7814 assert((!NNS || NNS->isDependent()) &&
7815 "Nested name specifier must be dependent");
7816
7817 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
7818 DependentTemplateName::Profile(ID, NNS, Name);
7819
7820 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
7821 DependentTemplateName *QTN =
7822 DependentTemplateNames.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
7823
7824 if (QTN)
7825 return TemplateName(QTN);
7826
7827 NestedNameSpecifier *CanonNNS = getCanonicalNestedNameSpecifier(NNS);
7828 if (CanonNNS == NNS) {
7829 QTN = new (*this, alignof(DependentTemplateName))
7830 DependentTemplateName(NNS, Name);
7831 } else {
7832 TemplateName Canon = getDependentTemplateName(CanonNNS, Name);
7833 QTN = new (*this, alignof(DependentTemplateName))
7834 DependentTemplateName(NNS, Name, Canon);
7835 DependentTemplateName *CheckQTN =
7836 DependentTemplateNames.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
7837 assert(!CheckQTN && "Dependent type name canonicalization broken");
7838 (void)CheckQTN;
7839 }
7840
7841 DependentTemplateNames.InsertNode(QTN, InsertPos);
7842 return TemplateName(QTN);
7843}
7844
7845/// Retrieve the template name that represents a dependent
7846/// template name such as \c MetaFun::template operator+.
7847TemplateName
7848ASTContext::getDependentTemplateName(NestedNameSpecifier *NNS,
7849 OverloadedOperatorKind Operator) const {
7850 assert((!NNS || NNS->isDependent()) &&
7851 "Nested name specifier must be dependent");
7852
7853 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
7854 DependentTemplateName::Profile(ID, NNS, Operator);
7855
7856 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
7857 DependentTemplateName *QTN
7858 = DependentTemplateNames.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
7859
7860 if (QTN)
7861 return TemplateName(QTN);
7862
7863 NestedNameSpecifier *CanonNNS = getCanonicalNestedNameSpecifier(NNS);
7864 if (CanonNNS == NNS) {
7865 QTN = new (*this, alignof(DependentTemplateName))
7866 DependentTemplateName(NNS, Operator);
7867 } else {
7868 TemplateName Canon = getDependentTemplateName(CanonNNS, Operator);
7869 QTN = new (*this, alignof(DependentTemplateName))
7870 DependentTemplateName(NNS, Operator, Canon);
7871
7872 DependentTemplateName *CheckQTN
7873 = DependentTemplateNames.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
7874 assert(!CheckQTN && "Dependent template name canonicalization broken");
7875 (void)CheckQTN;
7876 }
7877
7878 DependentTemplateNames.InsertNode(QTN, InsertPos);
7879 return TemplateName(QTN);
7880}
7881
7882TemplateName
7883ASTContext::getSubstTemplateTemplateParm(TemplateTemplateParmDecl *param,
7884 TemplateName replacement) const {
7885 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
7886 SubstTemplateTemplateParmStorage::Profile(ID, param, replacement);
7887
7888 void *insertPos = nullptr;
7889 SubstTemplateTemplateParmStorage *subst
7890 = SubstTemplateTemplateParms.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, insertPos);
7891
7892 if (!subst) {
7893 subst = new (*this) SubstTemplateTemplateParmStorage(param, replacement);
7894 SubstTemplateTemplateParms.InsertNode(subst, insertPos);
7895 }
7896
7897 return TemplateName(subst);
7898}
7899
7900TemplateName
7901ASTContext::getSubstTemplateTemplateParmPack(TemplateTemplateParmDecl *Param,
7902 const TemplateArgument &ArgPack) const {
7903 auto &Self = const_cast<ASTContext &>(*this);
7904 llvm::FoldingSetNodeID ID;
7905 SubstTemplateTemplateParmPackStorage::Profile(ID, Self, Param, ArgPack);
7906
7907 void *InsertPos = nullptr;
7908 SubstTemplateTemplateParmPackStorage *Subst
7909 = SubstTemplateTemplateParmPacks.FindNodeOrInsertPos(ID, InsertPos);
7910
7911 if (!Subst) {
7912 Subst = new (*this) SubstTemplateTemplateParmPackStorage(Param,
7913 ArgPack.pack_size(),
7914 ArgPack.pack_begin());
7915 SubstTemplateTemplateParmPacks.InsertNode(Subst, InsertPos);
7916 }
7917
7918 return TemplateName(Subst);
7919}
7920
7921/// getFromTargetType - Given one of the integer types provided by
7922/// TargetInfo, produce the corresponding type. The unsigned @p Type
7923/// is actually a value of type @c TargetInfo::IntType.
7924CanQualType ASTContext::getFromTargetType(unsigned Type) const {
7925 switch (Type) {
7926 case TargetInfo::NoInt: return {};
7927 case TargetInfo::SignedChar: return SignedCharTy;
7928 case TargetInfo::UnsignedChar: return UnsignedCharTy;
7929 case TargetInfo::SignedShort: return ShortTy;
7930 case TargetInfo::UnsignedShort: return UnsignedShortTy;
7931 case TargetInfo::SignedInt: return IntTy;
7932 case TargetInfo::UnsignedInt: return UnsignedIntTy;
7933 case TargetInfo::SignedLong: return LongTy;
7934 case TargetInfo::UnsignedLong: return UnsignedLongTy;
7935 case TargetInfo::SignedLongLong: return LongLongTy;
7936 case TargetInfo::UnsignedLongLong: return UnsignedLongLongTy;
7937 case TargetInfo::SignedIntCap: return IntCapTy;
7938 case TargetInfo::UnsignedIntCap: return UnsignedIntCapTy;
7939 }
7940
7941 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled TargetInfo::IntType value");
7942}
7943
7944//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7945// Type Predicates.
7946//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7947
7948/// getObjCGCAttr - Returns one of GCNone, Weak or Strong objc's
7949/// garbage collection attribute.
7950///
7951Qualifiers::GC ASTContext::getObjCGCAttrKind(QualType Ty) const {
7952 if (getLangOpts().getGC() == LangOptions::NonGC)
7953 return Qualifiers::GCNone;
7954
7955 assert(getLangOpts().ObjC);
7956 Qualifiers::GC GCAttrs = Ty.getObjCGCAttr();
7957
7958 // Default behaviour under objective-C's gc is for ObjC pointers
7959 // (or pointers to them) be treated as though they were declared
7960 // as __strong.
7961 if (GCAttrs == Qualifiers::GCNone) {
7962 if (Ty->isObjCObjectPointerType() || Ty->isBlockPointerType())
7963 return Qualifiers::Strong;
7964 else if (Ty->isPointerType())
7965 return getObjCGCAttrKind(Ty->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType());
7966 } else {
7967 // It's not valid to set GC attributes on anything that isn't a
7968 // pointer.
7969#ifndef NDEBUG
7970 QualType CT = Ty->getCanonicalTypeInternal();
7971 while (const auto *AT = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(CT))
7972 CT = AT->getElementType();
7973 assert(CT->isAnyPointerType() || CT->isBlockPointerType());
7974#endif
7975 }
7976 return GCAttrs;
7977}
7978
7979//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7980// Type Compatibility Testing
7981//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7982
7983/// areCompatVectorTypes - Return true if the two specified vector types are
7984/// compatible.
7985static bool areCompatVectorTypes(const VectorType *LHS,
7986 const VectorType *RHS) {
7987 assert(LHS->isCanonicalUnqualified() && RHS->isCanonicalUnqualified());
7988 return LHS->getElementType() == RHS->getElementType() &&
7989 LHS->getNumElements() == RHS->getNumElements();
7990}
7991
7992bool ASTContext::areCompatibleVectorTypes(QualType FirstVec,
7993 QualType SecondVec) {
7994 assert(FirstVec->isVectorType() && "FirstVec should be a vector type");
7995 assert(SecondVec->isVectorType() && "SecondVec should be a vector type");
7996
7997 if (hasSameUnqualifiedType(FirstVec, SecondVec))
7998 return true;
7999
8000 // Treat Neon vector types and most AltiVec vector types as if they are the
8001 // equivalent GCC vector types.
8002 const auto *First = FirstVec->getAs<VectorType>();
8003 const auto *Second = SecondVec->getAs<VectorType>();
8004 if (First->getNumElements() == Second->getNumElements() &&
8005 hasSameType(First->getElementType(), Second->getElementType()) &&
8006 First->getVectorKind() != VectorType::AltiVecPixel &&
8007 First->getVectorKind() != VectorType::AltiVecBool &&
8008 Second->getVectorKind() != VectorType::AltiVecPixel &&
8009 Second->getVectorKind() != VectorType::AltiVecBool)
8010 return true;
8011
8012 return false;
8013}
8014
8015//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8016// ObjCQualifiedIdTypesAreCompatible - Compatibility testing for qualified id's.
8017//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8018
8019/// ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol - return 'true' if 'lProto' is in the
8020/// inheritance hierarchy of 'rProto'.
8021bool
8022ASTContext::ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(ObjCProtocolDecl *lProto,
8023 ObjCProtocolDecl *rProto) const {
8024 if (declaresSameEntity(lProto, rProto))
8025 return true;
8026 for (auto *PI : rProto->protocols())
8027 if (ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(lProto, PI))
8028 return true;
8029 return false;
8030}
8031
8032/// ObjCQualifiedClassTypesAreCompatible - compare Class<pr,...> and
8033/// Class<pr1, ...>.
8034bool ASTContext::ObjCQualifiedClassTypesAreCompatible(QualType lhs,
8035 QualType rhs) {
8036 const auto *lhsQID = lhs->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
8037 const auto *rhsOPT = rhs->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
8038 assert((lhsQID && rhsOPT) && "ObjCQualifiedClassTypesAreCompatible");
8039
8040 for (auto *lhsProto : lhsQID->quals()) {
8041 bool match = false;
8042 for (auto *rhsProto : rhsOPT->quals()) {
8043 if (ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(lhsProto, rhsProto)) {
8044 match = true;
8045 break;
8046 }
8047 }
8048 if (!match)
8049 return false;
8050 }
8051 return true;
8052}
8053
8054/// ObjCQualifiedIdTypesAreCompatible - We know that one of lhs/rhs is an
8055/// ObjCQualifiedIDType.
8056bool ASTContext::ObjCQualifiedIdTypesAreCompatible(QualType lhs, QualType rhs,
8057 bool compare) {
8058 // Allow id<P..> and an 'id' or void* type in all cases.
8059 if (lhs->isVoidPointerType() ||
8060 lhs->isObjCIdType() || lhs->isObjCClassType())
8061 return true;
8062 else if (rhs->isVoidPointerType() ||
8063 rhs->isObjCIdType() || rhs->isObjCClassType())
8064 return true;
8065
8066 if (const ObjCObjectPointerType *lhsQID = lhs->getAsObjCQualifiedIdType()) {
8067 const auto *rhsOPT = rhs->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
8068
8069 if (!rhsOPT) return false;
8070
8071 if (rhsOPT->qual_empty()) {
8072 // If the RHS is a unqualified interface pointer "NSString*",
8073 // make sure we check the class hierarchy.
8074 if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *rhsID = rhsOPT->getInterfaceDecl()) {
8075 for (auto *I : lhsQID->quals()) {
8076 // when comparing an id<P> on lhs with a static type on rhs,
8077 // see if static class implements all of id's protocols, directly or
8078 // through its super class and categories.
8079 if (!rhsID->ClassImplementsProtocol(I, true))
8080 return false;
8081 }
8082 }
8083 // If there are no qualifiers and no interface, we have an 'id'.
8084 return true;
8085 }
8086 // Both the right and left sides have qualifiers.
8087 for (auto *lhsProto : lhsQID->quals()) {
8088 bool match = false;
8089
8090 // when comparing an id<P> on lhs with a static type on rhs,
8091 // see if static class implements all of id's protocols, directly or
8092 // through its super class and categories.
8093 for (auto *rhsProto : rhsOPT->quals()) {
8094 if (ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(lhsProto, rhsProto) ||
8095 (compare && ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(rhsProto, lhsProto))) {
8096 match = true;
8097 break;
8098 }
8099 }
8100 // If the RHS is a qualified interface pointer "NSString<P>*",
8101 // make sure we check the class hierarchy.
8102 if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *rhsID = rhsOPT->getInterfaceDecl()) {
8103 for (auto *I : lhsQID->quals()) {
8104 // when comparing an id<P> on lhs with a static type on rhs,
8105 // see if static class implements all of id's protocols, directly or
8106 // through its super class and categories.
8107 if (rhsID->ClassImplementsProtocol(I, true)) {
8108 match = true;
8109 break;
8110 }
8111 }
8112 }
8113 if (!match)
8114 return false;
8115 }
8116
8117 return true;
8118 }
8119
8120 const ObjCObjectPointerType *rhsQID = rhs->getAsObjCQualifiedIdType();
8121 assert(rhsQID && "One of the LHS/RHS should be id<x>");
8122
8123 if (const ObjCObjectPointerType *lhsOPT =
8124 lhs->getAsObjCInterfacePointerType()) {
8125 // If both the right and left sides have qualifiers.
8126 for (auto *lhsProto : lhsOPT->quals()) {
8127 bool match = false;
8128
8129 // when comparing an id<P> on rhs with a static type on lhs,
8130 // see if static class implements all of id's protocols, directly or
8131 // through its super class and categories.
8132 // First, lhs protocols in the qualifier list must be found, direct
8133 // or indirect in rhs's qualifier list or it is a mismatch.
8134 for (auto *rhsProto : rhsQID->quals()) {
8135 if (ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(lhsProto, rhsProto) ||
8136 (compare && ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(rhsProto, lhsProto))) {
8137 match = true;
8138 break;
8139 }
8140 }
8141 if (!match)
8142 return false;
8143 }
8144
8145 // Static class's protocols, or its super class or category protocols
8146 // must be found, direct or indirect in rhs's qualifier list or it is a mismatch.
8147 if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *lhsID = lhsOPT->getInterfaceDecl()) {
8148 llvm::SmallPtrSet<ObjCProtocolDecl *, 8> LHSInheritedProtocols;
8149 CollectInheritedProtocols(lhsID, LHSInheritedProtocols);
8150 // This is rather dubious but matches gcc's behavior. If lhs has
8151 // no type qualifier and its class has no static protocol(s)
8152 // assume that it is mismatch.
8153 if (LHSInheritedProtocols.empty() && lhsOPT->qual_empty())
8154 return false;
8155 for (auto *lhsProto : LHSInheritedProtocols) {
8156 bool match = false;
8157 for (auto *rhsProto : rhsQID->quals()) {
8158 if (ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(lhsProto, rhsProto) ||
8159 (compare && ProtocolCompatibleWithProtocol(rhsProto, lhsProto))) {
8160 match = true;
8161 break;
8162 }
8163 }
8164 if (!match)
8165 return false;
8166 }
8167 }
8168 return true;
8169 }
8170 return false;
8171}
8172
8173/// canAssignObjCInterfaces - Return true if the two interface types are
8174/// compatible for assignment from RHS to LHS. This handles validation of any
8175/// protocol qualifiers on the LHS or RHS.
8176bool ASTContext::canAssignObjCInterfaces(const ObjCObjectPointerType *LHSOPT,
8177 const ObjCObjectPointerType *RHSOPT) {
8178 const ObjCObjectType* LHS = LHSOPT->getObjectType();
8179 const ObjCObjectType* RHS = RHSOPT->getObjectType();
8180
8181 // If either type represents the built-in 'id' or 'Class' types, return true.
8182 if (LHS->isObjCUnqualifiedIdOrClass() ||
8183 RHS->isObjCUnqualifiedIdOrClass())
8184 return true;
8185
8186 // Function object that propagates a successful result or handles
8187 // __kindof types.
8188 auto finish = [&](bool succeeded) -> bool {
8189 if (succeeded)
8190 return true;
8191
8192 if (!RHS->isKindOfType())
8193 return false;
8194
8195 // Strip off __kindof and protocol qualifiers, then check whether
8196 // we can assign the other way.
8197 return canAssignObjCInterfaces(RHSOPT->stripObjCKindOfTypeAndQuals(*this),
8198 LHSOPT->stripObjCKindOfTypeAndQuals(*this));
8199 };
8200
8201 if (LHS->isObjCQualifiedId() || RHS->isObjCQualifiedId()) {
8202 return finish(ObjCQualifiedIdTypesAreCompatible(QualType(LHSOPT,0),
8203 QualType(RHSOPT,0),
8204 false));
8205 }
8206
8207 if (LHS->isObjCQualifiedClass() && RHS->isObjCQualifiedClass()) {
8208 return finish(ObjCQualifiedClassTypesAreCompatible(QualType(LHSOPT,0),
8209 QualType(RHSOPT,0)));
8210 }
8211
8212 // If we have 2 user-defined types, fall into that path.
8213 if (LHS->getInterface() && RHS->getInterface()) {
8214 return finish(canAssignObjCInterfaces(LHS, RHS));
8215 }
8216
8217 return false;
8218}
8219
8220/// canAssignObjCInterfacesInBlockPointer - This routine is specifically written
8221/// for providing type-safety for objective-c pointers used to pass/return
8222/// arguments in block literals. When passed as arguments, passing 'A*' where
8223/// 'id' is expected is not OK. Passing 'Sub *" where 'Super *" is expected is
8224/// not OK. For the return type, the opposite is not OK.
8225bool ASTContext::canAssignObjCInterfacesInBlockPointer(
8226 const ObjCObjectPointerType *LHSOPT,
8227 const ObjCObjectPointerType *RHSOPT,
8228 bool BlockReturnType) {
8229
8230 // Function object that propagates a successful result or handles
8231 // __kindof types.
8232 auto finish = [&](bool succeeded) -> bool {
8233 if (succeeded)
8234 return true;
8235
8236 const ObjCObjectPointerType *Expected = BlockReturnType ? RHSOPT : LHSOPT;
8237 if (!Expected->isKindOfType())
8238 return false;
8239
8240 // Strip off __kindof and protocol qualifiers, then check whether
8241 // we can assign the other way.
8242 return canAssignObjCInterfacesInBlockPointer(
8243 RHSOPT->stripObjCKindOfTypeAndQuals(*this),
8244 LHSOPT->stripObjCKindOfTypeAndQuals(*this),
8245 BlockReturnType);
8246 };
8247
8248 if (RHSOPT->isObjCBuiltinType() || LHSOPT->isObjCIdType())
8249 return true;
8250
8251 if (LHSOPT->isObjCBuiltinType()) {
8252 return finish(RHSOPT->isObjCBuiltinType() ||
8253 RHSOPT->isObjCQualifiedIdType());
8254 }
8255
8256 if (LHSOPT->isObjCQualifiedIdType() || RHSOPT->isObjCQualifiedIdType())
8257 return finish(ObjCQualifiedIdTypesAreCompatible(QualType(LHSOPT,0),
8258 QualType(RHSOPT,0),
8259 false));
8260
8261 const ObjCInterfaceType* LHS = LHSOPT->getInterfaceType();
8262 const ObjCInterfaceType* RHS = RHSOPT->getInterfaceType();
8263 if (LHS && RHS) { // We have 2 user-defined types.
8264 if (LHS != RHS) {
8265 if (LHS->getDecl()->isSuperClassOf(RHS->getDecl()))
8266 return finish(BlockReturnType);
8267 if (RHS->getDecl()->isSuperClassOf(LHS->getDecl()))
8268 return finish(!BlockReturnType);
8269 }
8270 else
8271 return true;
8272 }
8273 return false;
8274}
8275
8276/// Comparison routine for Objective-C protocols to be used with
8277/// llvm::array_pod_sort.
8278static int compareObjCProtocolsByName(ObjCProtocolDecl * const *lhs,
8279 ObjCProtocolDecl * const *rhs) {
8280 return (*lhs)->getName().compare((*rhs)->getName());
8281}
8282
8283/// getIntersectionOfProtocols - This routine finds the intersection of set
8284/// of protocols inherited from two distinct objective-c pointer objects with
8285/// the given common base.
8286/// It is used to build composite qualifier list of the composite type of
8287/// the conditional expression involving two objective-c pointer objects.
8288static
8289void getIntersectionOfProtocols(ASTContext &Context,
8290 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *CommonBase,
8291 const ObjCObjectPointerType *LHSOPT,
8292 const ObjCObjectPointerType *RHSOPT,
8293 SmallVectorImpl<ObjCProtocolDecl *> &IntersectionSet) {
8294
8295 const ObjCObjectType* LHS = LHSOPT->getObjectType();
8296 const ObjCObjectType* RHS = RHSOPT->getObjectType();
8297 assert(LHS->getInterface() && "LHS must have an interface base");
8298 assert(RHS->getInterface() && "RHS must have an interface base");
8299
8300 // Add all of the protocols for the LHS.
8301 llvm::SmallPtrSet<ObjCProtocolDecl *, 8> LHSProtocolSet;
8302
8303 // Start with the protocol qualifiers.
8304 for (auto proto : LHS->quals()) {
8305 Context.CollectInheritedProtocols(proto, LHSProtocolSet);
8306 }
8307
8308 // Also add the protocols associated with the LHS interface.
8309 Context.CollectInheritedProtocols(LHS->getInterface(), LHSProtocolSet);
8310
8311 // Add all of the protocols for the RHS.
8312 llvm::SmallPtrSet<ObjCProtocolDecl *, 8> RHSProtocolSet;
8313
8314 // Start with the protocol qualifiers.
8315 for (auto proto : RHS->quals()) {
8316 Context.CollectInheritedProtocols(proto, RHSProtocolSet);
8317 }
8318
8319 // Also add the protocols associated with the RHS interface.
8320 Context.CollectInheritedProtocols(RHS->getInterface(), RHSProtocolSet);
8321
8322 // Compute the intersection of the collected protocol sets.
8323 for (auto proto : LHSProtocolSet) {
8324 if (RHSProtocolSet.count(proto))
8325 IntersectionSet.push_back(proto);
8326 }
8327
8328 // Compute the set of protocols that is implied by either the common type or
8329 // the protocols within the intersection.
8330 llvm::SmallPtrSet<ObjCProtocolDecl *, 8> ImpliedProtocols;
8331 Context.CollectInheritedProtocols(CommonBase, ImpliedProtocols);
8332
8333 // Remove any implied protocols from the list of inherited protocols.
8334 if (!ImpliedProtocols.empty()) {
8335 IntersectionSet.erase(
8336 std::remove_if(IntersectionSet.begin(),
8337 IntersectionSet.end(),
8338 [&](ObjCProtocolDecl *proto) -> bool {
8339 return ImpliedProtocols.count(proto) > 0;
8340 }),
8341 IntersectionSet.end());
8342 }
8343
8344 // Sort the remaining protocols by name.
8345 llvm::array_pod_sort(IntersectionSet.begin(), IntersectionSet.end(),
8346 compareObjCProtocolsByName);
8347}
8348
8349/// Determine whether the first type is a subtype of the second.
8350static bool canAssignObjCObjectTypes(ASTContext &ctx, QualType lhs,
8351 QualType rhs) {
8352 // Common case: two object pointers.
8353 const auto *lhsOPT = lhs->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
8354 const auto *rhsOPT = rhs->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
8355 if (lhsOPT && rhsOPT)
8356 return ctx.canAssignObjCInterfaces(lhsOPT, rhsOPT);
8357
8358 // Two block pointers.
8359 const auto *lhsBlock = lhs->getAs<BlockPointerType>();
8360 const auto *rhsBlock = rhs->getAs<BlockPointerType>();
8361 if (lhsBlock && rhsBlock)
8362 return ctx.typesAreBlockPointerCompatible(lhs, rhs);
8363
8364 // If either is an unqualified 'id' and the other is a block, it's
8365 // acceptable.
8366 if ((lhsOPT && lhsOPT->isObjCIdType() && rhsBlock) ||
8367 (rhsOPT && rhsOPT->isObjCIdType() && lhsBlock))
8368 return true;
8369
8370 return false;
8371}
8372
8373// Check that the given Objective-C type argument lists are equivalent.
8374static bool sameObjCTypeArgs(ASTContext &ctx,
8375 const ObjCInterfaceDecl *iface,
8376 ArrayRef<QualType> lhsArgs,
8377 ArrayRef<QualType> rhsArgs,
8378 bool stripKindOf) {
8379 if (lhsArgs.size() != rhsArgs.size())
8380 return false;
8381
8382 ObjCTypeParamList *typeParams = iface->getTypeParamList();
8383 for (unsigned i = 0, n = lhsArgs.size(); i != n; ++i) {
8384 if (ctx.hasSameType(lhsArgs[i], rhsArgs[i]))
8385 continue;
8386
8387 switch (typeParams->begin()[i]->getVariance()) {
8388 case ObjCTypeParamVariance::Invariant:
8389 if (!stripKindOf ||
8390 !ctx.hasSameType(lhsArgs[i].stripObjCKindOfType(ctx),
8391 rhsArgs[i].stripObjCKindOfType(ctx))) {
8392 return false;
8393 }
8394 break;
8395
8396 case ObjCTypeParamVariance::Covariant:
8397 if (!canAssignObjCObjectTypes(ctx, lhsArgs[i], rhsArgs[i]))
8398 return false;
8399 break;
8400
8401 case ObjCTypeParamVariance::Contravariant:
8402 if (!canAssignObjCObjectTypes(ctx, rhsArgs[i], lhsArgs[i]))
8403 return false;
8404 break;
8405 }
8406 }
8407
8408 return true;
8409}
8410
8411QualType ASTContext::areCommonBaseCompatible(
8412 const ObjCObjectPointerType *Lptr,
8413 const ObjCObjectPointerType *Rptr) {
8414 const ObjCObjectType *LHS = Lptr->getObjectType();
8415 const ObjCObjectType *RHS = Rptr->getObjectType();
8416 const ObjCInterfaceDecl* LDecl = LHS->getInterface();
8417 const ObjCInterfaceDecl* RDecl = RHS->getInterface();
8418
8419 if (!LDecl || !RDecl)
8420 return {};
8421
8422 // When either LHS or RHS is a kindof type, we should return a kindof type.
8423 // For example, for common base of kindof(ASub1) and kindof(ASub2), we return
8424 // kindof(A).
8425 bool anyKindOf = LHS->isKindOfType() || RHS->isKindOfType();
8426
8427 // Follow the left-hand side up the class hierarchy until we either hit a
8428 // root or find the RHS. Record the ancestors in case we don't find it.
8429 llvm::SmallDenseMap<const ObjCInterfaceDecl *, const ObjCObjectType *, 4>
8430 LHSAncestors;
8431 while (true) {
8432 // Record this ancestor. We'll need this if the common type isn't in the
8433 // path from the LHS to the root.
8434 LHSAncestors[LHS->getInterface()->getCanonicalDecl()] = LHS;
8435
8436 if (declaresSameEntity(LHS->getInterface(), RDecl)) {
8437 // Get the type arguments.
8438 ArrayRef<QualType> LHSTypeArgs = LHS->getTypeArgsAsWritten();
8439 bool anyChanges = false;
8440 if (LHS->isSpecialized() && RHS->isSpecialized()) {
8441 // Both have type arguments, compare them.
8442 if (!sameObjCTypeArgs(*this, LHS->getInterface(),
8443 LHS->getTypeArgs(), RHS->getTypeArgs(),
8444 /*stripKindOf=*/true))
8445 return {};
8446 } else if (LHS->isSpecialized() != RHS->isSpecialized()) {
8447 // If only one has type arguments, the result will not have type
8448 // arguments.
8449 LHSTypeArgs = {};
8450 anyChanges = true;
8451 }
8452
8453 // Compute the intersection of protocols.
8454 SmallVector<ObjCProtocolDecl *, 8> Protocols;
8455 getIntersectionOfProtocols(*this, LHS->getInterface(), Lptr, Rptr,
8456 Protocols);
8457 if (!Protocols.empty())
8458 anyChanges = true;
8459
8460 // If anything in the LHS will have changed, build a new result type.
8461 // If we need to return a kindof type but LHS is not a kindof type, we
8462 // build a new result type.
8463 if (anyChanges || LHS->isKindOfType() != anyKindOf) {
8464 QualType Result = getObjCInterfaceType(LHS->getInterface());
8465 Result = getObjCObjectType(Result, LHSTypeArgs, Protocols,
8466 anyKindOf || LHS->isKindOfType());
8467 return getObjCObjectPointerType(Result);
8468 }
8469
8470 return getObjCObjectPointerType(QualType(LHS, 0));
8471 }
8472
8473 // Find the superclass.
8474 QualType LHSSuperType = LHS->getSuperClassType();
8475 if (LHSSuperType.isNull())
8476 break;
8477
8478 LHS = LHSSuperType->castAs<ObjCObjectType>();
8479 }
8480
8481 // We didn't find anything by following the LHS to its root; now check
8482 // the RHS against the cached set of ancestors.
8483 while (true) {
8484 auto KnownLHS = LHSAncestors.find(RHS->getInterface()->getCanonicalDecl());
8485 if (KnownLHS != LHSAncestors.end()) {
8486 LHS = KnownLHS->second;
8487
8488 // Get the type arguments.
8489 ArrayRef<QualType> RHSTypeArgs = RHS->getTypeArgsAsWritten();
8490 bool anyChanges = false;
8491 if (LHS->isSpecialized() && RHS->isSpecialized()) {
8492 // Both have type arguments, compare them.
8493 if (!sameObjCTypeArgs(*this, LHS->getInterface(),
8494 LHS->getTypeArgs(), RHS->getTypeArgs(),
8495 /*stripKindOf=*/true))
8496 return {};
8497 } else if (LHS->isSpecialized() != RHS->isSpecialized()) {
8498 // If only one has type arguments, the result will not have type
8499 // arguments.
8500 RHSTypeArgs = {};
8501 anyChanges = true;
8502 }
8503
8504 // Compute the intersection of protocols.
8505 SmallVector<ObjCProtocolDecl *, 8> Protocols;
8506 getIntersectionOfProtocols(*this, RHS->getInterface(), Lptr, Rptr,
8507 Protocols);
8508 if (!Protocols.empty())
8509 anyChanges = true;
8510
8511 // If we need to return a kindof type but RHS is not a kindof type, we
