8512 // build a new result type.
8513 if (anyChanges || RHS->isKindOfType() != anyKindOf) {
8514 QualType Result = getObjCInterfaceType(RHS->getInterface());
8515 Result = getObjCObjectType(Result, RHSTypeArgs, Protocols,
8516 anyKindOf || RHS->isKindOfType());
8517 return getObjCObjectPointerType(Result);
8518 }
8519
8520 return getObjCObjectPointerType(QualType(RHS, 0));
8521 }
8522
8523 // Find the superclass of the RHS.
8524 QualType RHSSuperType = RHS->getSuperClassType();
8525 if (RHSSuperType.isNull())
8526 break;
8527
8528 RHS = RHSSuperType->castAs<ObjCObjectType>();
8529 }
8530
8531 return {};
8532}
8533
8534bool ASTContext::canAssignObjCInterfaces(const ObjCObjectType *LHS,
8535 const ObjCObjectType *RHS) {
8536 assert(LHS->getInterface() && "LHS is not an interface type");
8537 assert(RHS->getInterface() && "RHS is not an interface type");
8538
8539 // Verify that the base decls are compatible: the RHS must be a subclass of
8540 // the LHS.
8541 ObjCInterfaceDecl *LHSInterface = LHS->getInterface();
8542 bool IsSuperClass = LHSInterface->isSuperClassOf(RHS->getInterface());
8543 if (!IsSuperClass)
8544 return false;
8545
8546 // If the LHS has protocol qualifiers, determine whether all of them are
8547 // satisfied by the RHS (i.e., the RHS has a superset of the protocols in the
8548 // LHS).
8549 if (LHS->getNumProtocols() > 0) {
8550 // OK if conversion of LHS to SuperClass results in narrowing of types
8551 // ; i.e., SuperClass may implement at least one of the protocols
8552 // in LHS's protocol list. Example, SuperObj<P1> = lhs<P1,P2> is ok.
8553 // But not SuperObj<P1,P2,P3> = lhs<P1,P2>.
8554 llvm::SmallPtrSet<ObjCProtocolDecl *, 8> SuperClassInheritedProtocols;
8555 CollectInheritedProtocols(RHS->getInterface(), SuperClassInheritedProtocols);
8556 // Also, if RHS has explicit quelifiers, include them for comparing with LHS's
8557 // qualifiers.
8558 for (auto *RHSPI : RHS->quals())
8559 CollectInheritedProtocols(RHSPI, SuperClassInheritedProtocols);
8560 // If there is no protocols associated with RHS, it is not a match.
8561 if (SuperClassInheritedProtocols.empty())
8562 return false;
8563
8564 for (const auto *LHSProto : LHS->quals()) {
8565 bool SuperImplementsProtocol = false;
8566 for (auto *SuperClassProto : SuperClassInheritedProtocols)
8567 if (SuperClassProto->lookupProtocolNamed(LHSProto->getIdentifier())) {
8568 SuperImplementsProtocol = true;
8569 break;
8570 }
8571 if (!SuperImplementsProtocol)
8572 return false;
8573 }
8574 }
8575
8576 // If the LHS is specialized, we may need to check type arguments.
8577 if (LHS->isSpecialized()) {
8578 // Follow the superclass chain until we've matched the LHS class in the
8579 // hierarchy. This substitutes type arguments through.
8580 const ObjCObjectType *RHSSuper = RHS;
8581 while (!declaresSameEntity(RHSSuper->getInterface(), LHSInterface))
8582 RHSSuper = RHSSuper->getSuperClassType()->castAs<ObjCObjectType>();
8583
8584 // If the RHS is specializd, compare type arguments.
8585 if (RHSSuper->isSpecialized() &&
8586 !sameObjCTypeArgs(*this, LHS->getInterface(),
8587 LHS->getTypeArgs(), RHSSuper->getTypeArgs(),
8588 /*stripKindOf=*/true)) {
8589 return false;
8590 }
8591 }
8592
8593 return true;
8594}
8595
8596bool ASTContext::areComparableObjCPointerTypes(QualType LHS, QualType RHS) {
8597 // get the "pointed to" types
8598 const auto *LHSOPT = LHS->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
8599 const auto *RHSOPT = RHS->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
8600
8601 if (!LHSOPT || !RHSOPT)
8602 return false;
8603
8604 return canAssignObjCInterfaces(LHSOPT, RHSOPT) ||
8605 canAssignObjCInterfaces(RHSOPT, LHSOPT);
8606}
8607
8608bool ASTContext::canBindObjCObjectType(QualType To, QualType From) {
8609 return canAssignObjCInterfaces(
8610 getObjCObjectPointerType(To)->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>(),
8611 getObjCObjectPointerType(From)->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>());
8612}
8613
8614/// typesAreCompatible - C99 6.7.3p9: For two qualified types to be compatible,
8615/// both shall have the identically qualified version of a compatible type.
8616/// C99 6.2.7p1: Two types have compatible types if their types are the
8617/// same. See 6.7.[2,3,5] for additional rules.
8618bool ASTContext::typesAreCompatible(QualType LHS, QualType RHS,
8619 bool CompareUnqualified,
8620 bool CompareCapabilityQualifier) {
8621 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
8622 return hasSameType(LHS, RHS);
8623
8624 return !mergeTypes(LHS, RHS, false, CompareUnqualified,
8625 CompareCapabilityQualifier)
8626 .isNull();
8627}
8628
8629bool ASTContext::propertyTypesAreCompatible(QualType LHS, QualType RHS) {
8630 return typesAreCompatible(LHS, RHS);
8631}
8632
8633bool ASTContext::typesAreBlockPointerCompatible(QualType LHS, QualType RHS) {
8634 return !mergeTypes(LHS, RHS, true).isNull();
8635}
8636
8637/// mergeTransparentUnionType - if T is a transparent union type and a member
8638/// of T is compatible with SubType, return the merged type, else return
8639/// QualType()
8640QualType ASTContext::mergeTransparentUnionType(QualType T, QualType SubType,
8641 bool OfBlockPointer,
8642 bool Unqualified) {
8643 if (const RecordType *UT = T->getAsUnionType()) {
8644 RecordDecl *UD = UT->getDecl();
8645 if (UD->hasAttr<TransparentUnionAttr>()) {
8646 for (const auto *I : UD->fields()) {
8647 QualType ET = I->getType().getUnqualifiedType();
8648 QualType MT = mergeTypes(ET, SubType, OfBlockPointer, Unqualified);
8649 if (!MT.isNull())
8650 return MT;
8651 }
8652 }
8653 }
8654
8655 return {};
8656}
8657
8658/// mergeFunctionParameterTypes - merge two types which appear as function
8659/// parameter types
8660QualType ASTContext::mergeFunctionParameterTypes(QualType lhs, QualType rhs,
8661 bool OfBlockPointer,
8662 bool Unqualified) {
8663 // GNU extension: two types are compatible if they appear as a function
8664 // argument, one of the types is a transparent union type and the other
8665 // type is compatible with a union member
8666 QualType lmerge = mergeTransparentUnionType(lhs, rhs, OfBlockPointer,
8667 Unqualified);
8668 if (!lmerge.isNull())
8669 return lmerge;
8670
8671 QualType rmerge = mergeTransparentUnionType(rhs, lhs, OfBlockPointer,
8672 Unqualified);
8673 if (!rmerge.isNull())
8674 return rmerge;
8675
8676 return mergeTypes(lhs, rhs, OfBlockPointer, Unqualified);
8677}
8678
8679QualType ASTContext::mergeFunctionTypes(QualType lhs, QualType rhs,
8680 bool OfBlockPointer,
8681 bool Unqualified) {
8682 const auto *lbase = lhs->getAs<FunctionType>();
8683 const auto *rbase = rhs->getAs<FunctionType>();
8684 const auto *lproto = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(lbase);
8685 const auto *rproto = dyn_cast<FunctionProtoType>(rbase);
8686 bool allLTypes = true;
8687 bool allRTypes = true;
8688
8689 // Check return type
8690 QualType retType;
8691 if (OfBlockPointer) {
8692 QualType RHS = rbase->getReturnType();
8693 QualType LHS = lbase->getReturnType();
8694 bool UnqualifiedResult = Unqualified;
8695 if (!UnqualifiedResult)
8696 UnqualifiedResult = (!RHS.hasQualifiers() && LHS.hasQualifiers());
8697 retType = mergeTypes(LHS, RHS, true, UnqualifiedResult, true);
8698 }
8699 else
8700 retType = mergeTypes(lbase->getReturnType(), rbase->getReturnType(), false,
8701 Unqualified);
8702 if (retType.isNull())
8703 return {};
8704
8705 if (Unqualified)
8706 retType = retType.getUnqualifiedType();
8707
8708 CanQualType LRetType = getCanonicalType(lbase->getReturnType());
8709 CanQualType RRetType = getCanonicalType(rbase->getReturnType());
8710 if (Unqualified) {
8711 LRetType = LRetType.getUnqualifiedType();
8712 RRetType = RRetType.getUnqualifiedType();
8713 }
8714
8715 if (getCanonicalType(retType) != LRetType)
8716 allLTypes = false;
8717 if (getCanonicalType(retType) != RRetType)
8718 allRTypes = false;
8719
8720 // FIXME: double check this
8721 // FIXME: should we error if lbase->getRegParmAttr() != 0 &&
8722 // rbase->getRegParmAttr() != 0 &&
8723 // lbase->getRegParmAttr() != rbase->getRegParmAttr()?
8724 FunctionType::ExtInfo lbaseInfo = lbase->getExtInfo();
8725 FunctionType::ExtInfo rbaseInfo = rbase->getExtInfo();
8726
8727 // Compatible functions must have compatible calling conventions
8728 if (lbaseInfo.getCC() != rbaseInfo.getCC())
8729 return {};
8730
8731 // Regparm is part of the calling convention.
8732 if (lbaseInfo.getHasRegParm() != rbaseInfo.getHasRegParm())
8733 return {};
8734 if (lbaseInfo.getRegParm() != rbaseInfo.getRegParm())
8735 return {};
8736
8737 if (lbaseInfo.getProducesResult() != rbaseInfo.getProducesResult())
8738 return {};
8739 if (lbaseInfo.getNoCallerSavedRegs() != rbaseInfo.getNoCallerSavedRegs())
8740 return {};
8741 if (lbaseInfo.getNoCfCheck() != rbaseInfo.getNoCfCheck())
8742 return {};
8743
8744 // FIXME: some uses, e.g. conditional exprs, really want this to be 'both'.
8745 bool NoReturn = lbaseInfo.getNoReturn() || rbaseInfo.getNoReturn();
8746
8747 if (lbaseInfo.getNoReturn() != NoReturn)
8748 allLTypes = false;
8749 if (rbaseInfo.getNoReturn() != NoReturn)
8750 allRTypes = false;
8751
8752 FunctionType::ExtInfo einfo = lbaseInfo.withNoReturn(NoReturn);
8753
8754 if (lproto && rproto) { // two C99 style function prototypes
8755 assert(!lproto->hasExceptionSpec() && !rproto->hasExceptionSpec() &&
8756 "C++ shouldn't be here");
8757 // Compatible functions must have the same number of parameters
8758 if (lproto->getNumParams() != rproto->getNumParams())
8759 return {};
8760
8761 // Variadic and non-variadic functions aren't compatible
8762 if (lproto->isVariadic() != rproto->isVariadic())
8763 return {};
8764
8765 if (lproto->getMethodQuals() != rproto->getMethodQuals())
8766 return {};
8767
8768 SmallVector<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo, 4> newParamInfos;
8769 bool canUseLeft, canUseRight;
8770 if (!mergeExtParameterInfo(lproto, rproto, canUseLeft, canUseRight,
8771 newParamInfos))
8772 return {};
8773
8774 if (!canUseLeft)
8775 allLTypes = false;
8776 if (!canUseRight)
8777 allRTypes = false;
8778
8779 // Check parameter type compatibility
8780 SmallVector<QualType, 10> types;
8781 for (unsigned i = 0, n = lproto->getNumParams(); i < n; i++) {
8782 QualType lParamType = lproto->getParamType(i).getUnqualifiedType();
8783 QualType rParamType = rproto->getParamType(i).getUnqualifiedType();
8784 QualType paramType = mergeFunctionParameterTypes(
8785 lParamType, rParamType, OfBlockPointer, Unqualified);
8786 if (paramType.isNull())
8787 return {};
8788
8789 if (Unqualified)
8790 paramType = paramType.getUnqualifiedType();
8791
8792 types.push_back(paramType);
8793 if (Unqualified) {
8794 lParamType = lParamType.getUnqualifiedType();
8795 rParamType = rParamType.getUnqualifiedType();
8796 }
8797
8798 if (getCanonicalType(paramType) != getCanonicalType(lParamType))
8799 allLTypes = false;
8800 if (getCanonicalType(paramType) != getCanonicalType(rParamType))
8801 allRTypes = false;
8802 }
8803
8804 if (allLTypes) return lhs;
8805 if (allRTypes) return rhs;
8806
8807 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = lproto->getExtProtoInfo();
8808 EPI.ExtInfo = einfo;
8809 EPI.ExtParameterInfos =
8810 newParamInfos.empty() ? nullptr : newParamInfos.data();
8811 return getFunctionType(retType, types, EPI);
8812 }
8813
8814 if (lproto) allRTypes = false;
8815 if (rproto) allLTypes = false;
8816
8817 const FunctionProtoType *proto = lproto ? lproto : rproto;
8818 if (proto) {
8819 assert(!proto->hasExceptionSpec() && "C++ shouldn't be here");
8820 if (proto->isVariadic())
8821 return {};
8822 // Check that the types are compatible with the types that
8823 // would result from default argument promotions (C99 6.7.5.3p15).
8824 // The only types actually affected are promotable integer
8825 // types and floats, which would be passed as a different
8826 // type depending on whether the prototype is visible.
8827 for (unsigned i = 0, n = proto->getNumParams(); i < n; ++i) {
8828 QualType paramTy = proto->getParamType(i);
8829
8830 // Look at the converted type of enum types, since that is the type used
8831 // to pass enum values.
8832 if (const auto *Enum = paramTy->getAs<EnumType>()) {
8833 paramTy = Enum->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
8834 if (paramTy.isNull())
8835 return {};
8836 }
8837
8838 if (paramTy->isPromotableIntegerType() ||
8839 getCanonicalType(paramTy).getUnqualifiedType() == FloatTy)
8840 return {};
8841 }
8842
8843 if (allLTypes) return lhs;
8844 if (allRTypes) return rhs;
8845
8846 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = proto->getExtProtoInfo();
8847 EPI.ExtInfo = einfo;
8848 return getFunctionType(retType, proto->getParamTypes(), EPI);
8849 }
8850
8851 if (allLTypes) return lhs;
8852 if (allRTypes) return rhs;
8853 return getFunctionNoProtoType(retType, einfo);
8854}
8855
8856/// Given that we have an enum type and a non-enum type, try to merge them.
8857static QualType mergeEnumWithInteger(ASTContext &Context, const EnumType *ET,
8858 QualType other, bool isBlockReturnType) {
8859 // C99 6.7.2.2p4: Each enumerated type shall be compatible with char,
8860 // a signed integer type, or an unsigned integer type.
8861 // Compatibility is based on the underlying type, not the promotion
8862 // type.
8863 QualType underlyingType = ET->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
8864 if (underlyingType.isNull())
8865 return {};
8866 if (Context.hasSameType(underlyingType, other))
8867 return other;
8868
8869 // In block return types, we're more permissive and accept any
8870 // integral type of the same size.
8871 if (isBlockReturnType && other->isIntegerType() &&
8872 Context.getTypeSize(underlyingType) == Context.getTypeSize(other))
8873 return other;
8874
8875 return {};
8876}
8877
8878QualType ASTContext::mergeTypes(QualType LHS, QualType RHS, bool OfBlockPointer,
8879 bool Unqualified, bool BlockReturnType,
8880 bool IncludeCapabilityQualifier,
8881 bool MergeVoidPtr, bool MergeLHSConst) {
8882 // C++ [expr]: If an expression initially has the type "reference to T", the
8883 // type is adjusted to "T" prior to any further analysis, the expression
8884 // designates the object or function denoted by the reference, and the
8885 // expression is an lvalue unless the reference is an rvalue reference and
8886 // the expression is a function call (possibly inside parentheses).
8887 assert(!LHS->getAs<ReferenceType>() && "LHS is a reference type?");
8888 assert(!RHS->getAs<ReferenceType>() && "RHS is a reference type?");
8889
8890 if (Unqualified) {
8891 LHS = LHS.getUnqualifiedType();
8892 RHS = RHS.getUnqualifiedType();
8893 }
8894 else if (MergeLHSConst) {
8895 if (LHS.isLocalConstQualified() && !RHS.isLocalConstQualified())
8896 RHS = RHS.withConst();
8897 }
8898
8899 QualType LHSCan = getCanonicalType(LHS),
8900 RHSCan = getCanonicalType(RHS);
8901
8902 // If two types are identical, they are compatible.
8903 if (LHSCan == RHSCan)
8904 return LHS;
8905
8906 // If the qualifiers are different, the types aren't compatible... mostly.
8907 Qualifiers LQuals = LHSCan.getLocalQualifiers();
8908 Qualifiers RQuals = RHSCan.getLocalQualifiers();
8909 if (LQuals != RQuals) {
8910 // If any of these qualifiers are different, we have a type
8911 // mismatch.
8912 if (LQuals.getCVRQualifiers() != RQuals.getCVRQualifiers() ||
8913 LQuals.getAddressSpace() != RQuals.getAddressSpace() ||
8914 LQuals.getObjCLifetime() != RQuals.getObjCLifetime() ||
8915 LQuals.hasUnaligned() != RQuals.hasUnaligned())
8916 return {};
8917
8918 // Exactly one GC qualifier difference is allowed: __strong is
8919 // okay if the other type has no GC qualifier but is an Objective
8920 // C object pointer (i.e. implicitly strong by default). We fix
8921 // this by pretending that the unqualified type was actually
8922 // qualified __strong.
8923 Qualifiers::GC GC_L = LQuals.getObjCGCAttr();
8924 Qualifiers::GC GC_R = RQuals.getObjCGCAttr();
8925 assert((GC_L != GC_R) && "unequal qualifier sets had only equal elements");
8926
8927 if (GC_L == Qualifiers::Weak || GC_R == Qualifiers::Weak)
8928 return {};
8929
8930 if (GC_L == Qualifiers::Strong && RHSCan->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
8931 return mergeTypes(LHS, getObjCGCQualType(RHS, Qualifiers::Strong));
8932 }
8933 if (GC_R == Qualifiers::Strong && LHSCan->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
8934 return mergeTypes(getObjCGCQualType(LHS, Qualifiers::Strong), RHS);
8935 }
8936 return {};
8937 }
8938
8939 // Okay, qualifiers are equal.
8940
8941 Type::TypeClass LHSClass = LHSCan->getTypeClass();
8942 Type::TypeClass RHSClass = RHSCan->getTypeClass();
8943
8944 // We want to consider the two function types to be the same for these
8945 // comparisons, just force one to the other.
8946 if (LHSClass == Type::FunctionProto) LHSClass = Type::FunctionNoProto;
8947 if (RHSClass == Type::FunctionProto) RHSClass = Type::FunctionNoProto;
8948
8949 // Same as above for arrays
8950 if (LHSClass == Type::VariableArray || LHSClass == Type::IncompleteArray)
8951 LHSClass = Type::ConstantArray;
8952 if (RHSClass == Type::VariableArray || RHSClass == Type::IncompleteArray)
8953 RHSClass = Type::ConstantArray;
8954
8955 // ObjCInterfaces are just specialized ObjCObjects.
8956 if (LHSClass == Type::ObjCInterface) LHSClass = Type::ObjCObject;
8957 if (RHSClass == Type::ObjCInterface) RHSClass = Type::ObjCObject;
8958
8959 // Canonicalize ExtVector -> Vector.
8960 if (LHSClass == Type::ExtVector) LHSClass = Type::Vector;
8961 if (RHSClass == Type::ExtVector) RHSClass = Type::Vector;
8962
8963 // If the canonical type classes don't match.
8964 if (LHSClass != RHSClass) {
8965 // Note that we only have special rules for turning block enum
8966 // returns into block int returns, not vice-versa.
8967 if (const auto *ETy = LHS->getAs<EnumType>()) {
8968 return mergeEnumWithInteger(*this, ETy, RHS, false);
8969 }
8970 if (const EnumType* ETy = RHS->getAs<EnumType>()) {
8971 return mergeEnumWithInteger(*this, ETy, LHS, BlockReturnType);
8972 }
8973 // allow block pointer type to match an 'id' type.
8974 if (OfBlockPointer && !BlockReturnType) {
8975 if (LHS->isObjCIdType() && RHS->isBlockPointerType())
8976 return LHS;
8977 if (RHS->isObjCIdType() && LHS->isBlockPointerType())
8978 return RHS;
8979 }
8980
8981 return {};
8982 }
8983
8984 // The canonical type classes match.
8985 switch (LHSClass) {
8986#define TYPE(Class, Base)
8987#define ABSTRACT_TYPE(Class, Base)
8988#define NON_CANONICAL_UNLESS_DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
8989#define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
8990#define DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class, Base) case Type::Class:
8991#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
8992 llvm_unreachable("Non-canonical and dependent types shouldn't get here");
8993
8994 case Type::Auto:
8995 case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
8996 case Type::LValueReference:
8997 case Type::RValueReference:
8998 case Type::MemberPointer:
8999 llvm_unreachable("C++ should never be in mergeTypes");
9000
9001 case Type::ObjCInterface:
9002 case Type::IncompleteArray:
9003 case Type::VariableArray:
9004 case Type::FunctionProto:
9005 case Type::ExtVector:
9006 llvm_unreachable("Types are eliminated above");
9007
9008 case Type::Pointer:
9009 {
9010 // Merge two pointer types, while trying to preserve typedef info
9011 QualType LHSPointee = LHS->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
9012 QualType RHSPointee = RHS->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
9013 if (Unqualified) {
9014 LHSPointee = LHSPointee.getUnqualifiedType();
9015 RHSPointee = RHSPointee.getUnqualifiedType();
9016 }
9017 // capability and non-capability pointers are not the same!
9018 // See https://github.com/CTSRD-CHERI/clang/issues/160
9019 if (IncludeCapabilityQualifier &&
9020 (LHS->getAs<PointerType>()->isCHERICapability() !=
9021 RHS->getAs<PointerType>()->isCHERICapability()))
9022 return QualType();
9023
9024 // special-case merging with void*
9025 if (MergeVoidPtr) {
9026 if (LHS->isVoidPointerType()) return RHS;
9027 if (RHS->isVoidPointerType()) return LHS;
9028 }
9029
9030 QualType ResultType = mergeTypes(LHSPointee, RHSPointee, false,
9031 Unqualified, BlockReturnType,
9032 IncludeCapabilityQualifier,
9033 MergeVoidPtr, MergeLHSConst);
9034 if (ResultType.isNull())
9035 return {};
9036 if (getCanonicalType(LHSPointee) == getCanonicalType(ResultType))
9037 return LHS;
9038 if (getCanonicalType(RHSPointee) == getCanonicalType(ResultType))
9039 return RHS;
9040 return getPointerType(ResultType);
9041 }
9042 case Type::BlockPointer:
9043 {
9044 // Merge two block pointer types, while trying to preserve typedef info
9045 QualType LHSPointee = LHS->getAs<BlockPointerType>()->getPointeeType();
9046 QualType RHSPointee = RHS->getAs<BlockPointerType>()->getPointeeType();
9047 if (Unqualified) {
9048 LHSPointee = LHSPointee.getUnqualifiedType();
9049 RHSPointee = RHSPointee.getUnqualifiedType();
9050 }
9051 if (getLangOpts().OpenCL) {
9052 Qualifiers LHSPteeQual = LHSPointee.getQualifiers();
9053 Qualifiers RHSPteeQual = RHSPointee.getQualifiers();
9054 // Blocks can't be an expression in a ternary operator (OpenCL v2.0
9055 // 6.12.5) thus the following check is asymmetric.
9056 if (!LHSPteeQual.isAddressSpaceSupersetOf(RHSPteeQual))
9057 return {};
9058 LHSPteeQual.removeAddressSpace();
9059 RHSPteeQual.removeAddressSpace();
9060 LHSPointee =
9061 QualType(LHSPointee.getTypePtr(), LHSPteeQual.getAsOpaqueValue());
9062 RHSPointee =
9063 QualType(RHSPointee.getTypePtr(), RHSPteeQual.getAsOpaqueValue());
9064 }
9065 QualType ResultType = mergeTypes(LHSPointee, RHSPointee, OfBlockPointer,
9066 Unqualified);
9067 if (ResultType.isNull())
9068 return {};
9069 if (getCanonicalType(LHSPointee) == getCanonicalType(ResultType))
9070 return LHS;
9071 if (getCanonicalType(RHSPointee) == getCanonicalType(ResultType))
9072 return RHS;
9073 return getBlockPointerType(ResultType);
9074 }
9075 case Type::Atomic:
9076 {
9077 // Merge two pointer types, while trying to preserve typedef info
9078 QualType LHSValue = LHS->getAs<AtomicType>()->getValueType();
9079 QualType RHSValue = RHS->getAs<AtomicType>()->getValueType();
9080 if (Unqualified) {
9081 LHSValue = LHSValue.getUnqualifiedType();
9082 RHSValue = RHSValue.getUnqualifiedType();
9083 }
9084 QualType ResultType = mergeTypes(LHSValue, RHSValue, false,
9085 Unqualified);
9086 if (ResultType.isNull())
9087 return {};
9088 if (getCanonicalType(LHSValue) == getCanonicalType(ResultType))
9089 return LHS;
9090 if (getCanonicalType(RHSValue) == getCanonicalType(ResultType))
9091 return RHS;
9092 return getAtomicType(ResultType);
9093 }
9094 case Type::ConstantArray:
9095 {
9096 const ConstantArrayType* LCAT = getAsConstantArrayType(LHS);
9097 const ConstantArrayType* RCAT = getAsConstantArrayType(RHS);
9098 if (LCAT && RCAT && RCAT->getSize() != LCAT->getSize())
9099 return {};
9100
9101 QualType LHSElem = getAsArrayType(LHS)->getElementType();
9102 QualType RHSElem = getAsArrayType(RHS)->getElementType();
9103 if (Unqualified) {
9104 LHSElem = LHSElem.getUnqualifiedType();
9105 RHSElem = RHSElem.getUnqualifiedType();
9106 }
9107
9108 QualType ResultType = mergeTypes(LHSElem, RHSElem, false, Unqualified);
9109 if (ResultType.isNull())
9110 return {};
9111
9112 const VariableArrayType* LVAT = getAsVariableArrayType(LHS);
9113 const VariableArrayType* RVAT = getAsVariableArrayType(RHS);
9114
9115 // If either side is a variable array, and both are complete, check whether
9116 // the current dimension is definite.
9117 if (LVAT || RVAT) {
9118 auto SizeFetch = [this](const VariableArrayType* VAT,
9119 const ConstantArrayType* CAT)
9120 -> std::pair<bool,llvm::APInt> {
9121 if (VAT) {
9122 llvm::APSInt TheInt;
9123 Expr *E = VAT->getSizeExpr();
9124 if (E && E->isIntegerConstantExpr(TheInt, *this))
9125 return std::make_pair(true, TheInt);
9126 else
9127 return std::make_pair(false, TheInt);
9128 } else if (CAT) {
9129 return std::make_pair(true, CAT->getSize());
9130 } else {
9131 return std::make_pair(false, llvm::APInt());
9132 }
9133 };
9134
9135 bool HaveLSize, HaveRSize;
9136 llvm::APInt LSize, RSize;
9137 std::tie(HaveLSize, LSize) = SizeFetch(LVAT, LCAT);
9138 std::tie(HaveRSize, RSize) = SizeFetch(RVAT, RCAT);
9139 if (HaveLSize && HaveRSize && !llvm::APInt::isSameValue(LSize, RSize))
9140 return {}; // Definite, but unequal, array dimension
9141 }
9142
9143 if (LCAT && getCanonicalType(LHSElem) == getCanonicalType(ResultType))
9144 return LHS;
9145 if (RCAT && getCanonicalType(RHSElem) == getCanonicalType(ResultType))
9146 return RHS;
9147 if (LCAT) return getConstantArrayType(ResultType, LCAT->getSize(),
9148 ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier(), 0);
9149 if (RCAT) return getConstantArrayType(ResultType, RCAT->getSize(),
9150 ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier(), 0);
9151 if (LVAT && getCanonicalType(LHSElem) == getCanonicalType(ResultType))
9152 return LHS;
9153 if (RVAT && getCanonicalType(RHSElem) == getCanonicalType(ResultType))
9154 return RHS;
9155 if (LVAT) {
9156 // FIXME: This isn't correct! But tricky to implement because
9157 // the array's size has to be the size of LHS, but the type
9158 // has to be different.
9159 return LHS;
9160 }
9161 if (RVAT) {
9162 // FIXME: This isn't correct! But tricky to implement because
9163 // the array's size has to be the size of RHS, but the type
9164 // has to be different.
9165 return RHS;
9166 }
9167 if (getCanonicalType(LHSElem) == getCanonicalType(ResultType)) return LHS;
9168 if (getCanonicalType(RHSElem) == getCanonicalType(ResultType)) return RHS;
9169 return getIncompleteArrayType(ResultType,
9170 ArrayType::ArraySizeModifier(), 0);
9171 }
9172 case Type::FunctionNoProto:
9173 return mergeFunctionTypes(LHS, RHS, OfBlockPointer, Unqualified);
9174 case Type::Record:
9175 case Type::Enum:
9176 return {};
9177 case Type::Builtin:
9178 // Only exactly equal builtin types are compatible, which is tested above.
9179 return {};
9180 case Type::Complex:
9181 // Distinct complex types are incompatible.
9182 return {};
9183 case Type::Vector:
9184 // FIXME: The merged type should be an ExtVector!
9185 if (areCompatVectorTypes(LHSCan->getAs<VectorType>(),
9186 RHSCan->getAs<VectorType>()))
9187 return LHS;
9188 return {};
9189 case Type::ObjCObject: {
9190 // Check if the types are assignment compatible.
9191 // FIXME: This should be type compatibility, e.g. whether
9192 // "LHS x; RHS x;" at global scope is legal.
9193 const auto *LHSIface = LHS->getAs<ObjCObjectType>();
9194 const auto *RHSIface = RHS->getAs<ObjCObjectType>();
9195 if (canAssignObjCInterfaces(LHSIface, RHSIface))
9196 return LHS;
9197
9198 return {};
9199 }
9200 case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
9201 if (OfBlockPointer) {
9202 if (canAssignObjCInterfacesInBlockPointer(
9203 LHS->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>(),
9204 RHS->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>(),
9205 BlockReturnType))
9206 return LHS;
9207 return {};
9208 }
9209 if (canAssignObjCInterfaces(LHS->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>(),
9210 RHS->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()))
9211 return LHS;
9212
9213 return {};
9214 case Type::Pipe:
9215 assert(LHS != RHS &&
9216 "Equivalent pipe types should have already been handled!");
9217 return {};
9218 }
9219
9220 llvm_unreachable("Invalid Type::Class!");
9221}
9222
9223bool ASTContext::mergeExtParameterInfo(
9224 const FunctionProtoType *FirstFnType, const FunctionProtoType *SecondFnType,
9225 bool &CanUseFirst, bool &CanUseSecond,
9226 SmallVectorImpl<FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo> &NewParamInfos) {
9227 assert(NewParamInfos.empty() && "param info list not empty");
9228 CanUseFirst = CanUseSecond = true;
9229 bool FirstHasInfo = FirstFnType->hasExtParameterInfos();
9230 bool SecondHasInfo = SecondFnType->hasExtParameterInfos();
9231
9232 // Fast path: if the first type doesn't have ext parameter infos,
9233 // we match if and only if the second type also doesn't have them.
9234 if (!FirstHasInfo && !SecondHasInfo)
9235 return true;
9236
9237 bool NeedParamInfo = false;
9238 size_t E = FirstHasInfo ? FirstFnType->getExtParameterInfos().size()
9239 : SecondFnType->getExtParameterInfos().size();
9240
9241 for (size_t I = 0; I < E; ++I) {
9242 FunctionProtoType::ExtParameterInfo FirstParam, SecondParam;
9243 if (FirstHasInfo)
9244 FirstParam = FirstFnType->getExtParameterInfo(I);
9245 if (SecondHasInfo)
9246 SecondParam = SecondFnType->getExtParameterInfo(I);
9247
9248 // Cannot merge unless everything except the noescape flag matches.
9249 if (FirstParam.withIsNoEscape(false) != SecondParam.withIsNoEscape(false))
9250 return false;
9251
9252 bool FirstNoEscape = FirstParam.isNoEscape();
9253 bool SecondNoEscape = SecondParam.isNoEscape();
9254 bool IsNoEscape = FirstNoEscape && SecondNoEscape;
9255 NewParamInfos.push_back(FirstParam.withIsNoEscape(IsNoEscape));
9256 if (NewParamInfos.back().getOpaqueValue())
9257 NeedParamInfo = true;
9258 if (FirstNoEscape != IsNoEscape)
9259 CanUseFirst = false;
9260 if (SecondNoEscape != IsNoEscape)
9261 CanUseSecond = false;
9262 }
9263
9264 if (!NeedParamInfo)
9265 NewParamInfos.clear();
9266
9267 return true;
9268}
9269
9270void ASTContext::ResetObjCLayout(const ObjCContainerDecl *CD) {
9271 ObjCLayouts[CD] = nullptr;
9272}
9273
9274/// mergeObjCGCQualifiers - This routine merges ObjC's GC attribute of 'LHS' and
9275/// 'RHS' attributes and returns the merged version; including for function
9276/// return types.
9277QualType ASTContext::mergeObjCGCQualifiers(QualType LHS, QualType RHS) {
9278 QualType LHSCan = getCanonicalType(LHS),
9279 RHSCan = getCanonicalType(RHS);
9280 // If two types are identical, they are compatible.
9281 if (LHSCan == RHSCan)
9282 return LHS;
9283 if (RHSCan->isFunctionType()) {
9284 if (!LHSCan->isFunctionType())
9285 return {};
9286 QualType OldReturnType =
9287 cast<FunctionType>(RHSCan.getTypePtr())->getReturnType();
9288 QualType NewReturnType =
9289 cast<FunctionType>(LHSCan.getTypePtr())->getReturnType();
9290 QualType ResReturnType =
9291 mergeObjCGCQualifiers(NewReturnType, OldReturnType);
9292 if (ResReturnType.isNull())
9293 return {};
9294 if (ResReturnType == NewReturnType || ResReturnType == OldReturnType) {
9295 // id foo(); ... __strong id foo(); or: __strong id foo(); ... id foo();
9296 // In either case, use OldReturnType to build the new function type.
9297 const auto *F = LHS->getAs<FunctionType>();
9298 if (const auto *FPT = cast<FunctionProtoType>(F)) {
9299 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI = FPT->getExtProtoInfo();
9300 EPI.ExtInfo = getFunctionExtInfo(LHS);
9301 QualType ResultType =
9302 getFunctionType(OldReturnType, FPT->getParamTypes(), EPI);
9303 return ResultType;
9304 }
9305 }
9306 return {};
9307 }
9308
9309 // If the qualifiers are different, the types can still be merged.
9310 Qualifiers LQuals = LHSCan.getLocalQualifiers();
9311 Qualifiers RQuals = RHSCan.getLocalQualifiers();
9312 if (LQuals != RQuals) {
9313 // If any of these qualifiers are different, we have a type mismatch.
9314 if (LQuals.getCVRQualifiers() != RQuals.getCVRQualifiers() ||
9315 LQuals.getAddressSpace() != RQuals.getAddressSpace())
9316 return {};
9317
9318 // Exactly one GC qualifier difference is allowed: __strong is
9319 // okay if the other type has no GC qualifier but is an Objective
9320 // C object pointer (i.e. implicitly strong by default). We fix
9321 // this by pretending that the unqualified type was actually
9322 // qualified __strong.
9323 Qualifiers::GC GC_L = LQuals.getObjCGCAttr();
9324 Qualifiers::GC GC_R = RQuals.getObjCGCAttr();
9325 assert((GC_L != GC_R) && "unequal qualifier sets had only equal elements");
9326
9327 if (GC_L == Qualifiers::Weak || GC_R == Qualifiers::Weak)
9328 return {};
9329
9330 if (GC_L == Qualifiers::Strong)
9331 return LHS;
9332 if (GC_R == Qualifiers::Strong)
9333 return RHS;
9334 return {};
9335 }
9336
9337 if (LHSCan->isObjCObjectPointerType() && RHSCan->isObjCObjectPointerType()) {
9338 QualType LHSBaseQT = LHS->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()->getPointeeType();
9339 QualType RHSBaseQT = RHS->getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>()->getPointeeType();
9340 QualType ResQT = mergeObjCGCQualifiers(LHSBaseQT, RHSBaseQT);
9341 if (ResQT == LHSBaseQT)
9342 return LHS;
9343 if (ResQT == RHSBaseQT)
9344 return RHS;
9345 }
9346 return {};
9347}
9348
9349//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9350// Integer Predicates
9351//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9352
9353unsigned ASTContext::getIntWidth(QualType T) const {
9354 if (const auto *ET = T->getAs<EnumType>())
9355 T = ET->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
9356 if (T->isBooleanType())
9357 return 1;
9358 // For builtin types, just use the standard type sizing method
9359 return (unsigned)getTypeSize(T);
9360}
9361unsigned ASTContext::getIntRange(QualType T) const {
9362 if (Target->SupportsCapabilities()) {
9363 if (T->isPointerType())
9364 if (T->getAs<PointerType>()->isCHERICapability())
9365 return Target->getPointerRangeForCHERICapability();
9366 if (T->isBuiltinType()) {
9367 int K = T->getAs<BuiltinType>()->getKind();
9368 if ((K == BuiltinType::IntCap || K == BuiltinType::UIntCap))
9369 return Target->getPointerRangeForCHERICapability();
9370 }
9371 if (T->isEnumeralType()) {
9372 if (T->getAs<EnumType>()->getDecl()->getIntegerType()->isIntCapType())
9373 return Target->getPointerRangeForCHERICapability();
9374 }
9375 assert(!T->isReferenceType() && "Should probably not be handled here");
9376 }
9377 return getIntWidth(T);
9378}
9379
9380QualType ASTContext::getCorrespondingUnsignedType(QualType T) const {
9381 assert((T->hasSignedIntegerRepresentation() || T->isSignedFixedPointType()) &&
9382 "Unexpected type");
9383
9384 // Turn <4 x signed int> -> <4 x unsigned int>
9385 if (const auto *VTy = T->getAs<VectorType>())
9386 return getVectorType(getCorrespondingUnsignedType(VTy->getElementType()),
9387 VTy->getNumElements(), VTy->getVectorKind());
9388
9389 // For enums, we return the unsigned version of the base type.
9390 if (const auto *ETy = T->getAs<EnumType>())
9391 T = ETy->getDecl()->getIntegerType();
9392
9393 const auto *BTy = T->getAs<BuiltinType>();
9394 assert(BTy && "Unexpected signed integer or fixed point type");
9395 switch (BTy->getKind()) {
9396 case BuiltinType::Char_S:
9397 case BuiltinType::SChar:
9398 return UnsignedCharTy;
9399 case BuiltinType::Short:
9400 return UnsignedShortTy;
9401 case BuiltinType::Int:
9402 return UnsignedIntTy;
9403 case BuiltinType::Long:
9404 return UnsignedLongTy;
9405 case BuiltinType::LongLong:
9406 return UnsignedLongLongTy;
9407 case BuiltinType::Int128:
9408 return UnsignedInt128Ty;
9409 case BuiltinType::IntCap:
9410 return UnsignedIntCapTy;
9411
9412 case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
9413 return UnsignedShortAccumTy;
9414 case BuiltinType::Accum:
9415 return UnsignedAccumTy;
9416 case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
9417 return UnsignedLongAccumTy;
9418 case BuiltinType::SatShortAccum:
9419 return SatUnsignedShortAccumTy;
9420 case BuiltinType::SatAccum:
9421 return SatUnsignedAccumTy;
9422 case BuiltinType::SatLongAccum:
9423 return SatUnsignedLongAccumTy;
9424 case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
9425 return UnsignedShortFractTy;
9426 case BuiltinType::Fract:
9427 return UnsignedFractTy;
9428 case BuiltinType::LongFract:
9429 return UnsignedLongFractTy;
9430 case BuiltinType::SatShortFract:
9431 return SatUnsignedShortFractTy;
9432 case BuiltinType::SatFract:
9433 return SatUnsignedFractTy;
9434 case BuiltinType::SatLongFract:
9435 return SatUnsignedLongFractTy;
9436 default:
9437 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected signed integer or fixed point type");
9438 }
9439}
9440
9441ASTMutationListener::~ASTMutationListener() = default;
9442
9443void ASTMutationListener::DeducedReturnType(const FunctionDecl *FD,
9444 QualType ReturnType) {}
9445
9446//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9447// Builtin Type Computation
9448//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9449
9450static QualType DecodeFunctionTypeFromStr(const char *&TypeStr, bool IsNested,
9451 bool IsNoReturn, bool IsNoThrow,
9452 bool ForceEmptyTy,
9453 const ASTContext &Context,
9454 ASTContext::GetBuiltinTypeError &Error,
9455 unsigned *IntegerConstantArgs);
9456
9457/// DecodeTypeFromStr - This decodes one type descriptor from Str, advancing the
9458/// pointer over the consumed characters. This returns the resultant type. If
9459/// AllowTypeModifiers is false then modifier like * are not parsed, just basic
9460/// types. This allows "v2i*" to be parsed as a pointer to a v2i instead of
9461/// a vector of "i*".
9462///
9463/// RequiresICE is filled in on return to indicate whether the value is required
9464/// to be an Integer Constant Expression.
9465static QualType DecodeTypeFromStr(const char *&Str, const ASTContext &Context,
9466 ASTContext::GetBuiltinTypeError &Error,
9467 bool &RequiresICE,
9468 bool AllowTypeModifiers) {
9469 // Modifiers.
9470 int HowLong = 0;
9471 bool Signed = false, Unsigned = false;
9472 RequiresICE = false;
9473
9474 // Read the prefixed modifiers first.
9475 bool Done = false;
9476 #ifndef NDEBUG
9477 bool IsSpecial = false;
9478 #endif
9479 while (!Done) {
9480 switch (*Str++) {
9481 default: Done = true; --Str; break;
9482 case 'I':
9483 RequiresICE = true;
9484 break;
9485 case 'S':
9486 assert(!Unsigned && "Can't use both 'S' and 'U' modifiers!");
9487 assert(!Signed && "Can't use 'S' modifier multiple times!");
9488 Signed = true;
9489 break;
9490 case 'U':
9491 assert(!Signed && "Can't use both 'S' and 'U' modifiers!");
9492 assert(!Unsigned && "Can't use 'U' modifier multiple times!");
9493 Unsigned = true;
9494 break;
9495 case 'L':
9496 assert(!IsSpecial && "Can't use 'L' with 'W', 'N', 'Z' or 'O' modifiers");
9497 assert(HowLong <= 2 && "Can't have LLLL modifier");
9498 ++HowLong;
9499 break;
9500 case 'N':
9501 // 'N' behaves like 'L' for all non LP64 targets and 'int' otherwise.
9502 assert(!IsSpecial && "Can't use two 'N', 'W', 'Z' or 'O' modifiers!");
9503 assert(HowLong == 0 && "Can't use both 'L' and 'N' modifiers!");
9504 #ifndef NDEBUG
9505 IsSpecial = true;
9506 #endif
9507 if (Context.getTargetInfo().getLongWidth() == 32)
9508 ++HowLong;
9509 break;
9510 case 'W':
9511 // This modifier represents int64 type.
9512 assert(!IsSpecial && "Can't use two 'N', 'W', 'Z' or 'O' modifiers!");
9513 assert(HowLong == 0 && "Can't use both 'L' and 'W' modifiers!");
9514 #ifndef NDEBUG
9515 IsSpecial = true;
9516 #endif
9517 switch (Context.getTargetInfo().getInt64Type()) {
9518 default:
9519 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected integer type");
9520 case TargetInfo::SignedLong:
9521 HowLong = 1;
9522 break;
9523 case TargetInfo::SignedLongLong:
9524 HowLong = 2;
9525 break;
9526 }
9527 break;
9528 case 'Z':
9529 // This modifier represents int32 type.
9530 assert(!IsSpecial && "Can't use two 'N', 'W', 'Z' or 'O' modifiers!");
9531 assert(HowLong == 0 && "Can't use both 'L' and 'Z' modifiers!");
9532 #ifndef NDEBUG
9533 IsSpecial = true;
9534 #endif
9535 switch (Context.getTargetInfo().getIntTypeByWidth(32, true)) {
9536 default:
9537 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected integer type");
9538 case TargetInfo::SignedInt:
9539 HowLong = 0;
9540 break;
9541 case TargetInfo::SignedLong:
9542 HowLong = 1;
9543 break;
9544 case TargetInfo::SignedLongLong:
9545 HowLong = 2;
9546 break;
9547 }
9548 break;
9549 case 'O':
9550 assert(!IsSpecial && "Can't use two 'N', 'W', 'Z' or 'O' modifiers!");
9551 assert(HowLong == 0 && "Can't use both 'L' and 'O' modifiers!");
9552 #ifndef NDEBUG
9553 IsSpecial = true;
9554 #endif
9555 if (Context.getLangOpts().OpenCL)
9556 HowLong = 1;
9557 else
9558 HowLong = 2;
9559 break;
9560 }
9561 }
9562
9563 QualType Type;
9564
9565 // Read the base type.
9566 switch (*Str++) {
9567 default: llvm_unreachable("Unknown builtin type letter!");
9568 case 'v':
9569 assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned &&
9570 "Bad modifiers used with 'v'!");
9571 Type = Context.VoidTy;
9572 break;
9573 case 'h':
9574 assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned &&
9575 "Bad modifiers used with 'h'!");
9576 Type = Context.HalfTy;
9577 break;
9578 case 'f':
9579 assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned &&
9580 "Bad modifiers used with 'f'!");
9581 Type = Context.FloatTy;
9582 break;
9583 case 'd':
9584 assert(HowLong < 3 && !Signed && !Unsigned &&
9585 "Bad modifiers used with 'd'!");
9586 if (HowLong == 1)
9587 Type = Context.LongDoubleTy;
9588 else if (HowLong == 2)
9589 Type = Context.Float128Ty;
9590 else
9591 Type = Context.DoubleTy;
9592 break;
9593 case 's':
9594 assert(HowLong == 0 && "Bad modifiers used with 's'!");
9595 if (Unsigned)
9596 Type = Context.UnsignedShortTy;
9597 else
9598 Type = Context.ShortTy;
9599 break;
9600 case 'i':
9601 if (HowLong == 3)
9602 Type = Unsigned ? Context.UnsignedInt128Ty : Context.Int128Ty;
9603 else if (HowLong == 2)
9604 Type = Unsigned ? Context.UnsignedLongLongTy : Context.LongLongTy;
9605 else if (HowLong == 1)
9606 Type = Unsigned ? Context.UnsignedLongTy : Context.LongTy;
9607 else
9608 Type = Unsigned ? Context.UnsignedIntTy : Context.IntTy;
9609 break;
9610 case 'c':
9611 assert(HowLong == 0 && "Bad modifiers used with 'c'!");
9612 if (Signed)
9613 Type = Context.SignedCharTy;
9614 else if (Unsigned)
9615 Type = Context.UnsignedCharTy;
9616 else
9617 Type = Context.CharTy;
9618 break;
9619 case 'b': // boolean
9620 assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned && "Bad modifiers for 'b'!");
9621 Type = Context.BoolTy;
9622 break;
9623 case 'z': // size_t.
9624 assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned && "Bad modifiers for 'z'!");
9625 Type = Context.getSizeType();
9626 break;
9627 case 'w': // wchar_t.
9628 assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned && "Bad modifiers for 'w'!");
9629 Type = Context.getWideCharType();
9630 break;
9631 case 'F':
9632 Type = Context.getCFConstantStringType();
9633 break;
9634 case 'G':
9635 Type = Context.getObjCIdType();
9636 break;
9637 case 'H':
9638 Type = Context.getObjCSelType();
9639 break;
9640 case 'M':
9641 Type = Context.getObjCSuperType();
9642 break;
9643 case 'a':
9644 Type = Context.getBuiltinVaListType();
9645 assert(!Type.isNull() && "builtin va list type not initialized!");
9646 break;
9647 case 'A':
9648 // This is a "reference" to a va_list; however, what exactly
9649 // this means depends on how va_list is defined. There are two
9650 // different kinds of va_list: ones passed by value, and ones
9651 // passed by reference. An example of a by-value va_list is
9652 // x86, where va_list is a char*. An example of by-ref va_list
9653 // is x86-64, where va_list is a __va_list_tag[1]. For x86,
9654 // we want this argument to be a char*&; for x86-64, we want
9655 // it to be a __va_list_tag*.
9656 Type = Context.getBuiltinVaListType();
9657 assert(!Type.isNull() && "builtin va list type not initialized!");
9658 if (Type->isArrayType())
9659 Type = Context.getArrayDecayedType(Type);
9660 else {
9661 Type = Context.getLValueReferenceType(Type);
9662 }
9663 break;
9664 case 'V': {
9665 char *End;
9666 unsigned NumElements = strtoul(Str, &End, 10);
9667 assert(End != Str && "Missing vector size");
9668 Str = End;
9669
9670 QualType ElementType = DecodeTypeFromStr(Str, Context, Error,
9671 RequiresICE, false);
9672 assert(!RequiresICE && "Can't require vector ICE");
9673
9674 // TODO: No way to make AltiVec vectors in builtins yet.
9675 Type = Context.getVectorType(ElementType, NumElements,
9676 VectorType::GenericVector);
9677 break;
9678 }
9679 case 'E': {
9680 char *End;
9681
9682 unsigned NumElements = strtoul(Str, &End, 10);
9683 assert(End != Str && "Missing vector size");
9684
9685 Str = End;
9686
9687 QualType ElementType = DecodeTypeFromStr(Str, Context, Error, RequiresICE,
9688 false);
9689 Type = Context.getExtVectorType(ElementType, NumElements);
9690 break;
9691 }
9692 case 'X': {
9693 QualType ElementType = DecodeTypeFromStr(Str, Context, Error, RequiresICE,
9694 false);
9695 assert(!RequiresICE && "Can't require complex ICE");
9696 Type = Context.getComplexType(ElementType);
9697 break;
9698 }
9699 case 'Y':
9700 Type = Context.getPointerDiffType();
9701 break;
9702 case 'P':
9703 Type = Context.getFILEType();
9704 if (Type.isNull()) {
9705 Error = ASTContext::GE_Missing_stdio;
9706 return {};
9707 }
9708 break;
9709 case 'J':
9710 if (Signed)
9711 Type = Context.getsigjmp_bufType();
9712 else
9713 Type = Context.getjmp_bufType();
9714
9715 if (Type.isNull()) {
9716 Error = ASTContext::GE_Missing_setjmp;
9717 return {};
9718 }
9719 break;
9720 case 'K':
9721 assert(HowLong == 0 && !Signed && !Unsigned && "Bad modifiers for 'K'!");
9722 Type = Context.getucontext_tType();
9723
9724 if (Type.isNull()) {
9725 Error = ASTContext::GE_Missing_ucontext;
9726 return {};
9727 }
9728 break;
9729 case 'p':
9730 Type = Context.getProcessIDType();
9731 break;
9732 case 'Q':
9733 if (Signed)
9734 Type = Context.getpthread_attr_tType();
9735 else
9736 Type = Context.getpthread_tType();
9737
9738 if (Type.isNull()) {
9739 Error = ASTContext::GE_Missing_pthread;
9740 return {};
9741 }
9742 break;
9743 case '(':
9744 Type =
9745 DecodeFunctionTypeFromStr(Str, /*IsNested=*/true, /*IsNoReturn=*/false,
9746 /*IsNoThrow=*/false, /*ForceEmptyTy=*/false,
9747 Context, Error, nullptr);
9748 assert(Str[0] == ')' && "unmatched '('");
9749 Str++;
9750 break;
9751 }
9752
9753 // If there are modifiers and if we're allowed to parse them, go for it.
9754 Done = !AllowTypeModifiers;
9755 while (!Done) {
9756 switch (char c = *Str++) {
9757 default: Done = true; --Str; break;
9758 case '*':
9759 case '&': {
9760 // Both pointers and references can have their pointee types
9761 // qualified with an address space.
9762 char *End;
9763 unsigned AddrSpace = strtoul(Str, &End, 10);
9764 if (End != Str) {
9765 // Note AddrSpace == 0 is not the same as an unspecified address space.
9766 Type = Context.getAddrSpaceQualType(
9767 Type,
9768 Context.getLangASForBuiltinAddressSpace(AddrSpace));
9769 Str = End;
9770 }
9771 if (c == '*') {
9772 ASTContext::PointerInterpretationKind PIK = ASTContext::PIK_Default;
9773 if (*Str == 'm') {
9774 PIK = ASTContext::PIK_Capability;
9775 Str++;
9776 }
9777 Type = Context.getPointerType(Type, PIK);
9778 }
9779 else
9780 Type = Context.getLValueReferenceType(Type);
9781 break;
9782 }
9783 // FIXME: There's no way to have a built-in with an rvalue ref arg.
9784 case 'C':
9785 Type = Type.withConst();
9786 break;
9787 case 'D':
9788 Type = Context.getVolatileType(Type);
9789 break;
9790 case 'R':
9791 Type = Type.withRestrict();
9792 break;
9793 }
9794 }
9795
9796 assert((!RequiresICE || Type->isIntegralOrEnumerationType()) &&
9797 "Integer constant 'I' type must be an integer");
9798
9799 return Type;
9800}
9801
9802/// DecodeFunctionTypeFromStr - This decodes the entire type descriptor
9803static QualType DecodeFunctionTypeFromStr(const char *&TypeStr, bool IsNested,
9804 bool IsNoReturn, bool IsNoThrow,
9805 bool ForceEmptyTy,
9806 const ASTContext &Context,
9807 ASTContext::GetBuiltinTypeError &Error,
9808 unsigned *IntegerConstantArgs) {
9809 if (TypeStr[0] == '\0') {
9810 Error = ASTContext::GE_Missing_type;
9811 return {};
9812 }
9813
9814 if (TypeStr[0] == ')') {
9815 assert(IsNested && "unmatched ')' found at end of type list");
9816 Error = ASTContext::GE_Missing_type;
9817 return {};
9818 }
9819
9820 SmallVector<QualType, 8> ArgTypes;
9821
9822 bool RequiresICE = false;
9823 Error = ASTContext::GE_None;
9824 QualType ResType = DecodeTypeFromStr(TypeStr, Context, Error,
9825 RequiresICE, true);
9826 if (Error != ASTContext::GE_None)
9827 return {};
9828
9829 assert(!RequiresICE && "Result of function cannot be required to be an ICE");
9830
9831 while (TypeStr[0] && TypeStr[0] != '.' && TypeStr[0] != ')') {
9832 QualType Ty = DecodeTypeFromStr(TypeStr, Context, Error, RequiresICE, true);
9833 if (Error != ASTContext::GE_None)
9834 return {};
9835
9836 // If this argument is required to be an IntegerConstantExpression and the
9837 // caller cares, fill in the bitmask we return.
9838 if (RequiresICE && IntegerConstantArgs)
9839 *IntegerConstantArgs |= 1 << ArgTypes.size();
9840
9841 // Do array -> pointer decay. The builtin should use the decayed type.
9842 if (Ty->isArrayType())
9843 Ty = Context.getArrayDecayedType(Ty);
9844
9845 ArgTypes.push_back(Ty);
9846 }
9847
9848 assert((TypeStr[0] != ')' || IsNested) &&
9849 "unmatched ')' found at end of type list");
9850
9851 if (ForceEmptyTy)
9852 return {};
9853
9854 assert((TypeStr[0] != '.' || TypeStr[1] == 0) &&
9855 "'.' should only occur at end of builtin type list!");
9856
9857 bool Variadic = (TypeStr[0] == '.');
9858
9859 FunctionType::ExtInfo EI(Context.getDefaultCallingConvention(
9860 Variadic, /*IsCXXMethod=*/false, /*IsBuiltin=*/true));
9861 if (IsNoReturn) EI = EI.withNoReturn(true);
9862
9863
9864 // We really shouldn't be making a no-proto type here.
9865 if (ArgTypes.empty() && Variadic && !Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus)
9866 return Context.getFunctionNoProtoType(ResType, EI);
9867
9868 FunctionProtoType::ExtProtoInfo EPI;
9869 EPI.ExtInfo = EI;
9870 EPI.Variadic = Variadic;
9871 if (Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus && IsNoThrow)
9872 EPI.ExceptionSpec.Type =
9873 Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus11 ? EST_BasicNoexcept : EST_DynamicNone;
9874
9875 return Context.getFunctionType(ResType, ArgTypes, EPI);
9876}
9877
9878/// GetBuiltinType - Return the type for the specified builtin.
9879QualType ASTContext::GetBuiltinType(unsigned Id,
9880 GetBuiltinTypeError &Error,
9881 unsigned *IntegerConstantArgs) const {
9882 const char *TypeStr = BuiltinInfo.getTypeString(Id);
9883 return DecodeFunctionTypeFromStr(TypeStr, /*IsNested=*/false,
9884 BuiltinInfo.isNoReturn(Id),
9885 BuiltinInfo.isNoThrow(Id),
9886 /*ForceEmptyTy=*/
9887 Id == Builtin::BI__GetExceptionInfo,
9888 *this, Error, IntegerConstantArgs);
9889}
9890
9891static GVALinkage basicGVALinkageForFunction(const ASTContext &Context,
9892 const FunctionDecl *FD) {
9893 if (!FD->isExternallyVisible())
9894 return GVA_Internal;
9895
9896 // Non-user-provided functions get emitted as weak definitions with every
9897 // use, no matter whether they've been explicitly instantiated etc.
9898 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD))
9899 if (!MD->isUserProvided())
9900 return GVA_DiscardableODR;
9901
9902 GVALinkage External;
9903 switch (FD->getTemplateSpecializationKind()) {
9904 case TSK_Undeclared:
9905 case TSK_ExplicitSpecialization:
9906 External = GVA_StrongExternal;
9907 break;
9908
9909 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition:
9910 return GVA_StrongODR;
9911
9912 // C++11 [temp.explicit]p10:
9913 // [ Note: The intent is that an inline function that is the subject of
9914 // an explicit instantiation declaration will still be implicitly
9915 // instantiated when used so that the body can be considered for
9916 // inlining, but that no out-of-line copy of the inline function would be
9917 // generated in the translation unit. -- end note ]
9918 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration:
9919 return GVA_AvailableExternally;
9920
9921 case TSK_ImplicitInstantiation:
9922 External = GVA_DiscardableODR;
9923 break;
9924 }
9925
9926 if (!FD->isInlined())
9927 return External;
9928
9929 if ((!Context.getLangOpts().CPlusPlus &&
9930 !Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft() &&
9931 !FD->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>()) ||
9932 FD->hasAttr<GNUInlineAttr>()) {
9933 // FIXME: This doesn't match gcc's behavior for dllexport inline functions.
9934
9935 // GNU or C99 inline semantics. Determine whether this symbol should be
9936 // externally visible.
9937 if (FD->isInlineDefinitionExternallyVisible())
9938 return External;
9939
9940 // C99 inline semantics, where the symbol is not externally visible.
9941 return GVA_AvailableExternally;
9942 }
9943
9944 // Functions specified with extern and inline in -fms-compatibility mode
9945 // forcibly get emitted. While the body of the function cannot be later
9946 // replaced, the function definition cannot be discarded.
9947 if (FD->isMSExternInline())
9948 return GVA_StrongODR;
9949
9950 return GVA_DiscardableODR;
9951}
9952
9953static GVALinkage adjustGVALinkageForAttributes(const ASTContext &Context,
9954 const Decl *D, GVALinkage L) {
9955 // See http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/xa0d9ste.aspx
9956 // dllexport/dllimport on inline functions.
9957 if (D->hasAttr<DLLImportAttr>()) {
9958 if (L == GVA_DiscardableODR || L == GVA_StrongODR)
9959 return GVA_AvailableExternally;
9960 } else if (D->hasAttr<DLLExportAttr>()) {
9961 if (L == GVA_DiscardableODR)
9962 return GVA_StrongODR;
9963 } else if (Context.getLangOpts().CUDA && Context.getLangOpts().CUDAIsDevice &&
9964 D->hasAttr<CUDAGlobalAttr>()) {
9965 // Device-side functions with __global__ attribute must always be
9966 // visible externally so they can be launched from host.
9967 if (L == GVA_DiscardableODR || L == GVA_Internal)
9968 return GVA_StrongODR;
9969 }
9970 return L;
9971}
9972
9973/// Adjust the GVALinkage for a declaration based on what an external AST source
9974/// knows about whether there can be other definitions of this declaration.
9975static GVALinkage
9976adjustGVALinkageForExternalDefinitionKind(const ASTContext &Ctx, const Decl *D,
9977 GVALinkage L) {
9978 ExternalASTSource *Source = Ctx.getExternalSource();
9979 if (!Source)
9980 return L;
9981
9982 switch (Source->hasExternalDefinitions(D)) {
9983 case ExternalASTSource::EK_Never:
9984 // Other translation units rely on us to provide the definition.
9985 if (L == GVA_DiscardableODR)
9986 return GVA_StrongODR;
9987 break;
9988
9989 case ExternalASTSource::EK_Always:
9990 return GVA_AvailableExternally;
9991
9992 case ExternalASTSource::EK_ReplyHazy:
9993 break;
9994 }
9995 return L;
9996}
9997
9998GVALinkage ASTContext::GetGVALinkageForFunction(const FunctionDecl *FD) const {
9999 return adjustGVALinkageForExternalDefinitionKind(*this, FD,
10000 adjustGVALinkageForAttributes(*this, FD,
10001 basicGVALinkageForFunction(*this, FD)));
10002}
10003
10004static GVALinkage basicGVALinkageForVariable(const ASTContext &Context,
10005 const VarDecl *VD) {
10006 if (!VD->isExternallyVisible())
10007 return GVA_Internal;
10008
10009 if (VD->isStaticLocal()) {
10010 const DeclContext *LexicalContext = VD->getParentFunctionOrMethod();
10011 while (LexicalContext && !isa<FunctionDecl>(LexicalContext))
10012 LexicalContext = LexicalContext->getLexicalParent();
10013
10014 // ObjC Blocks can create local variables that don't have a FunctionDecl
10015 // LexicalContext.
10016 if (!LexicalContext)
10017 return GVA_DiscardableODR;
10018
10019 // Otherwise, let the static local variable inherit its linkage from the
10020 // nearest enclosing function.
10021 auto StaticLocalLinkage =
10022 Context.GetGVALinkageForFunction(cast<FunctionDecl>(LexicalContext));
10023
10024 // Itanium ABI 5.2.2: "Each COMDAT group [for a static local variable] must
10025 // be emitted in any object with references to the symbol for the object it
10026 // contains, whether inline or out-of-line."
10027 // Similar behavior is observed with MSVC. An alternative ABI could use
10028 // StrongODR/AvailableExternally to match the function, but none are
10029 // known/supported currently.
10030 if (StaticLocalLinkage == GVA_StrongODR ||
10031 StaticLocalLinkage == GVA_AvailableExternally)
10032 return GVA_DiscardableODR;
10033 return StaticLocalLinkage;
10034 }
10035
10036 // MSVC treats in-class initialized static data members as definitions.
10037 // By giving them non-strong linkage, out-of-line definitions won't
10038 // cause link errors.
10039 if (Context.isMSStaticDataMemberInlineDefinition(VD))
10040 return GVA_DiscardableODR;
10041
10042 // Most non-template variables have strong linkage; inline variables are
10043 // linkonce_odr or (occasionally, for compatibility) weak_odr.
10044 GVALinkage StrongLinkage;
10045 switch (Context.getInlineVariableDefinitionKind(VD)) {
10046 case ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::None:
10047 StrongLinkage = GVA_StrongExternal;
10048 break;
10049 case ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::Weak:
10050 case ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::WeakUnknown:
10051 StrongLinkage = GVA_DiscardableODR;
10052 break;
10053 case ASTContext::InlineVariableDefinitionKind::Strong:
10054 StrongLinkage = GVA_StrongODR;
10055 break;
10056 }
10057
10058 switch (VD->getTemplateSpecializationKind()) {
10059 case TSK_Undeclared:
10060 return StrongLinkage;
10061
10062 case TSK_ExplicitSpecialization:
10063 if (Context.getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().isMicrosoft()) {
10064 // If this is a fully specialized constexpr variable template, pretend it
10065 // was marked inline. MSVC 14.21.27702 headers define _Is_integral in a
10066 // header this way, and we don't want to emit non-discardable definitions
10067 // of these variables in every TU that includes <type_traits>. This
10068 // behavior is non-conforming, since another TU could use an extern
10069 // template declaration for this variable, but for constexpr variables,
10070 // it's unlikely for a user to want to do that. This behavior can be
10071 // removed if the headers change to explicitly mark such variable template
10072 // specializations inline.
10073 if (isa<VarTemplateSpecializationDecl>(VD) && VD->isConstexpr())
10074 return GVA_DiscardableODR;
10075
10076 // Use ODR linkage for static data members of fully specialized templates
10077 // to prevent duplicate definition errors with MSVC.
10078 if (VD->isStaticDataMember())
10079 return GVA_StrongODR;
10080 }
10081 return StrongLinkage;
10082
10083 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition:
10084 return GVA_StrongODR;
10085
10086 case TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDeclaration:
10087 return GVA_AvailableExternally;
10088
10089 case TSK_ImplicitInstantiation:
10090 return GVA_DiscardableODR;
10091 }
10092
10093 llvm_unreachable("Invalid Linkage!");
10094}
10095
10096GVALinkage ASTContext::GetGVALinkageForVariable(const VarDecl *VD) {
10097 return adjustGVALinkageForExternalDefinitionKind(*this, VD,
10098 adjustGVALinkageForAttributes(*this, VD,
10099 basicGVALinkageForVariable(*this, VD)));
10100}
10101
10102bool ASTContext::DeclMustBeEmitted(const Decl *D) {
10103 if (const auto *VD = dyn_cast<VarDecl>(D)) {
10104 if (!VD->isFileVarDecl())
10105 return false;
10106 // Global named register variables (GNU extension) are never emitted.
10107 if (VD->getStorageClass() == SC_Register)
10108 return false;
10109 if (VD->getDescribedVarTemplate() ||
10110 isa<VarTemplatePartialSpecializationDecl>(VD))
10111 return false;
10112 } else if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
10113 // We never need to emit an uninstantiated function template.
10114 if (FD->getTemplatedKind() == FunctionDecl::TK_FunctionTemplate)
10115 return false;
10116 } else if (isa<PragmaCommentDecl>(D))
10117 return true;
10118 else if (isa<PragmaDetectMismatchDecl>(D))
10119 return true;
10120 else if (isa<OMPThreadPrivateDecl>(D))
10121 return !D->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext();
10122 else if (isa<OMPAllocateDecl>(D))
10123 return !D->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext();
10124 else if (isa<OMPDeclareReductionDecl>(D))
10125 return !D->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext();
10126 else if (isa<ImportDecl>(D))
10127 return true;
10128 else
10129 return false;
10130
10131 if (D->isFromASTFile() && !LangOpts.BuildingPCHWithObjectFile) {
10132 assert(getExternalSource() && "It's from an AST file; must have a source.");
10133 // On Windows, PCH files are built together with an object file. If this
10134 // declaration comes from such a PCH and DeclMustBeEmitted would return
10135 // true, it would have returned true and the decl would have been emitted
10136 // into that object file, so it doesn't need to be emitted here.
10137 // Note that decls are still emitted if they're referenced, as usual;
10138 // DeclMustBeEmitted is used to decide whether a decl must be emitted even
10139 // if it's not referenced.
10140 //
10141 // Explicit template instantiation definitions are tricky. If there was an
10142 // explicit template instantiation decl in the PCH before, it will look like
10143 // the definition comes from there, even if that was just the declaration.
10144 // (Explicit instantiation defs of variable templates always get emitted.)
10145 bool IsExpInstDef =
10146 isa<FunctionDecl>(D) &&
10147 cast<FunctionDecl>(D)->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
10148 TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition;
10149
10150 // Implicit member function definitions, such as operator= might not be
10151 // marked as template specializations, since they're not coming from a
10152 // template but synthesized directly on the class.
10153 IsExpInstDef |=
10154 isa<CXXMethodDecl>(D) &&
10155 cast<CXXMethodDecl>(D)->getParent()->getTemplateSpecializationKind() ==
10156 TSK_ExplicitInstantiationDefinition;
10157
10158 if (getExternalSource()->DeclIsFromPCHWithObjectFile(D) && !IsExpInstDef)
10159 return false;
10160 }
10161
10162 // If this is a member of a class template, we do not need to emit it.
10163 if (D->getDeclContext()->isDependentContext())
10164 return false;
10165
10166 // Weak references don't produce any output by themselves.
10167 if (D->hasAttr<WeakRefAttr>())
10168 return false;
10169
10170 // Aliases and used decls are required.
10171 if (D->hasAttr<AliasAttr>() || D->hasAttr<UsedAttr>())
10172 return true;
10173
10174 if (const auto *FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(D)) {
10175 // Forward declarations aren't required.
10176 if (!FD->doesThisDeclarationHaveABody())
10177 return FD->doesDeclarationForceExternallyVisibleDefinition();
10178
10179 // Constructors and destructors are required.
10180 if (FD->hasAttr<ConstructorAttr>() || FD->hasAttr<DestructorAttr>())
10181 return true;
10182
10183 // The key function for a class is required. This rule only comes
10184 // into play when inline functions can be key functions, though.
10185 if (getTargetInfo().getCXXABI().canKeyFunctionBeInline()) {
10186 if (const auto *MD = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(FD)) {
10187 const CXXRecordDecl *RD = MD->getParent();
10188 if (MD->isOutOfLine() && RD->isDynamicClass()) {
10189 const CXXMethodDecl *KeyFunc = getCurrentKeyFunction(RD);
10190 if (KeyFunc && KeyFunc->getCanonicalDecl() == MD->getCanonicalDecl())
10191 return true;
10192 }
10193 }
10194 }
10195
10196 GVALinkage Linkage = GetGVALinkageForFunction(FD);
10197
10198 // static, static inline, always_inline, and extern inline functions can
10199 // always be deferred. Normal inline functions can be deferred in C99/C++.
10200 // Implicit template instantiations can also be deferred in C++.
10201 return !isDiscardableGVALinkage(Linkage);
10202 }
10203
10204 const auto *VD = cast<VarDecl>(D);
10205 assert(VD->isFileVarDecl() && "Expected file scoped var");
10206
10207 // If the decl is marked as `declare target to`, it should be emitted for the
10208 // host and for the device.
10209 if (LangOpts.OpenMP &&
10210 OMPDeclareTargetDeclAttr::isDeclareTargetDeclaration(VD))
10211 return true;
10212
10213 if (VD->isThisDeclarationADefinition() == VarDecl::DeclarationOnly &&
10214 !isMSStaticDataMemberInlineDefinition(VD))
10215 return false;
10216
10217 // Variables that can be needed in other TUs are required.
10218 auto Linkage = GetGVALinkageForVariable(VD);
10219 if (!isDiscardableGVALinkage(Linkage))
10220 return true;
10221
10222 // We never need to emit a variable that is available in another TU.
10223 if (Linkage == GVA_AvailableExternally)
10224 return false;
10225
10226 // Variables that have destruction with side-effects are required.
10227 if (VD->getType().isDestructedType())
10228 return true;
10229
10230 // Variables that have initialization with side-effects are required.
10231 if (VD->getInit() && VD->getInit()->HasSideEffects(*this) &&
10232 // We can get a value-dependent initializer during error recovery.
10233 (VD->getInit()->isValueDependent() || !VD->evaluateValue()))
10234 return true;
10235
10236 // Likewise, variables with tuple-like bindings are required if their
10237 // bindings have side-effects.
10238 if (const auto *DD = dyn_cast<DecompositionDecl>(VD))
10239 for (const auto *BD : DD->bindings())
10240 if (const auto *BindingVD = BD->getHoldingVar())
10241 if (DeclMustBeEmitted(BindingVD))
10242 return true;
10243
10244 return false;
10245}
10246
10247void ASTContext::forEachMultiversionedFunctionVersion(
10248 const FunctionDecl *FD,
10249 llvm::function_ref<void(FunctionDecl *)> Pred) const {
10250 assert(FD->isMultiVersion() && "Only valid for multiversioned functions");
10251 llvm::SmallDenseSet<const FunctionDecl*, 4> SeenDecls;
10252 FD = FD->getMostRecentDecl();
10253 for (auto *CurDecl :
10254 FD->getDeclContext()->getRedeclContext()->lookup(FD->getDeclName())) {
10255 FunctionDecl *CurFD = CurDecl->getAsFunction()->getMostRecentDecl();
10256 if (CurFD && hasSameType(CurFD->getType(), FD->getType()) &&
10257 std::end(SeenDecls) == llvm::find(SeenDecls, CurFD)) {
10258 SeenDecls.insert(CurFD);
10259 Pred(CurFD);
10260 }
10261 }
10262}
10263
10264CallingConv ASTContext::getDefaultCallingConvention(bool IsVariadic,
10265 bool IsCXXMethod,
10266 bool IsBuiltin) const {
10267 // Pass through to the C++ ABI object
10268 if (IsCXXMethod)
10269 return ABI->getDefaultMethodCallConv(IsVariadic);
10270
10271 // Builtins ignore user-specified default calling convention and remain the
10272 // Target's default calling convention.
10273 if (!IsBuiltin) {
10274 switch (LangOpts.getDefaultCallingConv()) {
10275 case LangOptions::DCC_None:
10276 break;
10277 case LangOptions::DCC_CDecl:
10278 return CC_C;
10279 case LangOptions::DCC_FastCall:
10280 if (getTargetInfo().hasFeature("sse2") && !IsVariadic)
10281 return CC_X86FastCall;
10282 break;
10283 case LangOptions::DCC_StdCall:
10284 if (!IsVariadic)
10285 return CC_X86StdCall;
10286 break;
10287 case LangOptions::DCC_VectorCall:
10288 // __vectorcall cannot be applied to variadic functions.
10289 if (!IsVariadic)
10290 return CC_X86VectorCall;
10291 break;
10292 case LangOptions::DCC_RegCall:
10293 // __regcall cannot be applied to variadic functions.
10294 if (!IsVariadic)
10295 return CC_X86RegCall;
10296 break;
10297 }
10298 }
10299 return Target->getDefaultCallingConv(TargetInfo::CCMT_Unknown);
10300}
10301
10302bool ASTContext::isNearlyEmpty(const CXXRecordDecl *RD) const {
10303 // Pass through to the C++ ABI object
10304 return ABI->isNearlyEmpty(RD);
10305}
10306
10307VTableContextBase *ASTContext::getVTableContext() {
10308 if (!VTContext.get()) {
10309 if (Target->getCXXABI().isMicrosoft())
10310 VTContext.reset(new MicrosoftVTableContext(*this));
10311 else
10312 VTContext.reset(new ItaniumVTableContext(*this));
10313 }
10314 return VTContext.get();
10315}
10316
10317MangleContext *ASTContext::createMangleContext(const TargetInfo *T) {
10318 if (!T)
10319 T = Target;
10320 switch (T->getCXXABI().getKind()) {
10321 case TargetCXXABI::GenericAArch64:
10322 case TargetCXXABI::GenericItanium:
10323 case TargetCXXABI::GenericARM:
10324 case TargetCXXABI::GenericMIPS:
10325 case TargetCXXABI::iOS:
10326 case TargetCXXABI::iOS64:
10327 case TargetCXXABI::WebAssembly:
10328 case TargetCXXABI::WatchOS:
10329 return ItaniumMangleContext::create(*this, getDiagnostics());
10330 case TargetCXXABI::Microsoft:
10331 return MicrosoftMangleContext::create(*this, getDiagnostics());
10332 }
10333 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported ABI");
10334}

10336CXXABI::~CXXABI() = default;

10338size_t ASTContext::getSideTableAllocatedMemory() const {
10339 return ASTRecordLayouts.getMemorySize() +
10340 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(ObjCLayouts) +
10341 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(KeyFunctions) +
10342 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(ObjCImpls) +
10343 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(BlockVarCopyInits) +
10344 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(DeclAttrs) +
10345 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(TemplateOrInstantiation) +
10346 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(InstantiatedFromUsingDecl) +
10347 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(InstantiatedFromUsingShadowDecl) +
10348 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(InstantiatedFromUnnamedFieldDecl) +
10349 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(OverriddenMethods) +
10350 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(Types) +
10351 llvm::capacity_in_bytes(VariableArrayTypes);
10352}

10354/// getIntTypeForBitwidth -
10355/// sets integer QualTy according to specified details:
10356/// bitwidth, signed/unsigned.
10357/// Returns empty type if there is no appropriate target types.
10358QualType ASTContext::getIntTypeForBitwidth(unsigned DestWidth,
10359 unsigned Signed) const {
10360 TargetInfo::IntType Ty = getTargetInfo().getIntTypeByWidth(DestWidth, Signed);
10361 CanQualType QualTy = getFromTargetType(Ty);
10362 if (!QualTy && DestWidth == 128)
10363 return Signed ? Int128Ty : UnsignedInt128Ty;
10364 return QualTy;
10365}
10366
10367/// getRealTypeForBitwidth -
10368/// sets floating point QualTy according to specified bitwidth.
10369/// Returns empty type if there is no appropriate target types.
10370QualType ASTContext::getRealTypeForBitwidth(unsigned DestWidth) const {
10371 TargetInfo::RealType Ty = getTargetInfo().getRealTypeByWidth(DestWidth);
10372 switch (Ty) {
10373 case TargetInfo::Float:
10374 return FloatTy;
10375 case TargetInfo::Double:
10376 return DoubleTy;
10377 case TargetInfo::LongDouble:
10378 return LongDoubleTy;
10379 case TargetInfo::Float128:
10380 return Float128Ty;
10381 case TargetInfo::NoFloat:
10382 return {};
10383 }
10384
10385 llvm_unreachable("Unhandled TargetInfo::RealType value");
10386}

10465APValue *
10466ASTContext::getMaterializedTemporaryValue(const MaterializeTemporaryExpr *E,
10467 bool MayCreate) {
10468 assert(E && E->getStorageDuration() == SD_Static &&
10469 "don't need to cache the computed value for this temporary");
10470 if (MayCreate) {
10471 APValue *&MTVI = MaterializedTemporaryValues[E];
10472 if (!MTVI)
10473 MTVI = new (*this) APValue;
10474 return MTVI;
10475 }
10476
10477 return MaterializedTemporaryValues.lookup(E);
