10479
10480QualType ASTContext::getStringLiteralArrayType(QualType EltTy,
10481 unsigned Length) const {
10482 // A C++ string literal has a const-qualified element type (C++ 2.13.4p1).
10483 if (getLangOpts().CPlusPlus || getLangOpts().ConstStrings)
10484 EltTy = EltTy.withConst();
10485
10486 EltTy = adjustStringLiteralBaseType(EltTy);
10487
10488 // Get an array type for the string, according to C99 6.4.5. This includes
10489 // the null terminator character.
10490 return getConstantArrayType(EltTy, llvm::APInt(32, Length + 1),
10491 ArrayType::Normal, /*IndexTypeQuals*/ 0);
10492}
10493
10494StringLiteral *
10495ASTContext::getPredefinedStringLiteralFromCache(StringRef Key) const {
10496 StringLiteral *&Result = StringLiteralCache[Key];
10497 if (!Result)
10498 Result = StringLiteral::Create(
10499 *this, Key, StringLiteral::Ascii,
10500 /*Pascal*/ false, getStringLiteralArrayType(CharTy, Key.size()),
10501 SourceLocation());
10502 return Result;
10503}
10504
10505bool ASTContext::AtomicUsesUnsupportedLibcall(const AtomicExpr *E) const {
10506 const llvm::Triple &T = getTargetInfo().getTriple();
10507 if (!T.isOSDarwin())
10508 return false;
10509
10510 if (!(T.isiOS() && T.isOSVersionLT(7)) &&
10511 !(T.isMacOSX() && T.isOSVersionLT(10, 9)))
10512 return false;
10513
10514 QualType AtomicTy = E->getPtr()->getType()->getPointeeType();
10515 CharUnits sizeChars = getTypeSizeInChars(AtomicTy);
10516 uint64_t Size = sizeChars.getQuantity();
10517 CharUnits alignChars = getTypeAlignInChars(AtomicTy);
10518 unsigned Align = alignChars.getQuantity();
10519 unsigned MaxInlineWidthInBits = getTargetInfo().getMaxAtomicInlineWidth();
10520 return (Size != Align || toBits(sizeChars) > MaxInlineWidthInBits);
10521}
10522
10523/// Template specializations to abstract away from pointers and TypeLocs.
10524/// @{
10525template <typename T>
10526static ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode createDynTypedNode(const T &Node) {
10527 return ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode::create(*Node);
10528}
10529template <>
10530ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode createDynTypedNode(const TypeLoc &Node) {
10531 return ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode::create(Node);
10532}
10533template <>
10534ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode
10535createDynTypedNode(const NestedNameSpecifierLoc &Node) {
10536 return ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode::create(Node);
10537}
10538/// @}
10539
10540/// A \c RecursiveASTVisitor that builds a map from nodes to their
10541/// parents as defined by the \c RecursiveASTVisitor.
10542///
10543/// Note that the relationship described here is purely in terms of AST
10544/// traversal - there are other relationships (for example declaration context)
10545/// in the AST that are better modeled by special matchers.
10546///
10547/// FIXME: Currently only builds up the map using \c Stmt and \c Decl nodes.
10548class ASTContext::ParentMap::ASTVisitor
10549 : public RecursiveASTVisitor<ASTVisitor> {
10550public:
10551 ASTVisitor(ParentMap &Map) : Map(Map) {}
10552
10553private:
10554 friend class RecursiveASTVisitor<ASTVisitor>;
10555
10556 using VisitorBase = RecursiveASTVisitor<ASTVisitor>;
10557
10558 bool shouldVisitTemplateInstantiations() const { return true; }
10559
10560 bool shouldVisitImplicitCode() const { return true; }
10561
10562 template <typename T, typename MapNodeTy, typename BaseTraverseFn,
10563 typename MapTy>
10564 bool TraverseNode(T Node, MapNodeTy MapNode, BaseTraverseFn BaseTraverse,
10565 MapTy *Parents) {
10566 if (!Node)
10567 return true;
10568 if (ParentStack.size() > 0) {
10569 // FIXME: Currently we add the same parent multiple times, but only
10570 // when no memoization data is available for the type.
10571 // For example when we visit all subexpressions of template
10572 // instantiations; this is suboptimal, but benign: the only way to
10573 // visit those is with hasAncestor / hasParent, and those do not create
10574 // new matches.
10575 // The plan is to enable DynTypedNode to be storable in a map or hash
10576 // map. The main problem there is to implement hash functions /
10577 // comparison operators for all types that DynTypedNode supports that
10578 // do not have pointer identity.
10579 auto &NodeOrVector = (*Parents)[MapNode];
10580 if (NodeOrVector.isNull()) {
10581 if (const auto *D = ParentStack.back().get<Decl>())
10582 NodeOrVector = D;
10583 else if (const auto *S = ParentStack.back().get<Stmt>())
10584 NodeOrVector = S;
10585 else
10586 NodeOrVector = new ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode(ParentStack.back());
10587 } else {
10588 if (!NodeOrVector.template is<ParentVector *>()) {
10589 auto *Vector = new ParentVector(
10590 1, getSingleDynTypedNodeFromParentMap(NodeOrVector));
10591 delete NodeOrVector
10592 .template dyn_cast<ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode *>();
10593 NodeOrVector = Vector;
10594 }
10595
10596 auto *Vector = NodeOrVector.template get<ParentVector *>();
10597 // Skip duplicates for types that have memoization data.
10598 // We must check that the type has memoization data before calling
10599 // std::find() because DynTypedNode::operator== can't compare all
10600 // types.
10601 bool Found = ParentStack.back().getMemoizationData() &&
10602 std::find(Vector->begin(), Vector->end(),
10603 ParentStack.back()) != Vector->end();
10604 if (!Found)
10605 Vector->push_back(ParentStack.back());
10606 }
10607 }
10608 ParentStack.push_back(createDynTypedNode(Node));
10609 bool Result = BaseTraverse();
10610 ParentStack.pop_back();
10611 return Result;
10612 }
10613
10614 bool TraverseDecl(Decl *DeclNode) {
10615 return TraverseNode(
10616 DeclNode, DeclNode, [&] { return VisitorBase::TraverseDecl(DeclNode); },
10617 &Map.PointerParents);
10618 }
10619
10620 bool TraverseStmt(Stmt *StmtNode) {
10621 return TraverseNode(
10622 StmtNode, StmtNode, [&] { return VisitorBase::TraverseStmt(StmtNode); },
10623 &Map.PointerParents);
10624 }
10625
10626 bool TraverseTypeLoc(TypeLoc TypeLocNode) {
10627 return TraverseNode(
10628 TypeLocNode, ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode::create(TypeLocNode),
10629 [&] { return VisitorBase::TraverseTypeLoc(TypeLocNode); },
10630 &Map.OtherParents);
10631 }
10632
10633 bool TraverseNestedNameSpecifierLoc(NestedNameSpecifierLoc NNSLocNode) {
10634 return TraverseNode(
10635 NNSLocNode, ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode::create(NNSLocNode),
10636 [&] { return VisitorBase::TraverseNestedNameSpecifierLoc(NNSLocNode); },
10637 &Map.OtherParents);
10638 }
10639
10640 ParentMap &Map;
10641 llvm::SmallVector<ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode, 16> ParentStack;
10642};
10643
10644ASTContext::ParentMap::ParentMap(ASTContext &Ctx) {
10645 ASTVisitor(*this).TraverseAST(Ctx);
10646}
10647
10648ASTContext::DynTypedNodeList
10649ASTContext::getParents(const ast_type_traits::DynTypedNode &Node) {
10650 if (!Parents)
10651 // We build the parent map for the traversal scope (usually whole TU), as
10652 // hasAncestor can escape any subtree.
10653 Parents = llvm::make_unique<ParentMap>(*this);
10654 return Parents->getParents(Node);
10655}
10656
10657bool
10658ASTContext::ObjCMethodsAreEqual(const ObjCMethodDecl *MethodDecl,
10659 const ObjCMethodDecl *MethodImpl) {
10660 // No point trying to match an unavailable/deprecated mothod.
10661 if (MethodDecl->hasAttr<UnavailableAttr>()
10662 || MethodDecl->hasAttr<DeprecatedAttr>())
10663 return false;
10664 if (MethodDecl->getObjCDeclQualifier() !=
10665 MethodImpl->getObjCDeclQualifier())
10666 return false;
10667 if (!hasSameType(MethodDecl->getReturnType(), MethodImpl->getReturnType()))
10668 return false;
10669
10670 if (MethodDecl->param_size() != MethodImpl->param_size())
10671 return false;
10672
10673 for (ObjCMethodDecl::param_const_iterator IM = MethodImpl->param_begin(),
10674 IF = MethodDecl->param_begin(), EM = MethodImpl->param_end(),
10675 EF = MethodDecl->param_end();
10676 IM != EM && IF != EF; ++IM, ++IF) {
10677 const ParmVarDecl *DeclVar = (*IF);
10678 const ParmVarDecl *ImplVar = (*IM);
10679 if (ImplVar->getObjCDeclQualifier() != DeclVar->getObjCDeclQualifier())
10680 return false;
10681 if (!hasSameType(DeclVar->getType(), ImplVar->getType()))
10682 return false;
10683 }
10684
10685 return (MethodDecl->isVariadic() == MethodImpl->isVariadic());
10686}
10687
10688uint64_t ASTContext::getTargetNullPointerValue(QualType QT) const {
10689 LangAS AS;
10690 if (QT->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType()->isNullPtrType())
10691 AS = LangAS::Default;
10692 else
10693 AS = QT->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace();
10694
10695 return getTargetInfo().getNullPointerValue(AS);
10696}
10697
10698unsigned ASTContext::getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS AS) const {
10699 if (isTargetAddressSpace(AS)) {
10700 return toTargetAddressSpace(AS);
10701 }
10702 if (getTargetInfo().areAllPointersCapabilities() && AS == LangAS::Default) {
10703 // FIXME: hardcoding 200 here is ugly but we don't have TargetCodeGenInfo()
10704 return 200; // Hack for CHERI purecap ABI where we want default to mean AS200
10705 }
10706 return (*AddrSpaceMap)[(unsigned)AS];
10707}
10708
10709bool ASTContext::containsCapabilities(const RecordDecl *RD) const {
10710 for (auto i = RD->field_begin(), e = RD->field_end(); i != e; ++i) {
10711 const QualType Ty = i->getType();
10712 if (Ty->isCHERICapabilityType(*this))
10713 return true;
10714 if (const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>())
10715 if (containsCapabilities(RT->getDecl()))
10716 return true;
10717 if (Ty->isArrayType() && containsCapabilities(Ty))
10718 return true;
10719 }
10720 // In the case of C++ classes, also check base classes
10721 if (const CXXRecordDecl *CRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
10722 for (auto i = CRD->bases_begin(), e = CRD->bases_end(); i != e; ++i) {
10723 const QualType Ty = i->getType();
10724 if (const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>())
10725 if (containsCapabilities(RT->getDecl()))
10726 return true;
10727 }
10728 }
10729 return false;
10730}
10731
10732bool ASTContext::containsCapabilities(QualType Ty) const {
10733 // If we've already looked up this type, then return the cached value.
10734 auto Cached = ContainsCapabilities.find(Ty.getAsOpaquePtr());
10735 if (Cached != ContainsCapabilities.end())
10736 return Cached->second;
10737 // Don't bother caching the trivial cases.
10738 if (Ty->isCHERICapabilityType(*this))
10739 return true;
10740 if (Ty->isArrayType()) {
10741 QualType ElTy = QualType(Ty->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe(), 0);
10742 return containsCapabilities(ElTy);
10743 }
10744 const RecordType *RT = Ty->getAs<RecordType>();
10745 if (!RT)
10746 return false;
10747 bool Ret = containsCapabilities(RT->getDecl());
10748 ContainsCapabilities[Ty.getAsOpaquePtr()] = Ret;
10749 return Ret;
10750}
10751
10752QualType ASTContext::getCorrespondingSaturatedType(QualType Ty) const {
10753 assert(Ty->isFixedPointType());
10754
10755 if (Ty->isSaturatedFixedPointType()) return Ty;
10756
10757 const auto &BT = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>();
10758 switch (BT->getKind()) {
10759 default:
10760 llvm_unreachable("Not a fixed point type!");
10761 case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
10762 return SatShortAccumTy;
10763 case BuiltinType::Accum:
10764 return SatAccumTy;
10765 case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
10766 return SatLongAccumTy;
10767 case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
10768 return SatUnsignedShortAccumTy;
10769 case BuiltinType::UAccum:
10770 return SatUnsignedAccumTy;
10771 case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
10772 return SatUnsignedLongAccumTy;
10773 case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
10774 return SatShortFractTy;
10775 case BuiltinType::Fract:
10776 return SatFractTy;
10777 case BuiltinType::LongFract:
10778 return SatLongFractTy;
10779 case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
10780 return SatUnsignedShortFractTy;
10781 case BuiltinType::UFract:
10782 return SatUnsignedFractTy;
10783 case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
10784 return SatUnsignedLongFractTy;
10785 }
10786}
10787
10788LangAS ASTContext::getLangASForBuiltinAddressSpace(unsigned AS) const {
10789 if (LangOpts.OpenCL)
10790 return getTargetInfo().getOpenCLBuiltinAddressSpace(AS);
10791
10792 if (LangOpts.CUDA)
10793 return getTargetInfo().getCUDABuiltinAddressSpace(AS);
10794
10795 return getLangASFromTargetAS(AS);
10796}

10798// Explicitly instantiate this in case a Redeclarable<T> is used from a TU that
10799// doesn't include ASTContext.h
10800template
10801clang::LazyGenerationalUpdatePtr<
10802 const Decl *, Decl *, &ExternalASTSource::CompleteRedeclChain>::ValueType
10803clang::LazyGenerationalUpdatePtr<
10804 const Decl *, Decl *, &ExternalASTSource::CompleteRedeclChain>::makeValue(
10805 const clang::ASTContext &Ctx, Decl *Value);
10806
10807unsigned char ASTContext::getFixedPointScale(QualType Ty) const {
10808 assert(Ty->isFixedPointType());
10809
10810 const auto *BT = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>();
10811 const TargetInfo &Target = getTargetInfo();
10812 switch (BT->getKind()) {
10813 default:
10814 llvm_unreachable("Not a fixed point type!");
10815 case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
10816 case BuiltinType::SatShortAccum:
10817 return Target.getShortAccumScale();
10818 case BuiltinType::Accum:
10819 case BuiltinType::SatAccum:
10820 return Target.getAccumScale();
10821 case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
10822 case BuiltinType::SatLongAccum:
10823 return Target.getLongAccumScale();
10824 case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
10825 case BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum:
10826 return Target.getUnsignedShortAccumScale();
10827 case BuiltinType::UAccum:
10828 case BuiltinType::SatUAccum:
10829 return Target.getUnsignedAccumScale();
10830 case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
10831 case BuiltinType::SatULongAccum:
10832 return Target.getUnsignedLongAccumScale();
10833 case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
10834 case BuiltinType::SatShortFract:
10835 return Target.getShortFractScale();
10836 case BuiltinType::Fract:
10837 case BuiltinType::SatFract:
10838 return Target.getFractScale();
10839 case BuiltinType::LongFract:
10840 case BuiltinType::SatLongFract:
10841 return Target.getLongFractScale();
10842 case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
10843 case BuiltinType::SatUShortFract:
10844 return Target.getUnsignedShortFractScale();
10845 case BuiltinType::UFract:
10846 case BuiltinType::SatUFract:
10847 return Target.getUnsignedFractScale();
10848 case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
10849 case BuiltinType::SatULongFract:
10850 return Target.getUnsignedLongFractScale();
10851 }
10852}
10853
10854unsigned char ASTContext::getFixedPointIBits(QualType Ty) const {
10855 assert(Ty->isFixedPointType());
10856
10857 const auto *BT = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>();
10858 const TargetInfo &Target = getTargetInfo();
10859 switch (BT->getKind()) {
10860 default:
10861 llvm_unreachable("Not a fixed point type!");
10862 case BuiltinType::ShortAccum:
10863 case BuiltinType::SatShortAccum:
10864 return Target.getShortAccumIBits();
10865 case BuiltinType::Accum:
10866 case BuiltinType::SatAccum:
10867 return Target.getAccumIBits();
10868 case BuiltinType::LongAccum:
10869 case BuiltinType::SatLongAccum:
10870 return Target.getLongAccumIBits();
10871 case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
10872 case BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum:
10873 return Target.getUnsignedShortAccumIBits();
10874 case BuiltinType::UAccum:
10875 case BuiltinType::SatUAccum:
10876 return Target.getUnsignedAccumIBits();
10877 case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
10878 case BuiltinType::SatULongAccum:
10879 return Target.getUnsignedLongAccumIBits();
10880 case BuiltinType::ShortFract:
10881 case BuiltinType::SatShortFract:
10882 case BuiltinType::Fract:
10883 case BuiltinType::SatFract:
10884 case BuiltinType::LongFract:
10885 case BuiltinType::SatLongFract:
10886 case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
10887 case BuiltinType::SatUShortFract:
10888 case BuiltinType::UFract:
10889 case BuiltinType::SatUFract:
10890 case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
10891 case BuiltinType::SatULongFract:
10892 return 0;
10893 }
10894}
10895
10896FixedPointSemantics ASTContext::getFixedPointSemantics(QualType Ty) const {
10897 assert((Ty->isFixedPointType() || Ty->isIntegerType()) &&
10898 "Can only get the fixed point semantics for a "
10899 "fixed point or integer type.");
10900 if (Ty->isIntegerType())
10901 return FixedPointSemantics::GetIntegerSemantics(getIntWidth(Ty),
10902 Ty->isSignedIntegerType());
10903
10904 bool isSigned = Ty->isSignedFixedPointType();
10905 return FixedPointSemantics(
10906 static_cast<unsigned>(getTypeSize(Ty)), getFixedPointScale(Ty), isSigned,
10907 Ty->isSaturatedFixedPointType(),
10908 !isSigned && getTargetInfo().doUnsignedFixedPointTypesHavePadding());
10909}
10910
10911APFixedPoint ASTContext::getFixedPointMax(QualType Ty) const {
10912 assert(Ty->isFixedPointType());
10913 return APFixedPoint::getMax(getFixedPointSemantics(Ty));
10914}
10915
10916APFixedPoint ASTContext::getFixedPointMin(QualType Ty) const {
10917 assert(Ty->isFixedPointType());
10918 return APFixedPoint::getMin(getFixedPointSemantics(Ty));
10919}
10920
10921QualType ASTContext::getCorrespondingSignedFixedPointType(QualType Ty) const {
10922 assert(Ty->isUnsignedFixedPointType() &&
10923 "Expected unsigned fixed point type");
10924 const auto *BTy = Ty->getAs<BuiltinType>();
10925
10926 switch (BTy->getKind()) {
10927 case BuiltinType::UShortAccum:
10928 return ShortAccumTy;
10929 case BuiltinType::UAccum:
10930 return AccumTy;
10931 case BuiltinType::ULongAccum:
10932 return LongAccumTy;
10933 case BuiltinType::SatUShortAccum:
10934 return SatShortAccumTy;
10935 case BuiltinType::SatUAccum:
10936 return SatAccumTy;
10937 case BuiltinType::SatULongAccum:
10938 return SatLongAccumTy;
10939 case BuiltinType::UShortFract:
10940 return ShortFractTy;
10941 case BuiltinType::UFract:
10942 return FractTy;
10943 case BuiltinType::ULongFract:
10944 return LongFractTy;
10945 case BuiltinType::SatUShortFract:
10946 return SatShortFractTy;
10947 case BuiltinType::SatUFract:
10948 return SatFractTy;
10949 case BuiltinType::SatULongFract:
10950 return SatLongFractTy;
10951 default:
10952 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected unsigned fixed point type");
10953 }
